(103, 'UKCS Usage Guide', '<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image001.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>At top of this screen &ndash; enter UKCS and hit enter.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image003.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the &ldquo;Main Menu&rdquo; for UK.&nbsp; Option E is probably all you will need.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image005.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>Main menu for Merchant Maintenance &ndash; selection option of interest and put letter representing it in the function and hit .</p>\r\n<p>Option A</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image007.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>On the command line here you may enter a sold to coupled with a site number, ie, 431172886974, or the site number preceded by a &lsquo;9&rsquo;, ie, 9886974.&nbsp; You may call up any site by any other &lsquo;ID&rsquo; that the site is known by.&nbsp; An example is if you only know the UK Fuels id number, you may type in &lsquo;UK&rsquo; followed by the UK Fuels merchant id and hit enter.&nbsp; As long as the merchant id has been entered on the following screen, the site record may be called up using it.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image009.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>You may access this screen by entering &lsquo;PF15&rsquo; ( F3) from most of the other merchant screens. The only difficulty in calling a site up by these merchant id&rsquo;s is knowing the prefix.&nbsp; PH &ndash; for Allstar or PHH id, BC&mdash;for Barclay id, SHIP--ship to numbers, AM&mdash;American Express id, DI&mdash;Diners Club id, UK&mdash;UK Fuels number, BT&mdash;British Telecom account number, CJ&mdash;CH Jones id, &lsquo;9&rsquo;&mdash;for using site number only, PN&mdash;for phone number.&nbsp; This is a flexible file and can be added to or changed to make sense to the users.</p>\r\n<p>To add an additional merchant id, change the function from &lsquo;B&rsquo; to &lsquo;C&rsquo; and hit .&nbsp; Blank lines will open up for entry.&nbsp; If you enter a merchant id that is on another site, you will get an error message indicating that. To remove a merchant ID (alias), place a &lsquo;D&rsquo; on the selector code to the left of the entry you wish to delete and hit .</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image011.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the Discounts and Fees table indicating the rates at which a site is charged for transaction fees on their VCS statement.&nbsp; It can be accessed by typing a &lsquo;B&rsquo; on the Merchant Menu or any command line screen or hitting (shift ) on any screen where it is listed at the bottom in white.</p>\r\n<p>You may page through the various rates charged by using (page forward) and (page backward) for the same rate table.&nbsp; To look at other rate tables, either enter the rate table name in the yellow line at the top and hit or you can &lsquo;look through&rsquo; the various tables by using (table backward) and (table forward).</p>\r\n<p>To change any entry, change the &lsquo;B&rsquo; in the function code to a &lsquo;C&rsquo;.&nbsp; It will open in yellow all the changeable fields.</p>\r\n<p>There are two side-by-side sets of entries.&nbsp; TRANS TYPE &ndash; indicates the transaction type to be charged for. &nbsp;PT&mdash;indicates if the charge is &lsquo;Passed Through&rsquo; from the vendor. DISC&mdash;indicates the percentage rate the amount of the transactions are multiplied.&nbsp; FEE is the per transaction charge and PPL is the pence per litre charged.</p>\r\n<p>These charges affect the VCS billing, so be very careful with any changes.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image013.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the merchant history listing screen.&nbsp; It can be accessed by either typing &lsquo;C&rsquo; on the merchant menu or any command line screen or hitting on any screen where it is listing in white at the bottom of the screen. If you have a site displayed, it will carry the information forward and bring up the history for that site.&nbsp; To look at a different site, you may enter the sold to number in the merchant field and the site number in the dealer field.&nbsp; There is no shortcut here to bring up a site.&nbsp; However, you may (record backwards) and (record forward).</p>\r\n<p>The alpha character following the date indicates whether it is a &lsquo;T&rsquo;elcom statement or &lsquo;B&rsquo; for VCS billing statement.&nbsp; Information provided is totals with Net, VAT and Total.</p>\r\n<p>You may type an &lsquo;S&rsquo; on the corresponding selector code (the short yellow line to the left of the line) and hit to call up more detail.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image016.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the Merchant Summary Screen which is accessed by the selector code on a &ldquo;B&rdquo; statement from the Merchant History screen. This screen shows what the site was billed with summary information at the top with additional detail on the lower half of the screen by card type or transaction type.</p>\r\n<p>The red circle above shows that there are multiple pages to this.&nbsp; You can (page backward) (page forward) through these.</p>\r\n<p>(record backward) and (record forward) will take you through various statements for this same site.</p>\r\n<p>You can access a different site by entering the Sold To and Site number in the Merchant field.&nbsp; You may access specifically dated invoice information by entering the date desired.&nbsp; (US date format)</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image018.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is the Telecom Summary Screen which is accessed by the selector code on a &ldquo;T&rdquo; statement from the Merchant History screen. This screen shows what the site was billed with summary information at the top with additional detail on the lower half of the screen.</p>\r\n<p>(record backward) and (record forward) will take you through various statements for this same site.</p>\r\n<p>You can access a different site by entering the Sold To and Site number in the Merchant field.&nbsp; You may access specifically dated invoice information by entering the date desired.&nbsp; (US date format)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image020.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This is the Merchant Device Screen access by alpha character &lsquo;J&rsquo;.&nbsp; This shows POS devices that are at the site.&nbsp; If the TERM ID is red, it indicates that the device has been deleted.&nbsp; You can &lsquo;S&rsquo; (select) any device for additional information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image022.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the Merchant Device Detail screen.&nbsp; You access this screen by selecting a device from the Merchant Device Screen.&nbsp; If you have selected with an &lsquo;S&rsquo; on the Device Screen this screen will be displayed with fields in green.&nbsp; If you select the device with a &lsquo;C&rsquo;, these fields are displayed in yellow and can be updated.&nbsp; If you make changes and hit it will save the changes.&nbsp; If you hit or , the changes will not be saved.&nbsp; When you have executed the &lsquo;ADDD&rsquo; command, this screen will open with blanks in all fields for completion.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image024.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the Capping History Screen.&nbsp; This screen is accessed with the alpha &lsquo;L&rsquo;. Capping information is displayed since billing for January, 2012. This screen shows the volume the capping is based on, the actual charges from the invoice, the effective PPL, the PPL difference between the site&rsquo;s capping rate and the effective PPL rate. If capping is charged to the customer there will be an amount in the INV CAP AMT. If site is not capped monthly, the carry-over will be displayed in the carry-over field.</p>\r\n<p>You can select any line for additional information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image026.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the Capping History Detail Screen that is displayed upon selection from the Capping History Screen. This screen shows much of the same information with information about next and previous capping dates.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image028.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>This is the Merchant Name X-Ref screen accessed by the alpha character &lsquo;H&rsquo;.&nbsp; This screen allows you to search the merchant file by name, address, city, postal code or phone number. As little as one character can be entered in any field.&nbsp; The City can only be used in conjunction with another field.&nbsp; Each of the other fields can be searched alone.&nbsp; The results screen is shown below.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/ukcs/image030.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p>All entries that match the request will be displayed.&nbsp; If there is a &lsquo;D&rsquo; in the STAT column, it means the site is closed.&nbsp; You can select any site to review and if you have not moved from the Merchant Account Screen on your selection, when you hit , you will return to the results.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-08-09 09:46:16', 'l7d23b', '2014-10-13 12:23:43', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on using the UKCS program', '', 80004, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(104, 'ATG Fuel Alarms', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\">When an ATG Fuel Alarm e-mail is received in the group box, use the following procedure to resolve:</span><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Create a ticket in Heat under the affected store.<br /></span><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\"><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Call&nbsp;Service Station Systems&nbsp;at 408-971-2445.&nbsp; Advise the representative&nbsp;of the nature of the alarm and the site&rsquo;s contact and address information.&nbsp; <br /></span><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\"><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Forward the e-mail to Richard Kolberg indicating the ticket number advising that the situation has been reported to Service Station Systems.<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: medium; font-family: verdana,geneva;\">Once confirmed that the issue has been reported to Service Station Systems&nbsp;and Richard Kolberg, the ticket can be noted and closed.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-08-17 09:47:36', 'l7d23b', '2012-11-26 08:55:45', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Process for handling ATG alarms', '', 30005, 'Archive', 'N', ''),
(105, 'Port Reset FPX', '<p>This should always be the first step performed on a site that is experiencing communication issues if the lights on the FPX are normal.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Disconnect the power cable from the FPX.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Wait 30 seconds.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Ask the caller to identify the cables, by color, that are still plugged in to the back of the FPX.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Asking the colors will help you with reconnecting the cables later.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Have them remove the green cable from either COM1 or COM2.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Have them remove the cable plugged into WAN.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Have the caller reconnect the power cable only.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Wait 30 seconds.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Ask the caller to let you know when the carrier light begins to flash.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once the carrier light is flashing you can reconnect the WAN and COM cables.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Wait 30 seconds.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the FPX is locked up, this should remedy the issue and the site should be able to successfully test a card.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If the site still cannot process credit, continue troubleshooting.</p>', '2012-08-20 09:42:49', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-23 08:50:16', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to perform a port reset on a Fusion Point Express', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(106, 'AVS and CRInD Limits', '<table style=\"width: 100%; background-color: #b0c4de;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Reminder: If this is a new install or software reload, remind the technician that CRInD limits and AVS&nbsp;<strong>must</strong> be set. AVS should be automatically set from the network, but might be disabled at the individual card level.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\">Note</span>: Full service NJ sites are exempt from AVS requirements.</strong></span></p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"163\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>P</strong><strong>ASSPORT </strong><strong>L</strong><strong>ABEL </strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"98\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>RUBY LABEL </strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"130\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>Ruby Dispenser Limit</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"130\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>CRInD Auth Amt / <br />Ruby Disp Auth</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"130\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\"><strong>AVS Requirement</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"163\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">Proprietary</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"98\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">DM</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"130\">\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><span style=\"font-size: small;\">$150.00</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\" width=\"130\">\r\n<p class=\"De