(107, 'Gilbarco Passport Setup for Spacenet Prysm Pro', '<p class=\"Default\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 11pt;\">Network Settings</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"Default\">Buynet setting does not matter for Passport/Spacenet setups as it is IP&nbsp;based.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><strong>Passport Settings</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"Default\">Passport set for Connection Type: <strong>VSAT (Not VSAT w/ DIAL BACK UP)<br /></strong></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"Default\">Host IP: 204.194.125.9</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"Default\">IP Port: 7735</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Make sure the tech uses an uppercase \"L\" in the MID on the Passport.&nbsp; ex..&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">L</span>348XXXXXX001</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><strong>Router Settings</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"Default\">&nbsp;WAN IP: 192.168.1.30 <br /><br /></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"Default\">&nbsp;WAN Net Mask: 255.255.255.0 <br /><br /></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"Default\">&nbsp;WAN Gateway: 192.168.1.254 <br /><br /></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"Default\">&nbsp;WAN DNS: 10.5.48.1</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">The SageNet&nbsp;Prysm Pro will connect to the <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=128\" target=\"_blank\">Linksys RV042</a> via the Internet port. This will connect to LAN1 on the Prysm Pro.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><img src=\"upload/diag_prysm-gil.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"784\" height=\"564\" /></p>', '2012-08-20 15:25:30', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-13 08:50:34', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Setup instructions for Gilbarco Passport on Prysm Pro system', '', 10006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=128'),
(108, 'Preauth Limit Violation on MasterCard Fleet', '<p>When a station calls about a charge back for a Pre-Auth Limit Violation (code 90) on a MC Fleet card, these should be reversed if the limit is set at $200.00.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Verify in&nbsp;Client Line&nbsp;that the transaction authorized (AUTH) at $200.00 and the \"Card Type\" shows as \"MCFLT\".&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Email Brent Hix (<a href=\"mailto:brent.hix@valero.com\">brent.hix@valero.com</a>) with the store\'s information (jobber/dealer #, address) and transaction info (date, amount, partial card #).&nbsp; Brent will forward this information to the accounting group to have it reversed.&nbsp; <br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Open a ticket and let the station know we will get it corrected.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The correct pre-auth limit on a MasterCard Fleet card is $200.00 but there is a glitch in our system where they are charged back b/c of a limit violation b/c regular MasterCard should be set for $100.00 and it cannot distinguish the difference between&nbsp;a regular MasterCard and a MC Fleet card.&nbsp;</p>', '2012-08-20 15:29:30', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-13 09:17:23', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'What to do when a store is charged back for a MCFleet pump sale', '', 50005, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:brent.hix@valero.com'),
(109, 'Client Line Buynets', '<table style=\"width: 100%;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"><colgroup> <col width=\"146\" /> <col width=\"85\" /> <col width=\"183\" /> <col width=\"233\" /></colgroup>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"xl65\" width=\"146\" height=\"36\">Type</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl66\" width=\"85\">Buynet</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl66\" width=\"183\">Download Phone #</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl66\" width=\"233\">Alt. Download Phone #</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"xl67\" width=\"146\" height=\"21\">MULTITHREAD</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"85\">461800</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"183\">1-800-752-5124</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"233\">1-800-746-1810</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"xl67\" width=\"146\" height=\"21\">MULTITHREAD</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"85\">471800</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"183\">1-800-781-2370</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"233\">1-800-620-9116</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"xl67\" width=\"146\" height=\"21\">VSAT BUYNETS</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"85\">931699</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"183\">77090001</td>\r\n<td class=\"xl68\" width=\"233\">77090001</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2012-08-20 15:42:43', 'l7d23b', '2013-02-20 13:50:11', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Buynet listing', '', 40002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(110, 'Volume Incentive Program \"VIP\"', '<p>The&nbsp;Volume Incentive Program is a payment that&nbsp;will show on&nbsp;a jobber\'s&nbsp;EFT.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is for sites on the West Coast Only.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>They will be sent the breakdown for the adjustment a few days after the EFT notification.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This information will only show on a jobber\'s EFT. It will not show on their MSR.</p>\r\n<p>For questions, or to get more information on the&nbsp;incentive program, contact Cynthia Gonzales at Corporate 210-345-4511.</p>', '2012-08-20 15:54:22', 'l7d23b', '2013-01-16 14:20:55', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Volume Incentive Program \"VIP\" Information', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(111, 'Ruby / Sapphire Setup on Fusion Point Devices', '<p><span style=\"font-size: medium;\">&nbsp;Network Settings&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"Default\">Client Line Buynet required: 931699</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: medium;\">Must be installed as</span> <strong><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,Calibri;\"><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,Calibri;\">Enhanced Hughes VSAT </span></span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Baud: 9600<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Parity: None<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Data Bits: 8<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Stop Bits: 1<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Dial Numbers: 77090001<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Carrier Time Out: 15</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>FPX Wiring Diagram</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>To connect the two devices you will be using a proprietary cable provided by TNS. This cable will be labeled <strong>Converter Point</strong> and <strong>Terminal</strong>. <strong>Converter Point</strong> end will connect to either COM1 or COM2 port on the FPX and the&nbsp;<strong>Terminal</strong> end&nbsp;will connect to the Ruby or Sapphire port 1-9 (this is typically Com 2).&nbsp; The internet connection will connect to the WAN port on the back of the Fusion Point device.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/fpxrubycables.jpg\" alt=\"fpxrubycables\" width=\"640\" height=\"245\" /></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/diag_fpx-sapp.jpg\" alt=\"diag_fpx-sapp.jpg\" width=\"463\" height=\"389\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-08-20 15:56:28', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-13 08:39:20', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Setup instructions for Ruby / Sapphire on Fusion Point Express', '', 10003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(112, 'Wayne Nucleus setup on FPX platform', '<ul>\r\n<li>Terminal needs to be set up as dial<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Terminal ID &ndash; 5MXXXXXXXX001 (MID#)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Baud Rate &ndash; <span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">1200 </span>2400&nbsp;See Below.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Nucleus Dial Numbers &ndash; Does not matter, just fill it in.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>FPX Template &ndash; Wayne Nucleus<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Wayne Modem cable (P/N 850326-XXX-000-01-ZZZ or 891027-XXX-000-01-ZZZ depending on the Nucleus model being used) connects to TNS type 113 cable or modular adapter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>CRIND Limits &ndash; Listed as CAT limits in Nucleus setup<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>AVS &ndash; Not configurable in register, set up using special 127 in First Data profile<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Special Instructions</strong><br /><br /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The initialization string for the modem is default and should not be changed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Nucleus is very aggressive in attempting the PDL as soon as it recognizes network connectivity, be sure the flag is set prior to the configuration being saved.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the TNS type 113 modular adapter is used, a straight through CAT 5 cable needs to be run from the adapter to com 1 on the FPX.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>For SW version 7 and greater and new install, the baud rate is no longer adjustable and must be set to 2400 at the com device.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>For Wayne Wincor Nixdorf Beetle Hardware:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Terminal needs to be set up as dial</li>\r\n<li>Terminal ID &ndash; 5MXXXXXXXX001 (MID#)</li>\r\n<li>Baud Rate &ndash; <span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">1200 </span>2400&nbsp;See Below.</li>\r\n<li>Nucleus Dial Numbers &ndash; Does not matter, just fill it in.</li>\r\n<li>FPX Template &ndash; Wayne Nucleus</li>\r\n<li>Wayne Modem cable (P/N 850326-XXX-000-01-ZZZ or 891027-XXX-000-01-ZZZ depending on the Nucleus model being used) connects to TNS type 110 cable or modular adapter\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Type 110 is DB9 to RJ45 &ndash; TNS ships two cable types with each FPX</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>CRIND Limits &ndash; Listed as CAT limits in Nucleus setup</li>\r\n<li>AVS &ndash; Not configurable in register, set up using special 127 in First Data profile</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Special Instructions</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The initialization string for the modem is default and should not be changed.</li>\r\n<li>The Nucleus is very aggressive in attempting the PDL as soon as it recognizes network connectivity, be sure the flag is set prior to the configuration being saved.</li>\r\n<li>If the TNS type 110 modular adapter is used, a straight through CAT 5 cable needs to be run from the adapter to com 1 on the FPX.</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>For SW version 7 and greater and new install, the baud rate is no longer adjustable and must be set to 2400 at the com device.</strong></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>Host Modem Setup:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Navigate to Programming-System-Port Configuration</li>\r\n<li>Change COM 4 to SCANNER or NO_DEVICE if site does not have a scanner</li>\r\n<li>Change COM 1 to EXTERNAL_MODEM</li>\r\n<li>Move the Scanner cable from COM 1 to COM 4</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note: If the scanner has an external power brick then test the scanner with and without this extra power cable after the Beetle has been rebooted to ensure it still works correctly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Move the 110 host communication cable (Buypass\\First data HOST cable) from COM 4 to COM 1, remove the gender bender</li>\r\n<li>Use the 110 host communication cable and connect it to COM 2 of the FUSION POINT device</li>\r\n<li>Reset the Fusion point Device and reboot IPT#1 Nucleus Beetle for all changes to take effect</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note that it can take up to 5 to 10 minutes for everything to sync up properly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>&nbsp;Connection Diagram</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><img src=\"upload/fpx-to-nucleus.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"672\" height=\"501\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-08-20 15:59:20', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-27 08:47:13', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Setup instructions for Nucleus on Fusion Point Express', '', 10007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(113, 'Wayne Nucleus setup on Spacenet Prysm Pro', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Wayne Nucleus:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Connection Type - VSAT&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VSAT Source ID &ndash; 77090001<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Terminal ID &ndash; 5MXXXXXXXX001 (MID#)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Baud Rate &ndash; 9600 (default)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VSAT/FPX Template &ndash; Dresser Wayne Plus<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Wayne modem cable or host modem serial connection&nbsp;(P/N 850326-XXX-000-01-ZZZ or 891027-XXX-000-01-ZZZ depending on the Nucleus model being used) connects directly to IDU on port 1 / Prysm Com1<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>CRIND Limits &ndash; Listed as CAT limits in Nucleus setup<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>AVS &ndash; Not configurable in register, set up using special 127 in First Data profile<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Special Instructions</strong><br /><br /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Nucleus is very aggressive in attempting the PDL as soon as it recognizes network connectivity, be sure the flag is set prior to completing setup.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>IBM Nucleus will allow you to change Baud rate if set to VSAT. (9600)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Prysm template used should be: \"Dresser Wayne Plus\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Wayne Beatle Settings:</span></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Prysm template used should be: \"Nucleus\" template</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Navigate to Programming-System-Port Configuration</li>\r\n<li>Change COM 4 to SCANNER or NO_DEVICE if site does not have a scanner</li>\r\n<li>Change COM 1 to EXTERNAL_MODEM</li>\r\n<li>Move the Scanner cable from COM 1 to COM 4</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note: If the scanner has an external power brick then test the scanner with and without this extra power cable after the Beetle has been rebooted to ensure it still works correctly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Move the RS232 roll over cable (Buypass\\First data HOST cable) from COM 4 to COM 1, remove the gender bender</li>\r\n<li>Use the RS232 roll over cable and connect it to COM 1 of the Prysm</li>\r\n<li>Reboot the Prysm and IPT#1 Nucleus Beetle for all changes to take effect</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note that it can take up to 5 to 10 minutes for everything to sync up properly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Wiring Diagram</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/diag_prysm-nuc.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"738\" height=\"626\" /></p>', '2012-08-20 16:01:37', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-13 08:36:20', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Setup instructions for Nucleus on Skystar Advantage / Prysm Pro', '', 10007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(114, 'Linksys / Cisco RV042', '<p class=\"Default\"><img src=\"/new_kb/upload/linksys_rv0421.jpg\" alt=\"RV042 Front\" width=\"500\" height=\"332\" /><img src=\"/new_kb/upload/rvo_back.jpg\" alt=\"RV042 Back\" width=\"500\" height=\"299\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>', '2012-08-27 09:04:38', 'l7d23b', '2012-08-27 10:22:09', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Overview of router used for the Gilbarco Passport point of sale system', '', 20001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(115, 'Urgent or Emergency Gift Card Reloads', '<p>The estimated time&nbsp;WTS quotes for gift card reload orders&nbsp;is 24-48 business hours.&nbsp; If a customer advises they have urgent need for a gift card reload after normal business hours, however, WTS can process it.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Note: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">You will need the customer\'s full credit card number and expiration date in order to complete this request.&nbsp; Reflex only retains part of the credit card number in the customer\'s profile. You must look up the full card number in ClientLine.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Order&nbsp;Processing Procedure</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Submit order in Reflex and open Heat ticket as normal.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Print a copy of the reload order from Reflex\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The order will automatically print whenever you submit the order.</li>\r\n<li>If needed you can reprint the order by navigating to the &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">ReflexSVC</span>&rdquo; menu in Reflex and selecting &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SVC Admin</span>&rdquo;. In the &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">New Orders</span>&rdquo; tab locate the order you just submitted and click on the PDF icon in that cell.</li>\r\n<li>Once the PDF opens click &ldquo;Print&rdquo;.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Follow the steps below for specific payment method used.<br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Credit Card</h2>\r\nCharge the credit card on the wholesale VX520 machine&nbsp;at the front of the WTS office&nbsp;for the total amount of the order (this should include any handling fees that were charged).\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Using the VX520, select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Credit</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Enter in the full credit card number then press the green button.</li>\r\n<li>Enter in the expiration date (two digit month, two digit year) then select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Enter &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">400</span>&rdquo; for the product code # then select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Enter the &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Total</span>&rdquo; amount from the order and select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo; on the next screen</li>\r\n<li>The VX520 machine will run the transaction and print out the merchant copy receipt. Select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo; and it will also print out the customer copy.</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:</strong></span> If the sale was declined, advise the customer. If all information provided is correct (credit card number, expiration date) have the customer contact their bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2>Valero Consumer</h2>\r\nCharge <strong><u><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">only the subtotal amount on the POS</span></u></strong> at the front of the WTS office.&nbsp; When you charge the card, you will need the sub number and the expiration date.&nbsp;\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Note:</strong> the amount of the reload<strong> <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">must be less than $150.00</span></strong> as this is the daily charge limit for this type of account.</li>\r\n<li>Using the VX520, select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Credit</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Enter in the full credit card number then press the green button.</li>\r\n<li>Enter in the expiration date (two digit month, two digit year) then select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Enter &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">400</span>&rdquo; for the product code # then select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Enter the &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">subtotal</span>&rdquo; amount from the order and select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo; on the next screen</li>\r\n<li>The VX520 machine will run the transaction and print out the merchant copy receipt. Select &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo; and it will also print out the customer copy.</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:</strong></span> If the sale was declined, advise the customer. If all information provided is correct (credit card number, expiration date) have the customer contact their bank.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Click on the order entry under ReflexSVC &gt; SVC Admin.&nbsp;<br />If the charge was successful, enter the authorization number on the receipt into the <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Check #/ Credit Card Auth</span> field and click <strong>Charge Successful</strong>.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/checkccauth.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"409\" height=\"72\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Reload the gift card in ValueLink<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=116\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for instructions</a><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Enter the authorization number from ValueLink in the <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">VL Batch/Auth #</span> field and click <strong>Update Changes</strong>.<br /><img src=\"upload/vlrange.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"422\" height=\"60\" /></li>\r\n<li>Print a copy of the reload screen in ValueLink<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Sign your name on the copy of the order and write the authorization number beside the reload field on the order.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Update the HEAT ticket with the number of the gift card reloaded, amount reloaded, method of payment, approval number, and the authorization number in a journal entry.&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><u>Please do not close the ticket</u> </strong></span>as the gift card agent&nbsp;will need to update it with the order number and the Rams adjustment number.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Attach all the copies and put them in the order box in the Tech Support room.&nbsp; The gift card agent will assign an order number to the reload, process the Rams adjustment, and log it into the spreadsheet.&nbsp; Please note on the order that you used the wholesale POS so we can get with Staci Martinez to adjust it out of that machine.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-08-27 16:06:18', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-15 09:30:50', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Procedure for urgent/emergency gift card reloads', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=116');
INSERT INTO `article` (`artid`, `arttitle`, `artbody`, `createstamp`, `usercreate`, `modstamp`, `usermod`, `pubflag`, `rfcflag`, `comment`, `usercomment`, `commentstamp`, `summary`, `triggers`, `chainid`, `rolename`, `encflag`, `linkdoctext`) VALUES
(116, 'ValueLink Guide', '<p>Valulink is the system provided by First Data that WTS uses for maintenance of our Valero gift cards.&nbsp; Valulink enables us to perform such functions as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Check gift card balances</li>\r\n<li>Merge and move balances</li>\r\n<li>Freeze gift cards in case the card is lost/stolen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>This article will provide a overview of these functions that you may encounter.</p>\r\n<p><strong>First Data official guide:</strong> <a href=\"upload/docs/PBC_User_Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> to see the&nbsp;guide for Valulink provided by FD.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Valulink website:</strong> <a href=\"https://www.myclientline.net/PBCWeb\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> to navigate to the Valulink website.&nbsp; This can also be found on your Reflex notepad.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To access the card operations from ValueLink, click on the <strong>Account</strong> menu.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-blank-front-page.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"656\" height=\"252\" /></p>\r\n<p>At this screen, you must provide the gift card <strong>Account Number</strong> and <strong>Store Number</strong>.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Account Number</strong> </span>is the 19 digit gift card number beginning with 6032.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Check <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Default Merchant</span> </strong>box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Merchant Number</strong> </span>will auto-populate.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Store Number</strong> </span>will either be <strong>2011819996 or 2011819998<br /><br /></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Use <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">2011819996</span> </strong>for balance inquiries and transfers<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Use <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">2011819998</span> </strong>for reloads and to freeze the account if the card is missing.<strong> <br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Clerk ID and Txn Postal Code</strong> </span>is not required.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Click<strong> Submit</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-front-page.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"653\" height=\"249\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>ValueLink Menu Overview</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Account Details</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Gives a general overview of the gift card account</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Account History</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shows all activity that has been made on the card.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-card-home.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"851\" height=\"616\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>ValueLink Financial Transactions Options</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-financial-header.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"425\" height=\"65\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Activate</strong></p>\r\n<p>This activates an inactive card</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-activate.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"474\" height=\"209\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Adjustment</strong></p>\r\n<p>This is an option that is not often used by WTS.&nbsp; Please check with your supervisor before selecting this option.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Balance</strong></p>\r\n<p>Transfer - Using store # <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>2011819996</strong> </span>will give you the option of transferring the balance from one card to a inactive card:<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-balance-transfer.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"493\" height=\"195\" />&nbsp;<br />Merge - Using store # <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>2011819998</strong> </span>will give you the option of&nbsp;merging the balance from one card to a active&nbsp;card:</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-balance-merge.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"499\" height=\"196\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Redemption</strong></p>\r\n<p>Removes a specified value from the gift card</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-redemption.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"501\" height=\"198\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Reload (<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">use store # 2011819998 if this is a after hours reload for a gift card order</span>)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Adds a specified value to the card</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-reload - Copy 1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"503\" height=\"200\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Destroy Active</strong></p>\r\n<p>Destroys an active card. You <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\">must</span></span> check&nbsp;<strong>Remove Value</strong>&nbsp;as funds on a destroyed card are unobtainable.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-destroy.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"510\" height=\"189\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>ValueLink Non-Financial Transactions Options</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-non-financial-header.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"308\" height=\"62\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Account Status (<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">must use store # 2011819998 in order to see this option</span>)</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Freezing a gift card</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Note:</strong> This is the only option used by&nbsp;WTS.&nbsp; Please check with your supervisor&nbsp;about using any other&nbsp;options under the Non-Financial Transactions menu.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Select \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Freeze</span>\" whenever the customer has advised their gift card is missing or has been stolen.&nbsp; Alternatively, you will see \"Un-Freeze\" whenever a card is already frozen.&nbsp; </span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><strong><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/valulink-freeze.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"523\" height=\"190\" /></strong></span></p>', '2012-08-27 16:10:35', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-26 15:56:54', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'ValueLink overview and procedures', '', 40004, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'https://www.myclientline.net/PBCWeb'),
(117, 'Verifone VX570 Setup Instructions', '<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:</strong></span> VX570\'s are now considered \"End of Life\" by Bypass as of 2/1/17 and they are no longer providing support.&nbsp; If a site calls having problems processing credit or debit and normal troubleshooting will not resolve the issue please send an email to Mitzi with the site details so that it can be replaced with a VX 520.&nbsp; Standard turn around in getting these terminals out will be 3-5 business days.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please follow the steps below in order to setup the Omni 3750 to work with satellite: **DO NOT PROVIDE THIS INFORMATION TO STORE EMPLOYEES</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Attach the power cable to the Vx570, and then connect the other end to a wall outlet.<img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/VX570.jpg\" alt=\"Verifone Vx570\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Connect the yellow CAT-5 cross-over cable (provided with the Vx570) to the 10BaseT port on the back of the VX. Connect the other end of the cable to the LAN port on the Skystar IDU or&nbsp;Prysm Pro.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Go into &lsquo;Manager Function&rsquo;<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password is 111111 or 123456<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Go into &lsquo;Tech Setup&lsquo;<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password is 53484C (to get the C, press 2 and the alpha key 3 times)<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Look for &lsquo;Comm Configuration&rsquo;<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow key to the right of &lsquo;Comm Configuration&rsquo;<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press \'Change\'<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table style=\"valign: top;\" border=\"0\" frame=\"above\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>For devices on a Prysm Pro:<br /><br /></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Look for &lsquo;COMBO\'<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow key next to &lsquo;COMBO\' to select it<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the following information<br /><br /><br />\r\n<table style=\"border: 1px solid #000000;\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>HOST</td>\r\n<td>204.194.125.009</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>PORT</td>\r\n<td>7735</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>GATEWAY</td>\r\n<td>192.168.001.254</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MASK</td>\r\n<td>255.255.255.000</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>TERM - Primary</td>\r\n<td>192.168.001.020</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Terminal 002</td>\r\n<td>192.168.001.021</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Terminal 003</td>\r\n<td>192.168.001.022</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Terminal 004</td>\r\n<td>192.168.001.023</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>NOTICE:</strong> </span>If the merchant is advising they\'re unable to key <br />in a number or the terminal just beeps, make sure the field <br />is BLANK and not populated with 000.000.000.000. You will <br />have to use the yellow back arrow to clear the field.<br /><br /><strong><span style=\"color: #800000;\">ALERT:</span> </strong>If the station is installing multiple VXs, they <br />must use a switch off of LAN1 and connect the VXs to the switch.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>WARNING:</strong></span> After making any changes to the VX:<br />it MUST be&nbsp;powercycled for the changes to take affect.</p>\r\n<p>Press the key next to &lsquo;Done.&rsquo;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Then press the red X key twice to return to main menu.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td valign=\"top\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>For devices on a Fusion Point Express</strong>&nbsp;:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\">The VX570 <strong>will <span style=\"color: #993300; text-decoration: underline;\">not</span> work </strong>on the FPX platform.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: medium; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Wiring Setup - Prysm</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><img src=\"upload/diag_prysm-vx.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"699\" height=\"324\" /></strong></span></p>', '2012-08-27 16:11:16', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-05 09:25:00', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions for installing a single Vx570 at a satellite location', '', 10004, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(118, 'Ruby Gift Card Setup', '<p>Basic Setup:</p>\r\n<p>For software version 5.04.15 and higher.</p>\r\n<p><strong>This setup must be completed for all software versions. </strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow until the display reads, <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">\"NETWORK MANAGER\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Type the ID &amp; Password and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow until the display reads, <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">\"CONFIGURATION\" and press \"ENTER.\"&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow until the display reads, <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">\"DEALER CONFIGURATION\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Continue to press the \"ENTER\" key until you see the question; \"STORE VALUE CARDS ACCEPTED?\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Answer \"YES\" to this question when prompted and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted \"SVC ACTIVATION ALLOWED,\" an-swer \"YES\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted \"SVC RECHARGE ALLOWED,\" an-swer \"YES\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted \"SVC ACTIVATION MIN,\" key in \"5\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted \"SVC ACTIVATION MAX,\" key in \"300\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted \"SVC RECHARGE MIN,\" key in \"5\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted \"SVC RECHARGE MAX,\" key in \"300\" and press \"ENTER.\" <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The setup is now complete for Gift Card transac<span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">tions. Press \"EXIT.\" </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Additional Setup for Linking Sale &amp; Activation:</p>\r\n<p>For 5.04.15 software or higher.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow until the display reads, <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">\"MANAGER\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Type the ID &amp; Password and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow until the display reads, <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">\"CONFIGURATION\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow until the display reads, \"SALES CONFIGURATION\" and press \"ENTER.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow until the display reads, <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">\"Prepaid Card Activate Dept.\" <br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Assign a number for the Activation Department and <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">press \"ENTER.\" <br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow key until the display reads, <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">\"Prepaid Card Recharge Dept,\" <br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Assign a number for the Recharge Department and <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">press \"ENTER.\" <br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>The Additional Setup is now complete for Gift Card <span style=\"font-family: Candara,Candara;\">transactions. Press \"EXIT.\" </span></li>\r\n</ul>', '2012-09-04 09:45:38', 'l7d23b', '2012-11-08 10:49:11', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Setup instructions for Verifone Ruby gift cards', '', 10001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(119, 'Gift Card Reloads', '<p>To process&nbsp;a gift card&nbsp;reload, you will need to:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Print a copy of the reload order from Vanguard</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This must be done by an agent with elevated Vanguard access as full card numbers will need to be accessed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Charge the credit card on the&nbsp;VX570 in room 156S<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Attach the credit card recipt to the reload order<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Reload the gift card in ValueLink</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"null\" href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=116\">Click here for Instructions</a><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Print a copy of the reload screen<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Update the HEAT ticket with the amount reloaded, method of payment, approval number, and the authorization number<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Attach all the copies and put them in&nbsp;Terry Dunham\'s&nbsp;desk.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-09-18 09:56:52', 'l7d23b', '2014-08-27 12:07:09', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Procedure for after hours gift card reloads', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=116');
