(129, 'Gift Card Order/Reload Procedures ', '<p>Gift card orders and reloads are submitted by Wholesale Technical Support through our Reflex system.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To access the gift card system in Reflex, hover your&nbsp;cursor&nbsp;over the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">ReflexSVC</span>\" menu and select either \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SVC Order</span>\" or \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SVC Admin</span>\".</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-svc-header.png\" width=\"900\" height=\"122\" /></p>\r\n<p>The selection you make from the \"ReflexSVC\" menu will depend on what you need.&nbsp; Here is an overview of each selection:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>SVC Order:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Add a new customer</li>\r\n<li>Pulling up/searching for the customer\'s profile</li>\r\n<li>Start a new order/reload</li>\r\n<li>Edit an existing order</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-svc-order-screen.png\" width=\"521\" height=\"265\" /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>SVC Admin:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Locate an existing order by payment type (Credit card, Cost Center, Check, etc.)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-svc-admin-screen.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"536\" height=\"319\" /></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Adding a new customer</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; On the \"SVC Order\" screen, fill out the fields located in the customer information section:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Customer Name</strong> - customer\'s first and last name</li>\r\n<li><strong>Company Name</strong> - If this is for the customer\'s business, enter their business name.&nbsp; If this is a personal order, enter their first and last name.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Phone Number</strong> - customer\'s phone number</li>\r\n<li><strong>Street Address</strong> - customer\'s street address</li>\r\n<li><strong>Address 2</strong> - used for apartment numbers or suite numbers</li>\r\n<li><strong>City</strong> - customer\'s city</li>\r\n<li><strong>State</strong> - customer\'s state</li>\r\n<li><strong>Zip</strong> - customer\'s zip</li>\r\n<li><strong>Email</strong> - customer\'s email address.&nbsp; If the customer does not have a email address, use <a href=\"mailto:giftcard@valero.com\">giftcard@valero.com</a> &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Status:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>501C3</strong> - this is for non-profit customers.&nbsp; We require a copy of the customer\'s 501C3 designation letter they should have from the IRS.&nbsp; They can send this letter to us at <a href=\"mailto:giftcard@valero.com\">giftcard@valero.com</a> or fax it&nbsp;to us at <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">806-324-4759<a style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 806-324-4759\" href=\"#\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 806-324-4759\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></a></span>.&nbsp; For 501C3 customers we waive the standard 3% handling fee and <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">only charge $.25 per card</span>.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Promotion - </strong>used for gift card promotions.&nbsp; Check with David Cantor on what information is needed.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Corporate</strong> - used for Valero employees (including Valero refineries).&nbsp; Reflex will not charge a handling fee or per card cost for this status type.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>2.&nbsp; Once the information is filled out, click on \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Save Customer Data</strong></span>\".&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>3.&nbsp; This will bring up&nbsp;a dialog box with the&nbsp;new customer\'s ID number, click&nbsp;\"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>OK</strong></span>\".&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.&nbsp; Enter the new customer number in the \"Customer Number\" field and click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Begin Order</strong></span>\".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Pulling up/searching for the customer\'s profile</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SVC Order</span>\" screen, you can bring up the customer\'s profile by using one of two fields:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Customer Number - </strong>enter in the customer&nbsp;number if&nbsp;it is known.&nbsp; This is a number that is assigned to the customer\'s profile.&nbsp; On the dialog box that appears, click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">OK</span>\".&nbsp; <strong>&nbsp;</strong><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/reflex-gc-search.png\" width=\"339\" height=\"229\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Search Customer - </strong>if the customer number is not known, you can search for the customer\'s profile using this field.&nbsp; You can search for the profile&nbsp;using queries such as:<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>First name</li>\r\n<li>Last name</li>\r\n<li>Phone number (format - XXX-XXX-XXXX)</li>\r\n<li>Street address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 2.&nbsp; Once you have entered your query, click on \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Search</span>\".&nbsp; Reflex will bring up a list of&nbsp;results based on your query.&nbsp; Of the results that populate, click on the profile you would like to use.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3.&nbsp; On the dialog box that appears, click on \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">OK</span>\".&nbsp; This will bring up the customer\'s profile and you can&nbsp;start the gift card order.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Starting a new gift card order/reload</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The customer\'s gift card profile consists of three sections that consist of their billing information, order information, and their payment method/shipping type.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Verify customer\'s information:<br />&nbsp; </span></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The left hand side of the page will populate with their information that we have on file.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If this is the same information they want to use for their shipping, check the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Same as Customer Info</span>\" box located on the right.&nbsp; The shipping fields will populate with the information from the left&nbsp;side.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If they want&nbsp;to provide alternate shipping information for this order, manually key in the customer\'s information in the blank fields on the right.&nbsp; </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Note:</span></strong>&nbsp; if changes are needed to the customer\'s information, click on the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Customer Info</span>\" tab located at the&nbsp;top.&nbsp; Make the necessary changes and click on \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Save Customer Data</span>\".&nbsp; <br /><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-gc-customer-info.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"252\" /></span><br /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Populate the order information:<br /><br /></span></strong></strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The order information consists of the following information:</span><strong><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-gc-order-fields.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"802\" height=\"86\" /><br /></span></strong></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Card Type - <br /></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Fuel Only </strong>&ndash; These cards can only be used for fuel purchases either at the pump or inside the store.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Gift Card</strong> &ndash; These cards can be use for any merchandise inside the store or fuel at the pump.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Card Count</strong> &ndash; How many of one denomination are being requested.&nbsp; If multiple cards are being requested at different denominations, click on \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Add Card</span>\" to add a new row for each denomination requested.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Amount</strong> - dollar amount for each gift card requested.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Reload Card Number</strong> &ndash; if the order is for new cards, leave blank.&nbsp; If the order is for a reload, enter in the gift card number here.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the customer has submitted reload orders with us in the past, the gift card numbers used previously will be in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Previous Reloads</span>\" section located on the right.&nbsp; Check mark the box next to the gift card number and click on \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Move Selected to Order</span>\".&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><br /></span></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Complete the payment method/shipping&nbsp;type section<br /><br /></strong>The payment method/shipping type section is&nbsp;where you can select the&nbsp;Shipping Type and enter information pertaining to their&nbsp;method of payment.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong></span> The basic shipping type is UPS Ground, which is no cost to the customer.&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>If the customer requests expedited shipping</strong></span>, however, we can accommodate that request by sending it by FedEx shipping.&nbsp;<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=471\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> to see&nbsp;article # 471 for instructions on how to obtain a shipping quote from FedEx.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Note:</span>&nbsp; </strong>You <strong>MUST </strong>obtain the shipping cost from the FedEx website if expedited shipping is requested.&nbsp;&nbsp;Obtaining and providing this information into the order is the responsibility of the agent who takes the order.&nbsp; <strong>All costs must be in place before submitting the order.<br /><br /></strong><strong><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-gc-payment-method.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"617\" height=\"273\" /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Shipping Type<br /></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Free UPS Ground &ndash; </strong>standard free shipping type. 3-5 days shipping time. Not guaranteed.</li>\r\n<li><strong>FedEx 2 Day</strong> <strong>Air</strong> &ndash; 2 Day delivery</li>\r\n<li><strong>FedEx Standard Overnight</strong> &ndash; usually delivered before 3-4PM following business day.</li>\r\n<li><strong>FedEx Priority Overnight</strong> &ndash; usually delivered before 10AM the following business day.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>FedEx/UPS Acct #</strong>&ndash; customer provided FedEx or UPS&nbsp;account number. Not required.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Ship Weight</strong> &ndash; this is to be used on the FedEx website to determine shipping cost.&nbsp; Reflex automatically populates this field.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Shipping Cost</strong> &ndash; this is obtained from the FedEx website.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Method of Payment:<br /></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Credit</strong> - Amex, Visa, MasterCard, Discover</li>\r\n<li><strong>Valero Fleet</strong> - Valero Fleet/Commerical account</li>\r\n<li><strong>Valero Consumer</strong> - Valero consumer credit card</li>\r\n<li><strong>Check or Money Order </strong>- customer check/money order</li>\r\n<li><strong>Wire Transfer</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Valero Internal Cost Center</strong> - this is typically used by Valero employees from corporate that places orders</li>\r\n<li><strong>Quote Only</strong> - this is typically not used.&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">If the order is just for a \"quote only\", place that in the order notes.</span>&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Payment Card</strong> - click the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Modify</span>\" button to insert or change the customer\'s card information (credit card number and expiration date) or the&nbsp;information for a Valero Internal Cost Center order (Cost Center GL, Cost Number, and Company Code).&nbsp; &nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Card Expiration</strong> - auto populates when entered in the&nbsp;Payment Card field.&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Cost Center GL/Cost Number/Company Code - </strong>auto populates when entered in the Payment Card field.<strong>&nbsp; <br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Total Card Value - </strong>cost for the amount of the gift cards only, does not included any shipping or handling fees.<strong>&nbsp; <br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Handling Fee - </strong>the current handling fee for gift card orders/reloads is <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">3%</span>.&nbsp; This will auto populate by Reflex.&nbsp;<strong> <br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Card Cost Total - </strong>In the event the customer has a <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">501C3 status there is only a $.25 per card cost</span> in lieu of the 3% handling fee.&nbsp; There is also a $.25 per card cost if any reload requests are for <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">$5.00</span>.&nbsp;<strong> <br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Grand Total - </strong>this is the dollar amount total of the total card value plus any shipping and handling fees charge.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Order Number</strong> - this is the ticket number you create in Heat.&nbsp;&nbsp;Here are the steps to create a new&nbsp;\"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Consumer</span>\" ticket in Heat:<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>While in Heat, hold \"Ctrl\" and press \"N\" on your keyboard.&nbsp;&nbsp;This will open a new ticket.&nbsp; If the ticket is not a \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Consumer</span>\" ticket, hold \"Ctrl\" and&nbsp;press \"T\" on your keyboard and select \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Consumer</span>\".&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Enter \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">VLO</span>\" in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Store</span>\" field located at the top right corner and press \"tab\" on&nbsp;your keyboard.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>If the customer is an existing customer, enter&nbsp;in their phone number in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Preferred Phone</span>\" field or their last name in the last name field in Heat and press \"tab\".&nbsp; If the customer\'s information is in Heat, it will bring up a dialog box with the profiles that match the information you entered.&nbsp; Double click on the profile you would like to use.&nbsp; The customer\'s profile will populate in Heat.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>On the Heat menu bar located at the top, click <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">AutoTask &gt; Quick Ticket &gt; Gift Card Bulk Order</span>.&nbsp; Heat will begin the gift card order wizard that also creates a appointment for the gift card agent.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>The&nbsp;Heat ticket number&nbsp;can be located at the top left hand corner of the ticket (ex. 01527777).&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Order Notes</strong> &ndash; If there are any notes of any kind for the order, they go here. If you put special notes in the ticket, <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">they may be overlooked</span>.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Emailed Gift Card Orders/Reloads</strong></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:</strong></span> If the order was submitted to us via <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">email</span>, the following steps <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">must</span> </strong>also be performed:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Change the source to &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">email</span>&rdquo; in your HEAT ticket</li>\r\n<li>Immediately after pasting the order information in the notes, <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">copy and paste the full contents of your customer&rsquo;s email</span> body to the Assignment Notes of your ticket</li>\r\n<li>Alternatively, you may copy and paste the email contents into a Journal note (or &ldquo;Received Documents&rdquo; Journal entry) or you may save the email as a &ldquo;.msg&rdquo; and attach a copy to the ticket (Attachments tab and [right-click] select &ldquo;Add Attachment&rdquo;).<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Complete the order</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Type the Heat ticket number into the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Order Number</span>\" field.</li>\r\n<li>Make sure you have entered any order notes, if necessary.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Confirm the information in the order and click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Submit Order</span>\".</li>\r\n<li>Highlight and copy the information that appears in the dialog box and paste it into the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Assignment Notes</span>\" field in Heat, located under the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Assignment</span>\" tab in the ticket.&nbsp; Once that is completed, click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">OK</span>\" in the dialog box.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>A PDF copy of the order will auto-print on the printer located in WTS.&nbsp; Place this copy in the \"Gift Card Orders\" tray located next to the printer room in WTS.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>If you have confirmed the order has been printed successfully, close the PDF window that populates when the order is submitted.</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:</strong></span>&nbsp; if&nbsp;you entered the full credit card number on the order, the full card number will&nbsp;appear on the order invoice.&nbsp; Verify the full card number did appear on the&nbsp;invoice before closing the PDF window.&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><strong><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Edit an existing order</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Under the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SVC Order</span>\" menu, enter in the ticket number in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Order Editor</span>\" field and click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Go</span>\".&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Make the necessary changes to the order and then click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Update Order</span>\" at the bottom.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Locate an existing order</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Under the \"SVC Admin\" menu, you can locate an existing gift card order whether it\'s classified as \"New\", \"In Progress\", or \"Suspended\":&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">New Orders</span>\" tab show all orders that are pending to be processed.&nbsp; You can click on the orders to see a glimpse of the details for that order.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>The \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">In Process</span>\" tab shows orders that are&nbsp;currently in process.</li>\r\n<li>The \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Suspended</span>\" tab shows orders that&nbsp;have been suspended&nbsp;due to&nbsp;a declined credit card, returned check, or failed wire transfers.&nbsp; Once the order has gone through successfully it will be taken out of this area.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Additionally, you can locate an existing order by the Heat ticket number using the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Lookup</span>\" tab.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-gc-order-lookup.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"371\" height=\"92\" /></p>\r\n<p>Enter in the Heat ticket number in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Order Lookup</span>\" field and click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Search</span>\".&nbsp; Reflex will then bring up the PDF copy of the invoice so you can print or save it as needed.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>', '2012-10-10 09:50:34', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-13 08:46:55', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions on how to process gift card orders/reloads in Reflex', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:giftcard@valero.comindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=471'),
(133, 'Debit Networks in Clientline', '<ol>\r\n<li>Star West<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Star Northest<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Star Southeast<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Pulse<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Shazam<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Nyce<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Accel <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Maestro<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Interlink<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Alaska<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>AFFN Direct<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>PAVD Interlink</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-10-10 14:46:39', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-05 08:56:53', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Debit networks that need to be checked in site\'s Clientline profile', '', 40002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(137, 'Gilbarco Passport / American Express processing issue', '<p>From the Passport Terminal:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to the&nbsp;Tools menu<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Manager Workstation<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Setup<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Network Menu<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Concord<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Network Card Configuration<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select American Express in the credit card table<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the Page 2 Tab<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Change the Track Configuration field from Mandatory Track 1 to&nbsp;Preferred Track 1<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Save</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-10-19 11:13:55', 'l7d23b', '2013-05-06 09:15:25', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'For issues running some Amex cards on passports.', '', 10006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
