(139, 'Common Credit Card Decline Codes', '<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>2M -&nbsp;Enter Lesser Amount</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">Transaction exceeds preauthorized amount</p>\r\n<p>First Data reprocesses&nbsp;2M declines over $18.00&nbsp;automatically. The correction time can range anywhere from 2 to 6 weeks.</p>\r\n<p>Do not submit these, unless&nbsp;$18.00 or under, for adjustment, as this will cause a duplicate charge to the customer once adjusted by First Data.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2A - Unauthorized Usage</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">There are a few different types of 2A declines.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">Store forced&nbsp;authorization -&nbsp;Site lost communications and clerk was prompted to enter an approval number. Clerk keyed a&nbsp;number without&nbsp;contacting card company for a correct approval number.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\">2A decline on refund.&nbsp; Network will not correct, must be corrected in VT.</p>\r\n<p>2A declines on Valero cards will not be reprocessed by the network, you must submit manuals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">2T &nbsp;2G&nbsp; Message Edit Error</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>If Track Length in&nbsp;Client Line&nbsp;is high, Ex: &lsquo;Track Length:&nbsp; 59&rsquo;&nbsp;&nbsp;the pinpad is sending too many characters to validate.</p>\r\n<p>This ususally requires a pin pad replacement to&nbsp;resolve.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>4R&nbsp; Encryption Mismatch</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Site encryption and network encryption do not match.</p>\r\n<p>Confirm encryption on pinpad matches encryption at network level.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-10-19 11:52:55', 'l7d23b', '2013-08-22 08:24:49', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on specific types of declines', '', 50006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
