(141, 'New Jersey Gift Card Information', '<p>Due to recent a recent law that was passed in New Jersey, merchants are required to capture and bind a zip code to gift cards that are sold&nbsp;to New Jersey residents&nbsp;at the time of purchase.</p>\r\n<p>Our system was not build to handle this functionality, therefore, we cannot sell gift cards in New Jersey.</p>\r\n<p>American Express pulled their gift cards from the state about a year after we did.</p>\r\n<p>Most merchants will not honor the cards in NJ either.</p>\r\n<div id=\"imcontent\" dir=\"ltr\"><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"color: #000000; font-family: \'Segoe UI\'; font-size: 10pt; direction: ltr; -ms-word-wrap: break-word;\"><a title=\"https://www.dlapiper.com/en/us/insights/publications/2012/08/new-jersey-amends-controversial-gift-card-law/\" href=\"https://www.dlapiper.com/en/us/insights/publications/2012/08/new-jersey-amends-controversial-gift-card-law/\">https://www.dlapiper.com/en/us/insights/publications/2012/08/new-jersey-amends-controversial-gift-card-law/</a></span></div>', '2012-10-19 12:02:19', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-19 07:20:00', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information regarding selling giftcards to New Jersey residents', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'https://www.dlapiper.com/en/us/insights/publications/2012/08/new-jersey-amends-controversial-gift-card-law/');
