(144, 'RAMS Merchant Phone Number Change', '<ol>\r\n<li>Enter MPHN on the COMMAND line in rams.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>You will now have a menu to update the phone number for the merchant.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the correct phone number and press Enter.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-10-19 12:31:07', 'l7d23b', '2014-08-13 15:38:42', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to change a merchant phone number in RAMS', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(145, 'Change / Update Merchant ID in RAMS', '<p><strong>Note: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Only certain agents have access to change this in RAMS.&nbsp; If you are not sure who has access, please see your supervisor.&nbsp;</span> </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>To set the POS Type on the front page:</strong></p>\r\n<p>COMMAND: POST&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; CODE: Terminal type&nbsp;(TP, L3, VX, JZ)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>To set the full merchant ID in the Merchant/Dealer to Alias screen:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In the FUNCTION: field&nbsp;enter \"A\" press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In ALIAS enter the full merchant ID XXYYZZZZZZ001<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Tab to SEQ, enter 001<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Tab to ID, enter ID<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press Enter</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>To delete an entry in the Merchant/Dealer to Alias screen:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Move your cursor to the corresponding field,<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter a \"D\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Confirm delete with the F5 key.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-10-19 12:41:04', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-05 09:05:13', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to change / update Merchant IDs in RAMS', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 2', 'N', ''),
(146, 'Store requests name change', '<p>If a store owner calls requesting a major&nbsp;name change, they need to referred to their Jobber.</p>\r\n<p>Their jobber will need to contact their Valero Sales Rep to fill out a 1089 form to have the name changed.</p>', '2012-10-19 12:48:54', 'l7d23b', '2013-02-05 09:27:09', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'What to do when a store wants to change their name', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(147, 'Locating RAMS account number within Fleet / Consumer Valero cards', '<p>Valero Fleet and Consumer cards numbers located&nbsp;in Client Line have additional digits added to them for processing purposes.</p>\r\n<p>To find the RAMS account number from these cards, use the following guides.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Valero Fleet&nbsp;Cards:&nbsp;3062486121234567&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Remove the first 9 digits and take the next 6, dropping the final digit. 306248612<span style=\"background-color: #99cc00;\">123456</span>7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The RAMS account number for this card would be: 123456</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Valero Consumer or Commercial cards: 707101123456780001</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Remove the first 6 digits. The remainder will be the account number + sub number: 707101<span style=\"background-color: #99cc00;\">12345678</span><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\">0001</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The RAMS account number for this card would be 12345678-0001. 0001 being the sub number.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>All new IIN cards start with &lsquo;700038&rsquo; and the next 2 digits tell you what type of card it is.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #00ff00;\">700038</span><span style=\"background-color: #00ffff;\">00</span> is a consumer card</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #00ff00;\">700038</span><span style=\"background-color: #00ffff;\">10</span> is a Commercial or Fleet card</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #00ff00;\">700038</span><span style=\"background-color: #00ffff;\">01</span> is an insta-credit card</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The last 10 digits of the card number are the RAMS/FAMS Account Number. &nbsp;In this case, it is an Instacredit account number of 9454131740</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To find the <strong><em>real RAMS account</em></strong> associated with the Insta-credit account you have to go to the System Control (H) &agrave; Account NO / Ref NO (C) screen in RAMS and enter the TSP number.</p>\r\n<p>After entering the TSP number, hit enter, and it will pull up the RAMS account number associated with the TSP. If you want to see the actual TSP card on the account, you can see it on the card screen (D).</p>', '2012-10-19 13:00:03', 'l7d23b', '2016-05-09 13:07:22', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Locating RAMS account number within Fleet / Consumer Valero cards', '', 50006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(148, 'Small Credit Amount', '<p>The following instructions are for setting up a VeriFone POS to not print a signature line on credit card receipts for credit transactions that do not exceed this user configured limit.&nbsp; The limit entered is inclusive so signature lines will not appear on receipts up to and including the limit entered.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Using the Ruby to configure the value:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From cashier screen Press the <strong>&ldquo;Exit&rdquo; </strong>button<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Use the left-right arrow keys to navigate to <strong>&ldquo;System Setup&rdquo;<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>&ldquo;Enter&rdquo;</strong> key<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Use the left-right arrow keys to navigate to <strong>&ldquo;Network Manager&rdquo;<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>&ldquo;Enter&rdquo;</strong> key<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>System will request an <strong>I.D. </strong>and then a<strong> Password </strong>(This may require a call to the Valero Helpdesk to get a temporary backdoor users code.)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Use the left-right arrow keys to navigate to <strong>&ldquo;Configuration&rdquo;<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>&ldquo;Enter&rdquo;</strong> key<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Use the left-right arrow keys to navigate to <strong>&ldquo;Credit Card Configuration&rdquo;<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>&ldquo;Enter&rdquo;</strong> key<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Use the left-right arrow keys to navigate to the desired card type (This parameter must be set up for each card type individually)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>&ldquo;Enter&rdquo;</strong> key until you get to <strong>&ldquo;Small Credit Amount&rdquo;&nbsp; <em>(This is usually 38</em> times)<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Entered the desired amount:&nbsp; 25</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Repeat last three steps for each card type desired. This includes Visa, AmericanExpress, MasterCard, Discover, and Proprietary (Valero) cards.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Using SMS Configuration Manager to configure the value:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Network Manager</strong> from the menu bar<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the <strong>Credit Card</strong> tab<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the desired credit card type from the drop down menu<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the desired value for the &ldquo;<strong>Small Credit Amount&rdquo;</strong> parameter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Repeat last two steps for each card type desired</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-10-24 09:54:17', 'l7d23b', '2013-04-12 08:16:54', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to enable small credit amount on Ruby systems', '', 10001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
