(150, 'CRIND Limit and AVS Setup on Ruby', '<ol>\r\n<li>Exit from Sales<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If site has a Sapphire, right arrow to System Setup, press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Right Arrow to Network Manager, Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Make sure the caller does not log in to Network Manger. You need to follow the <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=143\" target=\"_blank\">backdoor login procedure</a> here.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to Configuration, Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to Credit Card Configuration, Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>You will see XX CC DISPLAY CODE 1\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The XX will correspond to card codes <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=106\" target=\"_blank\">listed here</a>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>To set AVS, Press Enter 26 times\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The display should read XX AVS PROMPT DCR.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set this option to YES. Press Enter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The display will now read: XX AVS PROMPT TYPE\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set this option to 1. Press Enter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The next option is XX TERM TIMEOUT. Press enter, this option does not need to be changed.</li>\r\n<li>The next option will be where you set CRIND limits. Proceed to the next step.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>To set CRIND Limits, press Enter 29 times from the XX CC DISPLAY CODE 1.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The display should read XX DISPENSER LIMIT. Set this accordingly and press Enter.</li>\r\n<li>The display will read XX DISPENSER AUTH. Set this accordingly and press Enter.</li>\r\n<li>Press the right arrow key to move to the next card.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Follow steps 8 and 9 for all card types listed</li>\r\n</ol>', '2012-10-25 10:17:47', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-02 11:54:09', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to setup or change CRInD limits and AVS on a VeriFone Ruby system', '', 10001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=143index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=106'),
(151, 'Spanish Translators for WTS', '<p>If you need assistance with handling a Spanish only call, please contact one of the following extensions</p>\r\n<p>Ext. 5053 - Spanish Level 1</p>\r\n<p>Ext. 5055 - Spanish Level 2</p>', '2012-11-15 11:50:59', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-04 14:13:46', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Spanish que extensions to translate spanish technical support calls', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(152, 'PDL on Ruby Terminals', '<table style=\"width: 100%; background-color: #b0c4de;\" border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Reminder: If this is a new install or software reload, remind the technician that CRInD limits and AVS&nbsp;<strong>must</strong> be set. AVS should be automatically set from the network, but might be disabled at the individual card level.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Exit from sales<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to System Setup<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to Network Manager<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Login via Backdoor</li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press 0 (zero)</li>\r\n<li>Press Enter</li>\r\n<li>Press Clear</li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Ruby will display ID=XX - Where XX is any number between 1-50</li>\r\n<li>Give the caller the <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=124\" target=\"_blank\">corresponding password for their XX ID.</a><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>Right arrow to Configuration<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The first option should say Parameter Download<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press Enter<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>This will start the parameter download.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Caller should see PDL Successful on Ruby display.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If PDL Error is displayed, re-flag the site and repeat the process.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2012-11-29 12:45:46', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-02 11:56:07', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to pull a parameter download on a Ruby terminal', '', 10001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=124'),
