(166, 'Gilbarco Passport Fuel Product Code Change', '<ol>\r\n<li>Log on to <strong>Manager Workstation<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Setup<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Forecourt<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Forecourt Installation<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Assign Network Codes<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Select the fuel type to be changed<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the bottom pane, select the correct code<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Update List<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Repeat steps 7 and 8 for all affected products<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Save changes</li>\r\n</ol>', '2013-01-29 10:23:56', 'l7d23b', '2014-08-01 08:45:33', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to change product codes on a Gilbarco Passport', '', 10006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(167, 'Common New Site Issues', '<p class=\"InfoBlue\">A few things can go wrong with a site set-up, not necessarily unrelated to challenges of managing sites post set-up. A few key frequently occurring issues include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lines are not ready: Mostly happens when the ISDN/PSTN line order is late. On sites going through the technology refresh, if this is caught on time, the site can be set live using a GPRS router. If the site is in an area of poor GPRS signal, the go live will be delayed until PSTN line and ADSL services are delivered.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Wrong MIDS and/or TIDS: The site cannot get authorisation if the MIDs are not setup or associated with the TIDS held by the card issuers and the bank acquirer. The online authorisation host and terminal provider must also have the MIDs and TIDs setup on the terminal. If there are mismatches or the terminal is not set up to accept a particular card, the card will fail online authorisation.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Delays in issuing MIDs: This is pretty common. Most suppliers will take 10 days to issue MIDs. The rule of the thumb is to aim to complete site set up as soon as the Barclays MID has been issued.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2013-01-29 16:18:23', 'l7d23b', '2013-10-23 14:18:02', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on UK new site setup issues', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
