(169, 'CRIND Limit and AVS Setup on Sapphire via SMS', '<ol>\r\n<li>Have the customer log in to SMS on the back office PC<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Log in as helpdesk or a user with the helpdesk role<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose Network Manager<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose Network Configuration<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Customer will need to allow the active x control<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose Credit Card <strong></strong>Backdoor<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on the individual card type and set the limits and/or AVS option&nbsp;for that card type<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Repeat the step 7&nbsp; until all cards have been changed<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Save changes</li>\r\n</ol>', '2013-01-29 16:26:57', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-13 08:35:16', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions on how to configure CRIND limits and AVS via SMS', '', 10002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(170, 'Incorrect time on Gempay due to Daylight Savings', '<p>If a site calls and says that there time is wrong after the time change you will dial into TMS.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the middle button on the Gempay<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Go to maintenance<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Go to download<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Go to connect<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>They will get #s and it will be dialing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The time should update after a few minutes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If that doesn&rsquo;t work, you can have them manually update the time.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Middle button on the Gempay<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Terminal<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Date/time<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Engineer Password\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>4832<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Change Time<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Delete Time(clear)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter correct time</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The correct time should be displayed.&nbsp;If it&nbsp;still not correct, raise a ticket with HTEC.</p>', '2013-01-29 16:28:38', 'l7d23b', '2016-01-07 08:43:56', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on updating the time on Gempays', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(171, 'Wayne Nucleus CRIND / CAT Limit Information', '<p>On the Wayne Nucleus systems, the Wayne technician has to change these limits.</p>\r\n<p>On Wayne Nucleus systems&nbsp;they are&nbsp;referred to as CAT limits, not CRIND limits.</p>', '2013-01-29 16:30:56', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-13 08:26:01', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on setting CRIND / CAT limits on a Wayne Nucleus', '', 10007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(172, 'Jobber/Dealer Portal Support Quick Reference', '<p>First time login</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Set up a new password after they have entered in the temporary password provided via email from their registration.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The new password cannot contain their first or last name, or company name. If your password contained one of these, they will need to use the <em>Forgot Password</em> link to reset your password.</li>\r\n<li>Password must be at least <strong>8 characters long</strong> and contain <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">3 out of the 4</span> requirements below:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>one upper case letter</li>\r\n<li>one lower case letter</li>\r\n<li>a number</li>\r\n<li>a special character</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When selecting browser&rsquo;s:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ensure their browser is Microsoft Internet Explorer 10 or higher (Other options include Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox and Apple Safari which can be downloaded for free)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"color: #800000;\">Enter the new portal from &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.valero.com/\">www.valero.com</a> and do not use previously saved bookmarks</span></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #800080;\"><strong>Note: New logins begin with WDI (<span style=\"font-family: courier new,courier;\">I</span> as in Indigo) not a <span style=\"font-family: courier new,courier;\">1</span>. If you have a customer calling advising their login doesn\'t work. Make sure they\'re using an \"<span style=\"font-family: courier new,courier;\">I</span>\" instead of a \"<span style=\"font-family: courier new,courier;\">1</span>\"</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>Note: When an entry advises to contact Sara Jackson, do NOT refer the customer to her. You need to contact her yourself. At no time will&nbsp;we ever refer a customer directly to her.&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If a user needs to setup security questions</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Navigate to Account Info Support &gt; User Profile &gt; Security Questions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br /><br />User Cannot Login - Old Login</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Need to re-register&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>User Cannot Login - New Login</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If they have a&nbsp;login ID, answer security question to receive email If no security question, reset password. If they&nbsp;don\'t have a&nbsp;login, contact Sarah Jackson to get login and&nbsp;then reset password</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Forgot login ID</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contact Sarah Jackson</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Forgot password - old login</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Need to re-register</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Forgot password - new login</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click Forgot your password and answer security question.&nbsp;&nbsp; If no security question, reset password</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Signed up on dealer portal - have not received login&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Check with Sarah Jackson to see if approved in system.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If not in system, contact their distributor&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>If in system, verify email address then reset and send</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>CTE information on dealer portal</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New login info is only sent at beginning of month for CTE access</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>New login - cannot login - blank security questions</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Reset password - go to User Profile and set up questions</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Unable to access MSR on unbranded portal</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>MSR is only on branded portal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Need access to update volume - branded</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Refer to their contract administrator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dealer wanting to verify portal&nbsp;registration</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Refer to their contract administrator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dealer requesting multiple sites on single dealer login</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Refer to their contract administrator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Incorrect email address</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contact Sarah Jackson-has to be reset in three places.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Incorrect site linked with login - dealer</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Refer to their contract administrator</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Re-registered - don\'t see same info</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contact Sarah Jackson to see if same sold to on both accounts</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dealer not seeing EFT</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contact Sarah Jackson to see if sold to is correct</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dealer not seeing Device Billing</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contact Sarah Jackson to see if sold to is correct</li>\r\n</ul>', '2013-01-29 16:34:02', 'l7d23b', '2015-07-06 08:48:36', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Solutions to common issues regarding the jobber/dealer portal', '', 40007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'http://www.valero.com/'),
(173, 'UK Glossary', '<p><strong>BMS</strong><br />Bank Merchant Acquirer, currently Barclaycard</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>CAD</strong><br />Card Acceptance Device</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>ADSL</strong><br />Broadband, Asymmetric digital subscriber line</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>GPRS</strong><br />Mobile SIM capability, fallback for the broadband service</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>ISDN</strong><br />Integrated services digital network. ISDN2e multipoint with 2 MSNs is used as the standard OLA comms method on legacy sites</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>MSN</strong><br />Multi subscriber numbering. Facility whereby you can have more than one telephone number allocated to your ISDN2e</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>OLA</strong><br />Online authorisation&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>EFT</strong><br />Electronic fund transfer</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>EPOS</strong><br />Electronic point of sale</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>Hot card file</strong><br />List of suspicious, fraudulent or barred cards. File is constantly updated and held by the OLA host</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>ISO</strong><br />Card compliant number range, usually associated with a card issuer</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>Card scheme rules</strong><br />Rules and regulations governing card schemes</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>Card PAN</strong><br />Primary Account Number</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>MID</strong><br />Merchant Identification number</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>TID</strong><br />Terminal Identification number</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>SIF</strong><br />Site information form</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>KYC</strong><br />Barclays Know Your Customer process</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>PSTN</strong><br />Public switched Telephone network (voice line for making calls and running the ADSL service)</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>Terminal</strong><br />Device hosting EFT in non-integrated sites (CAD)</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>Integrated POS</strong><br />(POS) hosting EFT and EPOS on a single device</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>PinPad</strong><br />PIN entry device</p>\r\n<p align=\"left\"><strong>WREN</strong><br />FIS Transaction records database</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-01-29 16:36:54', 'l7d23b', '2014-09-30 14:48:10', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Glossary of common UK Retail Tech terms', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(174, 'Merchant Identification Number', '<p>A Merchant ID is a way to identifiy a station within our network(s).</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; text-decoration: underline;\">Merchant ID Breakdown</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">POS Type Identifier</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">[TP]</span>48343453001</li>\r\n<li>The first 2 digits of the full ID are the POS Type identifier:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TP - Verifone Ruby/Topaz Sapphire</li>\r\n<li>L3 - Gilbarco Passport</li>\r\n<li>5M - Wayne Nucleus</li>\r\n<li>VX - Verifone VX570</li>\r\n<li>JS - VeriFone VX520</li>\r\n<li>JZ - Fiscal</li>\r\n<li>JD - NCR</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\">K4 - Verifone Omni (Unused)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\">2B - Gilbarco G-Site&nbsp;(Unused)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #808080;\">1D - Verifone Ruby&nbsp;(Unused)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">State Code </span>- (<span style=\"color: #000000;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=175\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> for state code listings</span>)</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TP<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">[48]</span>343453001</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The second set of digits is the State Code</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Buypass ID</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">TP48<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">[343453]</span>001</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The third set of digits is the Buypass ID.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">This is the identifier you will use when contacting the Buypass Helpdesk or accessing store information in Client Line.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Terminal ID</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">TP48343453<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">[001]</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The final set of digits is the Terminal ID.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">This allows the site to have multiple POS without having different Buypass ID.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '2013-01-30 16:21:09', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-02 13:40:43', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Merchant IDs', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=175');
