(176, 'Internet Explorer Configuration for Fleet Portal', '<p>If a customer is having issues accessing certain functions in the Fleet Portal, check the following&nbsp;settings.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From the Tools menu in Internet Explorer select Internet Options.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/tools.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"309\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the Internet Options window select the Security tab, click on the Trusted Sites zone, and click on the Sites Button.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/ieoptions.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"412\" height=\"519\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the Trusted sites window, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>uncheck the box for Require server verification (https:) for all sites in this zone</strong></span>,</p>\r\n<p>Type *.valero.com in the Add this website to the zone: field and click the Add button.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/ietrusted.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"384\" height=\"342\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the Internet Options window click on the Custom Level button.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/iecustomer.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"409\" height=\"516\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the Security Settings window locate the Automatic prompting for file downloads setting and click the radio button for Enable.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/iesecurity.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"414\" height=\"478\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click OK to close the Security Settings window, click Yes to the Warning! message and click OK again to close the Internet Options window.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/iewarning.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"380\" height=\"120\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From the Tools menu in Internet Explorer select Pop-up Blocker &gt; Pop-up Blocker Settings.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/iepop.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"376\" height=\"305\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the Pop-up Blocker Settings window, type *.valero.com in the Address of website to allow:, click the Add button, and click the Close button.<br /><br />NOTE: Other Pop-up blockers (IE Google Toolbar, Yahoo Toolbar, etc) must also be disabled or configured to allow pop-ups from *.valero.com .</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/iepop2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"435\" height=\"476\" /></p>', '2013-02-18 11:10:28', 'l7d23b', '2013-02-20 14:54:01', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions on configuring IE7 and IE8 for the Fleet Portal', '', 40008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
