acredit IP sets', '', 10009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(178, 'Instacredit issues and troubleshooting', '<p>Typically, you will only encounter errors when a store is calling to install an Instacredit device.</p>\r\n<p>The only error&nbsp;for the device is:&nbsp;\"Your application cannot be processed due to techincal difficulties. Any data entered has been erased.\"</p>\r\n<p>This error indicates connectivity issues to the outside network.</p>\r\n<p>Log in to the&nbsp;InstaCredit Device and verify settings:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Paperclip the MX870 until the heartbeat lights flash out of sequence.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>You will be presented with a login screen.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/insta_login.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"286\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter 020456<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once logged in, you will be presented with a screen of icons.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/insta_screen1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"303\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Configure<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Network <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Ethernet<br /><br /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/insta_ethconfig.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"400\" height=\"299\" />\r\n<table style=\"width: 397px; height: 199px;\" border=\"0\" align=\"right\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Notice the eth0 entry. This can indicate where the issue is.</p>\r\n<p>If it reads eth0: UP &gt;&gt; Link: UP and the site is getting an error:<br />This indicates a communication issue past the network. <br />Look for a configuration issue with the addressing.</p>\r\n<p>If it reads eth0: UP &gt;&gt; Link: DOWN <br />This indicates an issue&nbsp;with&nbsp;the connection to the gateway. The gateway will be the comm device&nbsp;(ex.&nbsp;Prysm, FPX).&nbsp;This can be a physical connection issue,&nbsp;a mistake in the addressing configuration, or an unprogrammed port on the comm device.</p>\r\n<p>If it reads eth0: DOWN &gt;&gt; Link: DOWN<br />The ethernet port is disable on the Instacredit Device.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Verify the settings to make sure they match with their <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=177\" target=\"_blank\">corresponding setup info</a>.</p>\r\n<p>If the settings are incorrect for the communication type, <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=160\">click here</a>, and step through&nbsp;the appropriate changes.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/alert2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"27\" />If the site is reporting normal functionality, but the touchscreen is not printing the corresponding keypress; i.e. pressing \"6\" prints a \"K\" on the screen, follow these calibration instructions.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Choose &ldquo;Configure&rdquo; from the main screen<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Hit the blue right arrow key once<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose &ldquo;Calibrate&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Screen will go black and then come back to the menu<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Hit the left arrow key twice<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose &ldquo;file manager&rdquo; and &ldquo;restart&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>After all settings have been verified and the device is still failing. Please contact Mizti with the device serial number for replacement.</p>', '2013-02-19 10:57:35', 'l7d23b', '2013-04-17 15:28:04', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions on troubleshooting the Instacredit device', '', 10009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=177index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=160'),
(179, 'Virtual Terminal Request Requirements', '<p>When submitting Virtual Terminal requests, the following information is required in the heat ticket.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Last 4 digits of the card number</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Card Expiration Date</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Approval/Authorization Number<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Transaction Date<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Adjustment (charge or return)&nbsp;Amount</li>\r\n</ul>', '2013-02-19 15:35:45', 'l7d23b', '2013-02-19 15:39:30', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Necessary information for submitting Virtual Terminal requests', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(180, 'Preauth Holds', '<p>An Authorization hold (also card authorization, preauthorization, or preauth) is the practice within the banking industry of authorizing electronic transactions done with a debit card or credit card and holding this balance as unavailable either until the bank posts the completion amount (also called settlement), or the hold \"falls off.\" In the case of debit cards, authorization holds can fall off the account (thus rendering the balance available again) anywhere from 1&ndash;5 days after the transaction date depending on the bank\'s policy; in the case of credit cards, holds may last as long as 30 days, depending on the issuing bank.</p>\r\n<p><br />Signature-based (non-PIN-based) credit card transactions are a two-step process, consisting of an authorization and a settlement.<br />Once the customer swipes their card at the pump, the financial institution that backs the card authorizes a certain amount of money from the available balance of the card. The hold amount can be anywhere from $1.00 to $125.00 depending on the FI.</p>\r\n<p><strong>A)</strong> When the customer hangs up the pump, our network notifies the customer&rsquo;s FI of the amount purchased. At this point, the FI should post the completion amount to the customer\'s account and remove the hold. This is an almost instant process.</p>\r\n<p><br />This, unfortunately, isn\'t always the case.</p>\r\n<p><br /><strong>B)</strong> Some FIs will wait till our location performs a day close to capture the completion amount. If the FI uses this procedure, it can take up to 3-4 business days for the completion to post to the customer&rsquo;s account. During this time, they will only see the preauthorization hold on their account.<br />FIs will not release a preauthorization hold if there is a completion pending.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How to handle a preauthorization hold call</span><br />When a customer calls to report a hold on their account, first look up the transaction in Client Line to see what happened.</p>\r\n<p><br />If there is a completion,</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>let the customer know that once their bank posts the fuel sale to their account, the hold will release. This usually takes a maximum of 3 business days after the card swipe.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If there is a completion but the customer says they\'ve always swiped their card at the pump, and they\'ve never seen a hold before,</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The customer has been experiencing what happens in section <strong>A)</strong>. Their bank probably missed the notification from the pump hangup&nbsp;and will wait for the store settlement to complete the transaction.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br />If there is not a completion, the hold can stay on the customer&rsquo;s account anywhere from 7 &ndash; 30 days.&nbsp; Let the customer know that we (Valero) are not in control of posting or releasing the hold, but we might still be able to help.</p>\r\n<p><br />If the transaction was done as <strong>credit</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Let the customer know that their card company is waiting on a completion amount from us. Since there wasn&rsquo;t a completion issued, their card company has a maximum number of days they&rsquo;ll wait. We can push through a completion for a penny to give the bank something to settle on. Once settled, they&rsquo;ll remove the hold. This procedure can still take up to 3 business days to complete.<br />This is commonly referred to as a pennyfix.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Let the customer know that we can provide a faxed form requesting release of the hold and statement that we will not be settling on any amount of the authorization.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Have the customer\'s bank or card company contact WTS directly. Give the customer a ticket number to have the bank reference when they call</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If the transaction was done as <strong>debit</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Let the customer know that we can provide a faxed form requesting release of the hold and statement that we will not be settling on any amount of the authorization.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Have the customer\'s bank or card company contact WTS directly. Give the customer a ticket number to have the bank reference when they call</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In some cases the customers haven been told by their banks or card companies that valero is in complete control of the hold and we have to release it. This is not the case. Please have the customer have their card company or bank contact us directly.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Recently Visa has sent out a notice to merchants concerning pump holds. The notice states:</p>\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Visa&rsquo;s Petroleum and C-Store team has heard from many of our partners about the frustrating conversations that sometimes take place with your customers around who is responsible for holds placed on a customer&rsquo;s funds. In an effort to support your customer facing communication we have a section on our website that explains that you are not responsible for those holds. Below is the verbiage on Visa.com and directions to the web page.</p>\r\n<p><strong>What is a gas pump hold?</strong><br />When you pay at the pump, some card issuers place a &ldquo;hold&rdquo; on their cardholders&rsquo; funds in anticipation of the final transaction amount, to help ensure their cardholders&rsquo; accounts do not become overdrawn. Gas merchants do not place holds.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n<p>To locate the information, go to Visa.com.</p>\r\n<p>Click \"Ask Visa\" in the upper right corner of the screen.<br /><img src=\"upload/visa_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"407\" height=\"144\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click the entry [+] What is a gas pump hold?<br /><img src=\"upload/visa_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"485\" height=\"227\" /></p>', '2013-03-04 13:39:25', 'l7d23b', '2013-03-04 14:24:29', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Preauthrization holds', '', 50006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(181, 'Retail Site Conversion', '<p>69950 XXXXX All Texas Retail Sites</p>\r\n<p>69951 XXXXX All California Retail Sites</p>\r\n<p>69952 XXXXX All Other Retail Sites</p>\r\n<p>Store numbers, dealer Number and Merchant IDs remain the same.</p>\r\n<p>The data warehouse has not been converted yet so to look up the old Jobber Dealer number for a site look at the permanent note that systems put on every store during their conversion [shift-f5].&nbsp; You can still look up the RAMS Merchant Record with the dealer number &lsquo;9ddddd&rsquo; and the merchant number &lsquo;mmmmmm&rsquo; and the DS lookup &lsquo;ds0stno&rsquo; (&lsquo;DS&rsquo;+&rsquo;0&rsquo;+four digit store number.&nbsp; The old Jobber merchant records are in RAMs still but the cross Reference Page [shift F3] has been moved to the new record</p>', '2013-03-04 14:45:15', 'l7d23b', '2013-03-04 14:45:15', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'New jobber numbers for retail sites in RAMS', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
