(195, 'eProcurement / ePS infomration', '<p>Wholesale is doing a soft rollout of it new eProcurement web site for Dealers, Jobbers and Installers.&nbsp; (soft means the site is live and probably only the sites or individuals that were aware of it (pilot sites and users, etc.)will be using it) This site is accessible directly from our Wholesale/Dealer Portal.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If a customer calls with troubles accessing or using this functionality, after we are assured they have normal working access to our portal, we need to refer them to the ePS Support &nbsp;Group at (855) 690-3774 or&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:ePShelp@eprosvcs.com\">ePShelp@eprosvcs.com</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A full scale rollout will occur within two weeks.&nbsp; Note this website is only compatible with MS Explorer versions 8 and above.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>ePS or eProcurement (Valero eSource on the Branded Home Page) is a value added service being managed and supported by a third party whereby Valero&rsquo;s wholesale Dealers and Jobbers can access a website via our Portal to order Valero branded supplies for their stores from multiple vendors similar to amazon.com but leveraging the purchasing power of Valero.&nbsp; We do not support this website or any issues encountered with its use.&nbsp; We merely supply the 800 number to dealers and jobbers for support.&nbsp; Please code your tickets as &ldquo;unsupported&rdquo;.</p>', '2013-07-15 16:18:39', 'l7d23b', '2013-08-05 16:06:34', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'eProcurement / ePS infomration', '', 40007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:ePShelp@eprosvcs.com'),
(196, 'How to Dial Internationally', '<p>International calling:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Dial 9 to get an outside line<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>First Dial 011 (to get out internationally)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>+44 (for the UK)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Then the # listed.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Example: 9-011-44-2838364910 (this is a real # to Woods Centra #491625)</p>\r\n<p>If you are getting the recording &ldquo; the international number you have dialed is not in service in the country you are calling&rdquo;, check the phone number again and remove the first 0 if there is one.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Calling UK Extensions:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">7584 + 4 digit extension</p>', '2013-07-18 10:33:12', 'l7d23b', '2015-07-23 10:37:26', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to Dial Internationally', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(197, 'Response to Inquiries Relative to Other Valero Branded Programs', '<p>In response to inquiries regarding other Valero Branded Programs,&nbsp;please give the following response:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&ldquo;Valero will expand the Valero eSource Catalog going forward to include additional products.&nbsp; We appreciate feedback regarding your product interests; therefore, please send product comments to &lsquo;<a href=\"mailto:rene.munoz@valero.com\">rene.munoz@valero.com</a>&rsquo;.&rdquo;</p>', '2013-07-24 10:04:42', 'l7d23b', '2013-07-25 08:13:35', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Response to Inquiries Relative to Other Valero Branded Programs', '', 40013, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:rene.munoz@valero.com'),
(198, 'Gift Card Adjustment Processing Information', '<p>Clarifying the use of the Store Number Field in ValueLink Screens</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>02011819998 is for use when there is a payment from a customer for a Bulk Order, Order or Reload.</li>\r\n<li>02011819996 is for all other needs.&nbsp; Card Transfers, adjustments, deactivations, write-offs, etc.;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>When activating a card that a store failed to activate, the store received payment, not us here at the center, so use 02011819996,.&nbsp; If you are unable to complete a function in Valuelink using the correct Store Number (9996 or 9998), print the error screen and bring it to your supervisor with a description of what you were attempting to do.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>To All WTG Agents processing solutions that require MSR adjustments through RAMs:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Emailed&nbsp;MSR adjustment requests to Staci Martinez are no longer allowed.&nbsp; Instead, use the \"Accounting Adjustment Request\" under the \"Adjustments\" menu.</p>\r\n<p>When making adjustments to Gift Cards, (using the correct codes as clarified above), include a copy of the ValueLink screen print after submitting the adjustment in ValueLink, &nbsp;stapled or clipped to your HEAT ticket copy to Staci.</p>\r\n<p>If your HEAT ticket is a Consumer Type ticket, be sure to hand write the Jobber Dealer number of the store that needs to be adjusted clearly on the face of your ticket copy for Staci.</p>\r\n<p>Remember, whenever you make a change to a proprietary customer&rsquo;s account or transactions (adj, refund, charge, etc.) always place a note on the account in RAMs describing what you did and why.</p>', '2013-08-01 10:23:57', 'l7d23b', '2013-10-22 12:08:40', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Gift Card Adjustment Processing Information', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(199, 'Duplicate Transactions', '<p>Duplicate charges to cards can occur for a few different reasons:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Communications and Network&nbsp;Issues</li>\r\n<li>POS Issues</li>\r\n<li>Clerk / Customer Error</li>\r\n<li>Cardholder Network Issue</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Duplicate from communications and network&nbsp;issues</h3>\r\n<p>If a site is having issues with their network connectivity, the station\'s point of sale system may attempt to re-process a transaction that seemed unsuccessful, but actually was.</p>\r\n<p>In this situation, you\'ll see two charges for the same amount on the same card within minutes of each other.</p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #dbdbdb;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"121\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Card No.</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"104\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Date/Tim</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"68\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Card Type</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"73\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Authorizer</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"112\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Transaction Type</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"74\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Amount($)</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Apprvd/ Dclnd</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"125\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Aprvd/ Dclnd Code</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">415977******8470</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">6/26/2015 6:49</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">DEBIT</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">INTERLNK</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">PUR</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">102.72</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">A</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">875160</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">415977******8470</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">6/26/2015 6:49</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">DEBIT</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">INTERLNK</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">PUR</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">102.72</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">A</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">473826</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A similar&nbsp;scenario happens when the network takes too long to acknowledge a sale.&nbsp;The point of sale system will issue a TOR (Timed Out Reversal) to cancel that sale and send up another sale with the same information.</p>\r\n<p>Customers can mistake these for a duplicate as the reversal has not posted to their account yet.</p>\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #dbdbdb;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"121\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Card No.</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"89\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Date/Tim</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"68\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Card Type</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"74\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Authorizer</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"112\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Transaction Type</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"74\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Amount($)</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Apprvd/ Dclnd</span></td>\r\n<td width=\"125\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Aprvd/ Dclnd Code</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">511308******7214</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">7/7/2015 9:30</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">MASTERC</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">MASTERCD</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">PUR</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">3.91</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">A</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">93015</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">511308******7214</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">7/7/2015 9:30</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">MASTERC</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">BUYPASS</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">TOR</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">3.91</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">A</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">93015</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">511308******7214</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">7/7/2015 9:30</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">MASTERC</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">MASTERCD</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">PUR</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">3.91</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">A</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">93049</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>POS Issues</h3>\r\n<p>Some duplications are caused by issues stemming for the point of sale software.</p>\r\n<p>If the POS becomes unresponsive while a sale is being processed, the clerk may have the customer re-run their card. This can sometimes result in a duplication.</p>\r\n<p>POS software issues can cause looping transactions. This is when a single sale is pushed to the network&nbsp;multiple times.&nbsp;The network will usually not process additional sales that are part of a loop.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Cardholder Network Issue</h3>\r\n<p>Sales can also be duplicated on the cardholder\'s credit network.</p>\r\n<p>A customer may call to report a double charge to their account but we only find the sale was sent once and paid only once to our station. If this is the case, the customer needs to address the situation with their bank.&nbsp;Advise the customer to contact their bank and report that the merchant has confirmed the sale was only processed one time from their system. If the bank needs any further information or needs to verify information, let the customer know we\'ll be happy to work with their bank to expedite the process.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Handling Duplicates</h3>\r\n<p>When a station or a customer call in regarding a duplicate sale:</p>\r\n<p>Obtain the store information, date of transaction, and sale amount or the last 4 of the card number used.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Locate the transaction in Client Line.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Check if there were any corrections issued already (TORs or any reversals).<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Locate the transaction in Data Warehouse (this is to confirm the sale was actually paid to the station twice).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the sale was processed once and charged twice, refer to the \"<strong>Cardholder Network Issue</strong>\" above.</li>\r\n<li>If the sale was&nbsp;made at a pump, processed twice, and paid twice, issue a return for the duplicate amount.</li>\r\n<li>If the sale was an inside purchase:<br /><br /></li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Contact the station management and describe the situation.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Station management will need to research the transaction and either approve or the deny the return to the customer.<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the request was denied, advise the customer to dispute the sale though their card issuer.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the request was approved, submit an adjustment request for the duplicate amount.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-08-06 15:41:29', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-02 13:11:15', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how to identify and process duplicate charges', '', 50006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(200, 'Arco Retalix Sites', '<p>For a backoffice only issue</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open a ticket for the Retail Helpdesk to handle once they\'re in.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For Register/Register Back Office/Credit Issues</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Valero will conference in the Arco Elite Helpdesk.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Paypoint</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contacted by Arco Elite Helpdesk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Hughes Satellite</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dispatched by Arco Elite Helpdesk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>POS Hardware issues</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If ARCO determines the issue is hardware related, they will ask the Valero Helpdesk to contact our contracted service provider for hardware, which is CETEC. <strong>CETEC will only be contacted when directed by the Arco Helpdesk.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Preauthorization Holds</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To assist customers with a preauth hold on their account, contact the Arco Elite helpdesk. You will speak with a Tier 1 technician first and will need to give the SVB id for the station. Advise the Tier 1 that you need the authorization number for the transaction. They will forward you to a Tier 2. Ask to have the transaction detail emailed to you.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; width: 60%; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Vendor</td>\r\n<td>Contact Number</td>\r\n<td>Indentification</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ARCO Elite Helpdesk</td>\r\n<td>1-800-ARCOFIX (272-6349) Press 3 then 1</td>\r\n<td>SVB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Paypoint</td>\r\n<td>Contacted by ARCO Elite Helpdesk</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Hughes Satellite</td>\r\n<td>Contacted by ARCO Elite Helpdesk</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>CETEC</td>\r\n<td>1-310-323-6730 option 4</td>\r\n<td>SAP</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>FMI</td>\r\n<td>1-888-505-2170</td>\r\n<td>Store Number</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"margin-left: auto; width: 60%; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Store (FMI)</td>\r\n<td>Arco (SVB)</td>\r\n<td>CETEC (SAP)</td>\r\n<td>Jobber ID</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3427</td>\r\n<td>9221839</td>\r\n<td>54365</td>\r\n<td>J7003</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3612</td>\r\n<td>9222159</td>\r\n<td>54366</td>\r\n<td>J7005</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3615</td>\r\n<td>9222472</td>\r\n<td>54368</td>\r\n<td>J7007</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3616</td>\r\n<td>9222688</td>\r\n<td>54369</td>\r\n<td>J7008</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3618</td>\r\n<td>9222894</td>\r\n<td>54370</td>\r\n<td>J7010</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>3636</td>\r\n<td>2999966</td>\r\n<td>54371</td>\r\n<td>J7006</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2013-08-06 16:16:01', 'l7d23b', '2013-08-06 16:52:16', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Support Information for Arco Retalix sites', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '');
