(202, 'HEATboard Information', '<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Creating a HEATboard</span></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Begin and complete (but don\'t close) the lead ticket.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click Autotask<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Mouseover HEAT Board<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click AMA - Create new HB<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter a description for the HEATboard, Click OK.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Associating a call to a Heat Board</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>There are two ways to associate/link your ticket to an existing HEATboard.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/heatboard-window.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"314\" /></p>\r\n<p>First:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Locate the HEATboard sidebar&nbsp;window in Heat.&nbsp; <br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If you can not find the HEATboard window, click on View &gt; InfoCenter &gt; Check \"Show HEATboard\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If&nbsp;the Global menu is selected, click on \"Global\" and select \"HEATBoard Wholesale\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Right click on the relevant HEATboard issue&nbsp;you\'re&nbsp;needing to associate to, select \"Link current call\". <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click AutoTask, mouseover HEAT Board, select AMA&nbsp;- Copy Call from HB<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted, enter&nbsp;the Jobber/Dealer number<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Heat will auto-populate the new ticket<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click Save<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the blue thumbtack beside the current HEATBoard<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Check box that prompts: Allow Call to be Autoclosed<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click OK<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click Save again</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To close a HEATBoard</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Close Lead call<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Right click the current HEATBoard in the HEATBoard window<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Close Linked Calls</li>\r\n</ol>', '2013-08-08 12:48:34', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-21 16:03:15', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'HEATboard creation, call association, and closure information', '', 40003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(203, 'Inside Store Prepay Methods and Practices', '<p>Ruby/Sapphire and Topaz Sapphire process credit prepays multiple ways:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Credit Prepays sent to the host as a sale. No AutoRefund. &nbsp;Causes an issue where the customer has to come inside if the entire prepay amount is not dispensed.&nbsp; Also the refund due the customer can be tendered using any MOP which merchants do not like. Customer has to come into the store to get a detailed receipt.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Credit Prepays send to the host as a sale but automatically refunded to the card if under-run.&nbsp; Customer has to come into the store to get the receipt for an under-run.&nbsp; Customer has to come into the store to get a receipt for the fuel details.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Fast Credit.&nbsp; Prepay sent to the host as an auth. &nbsp;Cannot add merchandise and a receipt is printed at the DCR.&nbsp; The completion is sent to the host after the customer dispenses fuel.&nbsp; You cannot add merchandise to the ticket in this case.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Fast Credit with merchandise. Prepay is sent to the host as an auth.&nbsp; A completion is sent to the host after the cashier completes the transaction using pump# fuel for the &ldquo;due&rdquo; transaction.&nbsp; The customer must come back into the store for a detailed receipt.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br />Various methods of performing prepays were added to Ruby and Sapphire over the years.&nbsp; They all had issues that merchants and major oils did not like.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Because of this Verifone implemented credit prepays in the Commander&nbsp;as authorizations where you can add merchandise and a detailed receipt is printed at the DCR with the merchandise.&nbsp; A completion is sent to the host after the customer fuels.&nbsp; This does not require the cashier to complete the transaction after the customer completes dispensing fuel.</p>', '2013-08-16 16:55:54', 'l7d23b', '2013-08-16 16:55:54', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how Sapphire and Commander systems handle prepays.', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(204, 'GemPay Pilot Site Info', '<p>All the Gempay pilot sites in rams now have a &ldquo;Gempay&rdquo; added to their device screen. There is also a note showing&nbsp;if&nbsp;the sites are the pilot sites.</p>\r\n<p>These sites will show up with multiple terminals in the device screen (look up the site #, then type &ldquo;J&rdquo;, enter).</p>\r\n<p>If we get calls on any site that has a Gempay, just ignore the other terminals listed.</p>', '2013-08-21 16:32:27', 'l7d23b', '2014-03-12 08:22:28', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on GemPAY device IDs', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(205, 'FastFuels Invoicing Information', '<p>European Finished &amp; Specialty Products Accounting handles FastFuels billing for our UK sites. Sean von Muldau is the supervisor of the department and can be reached at <a href=\"mailto:Sean.vonMuldau@valero.com\">Sean.vonMuldau@valero.com</a>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-09-04 09:23:37', 'l7d23b', '2013-09-23 14:16:01', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'FastFuels Invoicing Information', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:Sean.vonMuldau@valero.com'),
(206, 'ADSL Issues Troubleshooter', '<p>Contacts:</p>\r\n<p>TNS -&nbsp;0845 111 2037 <a href=\"mailto:eubroadband@tnsi.com\">eubroadband@tnsi.com</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img class=\"null\" style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/ADSL%20Communications%20Issues.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"362\" /></p>', '2013-09-19 09:31:52', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-16 05:15:10', 'lc9782', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'ADSL Issues Troubleshooter', '', 80007, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:eubroadband@tnsi.com'),
(209, 'Support information for new Commerical Card Range', '<p>With the introduction of a new commercial bin range, we&rsquo;ll be assisting the fleet group by tracking down any issues that may arise at our stores.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you need to create a manual for a new commercial card, use the<strong> last 8 digits</strong> of the number that appears in Client Line.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><br />Fleet reps will be contacting us to verify we can see the transactions on card numbers beginning 7000381.<br /><br />If you receive a call from a Fleet rep, lookup the station in Client Line and verify we can see the transactions at the network.<br /><br />If you are able to see transactions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Let the rep know and they will handle the issue going forward.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you are unable to see the transactions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Create a ticket in Heat and give the ticket number to the Fleet rep.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>At this point we will need to work with the station to verify they are setup correctly.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>If the station has a Gilbarco Passport:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Contact the site and advise that we have determined there is a Valero card that is not working correctly at their location, and there is a quick change that needs to be made at the Passport to correct the issue.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On the passport, go to the Tools menu.</li>\r\n<li>Select Manager Workstation.</li>\r\n<li>Select Network Menu.</li>\r\n<li>Select Concord.</li>\r\n<li>Select Network Card Configuration.</li>\r\n<li>This will bring you to the card table. Locate Proprietary&nbsp;Fleet and select it.</li>\r\n<li>Check the box that reads Card Enabled.</li>\r\n<li>Select Save.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>This will enable the Proprietary Fleet card for use on the Passport.</p>\r\n<p>At this time you will need to Nerybel Garcia (<a href=\"mailto:Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com\">Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com</a>) and let her know the issue is resolved at the station level.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>If the station has a Ruby Sapphire:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Contact the site and advise that we have determined there is a Valero card that is not working correctly at their location, and we will need to have them check the card programming on their Ruby.</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 90%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"color: #993300;\">Important Notice&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"color: #993300;\">Only sites running the valero card table will be able to accept this new card type. To check which card table is loaded follow the instructions below.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On the ruby, exit from sales.</li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to System setup, hit Enter.</li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to Network Configuration, hit Enter.</li>\r\n<li>Press 0 (zero).</li>\r\n<li>Press Enter.</li>\r\n<li>Press Clear.</li>\r\n<li>Give the station <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=124\" target=\"_blank\">the corresponding password for backdoor access</a>, press Enter.</li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to Configuration, press Enter.</li>\r\n<li>Right arrow to Credit Card Configuration, press Enter.</li>\r\n<li>If the Valero card table is loaded, there will be two entries for card type <strong>DM</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"width: 90%; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 48.63px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 48.63px;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">If the station only has one entry for card type DM, they are using the generic card table and will have to have&nbsp;a technician load the Valero card table.<br /></span></strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 40px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 40px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">If you receive resistance from the station on calling out their technician, let them know reloading the card deck takes about 10 minutes and was part of their tech\'s original duty to&nbsp;setup their station correctly when the station was initially installed or upgraded.</span></strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>If the station <em>does</em> have 2 <strong>DM</strong> entries:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Right arrow to <strong>DF</strong> and press Enter 4 times.</li>\r\n<li>Ruby should read: <strong>DF</strong> enabled (Y/N)</li>\r\n<li>Make sure Y is selected, press Enter.</li>\r\n<li>Once this is complete, exit out and have site return to sales.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>This will enable the new Commerical Fleet&nbsp;IIN card for use on the Ruby/Sapphire.</p>\r\n<p>At this time you will need to Nerybel Garcia (<a href=\"mailto:Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com\">Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com</a>) and let her know the issue is resolved at the station level.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>If the station has a Topaz Sapphire:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Refer the site to their technician to have the card table checked to make sure they have both DM entries enabled, or have the card table reloaded to the correct spec.</p>\r\n<p>Keep record and check up with the site to make sure the change has been completed.</p>\r\n<p>Once you receive word the change has been made, email Nerybel Garcia (<a href=\"mailto:Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com\">Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com</a>) and let her know the issue is resolved at the station level.</p>', '2013-09-26 14:45:21', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-13 15:14:38', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on new card range and support issues', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:Nerybel.Garcia@valero.comindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=124mailto:Nerybel.Garcia@valero.commailto:Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com'),
(210, 'Script for Commercial Cards - IIN', '<p>The following script is for commerical customers that are concerned about losing their cash/credit discount at the pump.</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 90%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">We have recently identified a number of commercial accounts that have incorrectly been issued cards on our consumer credit card platform.&nbsp; In order to correctly provide the services your commercial account requires we have reissued new cards to your company that correctly identify your account as a commercial/business account.&nbsp; </span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">If you are interested in fuel discounts for purchases made at Valero branded locations I would encourage you to look at our Valero Fleet card which provides discounts based on the number of gallons purchased monthly. I can provide you additional information on our Valero Fleet Card if you would like to look into this option.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif; font-size: 12pt;\">(If they continue to question the cash/credit pricing)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family: tahoma,arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">The ability for a Valero branded location to provide unique pricing at the pump for certain payment cards is based on the type of card that is used.&nbsp; Your cards are now properly identified as commercial credit cards rather than consumer credit cards.</span></strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-09-27 12:32:42', 'l7d23b', '2013-09-27 12:34:58', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Script for commercial customers concerning cash discounting', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
