(224, 'UK-IP Conflict with Back Office PC and the Digi Router ', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>UK-IP Conflict with Back Office PC and the Digi Router Instructions</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>First Step- </strong>Determine the Digi Router IP Default Gateway</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pre-May 2015: 192.168.0.254</li>\r\n<li>Post-May 2015: 192.168.0.253</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>*</strong>The IP is determined by the date the site became a Valero site.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Second Step-</strong> Determine the Back Office PC Default Gateway</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Have site go to Back Office PC and click on Start Button</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/ip-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"491\" height=\"518\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>In the search programs and files field, type CMD and hit enter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/ip-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"491\" height=\"518\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The &ldquo;black&rdquo; DOS window should open</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/ip-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"677\" height=\"342\" /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Next type in IPCONFIG and hit enter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/ip-4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"677\" height=\"342\" /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This will bring up the settings- have site search for &ldquo;Ethernet adapter Local Area Connection&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Then look for &ldquo;Default Gateway&rdquo; (this is the IP you need)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/ip-5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"677\" height=\"342\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>If the Back Office IP is the same as the Digi Router IP, the site will need to get the Back Office IP address changed as this is causing a conflict which is affecting the site&rsquo;s ability to process transactions.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-10-18 13:25:35', 'l7d23b', '2017-02-17 10:12:03', 'lqnwmy', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions ', '', 80007, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(225, 'Terminals Hints and Tips', '<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">HydraPOS</span> </span></p>\r\n<p>Integrated tills (Where the EPOS and EFT are combined) are manufactured by HTEC but are not necessarily <em>maintained</em> by HTEC &ndash; Examples of other suppliers are James Hall, Cappers, etc. Always check by asking HTEC first and if they do not support it ask the retailer who supports their integrated till.</p>', '2013-10-18 13:31:26', 'l7d23b', '2013-11-11 08:11:53', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Extra / Misc info on UK processing terminals.', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '');
