(226, 'Refresh Support Model', '<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Polling</span></span></p>\r\n<p>Unlike the legacy model, in&nbsp;this model the terminal does not wait for another system to fetch the transactions. It sends out an acknowledgement and a record with every transaction to FIS, much like our US model. <br /><br />Unlike the US model, the retailer has to run the end of day process which triggers the batch process to transmit the day&rsquo;s transactions to FIS. <br />FIS then build a settlement file to send to the acquirers. FIS is passive and won&rsquo;t request the files but will wait for the files to arrive. If the end of day process doesn&rsquo;t take place prior to the cut-off the day&rsquo;s transactions will not be sent to the acquirers and as a result the retailer&rsquo;s settlement payment will be delayed.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>FIS generates files on a daily basis that are&nbsp;stored in the group mailbox under &ldquo;Completed&rdquo; folder:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #000000; text-decoration: underline;\">End of Day File </span></span><br /><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Where FIS have waited but not received any information. 90% of the time it will be where the second terminal in a 1-till site has been used to take transactions rather than the main terminal. When the End of day is triggered on the till it then triggers it on the terminal. If the terminal is standalone but FIS have received records of transactions that they have authorised but the end of day process hasn&rsquo;t been carried out. In this situation the end of day process has to be done manually. Rcetailers shouldn&rsquo;t use this spare terminal unless there is a problem with the main one but there may be instances where they will.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Suspense File</span><br />Where a file is received but FIS can see duplicate transactions. As they can&rsquo;t reconcile them FIS won&rsquo;t forward them to the bank and will hold in suspense.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Communications</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">ADSL with GPRS Backup</span><br />Transactions will be transmitted&nbsp;with an ADSL modem/router combo. The device uses GPRS(cellular) backup if the ADSL connection fails.&nbsp;If the site is in an area with a weak signal an aerial can be installed to boost the signal. UKRT have spare aerials in stock.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">*TNS provides the broadband installation and support from BT.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; text-decoration: underline;\">Tills</span></p>\r\n<p>Various -&nbsp;Not supported by VCS</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Terminals</span></span></p>\r\n<p>HTEC Gempay &ndash; Various modes:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Linked To the terminal -&nbsp;EFT and EPOS functionality are separate</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Integrated -&nbsp;Incorporate EPOS and EFT functionality, e.g. HypdraPOS, Iridium</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Standalone - For back-up purposes on 1-till sites. If used, the retailer has to key the transaction in twice, first on the till and then on the terminal, and has to carry out an end of day process.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; text-decoration: underline;\">Online Authorization</span></p>\r\n<p>Authorizer: FIS&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Every night FIS receives settlement files from each site and matches the transactions to the authorisation code they&rsquo;ve given in order to build the Valero settlement file for each acquirer. FIS will then send the relevant transactions to each acquirer who then use this information to pay retailers for reconciled transactions. If acquirers can&rsquo;t match the authorisation code with the information they&rsquo;ve received they won&rsquo;t settle the transaction.</p>\r\n<p>Transaction File This is currently being worked on will be produced by FIS for retailers and will summarise transactions on a weekly basis.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Transaction File</span></span></p>\r\n<p>This is currently being worked on will be produced by FIS for retailers and will summarise transactions on a weekly basis.</p>', '2013-10-18 09:42:28', 'l7d23b', '2013-10-22 11:00:05', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Overview and Support on UK Retail Refresh sites', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', '', ''),
