(228, 'Gempay 3  Pilot Information', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Gempay 3 will replace the Gempay 1 Terminals and PIN pads on Texaco branded service stations.</p>\r\n<p>A formal pilot will run between Wednesday 21<sup>st</sup> June and Wednesday 5<sup>th</sup> July at the following sites:</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 420.5px; height: 287px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\"><strong>Site ID</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\"><strong>Site Name</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\"><strong>Area Manager</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">253299</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Lancashire Hill Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Paul Atherton</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">251851</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Mabco Reddish Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Paul Atherton</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">491803</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Mabco Caroline</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Paul Atherton</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">886511</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Mere Motors</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Peter King</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">887087</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Manor Queens Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Paul Andrew</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">886447</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Threeways Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Doreen Marshall</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">886804</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Central Convenience Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Elaine Davies</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">886239</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Jubits Lane Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Paul Andrew</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">490667</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Cotton Street Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Doreen Marshall</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 69px;\">251002</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 213px;\">Barking Service Station</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 121.5px;\">Doreen Marshall</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The sites have been advised of the details of the pilot. An HTEC engineer will attend each pilot site on either Monday 19<sup>th</sup> June or Tuesday 20<sup>th</sup> June 2017 to install Gempay 3 equipment and familiarize the site with its functionality.</p>\r\n<p>The pilot process is simple and non-intrusive and as an extra precaution, existing Gempay 1 equipment will be retained on sites during the pilot.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Following a successful pilot, we are scheduled to deploy Gempay 3 to the rest of the network for sites currently on Gempay 1 in early July 2017. We are then anticipating that we will complete the rollout in early 2018.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Gempay 3 Equipment</strong>:</p>\r\n<p>Gempay 3 Terminal:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/gempay-3-terminal.png\" alt=\"Gempay 3 Terminal\" width=\"215\" height=\"209\" /></p>\r\n<p>Gempay 3 Pin Pad:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/gempay-3-pin-pad.png\" alt=\"Gempay 3 Pin Pad\" width=\"200\" height=\"181\" /></p>\r\n<p>Below are some of the key benefits of the new Gempay 3:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Meets regulatory requirements</li>\r\n<li>Contactless is enabled as standard</li>\r\n<li>Enhanced security features</li>\r\n<li>Full colour display</li>\r\n<li>Virtual keyboard</li>\r\n<li>Sturdy and reliable platform</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-10-18 13:46:59', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-05 10:20:58', 'lqnwmy', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Gempay 3 Pilot Information', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(230, 'Card Issues Troubleshooter', '<p>For card issue contacts, <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=164\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a>.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/card%20issues.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"797\" height=\"323\" /></p>', '2013-10-23 11:30:38', 'l7d23b', '2013-10-23 14:24:50', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Card Issues Troubleshooter', '', 80007, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=164'),
(231, 'Card Processing Hints and Tips', '<ul>\r\n<li>ALL Valero sites should take EuroShell and BP Routex cards &ndash; Tend to have issues with Micros (Iridium) sites.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Bin range for Euroshell cards that are accepted at sites are 700/2056 and 700/2057 example card # <strong>7002057</strong>707050718932.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If a card comes up as unknown refer to the Card PAN Range document to confirm whether the site should be accepting this card.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If a card is not accepted &ndash; Check that site should be accepting the card, check the MID, for BMS check the MID/TID combination.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>If a site has a UK Fuels MID that starts with &ldquo;12&rdquo; that means that the site doesn&rsquo;t accept bunkering cards, i.e. Texaco only.&nbsp; Otherwise, the site can take UK Fuels bunkering cards.<br /><br /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>If the site is an AD (Authorized distributor), and they want to accept Fast Fuels Cards. Karen Goane has to approve that before any action can be taken.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the site is a normal Retailer, we can proceed with contacting the terminal provider and UK fuels to see what needs to be done.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Some BP Routex cards may not be accepted at stations. These are most likely bunkering cards. The way to identify a BP bunkering card is:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The card will have a lower case black \"b\" on the face or,</li>\r\n<li>The 13th digit of the card will be a \"9\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '2013-10-23 14:29:04', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-21 09:11:55', 'lc9782', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Card Processing Hints and Tips', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
