(235, 'Refunding a WEX Card on the Accounting Room VX520', '<p>In the room next to the accounting department (where the accounting printer is located), there is a VX520 terminal that WTS uses in the event a refund is needed on a Wright Express (WEX) transaction.&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p>To process a refund on a Wright Express card, you will need the following information:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><u>Card #</u></span></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> <u>Expiration Date</u></span></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> <u>Driver #</u></span></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><u>Vehicle #</u></span></strong></li>\r\n<li style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><u><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Odometer #</span><br /><br /></u></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><u>Steps to process a WEX refund on the VX520</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On the VX520, select &ldquo;<strong><u>Refund/Return</u></strong>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;<strong><u>Credit</u></strong>&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter in the full <strong><u>WEX card #</u></strong>. Press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Enter</span>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong><u>expiration date</u></strong> (MM/YY). Press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">DONE</span>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the <strong><u>Vehicle #</u> (must be a 5 digit #, ex. <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">01234</span>).</strong><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>The VX520&nbsp;will ask for the &ldquo;<strong><u>Sequence #</u></strong>&rdquo;. <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Leave this field blank</span> and press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">DONE</span>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The pin pad attached will prompt you to enter the following information. Enter all of this information and press the green \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Enter</span>\" button on the pinpad on each one once entered:<br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong><u>Driver #</u></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong><u>Odometer #<br /><br /></u></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong><u>product code # 400</u></strong>. Press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">DONE</span>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong><u>dollar amount of refund</u></strong>, ex. &ldquo;80.00&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Leave the <strong><u>Refund Product #</u></strong> blank. Press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Done</span>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>You will be prompted&nbsp;to enter a tax amount, <strong><u>leave this blank</u></strong> and press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">DONE</span>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The VX520 will then give you a final screen showing &ldquo;<strong><u>REFUND</u></strong>&rdquo; at the top of the screen and the dollar amount. Press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">DONE</span>&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once the&nbsp;VX520 has completed the refund, it will say &ldquo;<strong><u>Please tear off receipt and give to customer</u></strong>&rdquo;. Tear off this receipt and press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">DONE</span>&rdquo;.&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>The&nbsp;VX520 will then print out another receipt that is typically for the store. <strong><u>Tear this receipt off</u></strong> and press &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">DONE</span>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><u>Final Steps</u></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Print a copy of your HEAT ticket and staple the receipts to the ticket and place it in your files.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Submit an accounting adjustment request in Reflex to charge site for refund.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2013-10-23 14:48:20', 'l7d23b', '2017-08-18 14:55:17', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to submit a refund on a WEX card on the VX520 in the Accounting Room', '', 10012, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
