(239, 'GemPay General Purpose/Select button End of Day', '<p>If a&nbsp;UK site is having issues locating the &ldquo;general purpose/select&rdquo; button and needs help on where to perform their day close:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/gempayselectbtn.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"151\" height=\"194\" /></p>\r\n<p>After you have them press the &ldquo;general purpose/select&rdquo; button, it will come up with a menu:</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/gempayMainMenu.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"313\" height=\"216\" /></p>\r\n<p>This should be the first selection on the menu, however, if you need to, have them press the down arrow (the button on the right of the &ldquo;general purpose/select&rdquo; button until &ldquo;transactions&rdquo; is highlighted.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It will then give you a list of options to choose from:</p>\r\n<p>Transactions</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Manual (protected by Supervisor password)</li>\r\n<li>Pre Auth</li>\r\n<li>Refund (protected by Supervisor password)</li>\r\n<li>Duplicate</li>\r\n<li>Last Transaction</li>\r\n<li>Earlier Transaction</li>\r\n<li>End of Shift</li>\r\n<li>End of Day</li>\r\n<li>End of Shift</li>\r\n<li>End of Day</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Press the down arrow key until the &ldquo;end of day&rdquo; is highlighted and then press the &ldquo;general purpose/select&rdquo; key.&nbsp;</p>', '2013-11-11 08:28:18', 'l7d23b', '2013-11-11 08:40:23', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how to perform an End of Day close on a GemPay', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(240, 'NACS Product Codes', '<p><a href=\"upload/docs/PaymentSystemProductCodes_3 090415.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for PDF.</a></p>', '2013-11-11 08:48:57', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-02 13:56:49', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Updated 2/23/17', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(241, 'Completing a configuration change on Gempay terminals', '<p>Once changes have been made by HTEC for a site&rsquo;s configuration, the Gempay terminal needs to connect to TMS to download these changes.&nbsp; <br /><br />HTEC normally does this but we can complete the process as well.</p>\r\n<p>Ask the site contact to carry out the following tasks on each Gempay terminal:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the OK (Middle) button on the terminal<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to Maintenance and press OK<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to Download and press OK<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to Connect and press OK<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The display should show five zeroes &ldquo;00000&rdquo;, press OK</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The terminal should show a message indicating that it connecting to TMS.&nbsp; Once the download is complete a successful message should appear along the lines of &ldquo;Installation OK &ndash; Scenario Installed&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #993366;\">Note: The terminal may need to be rebooted after the dial-in for the settings to apply.</span></strong></p>', '2013-11-15 08:27:32', 'l7d23b', '2014-08-18 09:53:05', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions on how to finalize a configuration change on Gempay terminals', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(242, 'Manager Password on Gempay', '<p>The password for keying manuals is normally the last 6 digits of the sites\' phone number.&nbsp; If that does not work the default password is 689200</p>', '2013-11-21 11:14:14', 'l7d23b', '2014-04-16 06:50:11', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Manager Passwords for Gempays', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(243, 'HTEC Metro B2B Portal', '<p>Metro B2B can be accessed at <a href=\"https://serviceportal.htec.co.uk/Dashboard\">https://serviceportal.htec.co.uk/Dashboard</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once logged in, you will see the following screen.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/metro-1.1.png\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To open a ticket with HTEC, click the green telephone button in the upper right corner.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The following screen will be displayed.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/metro-1.2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In the \"Site\" dropdown, type in the site ID number.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the \"Reference\" field, enter your HEAT ticket number.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the issue the site is having&nbsp;in the \"Details\" field.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the&nbsp;\"CC\" field, enter&nbsp;the email address: <a href=\"mailto:vcssupport@valero.com\">vcssupport@valero.com</a>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once the information has been filled out, click \"Submit\" to submit the request.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To search for sites, click the Sites link on the left side of the screen:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/metro-1.13.png\" width=\"236\" height=\"240\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The following screen will be displayed:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/metro-1.11.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Key in the Site ID next to the search radio button.</p>\r\n<p>Click the Radio Button and the following screen will appear with the site information:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/metro-1.4.png\" width=\"716\" height=\"636\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click on the \"Blue\" Highlighted,&nbsp;Site ID number to pull up the Site information.</p>\r\n<p>The initial page shows all active tickets currently open in Metro at the bottom:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/metro-1.5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>By clicking on the History tab at the bottom, you can view all closed tickets:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/metro-1.8.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To access site detail, click on the details tab.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/metro-1.6.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /><br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>To access any Allocation to the site, click on the Allocations tab.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/metro-1.9.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /></p>\r\n<p>To access the inventory list or TIDs at the site, click on the Inventory tab.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/metro-1.10.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"716\" height=\"637\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-12-03 09:27:15', 'l7d23b', '2017-02-10 09:37:26', 'lqnwmy', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Metro', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'https://serviceportal.htec.co.uk/Dashboardmailto:vcssupport@valero.com'),
(244, 'WREN Usage Directions and Information', '<p>Wren can be accessed at <a href=\"https://services.transaxpay.com/wren/login\">https://services.transaxpay.com/wren/login</a></p>\r\n<p>After logging in, you will be presented with the following screen.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/wrenSelect.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"821\" height=\"369\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Select \"Run\" under the \"Transactions by site.\"</p>\r\n<p>You will be presented by the following screen.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/wrensearch1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"721\" height=\"425\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Enter the \"Site ID\" and select the result below.</p>\r\n<p>Set the beginning and ending dates.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/wrensearch2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"721\" height=\"425\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The results page will look like this:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/wrenresult.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"826\" height=\"699\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>By selecting \"Download\" you can load the results into Excel.</p>', '2013-12-03 09:50:55', 'l7d23b', '2013-12-09 08:11:01', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'WREN - The FIS Merchant Payment Web Reporting Engine', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'https://services.transaxpay.com/wren/login'),
(245, 'GemPay Mini Keyboard Replacement Guidelines', '<p>If a UK Site requests the replacement of the Mini Keyboard, please follow the guidelines below:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Advise the site they will be required to return the damaged Mini keyboard within 1 week of the receipt of the replacement Mini keyboard or the site will incur and automatic fee of &pound;20.</li>\r\n<li>Email the site a copy&nbsp;of the provided letter <a title=\"Mini Keyboard Return Request\" href=\"upload/vcs-damaged-keyboard-comms.pdf\">Mini Keyboard Return Request</a></li>\r\n<li>Then note your heat ticket that you have emailed the letter to the site</li>\r\n</ul>', '2013-12-04 08:10:08', 'l7d23b', '2017-10-04 03:43:59', 'lqnwmy', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'GemPay Mini Keyboard Replacement Guidelines', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(246, 'Heat CST-Retail/Wholesale Separation', '<p>As part of the CST spinoff, we will no longer be sharing the same Heat database with CST and Retail Operations.</p>\r\n<p>After the transfer, we will not be able to see any new tickets created by CST or Retail Operations, nor will they be able to see ours.</p>\r\n<p>Due to the separation, a few processes will change:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Since CST will be unable to see our tickets, Heat will automatically send an email to the CST Helpdesk&nbsp;at the end of the retail overnight auto task. This means that the entire problem needs to be given in the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">problem statement</span> when prompted by the auto task.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>We will now close <strong>all</strong> retail overnight tickets on our side with either the appropriate resolution or logged ticket to CST via automated Heat email.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Fuel spill procedures will not change, but the retail mailbox email address&nbsp;has been added automatically&nbsp;to fuel spills, and our ticket number needs to be identified in the subject line following the store number: VLO ticket XXXXXXX.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2013-12-04 09:33:58', 'l7d23b', '2013-12-04 09:48:45', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on changes to Heat due to CST-Retail/Wholesale Separation', '', 40003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
