(248, 'Warehouse Login Config', '<p>Screen shot of login parameters for connecting to Lucy through SQL Server Management Studio:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/SQL%20Login%20Parameters.png\" alt=\"SQL Login Parameters\" width=\"426\" height=\"321\" /></p>', '2014-01-27 12:53:07', 'lkrfbb', '2014-01-27 12:53:07', 'lkrfbb', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Graphic showing login parameters for SQL Server Management Studio', '', 100001, 'IS User', 'N', ''),
(251, 'Heat Data Loss', '<p>The CST data purge will include the following fields in HEAT:</p>\r\n<p>Please note the data from these fields will be <strong>deleted</strong> and no longer searchable.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Brand</li>\r\n<li>Circuit ID</li>\r\n<li>Maintenance Office</li>\r\n<li>Cost Center</li>\r\n<li>Pump Count</li>\r\n<li>Pump Type</li>\r\n<li>Software Version</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Store Hours</span></li>\r\n<li>Grocery Delivery Info</li>\r\n<li>Store Features</li>\r\n<li>Store Manager</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Area Manager</span></li>\r\n<li>Zone Manager</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Employee Contacts</span></li>\r\n<li>Site Equipment Configuration (Non-POS)</li>\r\n<li>Store Status and Dates (built, opened, closed, remodeled, acquired)</li>\r\n<li>Region</li>\r\n<li>County</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\">Cross Street</span></li>\r\n<li>Fuel Carrier Name</li>\r\n<li>Company Code</li>\r\n<li>Safe Type</li>\r\n</ol>', '2014-01-29 15:09:32', 'l7d23b', '2014-01-29 15:16:17', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on CST Heat fields', '', 40003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(252, 'Acumera Merchant Gateway Troubleshooting', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">The purpose of this document is to equip Valero support personnel with a foundational knowledge and strategy when an Acumera Merchant Gateway (AMG) stops reporting in AcuVigil(TM) and provide initial troubleshooting to use with on-site personnel.&nbsp; AMGs that stop reporting on AcuVigil will change its location block from GREEN, YELLOW, BLUE, or ORANGE to RED.&nbsp; Location block color descriptions are found in AcuVigil by clicking on the Help link located in the upper right-hand corner.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Background</strong><br />AMGs are connected to the Internet via a carrier modem (DSL, Cable, or other).&nbsp; When the AMG has stopped reporting (location block is RED in AcuVigil) the initial troubleshooting may include rebooting the AMG and carrier equipment.<br /><br /><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Initial Troubleshooting Processes</strong><br />Support personnel can contact a location to engage store personnel in troubleshooting after identifying the location in AcuVigil.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Confirm the AMG has power</strong><br />Ask store personnel to check and verify if PWR indicator is lit on the AMG. Indicator lights are situated on the top sloped edge of the AMG. Note: Confirm store personnel are looking downward at the lights on the top edge of the AMG. In some cases they may need a step ladder to see the lights. Below are examples of the labels on the the top sloped edge of the AMG.<br /><br /><br /><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/amg1-1.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"502\" height=\"75\" /></span></span>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Figure 1.1 - PWR Light will show immediately when power is connected</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/amg1-2.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"502\" height=\"75\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Figure 1.2 - 10-12 Seconds after power is connected, CLOUD, SEC, TEMP, DOOR, &amp; DIAG lights will blink 3 times.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/amg1-3.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"502\" height=\"75\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Figure 1.3 - LAN and WAN lights during boot sequence. The AMG will attempt to connect to the Internet for 5 minutes. It will reboot if it does not connect to the Internet.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/amg1-4.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"502\" height=\"75\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Figure 1.4 - CLOUD light indicates AMG is connected to the Internet (approximately 60-90 seconds from initial power-on).</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If no PWR light is present, request personnel to determine source of power issue (AMG unplugged, problem with UPS, circuit breaker&nbsp;tripped, etc...) and correct if possible.&nbsp; If power is corrected, move to step 1.b.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If PWR is lit as shown in Figure 1.1 above, have the person observe what other indicator lights are illuminated on the AMG.&nbsp; Record the other lights they indicate and proceed to step 1.c.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Request the store personnel to observe the light indicator status on the carrier equipment.&nbsp; Ensure there is at least a power light indicator.&nbsp; Carrier equipment varies based on the provider.&nbsp; Proceed to step 2.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><br /><br /></span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Power Cycling AMG and Carrier Modem</strong><br />Power cycling the AMG and the carrier modem may reset the Internet connection and return the AMG to a GREEN reporting status. Request store personnel assist in power cycling the AMG following these steps:<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Disconnect the power cord from the AMG.&nbsp; The AMG&rsquo;s power cord is black and is plugged into the furthest right-hand port on the AMG.&nbsp; The power cord looks similar to a cell phone charging power cord.&nbsp; The power port is labeled &ldquo;12 VDC&rdquo; on the AMG.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Locate the carrier modem (a.k.a. Customer Premise Equipment or CPE) and disconnect its power.&nbsp; The brand name and model of carrier modem depends on the carrier (DSL, Cable, or other).&nbsp; If the store personnel cannot locate the carrier modem, ask them to trace the Ethernet cable plugged into the Ethernet-WAN port on the AMG.&nbsp; The Ethernet-WAN port should be connected to the carrier modem.&nbsp; Continue to the next step.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Wait up to 120 seconds with carrier modem and AMG powered off.&nbsp; Continue to the next step.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Reconnect power to the carrier modem FIRST.&nbsp; After power is reconnected to the carrier modem, wait for the modem to get a green DSL, Internet, or Online light OR wait 90 seconds and then go to step 2.e.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Reconnect power to the AMG SECOND.&nbsp; Wait 90 seconds.&nbsp; Ask store personnel to observe the CLOUD light on the AMG.&nbsp; If the CLOUD light is not illuminated within 5 minutes, there may be a problem with the connection between the AMG and the CPE.&nbsp; Request store personnel to check cable connections.&nbsp; Continue on to step 2.f.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>It may take up to 5 minutes before a location shows up as GREEN and reporting in AcuVigil.&nbsp; Check the location block in AcuVigil to determine if the MG has returned to reporting.&nbsp; Request store personnel test and verify a positive Internet Connection.&nbsp; If the test is negative, proceed to step 3.<br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><br /><br /><br /></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">What to do If Power Cycling does not return AMG to reporting?</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">If the prescribed procedure does not return the AMG to reporting, open a support request in <a href=\"https://acuvigil.acumera.net/\" target=\"_blank\">AcuVigil</a> to request support. Be certain to note what light indicators are illuminated on the AMG and Carrier equipment when creating a support request. If there is already a support request created, please contact the Acumera NOC at <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">512-687-7401<a style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 512-687-7401\" href=\"#\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 512-687-7401\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></a></span>.</span></p>', '2014-02-04 09:12:15', 'l7d23b', '2017-05-01 11:52:59', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Basic Troubleshooting for Acumera Merchant Gateway Devices', '', 30007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'https://acuvigil.acumera.net/');
