(253, 'Acuvigil Location Status Notification Definitions', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Status Notification Color Definitions</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">OK - GREEN</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 80px; height: 80px; background: #8fc07c;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Location #<br />City<br />Carrier</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Definition: A location with a GREEN status notification means all systems are up and running correctly. Locations with a red outline currently have an open support request. Locations with a black outline do not have an open support request.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">DOWN - RED</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 80px; height: 80px; background: #e47757;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Location #<br />City<br />Carrier</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Definition: A location with a RED status notification means the Acumera MG is not currently reporting. The location may not be operating as expected due to power, carrier network, or equipment.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Expectations: Acumera will diagnose locations with a RED status notification as quickly as possible and communicate with customers by utilizing a Support Request via <a href=\"https://acuvigil.acumera.net/\" target=\"_blank\">AcuVigil</a>. Acumera prioritizes locations with a RED status notification according the length of time the Acumera MG has not been reporting its status.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">CRITICAL - ORANGE</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 80px; height: 80px; background: #f7c890;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Location #<br />City<br />Carrier</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Definition: A location with an ORANGE status notification means the Acumera MG is reporting, but one or more of components are not functioning properly and need attention. Critical type errors include;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Expectations: Acumera expects customers will monitor and request support for locations with an ORANGE status notification. The best and quickest way to request assistance with remedying a location with an ORANGE status notification is to open a Support Request in <a href=\"https://acuvigil.acumera.net/\" target=\"_blank\">AcuVigil</a> and communicate the symptoms of the issue and the desired support.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">AcuVigil Users with 2 Factor Authentication enabled can register devices and restart failed VPN tunnels.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">AcuVigil Users can create and schedule emailed &ldquo;Devices Not Responding&rdquo; alerts to assist with device status.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">WARNING - YELLOW</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 80px; height: 80px; background: #faf27a;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Location #<br />City<br />Carrier</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Definition: A location with a YELLOW status notification means the Acumera MG is reporting, but there is an Automatic Tank Gauge (ATG) alert communicated from the ATG to the MG.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Expectations: Acumera expects customers will address the ATG alert associated with YELLOW status notifications. Contact Acumera via an <a href=\"https://acuvigil.acumera.net/\" target=\"_blank\">AcuVigil</a> Support Request if support is required.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">INFO - BLUE</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 80px; height: 80px; background: #a3d8f2;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Location #<br />City<br />Carrier</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Definition: A location with a BLUE status notification means the Acumera MG is reporting, but there are issues that may require customer intervention and/or service. For example, a blue status may indicate that there are localized issues with the DSL connection (re-trains or errors) or the VPN tunnel, or that the Merchant Gateway\'s internal temperature is elevated.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Expectations: Acumera expects customers will provide feedback regarding symptoms from locations with BLUE status notification. Acumera will do its best to diagnose the possible cause at a location with a BLUE status notification and contact the carrier when, and if, needed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">GREY</span></strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 80px; height: 80px; background: #d3d3d3;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Location #<br />City<br />Carrier</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Definition: A location with a GREY status notification means the Acumera MG has not been installed at the location.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Expectations: Contact Acumera&rsquo;s Provisioning team at <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">512-687-7402<a style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 512-687-7402\" href=\"#\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 512-687-7402\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></a></span> for questions about locations with GREY status notification.</span></p>', '2014-02-04 09:46:21', 'l7d23b', '2017-05-01 12:06:06', 'ln524h', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Location status information in Acuvigil', '', 30007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'https://acuvigil.acumera.net/https://acuvigil.acumera.net/https://acuvigil.acumera.net/'),
(254, 'Spacenet Dispatch Script', '<p>Effective immediately, every dispatch of a SpaceNet technician <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">requires a separate journal entry</span> </strong>in your HEAT ticket specifying that you read the following script to your customer.&nbsp; You need to include your customer&rsquo;s<strong> first and last name</strong> along with a notation that that individual authorized the dispatch:</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&ldquo;In an effort to resolve this issue, we can dispatch a technician from our communication partner.&nbsp; Please be advised that if the technician determines the issue is with the store&rsquo;s environment or equipment this will be a billable service call.&nbsp; Do you agree to us dispatching a technician to your site to try and resolve the issue?&rdquo;</strong></p>', '2014-02-05 08:03:18', 'l7d23b', '2014-02-05 08:03:28', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Spacenet Dispatch Script', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(255, 'Gempay Retailer Settlement Reports', '<p>For Gempay retailers who require help in accessing their Settlement Reports (ATOS only provide Settlement Reports for polled sites) please direct them to Texaco Station, <a href=\"http://www.texacostation.com/\">www.TexacoStation.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Gempay sites are not polled. The transaction records are forwarded by the terminal every day as part of the end of day process.</p>\r\n<p>Settlement reports are the equivalent of polling reports, and are produced every week to show a complete breakdown of transactions from the sites which have been submitted for payment</p>\r\n<p>All retailers have access to this site as they use it to order fuel, etc.&nbsp; For head office personnel who require access they can do so by clicking the &ldquo;Register or Request Access&rdquo; link at the welcome page:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/texportal01.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"612\" height=\"346\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;To access Settlement Reports for Gempay terminals retailers need to select &ldquo;Settlement Reports&rdquo; on the E-Billing menu:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/texportal02.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"584\" height=\"270\" /></p>', '2014-02-05 10:05:21', 'l7d23b', '2014-04-13 08:18:13', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on accessing settlement reports for Gempay Retailers', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'http://www.texacostation.com/'),
(256, 'Wayne Nucleus Small Credit Amount Setup', '<ol>\r\n<li>From the main menu, go to Programming<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Application<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Network<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>At the bottom-right of the screen locate Modify Signature Limit.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>This will take you to a card deck. From here select the card to change&nbsp;small credit amount.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Save the changes. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes will not take affect until the Nucleus is rebooted.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2014-02-11 09:50:10', 'l7d23b', '2017-05-01 12:09:18', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions to configure small credit amount on Wayne Nucleus', '', 10007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(259, 'Jobber/Dealer Portal Password Change or Reset Request', '<p>Submit a Service Request by navigating to the Service Request Catalog Self Service application located at <a href=\"http://help.valero.com/\">http://help.valero.com</a></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>In the search box, type &ldquo;Wholesale&rdquo; and click the magnifying glass icon to search.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/portal1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"710\" height=\"190\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>After selecting the &lsquo;Support&rsquo; tab and searching &lsquo;Wholesale Portal&rsquo;, the default option is still to create a Request and not a ticket. Select the CI again in the &lsquo;Support&rsquo; list or change the catalog option to &lsquo;Support&rsquo; to create a ticket.</p>\r\n<img src=\"upload/portal2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"712\" height=\"337\" /></li>\r\n</ul>', '2014-02-11 14:29:54', 'l7d23b', '2014-03-20 08:49:34', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on opening a ticket for a Jobber/Dealer portal password change or reset', '', 40007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'http://help.valero.com/'),
(260, 'Stripes Commander Installs', '<p>Stripes is making a push to get most of their sites moved over to the new VeriFone Commander System.&nbsp; Spacenet has been made aware of the change but the information may have not been relayed to all of their helpdesk.&nbsp; If you have a Stripes station call in advising they are upgrading to the Commander at their location and need the Prysm configured accordingly, contact Spacenet and check how <strong>LAN 2</strong> is configured. It should be configured identically to <strong>LAN 1</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In normal cases, LAN 2 is <strong>not</strong> configured. If LAN 2 isn\'t&nbsp;configured, either ask the Spacenet helpdesk tech to make the change, or open a Spacenet ticket.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table class=\"null\" style=\"margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"3\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Use reference site: <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #00ccff; text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #ff6600; text-decoration: underline;\">30216-47500-99285</span> </span></span>if Spacenet has any </strong><strong>questions </strong><strong>about how your site should be configured.</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Stripes uses LAN 1 for their backoffice equipment and LAN 2 for their Commander.&nbsp; This is the only difference between Stripes Commander setups and everyone else, as everyone else uses LAN 1 for the Commander.</p>', '2014-02-11 16:18:31', 'l7d23b', '2014-08-25 06:43:50', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information regarding Prysm setup for Stripes Commanders', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(261, 'UK Transaction Settlement Timings', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 140px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"445\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Acquirers</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Settlement Date</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Barclays</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>T+3</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>American Express</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>T+5</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>UK Fuels - FastFuel</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>T+10</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>AllStar</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>T+13</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>UK Fuels - Texaco the Business</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>T+15</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>CH Jones</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>N/A - Bunkering </strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key: <br /></strong><strong>T = Transaction Date</strong></p>', '2014-02-19 10:22:04', 'l7d23b', '2016-07-26 12:11:54', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on settlement timings on UK card types', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(262, 'UK Gempay Product Coding', '<p><a href=\"upload/APACS%20Product Codes And Oil Co Standards.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">APACS Product Codes And Oil Co Standards</a></p>', '2014-02-19 13:29:24', 'l7d23b', '2014-07-10 06:22:58', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Product code list for UK sites on Gempay.', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'L2 L2 L2 L2 L2'),
(263, 'FPX Port Forwarding', '<p>UDP&nbsp;on ports 500 and 4500</p>\r\n<p>TCP on port 47</p>\r\n<p>TCP&nbsp;on port 50 for 3 different public addresses - 206.66.146.1; 208.224.248.129; 204.8.249.1</p>', '2014-02-20 09:50:25', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-23 08:51:55', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on port forwarding for FPXs behind Routers/Firewalls', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(264, 'Acumera Support Resource', '<h4>Support Documents</h4>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"upload/docs/Valero Processor Connections Service Installation Instructions 2016nov21.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Valero Processor Connections</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"upload/docs/TechnicalSupportEscalationProcessValero.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Tiered Support Guide</a></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"upload/docs/AcuVigilStatusNotificationGuideValero.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AcuVigil Status Notification Guide</a> - </strong>description of indicator lights on the AMG</p>\r\n<p><strong><a href=\"upload/docs/TechnicalSupportEscalationProcessValero.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Technical Support Escalation Process</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tier 3 support hours are 6am &ndash; 10pm CT.&nbsp; If there are activations outside of this time, please refer to the Technical Support Escalation Process above.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Update: &nbsp;After creating an Acuvigil ticket, email our Heat ticket number to <a href=\"mailto:team@acumera.net\">team@acumera.net</a>.<br /><br /></strong></p>\r\n<h4>Acumera Billing Codes</h4>\r\n<p>MSR entry: Monthly CStore CNT Billing</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 275px; margin-right: 20px; float: left;\" border=\"1\" width=\"379\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"89\"><strong>RAMS Billing Code: A6</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"424\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Description</span></strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"74\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fee</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #99caff;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>ONE TIME SETUP CHARGES</strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Fuel Connections Service</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><em>Merchant Gateway</em></td>\r\n<td>$&nbsp;379.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><em>Setup Installation (Required)-One time charge</em></td>\r\n<td>$&nbsp;200.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>Total</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>$&nbsp;579.00</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Description</span></strong></td>\r\n<td><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fee</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #99caff;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>RECURRING CHARGES</strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Fuel Connections Service</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><em>Monthly Fee</em></td>\r\n<td>$&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>Total</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>$&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20.00</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style=\"height: 275px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"379\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"424\"><strong>RAMS Billing Code: A7</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"74\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"424\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Description</span></strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"74\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fee</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #8ade8a;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>ONE TIME SETUP CHARGES</strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>C-Store Connentions</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><em>Merchant Gateway</em></td>\r\n<td>$ 379.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><em>Setup Installation (Required)-One time charge</em></td>\r\n<td>$ 250.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>Total</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>$&nbsp;629.00</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Description</span></strong></td>\r\n<td><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fee</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #8ade8a;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>RECURRING CHARGES</strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>C-Store Connentions</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><em>Monthly Fee</em></td>\r\n<td>$&nbsp;&nbsp; 65.00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>Total</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #fff6a3;\"><strong>$&nbsp;&nbsp; 65.00</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>WTS Support Scope</h4>\r\n<p>Provide Level 1 online, telephone, and/or email customer support 24/7, less designated holidays for standard support.</p>\r\n<p>Other than direct phone calls in&nbsp;to us, we can take no longer than 4 hours to address any non-phone reported issues. This includes requests via email or the AcuVigil portal.</p>\r\n<p>On initial call or within the 4 hour window, we must:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Acknowledge customer support request.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Gather customer&rsquo;s information and system status&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Create a service ticket and begin entering this information into the service ticket. (Need to determine integration capabilities between AcuVigil, or if we can perhaps use email connectors to accomplish communication between the two systems?)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Initiate a&nbsp;call for remote diagnosis, utilizing on-site personnel to determine:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The status of power to the location and equipment</li>\r\n<li>If cables are connected to the equipment appropriately</li>\r\n<li>The Broadband Modem has appropriate status lights for Internet connection</li>\r\n<li>The Acumera MG is connecting to the Internet (CLOUD light = GREEN)<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Continue remote resolution actions based diagnosis. Actions may include:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Request personnel to power cycle the MG and Broadband Modem</li>\r\n<li>Request personnel to check cables are connected appropriately</li>\r\n<li>Other resolution actions appropriate to the diagnosed issue<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Document in an AcuVigil<sup>(TM)</sup> support request the diagnosed issue and details of remote resolution action(s) including status of lights on equipment.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Recommend replacement equipment if it is determined to be inoperable (e.g. no lights on device even when power is tested at two different outlets and outlets are determined to have power).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If it is thought to be a carrier related issue, document such and assign the ticket to Acumera for Level 2 support.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Consult with AcuVigil<sup>(TM) </sup>to determine status of VPN.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Moves/Replacement/Changes to device registration and/or security policy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Proactive Monitoring</h4>\r\n<p>We are asked to monitor sites that are in the&nbsp;AcuVigil portal for potential issues&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Check AcuVigil<sup>(TM) </sup>status for location(s) reporting as down or not-responding devices.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If a device is determined down or not responding through observation of AcuVigil, from that time that a device goes down or not responding, create a service ticket within the timeframes listed above..<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Initiate contact with broadband provider to determine possible carrier related issues when appropriate and document result of contact (indicate whether outage related).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once a Tier 1 issue has been resolved, contact location to verify issue has been resolved, note verification in the service ticket, and close service ticket support requests within the timeframes listed above once support request is addressed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Escalation and transition when appropriate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Typical Daily Procedures</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Field inbound customer calls<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Issue information documentation\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Standard Valero Operating Procedures</li>\r\n<li>Standard Valero Support Documentation<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Monitoring and initiate investigation into location or devices not responding\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Expectation is Valero will proactively monitor customer sites, open support tickets provide Level 1 support</li>\r\n<li>Field initial inbound customer calls and provide Level 1 support <br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>User name and password issues<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Customer questions about AcuVigil<sup>(TM)</sup> interface<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Broadband provider contact<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Power cycling carrier and MG<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Providing active remote support via phone<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Standard Level 1 troubleshooting<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Diagnosis of possible root cause(s) for not-responding location or device Moves/Replacement/Changes to device registration and/or security policy<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Observe DNS name of a location resolves to reported IP address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Acumera\'s Scope</h4>\r\n<p>Supports Valero for New Merchant Gateway setup and security changes. Engage development and engineering teams to resolve issues.</p>\r\n<h5>Approach</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Respond to phone or AcuVigil<sup>(TM) </sup>dashboard support requests escalated by Valero<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Confer with Valero regarding resolution action(s).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Final resolution of issue to customer satisfaction.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>Responsibilities</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Four hour response time (during normal Acumera NOC business hours) to Valero initiated escalations<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In-depth analysis of escalated calls or tickets<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>AcuVigil<sup>(TM) </sup>dashboard trouble-shooting<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Acumera Merchant Gateway trouble-shooting<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Network configuration<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Network security issues<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Restarting VPN tunnels<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Verify solutions and add to knowledge base and, if appropriate, work with development team to characterize new features or bug for future releases and/or versions.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Security policy design<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>Typical Issues</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Security policy additions, changes and trouble-shooting<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Company wide network numbering or configuration changes<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VPN design, implementation, and changes<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VPN concentrator and routing troubleshooting<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Resolving M2M interface issues, such as Automatic Tank Gauge connections<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Setting up automated reports</li>\r\n</ul>', '2014-02-21 10:41:11', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-19 12:21:41', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Acumera Support Resource', '', 30007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:team@acumera.net'),
(265, 'Gempay Large Log File Error', '<p>To correct the \"Large Log File\" Error on Gempays, follow these steps:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Reboot the Gempay</span><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Press the &ldquo;General/Select button&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;Maintenance&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Select \"Reboot\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Press the &ldquo;General/Select button&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;Maintenance&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;Download&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;Connect&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press &ldquo;Enter&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press &ldquo;Ok&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #800080;\">Reboot the Gempay again</span><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Press the &ldquo;General/Select button&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;Maintenance&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Select \"Reboot\"</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-03-17 06:38:04', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-25 08:14:11', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to fix the large log file errors on Gempays', '', 80003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(266, 'UK Heat / Sharepoint Ticket Priority Classifications', '<h4><span style=\"background-color: #ff0000; color: #ffffff;\">Critical</span></h4>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #3366ff;\">Heat Priority: 1 - Emergency<br /><br />Ops Log&nbsp;Priority: High<br /></span></strong></span></h4>\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Issue&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Description&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Response Timeframe</td>\r\n<td>Escalation&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Comments&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Total communications failure on site</td>\r\n<td>Loss of DSL and GPRS</td>\r\n<td>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 24 hours</td>\r\n<td>TNS Account Manager, TNS service Manager, TNS delivery Team Lead</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cannot take any cards</td>\r\n<td>Cannot take all cards</td>\r\n<td>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 6 hours</td>\r\n<td>HTEC, FIS Account Manager, TNS</td>\r\n<td>Where it is not easily apparent where the fault has arisen from, there will be a period of analysis to help identify the failing service</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cannot take Visa cards</td>\r\n<td>Site cannot take visa credit or debit cards</td>\r\n<td>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 6 hours</td>\r\n<td>Barclays, FIS, HTEC</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Due payments over 3 days late</td>\r\n<td>Settlement to sites over 3 days late&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Contact site and Area Manager</td>\r\n<td>Relevant supplier contact</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Requests to support fraud investigations</td>\r\n<td>Requests from Police or other relevant organisation to support a fraud investigation on site</td>\r\n<td>Immediate</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Cannot accept Allstar cards</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;Allstar transactions failure</td>\r\n<td>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 6 hours</td>\r\n<td>Relevant supplier contact</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\">Medium</span></h4>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #3366ff;\">Heat Priority:&nbsp;2 - Elevated<br /><br />Ops Log&nbsp;Priority: Medium</span></span></strong></span></h4>\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Issue&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Description&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Response Timeframe</td>\r\n<td>Escalation&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Comments&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ADSL down/GPRS UP</td>\r\n<td>ADSL or PSTN down on a site</td>\r\n<td>Contact TNS, request fix in 48 hours</td>\r\n<td>TNS Account Manager, TNS service Manager, TNS delivery Team Lead</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Fuel Card not accepted</td>\r\n<td>Any scheme outside Allstar</td>\r\n<td>Contact site, raise issue, request fix 48 hours</td>\r\n<td>Card issuer, relevant supplier</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Single terminal failure</td>\r\n<td>Single terminal on a 2/more terminal site</td>\r\n<td>VCS helpdesk, raise with HTEC, initial assessment, terminal delivery within 5 days</td>\r\n<td>HTEC</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Reconciliation Issues</td>\r\n<td>Site unable to reconcile transactions</td>\r\n<td>Contact site, provide reports/access to reports within 5 days</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"background-color: #99cc00;\">Low</span></h4>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffffff; color: #3366ff;\">Heat Priority:&nbsp;3 - Standard<br /><br />Ops Log&nbsp;Priority: Low</span></span></strong></span></h4>\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Issue&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Description&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Response Timeframe</td>\r\n<td>Escalation&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Comments&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>PINpad failure</td>\r\n<td>VCS helpdesk, request PINpad</td>\r\n<td>VCS helpdesk, request PINpad</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Keyboard failure</td>\r\n<td>VCS helpdesk, request Keyboard</td>\r\n<td>VCS helpdesk, request Keyboard</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Back Office issues</td>\r\n<td>Back office</td>\r\n<td>Raise with supplier</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Site must have a contract with the supplier</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>POS issues</td>\r\n<td>POS</td>\r\n<td>Raise with supplier</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Requests for configuration changes (cashback, for example)</td>\r\n<td>POS</td>\r\n<td>Raise with supplier</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2014-03-25 08:22:04', 'l7d23b', '2014-11-24 13:10:35', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'UK Heat / Sharepoint  Ticket Priority Classifications', '', 80002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(267, 'Gempay EOD Product Coding', '<p>The end of day report for Gempays will have a list of printed product codes that do not match their terminal or tills&rsquo; codes.</p>\r\n<p>If a station calls concerned about this difference, please advise the station that these codes are only a host-level translation of the till/terminal codes and will not impact in their ability to be paid.</p>', '2014-03-27 09:31:47', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-25 08:20:51', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on product codes printed on end of day reports for Gempay', '', 80003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(268, 'Star Rewards operating rules on Valero sites', '<ul>\r\n<li>The terminal will prompt a loyalty card from the customer when the transaction is a qualifying transaction.</li>\r\n<li>Starrewards are only available on qualifying fuel sales, for both cash and card transactions.</li>\r\n<li>Starrewards are not available on non-fuel transactions, including shop sales for dry goods.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>Running Starrewards on Idle Mode on the Gempay 3&nbsp;Terminal</h4>\r\n<p>The option to run Starreward transactions on Gempay terminals on idle mode has been Implemented on your site, and this will enable you award loyalty points for qualifying cash purchases.</p>\r\n<p>Please note: This is a manual sale and you must run it as a manual sale. For clarity, follow the steps listed below.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press the F2 key on the Gempay to start a manual sale.</li>\r\n<li>When asked for the supervisor code, please enter the site&rsquo;s supervisor code.</li>\r\n<li>When it displays the menu to enter an amount, enter the sale amount and press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Follow the prompt and enter Volume.</li>\r\n<li>When prompted for the card, swipe the loyalty card.</li>\r\n<li>Complete the loyalty transaction.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Card types that should attract loyalty:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All standard bank cards: credit, debit, Amex, Master card.</li>\r\n<li>Qualifying fuel cards: Allstar, The Business, BP Routex.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Exclusions:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Please note:</strong>&nbsp; All bunker cards are excluded from the loyalty program because there is a discount already built into the bunker scheme. Excluded cards are:</li>\r\n<li>Euroshell</li>\r\n<li>Keyfuels</li>\r\n<li>UKFuels Fleetone</li>\r\n<li>UKFuels Bunker Cards</li>\r\n<li>RED Card</li>\r\n<li>Fast Fuels</li>\r\n<li>All sales for non-fuel products, irrespective of whether payment is by cash or card.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Loyalty awards:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Loyalty is awarded on a point (worth 1p)&nbsp;per&nbsp;litre basis, i.e. 4 litres will only attract 4 points.</li>\r\n<li>Loyalty is only awarded on the fuel element of the sale.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Points:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Points can take up to 24 hrs. to update.</li>\r\n<li>Points on Gempay sites it is a reflection of the latest points file supplied by the loyalty host to FIS.</li>\r\n<li>Customers can verify their points either by logging onto the Starrewards site or calling the Starrewards helpdesk. The helpdesk number is on the Starrewards receipt.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2014-04-08 06:32:51', 'l7d23b', '2017-10-23 08:54:58', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'These rules define product selection rules governing loyalty on Valero sites.', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(269, 'Gempay EOD Reprint Instructions', '<p>As we do not have access to see if a site successfully performed an end of day, a workaround has been discovered to test.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On the Gempay, press the middle button<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Use the arrow buttons to navigate down to the \"Transactions\" option and press the middle button to select.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Use the arrow buttons to navigate to \"Duplicate\" and press the middle button to select.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select End of Day.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>A&nbsp;list of tickets will display. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose the entry with the highest number then select Duplicate.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This will print out the last end of day that was performed&nbsp;(as long as the entry with the highest number was selected). The EOD will have a date of original completion.&nbsp;Based off that date, we can confirm, for the site, the last EOD that was completed.</p>', '2014-04-17 07:21:55', 'l7d23b', '2015-08-31 07:24:47', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on reprinting EODs to check for failed closes', '', 80003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(270, 'VCS Additional POS and Terminal request process', '<p>We may receive calls from retailers requesting additional terminals for their site. Please follow these steps to complete the request.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><strong><em>Please note</em></strong>: It is the retailer&rsquo;s responsibility to arrange the POS install date, and this is also at Retailer&rsquo;s cost. However soon as we are informed of the POS install date, it is VCS responsibility to arrange for terminal preparation and supply, and engineering support for the POS/Terminal linking.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>The following information is required when setting up a new terminal request.</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Setup Type</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If the station is installing a new till(s):<img style=\"float: right; margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px;\" src=\"upload/linktype.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"423\" height=\"307\" /></li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Obtain the install date of the new till(s).</li>\r\n<li>Obtain the number of tills being added.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>If the station has already installed a new till(s).<br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Obtain the number of tills that were added.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>Till Link Type<br />To obtain the link type, have the station check if there is a cable connected <strong>under</strong> the terminal in the RS port.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If there is a cable, this is an F75 link.</li>\r\n<li>If there is no cable, this is an OPI link or standalone.<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The site should be able to tell you if the till is already linked to the terminal. If not, trace the cable from the Gempay. If it is linked, it will attach to the till, if it is standalone, it will connect directly to the router or switch.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Till Link Type Switch</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the site currently has F75 and they\'re wanting to switch to OPI on the new and old terminals, the following conditions <strong>must be met:</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The site must be running one of the following support till types:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Micros</li>\r\n<li>HTEC Hydrapos</li>\r\n<li>HTEC Indigo</li>\r\n<li>Point4<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The site must have active till support for their system.<br />This type of change will usually require a vendor meet if there are any issues with the cutover.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The site must have a properly configured router from TNS. <br /><br /></span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><br /></strong></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Send an email to&nbsp;Paula Leslie&nbsp;- <a href=\"mailto:pleslie@tnsi.com\">pleslie@tnsi.com</a></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Have Jane confirm the router will be able to support additional&nbsp;terminal(s)/till(s) and/or link type changes and option type it is set for.<br /><strong>IMPORTANT: Let Jane know this is strictly an enquiry so she does not begin the process.</strong><br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jane will confirm if the router is ready to go, needs to be reprogrammed, or needs to be replaced.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If the router requires replacement, it will need to initiated by Jane, please let her know to go ahead and dispatch a new router and, if possible, provide an arrival date for the new router. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Advise the site&nbsp;to allow 5-7 business days for the replacement to arrive.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once we\'ve been provided a completion/replacement date for the router, we can now work with HTEC on ordering equipment and scheduling an engineer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>A request will need to be sent to <a href=\"mailto:InstallationRequest@htec.co.uk\">InstallationRequest@htec.co.uk</a>&nbsp;to request new TIDs and terminals. Include the following info in the request:<br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Till installation date if not already installed. If new tills were&nbsp;already installed, state this in the email.</li>\r\n<li>Number of tills being added.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 108px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Option 1 - Standard Configuration</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Option 2 - GEM/SPAR Configuration</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Option 3 - Standalone Configuration</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">This provides a range of IP address for the tills and terminals</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">This provides a range of IP address for the tills and terminals for GEM / SPAR Sites</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">This is a configuration for only Gempay terminals with no till IP addressing</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Ex. Pos: 192.168.0.2 - 192.168.0.XXX</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Ex. Pos: 200.1.100.1 - 200.1.100.XXX</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Ex. Gempay: 192.168.0.50 - 192.168.0.XXX</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Ex. Gempay: 200.1.100.50 - 200.1.100.XXX</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">&nbsp;Ex. Gempay: 192.168.0.50 - 192.168.0.XXX</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2014-04-17 10:00:06', 'l7d23b', '2017-11-13 05:58:18', 'lqnwmy', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'VCS Additional POS and Terminal request process', '', 80002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:pleslie@tnsi.commailto:InstallationRequest@htec.co.uk'),
(271, 'Valuelink Password Reset', '<ol>\r\n<li>Call Valuelink Help Desk: 866-874-7901<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>They will ask for the name of the business, tell them &ldquo;Valero Energy&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Valuelink Rep will ask for the Merchant ID or Valuelink Merchant ID. It is: 94981080001<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Rep will then ask for a \"Store Number.\" You can use any CST BC# or the information provided below.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Give Rep address to that CST store<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Rep will ask for your user ID and then reset your password.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">CST 1029</span></p>\r\n<p>Store Number: 02011811029</p>\r\n<p>Store Address: 4902 E Houston &nbsp;San Antonio TX 78220</p>', '2014-05-12 10:19:22', 'l7d23b', '2014-05-12 10:19:56', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to reset your Valuelink password', '', 40004, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(272, 'Voucher Information', '<p>All stationary should be ordered through our approved supplier, UK Paper Rolls.</p>\r\n<p>Their website is <a href=\"http://www.pdqconsumables.com/\">http://www.pdqconsumables.com</a></p>\r\n<p>If the site does not have an imprinter or vouchers, they can order the \"Welcome Pack\" from the website. It includes the manual imprinter, imprinter plate, and vouchers.</p>', '2014-05-12 10:45:04', 'l7d23b', '2014-09-30 14:51:15', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on stationary, vouchers, imprinters, and plates', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'http://www.pdqconsumables.com/');
