(283, 'Ops Manual 11 - VCS Helpdesk', '<p><strong>11&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;VCS HELPDESK</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Helpdesk functions are currently performed by the TCS helpdesk on legacy sites. The TCS helpdesk is outsourced to ATOS, the company currently responsible for polling transactions on Valero sites.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">The VCS helpdesk in Amarillo supports all sites deployed under the Retail Technology refresh project, and will become the only helpdesk supporting retail technology in the UK as soon as the migration of sites is completed, and the TCS helpdesk will cease to exist as a support desk.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/vcssupport.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"554\" height=\"538\" />Figure 11: VCS Support Desk Process</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The VCS helpdesk is the first port of call for all site issues. The helpdesk is expected to analyse the issues presented, and make a decision on what the issue is, and what supplier is best placed to resolve it.</p>\r\n<p>Whilst legacy sites are expected to ring the TCS helpdesk, there will be occasion when legacy sites will call the VCS helpdesk:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-roman;\">\r\n<li>Helpdesk analysts should run through the issues presented and where possible, raise a call with the TCS helpdesk.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>It is acceptable for the analysts to take the call and seek guidance from the UK Retail Technology team on next steps.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/vcshd.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"810\" height=\"512\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Figure 12: VCS Helpdesk Issue/Escalation Process<br /><br /><br /><br /></p>', '2014-07-30 07:22:56', 'l7d23b', '2014-07-30 07:26:59', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Card Systems Operations and Maintenance Manual', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(284, 'Ops Manual 12 - Contract support/Vendor Mgmt', '<p><strong>12&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; CONTRACT SUPPORT/VENDOR MANAGEMENT</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This refers to the process of managing the relationship between Valero and vendors supporting the VCS proposition. <br />These vendors and suppliers are highlighted in figure 1. Vendor management is currently run by the VCS Retail Technology team and includes:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-roman;\">\r\n<li>Account management</li>\r\n<li>Contracts support and negotiation</li>\r\n<li>SLA monitoring and reporting</li>\r\n<li>Escalation of issues<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/ops11.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"734\" height=\"832\" /></p>', '2014-07-30 07:26:35', 'l7d23b', '2016-01-07 09:10:13', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Card Systems Operations and Maintenance Manual', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(285, 'Ops Manual 13 - Regulatory Requirements', '<p><strong>13&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;REGULATORY REQUIREMENTS</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">The prevalent regulations on Valero sites in the UK are the PCIDSS regulations. These regulations address how card data is dealt with on sites. For instance, there is a requirement that the full card pan should not be displayed on either card receipts or held anywhere on site. On legacy sites, these full PANs are still held on the retailer transaction copy largely because there is no means of reconciling transactions on these sites where there are queries.</p>', '2014-07-30 07:30:34', 'l7d23b', '2014-07-30 07:30:34', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Card Systems Operations and Maintenance Manual', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(286, 'Ops Manual 1 - Table of Contents', '<p><a href=\"#intro\"><strong>1&nbsp;INTRODUCTION</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">1.1&nbsp;Purpose<br />1.2&nbsp;Audience</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=287\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>2&nbsp;GLOSSARY OF TERMS</strong></a></p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=275\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>3&nbsp;VALERO CARD SERVICES</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">3.1&nbsp;The Vcs partners/suppliers<br />3.1.1&nbsp;ATOS<br />3.1.2&nbsp;BarclayCard (BMS)<br />3.1.3&nbsp;Card terminal providers<br />3.1.4&nbsp;Online Authorisation (OLA)<br />3.1.5&nbsp;Comms Providers<br />3.2&nbsp;The Brand<br />3.3&nbsp;Branding, non-branding and fuel agreements</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=276\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>4&nbsp;CARD SYSTEMS</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">4.1&nbsp;EFT, EPOS<br />4.2&nbsp;Types of Terminals<br />4.2.1&nbsp;Types of Terminal links<br />4.3&nbsp;Types of POS<br />4.4&nbsp;Legacy technology vs Technology Refresh<br />4.5&nbsp;Integrated Points of Sale<br />4.6&nbsp;Terminals in Linked Mode<br />4.7&nbsp;Standalone terminals<br />4.8&nbsp;The Gempay Terminal</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">II.&nbsp;Option 2 &ndash; Legacy Protocol (F75 or A77.03) Support (Linked mode)<br />III.&nbsp;Option 3 &ndash; Stand Alone Mode (single or unsupported POS)</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=277\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>5&nbsp;CARD TYPES</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">5.1&nbsp;Commercial credit, debit cards<br />5.2&nbsp;Starrewards loyalty cards<br />5.3&nbsp;Fuel cards<br />5.4&nbsp;Local Account cards</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=278\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>6&nbsp;LEGACY POLLING</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">6.1&nbsp;What is Polling?<br />6.2&nbsp;Addressing polling failures</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=279\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>7&nbsp;TRANSACTIONS, SETTLEMENT AND MISSING TRANSACTIONS</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">7.1&nbsp;The bank merchant acquirer and card issuers<br />7.2&nbsp;Online authorisation and transaction switching<br />7.3&nbsp;Settlement files<br />7.3.1&nbsp;How to Access Settlement files from Texaco Station<br />7.4&nbsp;Trouble shooting missing transactions</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=280\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>8&nbsp;NEW SITE SETUP</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">8.1&nbsp;Site setup process<br />8.2&nbsp;Proforma<br />8.3&nbsp;The vcs pack<br />8.3.1&nbsp;BMS forms<br />8.3.2&nbsp;American Express<br />8.3.3&nbsp;UKFuels<br />8.3.4&nbsp;Allstar<br />8.4&nbsp;Merchant and Terminal IDentity numbers (mids and Tids)<br />8.5&nbsp;Ordering Telecomms<br />8.6&nbsp;Site Survey<br />8.7&nbsp;Site Readiness Process<br />8.8&nbsp;Trouble shooting site setup<br />8.9&nbsp;Archiving setup documents</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=281\"><strong>9&nbsp;SITE CLOSURE</strong></a></p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=282\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>10&nbsp;SUPPORTING EFT</strong></a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">10.1&nbsp;Trouble shooting EFT issues<br />10.2&nbsp;BARCLAYS OFFLINE Process<br />10.3&nbsp;Settlement issues on the Gempay<br />10.4&nbsp;Managing terminal withdrawals<br />10.5&nbsp;Other Gempay usual support Issues<br />10.6&nbsp;Site connectivity trouble shooting<br />10.7&nbsp;Key support contacts</p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=283\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>11&nbsp;VCS HELPDESK</strong></a></p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=284\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>12&nbsp;CONTRACT SUPPORT/VENDOR MANAGEMENT</strong></a></p>\r\n<p><br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=285\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>13&nbsp;REGULATORY REQUIREMENTS</strong></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><a id=\"intro\"></a>1&nbsp;INTRODUCTION</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>1.1&nbsp;PURPOSE</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This document outlines the roles and functions of the UK Technology team and is intended to act as a guide for functions either working in the Retail Technology business area or supporting any of the areas described below.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>1.2&nbsp;AUDIENCE</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Functions or people working in retail technology, VCS Helpdesk or supporting retail systems.</p>', '2014-07-30 07:40:28', 'l7d23b', '2014-07-30 08:28:00', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Card Systems Operations and Maintenance Manual', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '#introindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=287index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=275index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=276index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=277index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=278index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=279index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=280index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=281index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=282index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=283index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=284index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=285'),
(287, 'Ops Manual 2 - Glossary of Terms', '<p><strong>2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Glossary of Terms</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 525px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"738\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p><strong>Acronym</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p><strong>Description</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>BMS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Bank Merchant Acquirer, currently Barclaycard</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>CAD</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Card Acceptance Device</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>ADSL</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Broadband, Asymmetric digital subscriber line</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>GPRS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Mobile SIM capability, fallback for the broadband service</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>ISDN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Integrated services digital network. ISDN2e multipoint with 2 MSNs is used as the standard OLA comms method on legacy sites</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>MSN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Multi subscriber numbering. Facility whereby you can have more than one telephone number allocated to your ISDN2e</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>OLA</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Online authorisation</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>EFT</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Electronic fund transfer</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>EPOS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Electronic point of sale</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>EMV</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Europay, MasterCard and Visa, a global standard for inter-operation of integrated circuit cards and IC card capable point of sale terminals.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>Hot card file</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>List of suspicious, fraudulent or barred cards. File is constantly updated and held by the OLA host</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>ISO</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Card compliant number range, usually associated with a card issuer</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>Card scheme rules</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Rules and regulations governing card schemes</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>Card PAN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Primary Account Number</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>MID</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Merchant Identification number</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>TID</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Terminal Identification number</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>SIF</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Site information form</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>KYC</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Barclays Know Your Customer process</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>PSTN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Public switched Telephone network (voice line for making calls and running the ADSL service)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>Terminal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>Device hosting EFT in non-integrated sites (CAD)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>Integrated POS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>(POS) hosting EFT and EPOS on a single device</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>PinPad</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>PIN entry device</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"133\">\r\n<p>WREN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"491\">\r\n<p>FIS Transaction records database</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2014-07-30 08:25:03', 'l7d23b', '2014-07-30 08:25:29', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Card Systems Operations and Maintenance Manual', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(288, 'BP Card Acceptance Change', '<p>On the August 12th, BP Routex cards on Valero Texaco Stations running on Gempay terminals , will go from swipe and signature-only to Swipe and PIN. As part of this process, HTEC will enable the PIN and make the software available for the terminals to download on the 11th. This is usually a benign process and terminals will pick it up if they dial into TMS. However where a terminal fails to dial-in and HTEC cannot get the site&rsquo;s attention so they can dial the site in, the site will most likely miss the download.</p>\r\n<p>Sites that don&rsquo;t pick up the software patch may find themselves unable to take BP cards on the 12<sup>th</sup>. If this happens and the call comes through to the Helpdesk, please walk the site through dialling their terminals into TMS so they can pick up the patch.</p>\r\n<p>Instructions on having the terminal dial in are available by <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=241\" target=\"_blank\">clicking here and accessing article: 241.</a></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #993366;\">Note: The terminal may need to be rebooted after the dial-in for the settings to apply.</span></strong></p>', '2014-08-09 09:28:03', 'l7d23b', '2014-09-30 14:54:08', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on BP card acceptance', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=241'),
(289, 'BP Card PIN Issue', '<p>BP&nbsp;has changed their fuel card process and introduced swipe and pin security requiring a PIN number.</p>\r\n<p>The PIN number is prompted on the terminal but not on the pin pad. In order to rectify this issue you will need to perform the following processes on <strong>each</strong> of the effected terminals.</p>\r\n<p>The terminals need to be dialed into TMS to download the configuration fix and you will need to know your <strong>supervisor password (689200).</strong> The process will take about 5 minutes in total and will also involve a reboot of the terminal. Please follow the instructions below.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">All&nbsp;4 processes must be followed to complete the configuration which should take no longer than a few minutes in total.</span> </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Process 1</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the OK (Middle) Button on the terminal</li>\r\n<li>Press the down arrow button to Maintenance and press OK</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select download and press&nbsp;OK</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select connect and press OK</li>\r\n<li>The display should show five zero&rsquo;s (&ldquo;00000&rdquo;) press OK</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;Connecting to TMS&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The Screen will then display &ldquo;TMS connection Made&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;TMS Disconnected&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then return to the default screen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reboot the terminal</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the OK (Middle) Button on the terminal</li>\r\n<li>Press the down arrow button to Maintenance and press OK</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select Reboot and press&nbsp;OK</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Process&nbsp;2</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the OK (Middle) Button on the terminal</li>\r\n<li>Press the down arrow button to Maintenance and press OK (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select download and press ok (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select connect and press OK (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>The display should show five zero&rsquo;s (&ldquo;00000&rdquo;)</li>\r\n<li>Press the yellow (Clear) button to clear the five zero&rsquo;s</li>\r\n<li>Enter code (11112) and press ok (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>You may be asked for your supervisor code. If this is the case press the up arrow button to select supervisor then press ok</li>\r\n<li>Enter your supervisor password <strong>(689200)</strong></li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;Connecting to TMS&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The Screen will then display &ldquo;TMS connection Made&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;TMS Disconnected&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then return to the default screen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Process 3</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the OK (Middle) Button on the terminal</li>\r\n<li>Press the down arrow button to Maintenance and press OK (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select download and press ok (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select connect and press OK (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>The display should show five zero&rsquo;s (&ldquo;00000&rdquo;)</li>\r\n<li>Press the yellow (Clear) button to clear the five zero&rsquo;s</li>\r\n<li>Enter code (11113) and press ok (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>You may be asked for your supervisor code. If this is the case press the up arrow button to select supervisor then press ok</li>\r\n<li>Enter your supervisor password <strong>(689200)</strong></li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;Connecting to TMS&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The Screen will then display &ldquo;TMS connection Made&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;TMS Disconnected&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then return to the default screen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reboot the terminal</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the OK (Middle) Button on the terminal</li>\r\n<li>Press the down arrow button to Maintenance and press OK</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select Reboot and press&nbsp;OK</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Process 4</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the OK (Middle) Button on the terminal</li>\r\n<li>Press the down arrow button to Maintenance and press OK (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select download and press ok (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow button to select connect and press OK (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>The display should show five zero&rsquo;s (&ldquo;00000&rdquo;)</li>\r\n<li>Press the yellow (Clear) button to clear the five zero&rsquo;s</li>\r\n<li>Enter code (11111) and press ok (Middle)</li>\r\n<li>You may be asked for your supervisor code. If this is the case press the up arrow button to select supervisor then press ok</li>\r\n<li>Enter your supervisor password <strong>(689200)</strong></li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;Connecting to TMS&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The Screen will then display &ldquo;TMS connection Made&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;Downloading&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>The screen will then display &ldquo;Restart Requested&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>o&nbsp;&nbsp; At this point the terminal will reboot and install the new version of software and return to the default screen.</p>', '2014-08-19 09:59:58', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-22 06:27:56', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'PIN number is prompted on the terminal but not on the pin pad', '', 80001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(290, 'UK Outage Procedure', '<p>If you are receiving calls concerning a similar issue across multiple stations, follow the steps below.</p>\r\n<p><strong></strong>Denotes required step.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step 1</strong> - <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=364\" target=\"_blank\">Identify there is an outage<br /><br /></a></li>\r\n<li><strong>Step 2</strong> - Determine an agent to take point on the outage.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Agent on point <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">must</span> </strong>be logged into the VCS Mailbox during the entirety of the outage as vendors send updates to this box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step&nbsp;3 -</strong> Notify management by email:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Step 6a - If this is a <strong>major</strong> incident:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"mailto:Debra.burnett@valero.com; martin.reynolds@valero.com; Jacqui.john@valero.com; john.mozie@valero.com; asif.rafique@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com; andrew.cox@valero.com; julie.lunnon@valero.com; karolyn.ross@valero.com; Keith.Evans@valero.com; Adele.Shackleton@valero.com?Subject=Initial%20-%20UK%20Outage%20Notification&amp;Body=This%20is%20initial%20notification%20of%20a%20severe%20incident%20that%20is%20currently%20impacting%20station%20trading.%20We%20are%20in%20the%20process%20of%20identifying%20the%20specific%20point%20of%20failure%20and%20will%20update%20once%20we%20have%20more%20information.\">Notify management by email<br /><br /></a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"mailto:Debra.burnett@valero.com; martin.reynolds@valero.com; Jacqui.john@valero.com; john.mozie@valero.com; asif.rafique@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com?Subject=Update%20-%20UK%20Outage%20Notification&amp;Body=Update%20to%20issue%3A\" target=\"_blank\">Notify management on updates</a><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Step 6b&nbsp;- If this is a <strong>minor</strong> incident:<br /><br /><br /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table style=\"height: 21px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; background-color: #545454;\" border=\"1\" width=\"827\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #00ff00;\">IMPORTANT - This process may change in the future. Please always re-read.</span></h3>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">If the issue&nbsp;has&nbsp;generated less than&nbsp;5 consecutive calls and/or the issue is with a low volume card processor: Euroshell, BP, or Amex; <span style=\"color: #ff00ff;\">skip steps 3 and 4</span> and continue at <span style=\"color: #ff00ff;\">step 5</span>.</span></h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step&nbsp;4</strong> - If current staffing is unable to handle the elevated call volume, <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=363\" target=\"_blank\">turn on the outage message</a>&nbsp;- Article 363<br />Activate Amarillo Outage Message on phone</li>\r\n<li>Activate UK Outage Message<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step&nbsp;5</strong> - <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=316\" target=\"_blank\">Send out an alert to all stations advising of the problem</a>&nbsp;- Article 316<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\">If updates become available, you will need to send an updated alert message&nbsp;and another message once the issue is resolved<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Step&nbsp;6 - </strong></span></span>If you are handling the outage without assistance from a UK on-call Analyst:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=367\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to access vendor contact information to report the identified issue.<br /><br /></a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Step&nbsp;7</strong> - If you are unable to reach a vendor (FIS, TNS, etc.) or a vendor has taken more than 30 minutes to reply to an inquiry concerning an issue, <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=312\" target=\"_blank\">contact on-call UK personnel. <br /><br /></a></li>\r\n<li><strong>Step&nbsp;8 -</strong> Close out the outage once resolved.<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=363#disable\" target=\"_blank\">Disable the outage message.</a></li>\r\n<li>Deliver beginning and ending dates and times, reason for outage, any further details gained to Debra.<br /><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=433\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to see an example of a wrap-up email.</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '2014-08-25 07:37:35', 'l7d23b', '2016-06-06 08:06:08', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on handling a UK vendor outage', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=364mailto:Debra.burnett@valero.com; martin.reynolds@valero.com; Jacqui.john@valero.com; john.mozie@valero.com; asif.rafique@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com; andrew.cox@valero.com; julie.lunnon@valero.com; karolyn.ross@valero.com; Keith.Evans@valero.com; Adele.Shackleton@valero.com?Subject=Initial - UK Outage Notification&amp;Body=This is initial notification of a severe incident that is currently impacting station trading. We are in the process of identifying the specific point of failure and will update once we have more information.mailto:Debra.burnett@valero.com; martin.reynolds@valero.com; Jacqui.john@valero.com; john.mozie@valero.com; asif.rafique@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com?Subject=Update - UK Outage Notification&amp;Body=Update to issue%3Aindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=363index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=316index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=367index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=312index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=363#disableindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=433'),
(291, 'Popup Blocker Guide', '<table style=\"height: 23px; vertical-align: top; width: 582px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: top;\">Windows</span>\r\n<p><a href=\"#ie6\">Internet Explorer 6</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#ie7\">Internet Explorer 7</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#ie10\">Internet Explorer 10</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#ff\">Firefox</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#gc\">Chrome</a></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: top;\">Mac</span>\r\n<p><a href=\"#mff\">Firefox</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#mm\">Mozilla</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#ms\">Safari</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; vertical-align: top;\">Toolbars</span>\r\n<p><a href=\"#yt\">Yahoo</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#mt\">MSN</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#at\">AOL</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#gt\">Google</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"ie6\"></a>Internet Explorer 6</h3>\r\n<p>How to disable Internet Explorer 6 popup blocker (Windows XP)</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Tools</strong> menu, select <strong>Internet Options</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/IE6_1.png\" alt=\"Windows\" width=\"343\" height=\"199\" border=\"1\" /><br /><br /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Privacy</strong> tab, uncheck <strong>Block pop-ups</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/IE6_2.png\" alt=\"Windows\" width=\"406\" height=\"459\" border=\"1\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"ie7\"></a>Internet Explorer 7</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Tools</strong> menu, select <strong>Internet Options</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/IE7_1.png\" alt=\"Windows\" width=\"343\" height=\"199\" border=\"1\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Privacy</strong> tab, uncheck <strong>Turn on Pop-up Blocker </strong>and click <strong>\"OK\".<br /></strong><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/IE7_2.jpg\" alt=\"Windows\" width=\"367\" height=\"454\" border=\"1\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><a id=\"ie10\"></a>Internet Explorer 10</h3>\r\n<h2 class=\"subtitle\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Turning off pop-up blocker completely<img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/8405713_f260.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"260\" height=\"328\" /></span></h2>\r\n<div id=\"txtd_24245250\" class=\"txtd\">\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">By default, the pop-up blocker in Internet Explorer 10 is <strong>automatically activated. </strong>It may be possible to bypass the pop-up blocker by simply holding the CTRL button when clicking a link. However, it\'s easy enough to take the extra step and deactivate pop-up blocker in Internet Explorer completely. All you\'ll need to do is click a small check box in the Privacy tab under Internet Options.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>To disable pop-up blocker in Internet Explorer 10:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Click the Internet Explorer icon on the desktop to open the program.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Tools button in the toolbar at the top of the browser window.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Internet Options from the Tools menu.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Privacy tab in the Internet Options pop-up window.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Clear the check mark next to \"Turn on Pop-Up Blocker\" so that it is deselected (see Figure 1).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click OK.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Modifying pop-up blocker settings</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/8405721_f260.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"260\" height=\"331\" /></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Rather than turn off pop-up blocker completely, you may want to make minor changes to the Internet privacy settings so that pop-ups are only blocked for certain sites. This is also easy to do using the Internet Options menu in the browser.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"modfloat full\">\r\n<div id=\"mod_24245775\" class=\"module moduleText color0\">\r\n<div id=\"txtd_24245775\" class=\"txtd\">\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Before you modify settings, it\'s important to realize that Internet Explorer does not automatically block all pop-ups. For example, sites from the local Intranet are not blocked since the browser assumes they pose no risk to the user. Therefore, you may find that the sites you want to enable pop-ups for are already included on the default list.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">To see a list of sites currently enabled by Internet Explorer, you\'ll need to access the Pop-Up Blocker Settings from the Internet Options menu.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>To access the Pop-up blocker settings:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Open up Internet Explorer and click the Tools button in the top toolbar.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Internet Options, then click the Privacy tab.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Settings button next to Pop-Up blocker (see Figure 2).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the URLs of sites you wish to allow pop-ups for in the text box (see Figure 3).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click Close, and then Apply.\r\n<div class=\"floatclear\"><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/8405724_f260.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"260\" height=\"282\" /></div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div id=\"img_desc_8405726\" class=\"caption_half\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;<hr /></div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<h3 class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;<a id=\"ff\"></a>Firefox</h3>\r\n<p class=\"caption_half\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div class=\"caption_half\">\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Click the menu icon <img src=\"upload/ff0.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"40\" height=\"31\" />&nbsp;and&nbsp;click <strong>Options <img src=\"upload/ff00.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"62\" height=\"62\" /></strong><br /><br /><br /><img src=\"upload/ff2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"746\" height=\"597\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Click the <strong>Content</strong> tab on the left and then click the <strong>Exceptions</strong> button to the right of the Pop-ups checkbox. Leave<strong> Block pop-up winodws</strong> checked.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/ff3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"746\" height=\"638\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Type in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">valero.com</span> and click <strong>allow<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/ff4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"746\" height=\"638\" /><br /><br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Save Changes<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/ff5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"746\" height=\"638\" /></strong><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><a id=\"gc\"></a>Chrome</h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>To see blocked pop-ups for a site, follow the steps listed below:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If pop-ups have been blocked, you\'ll see the <img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/chrome_95472_alert.gif\" alt=\"blocked pop-up alert\" width=\"24\" height=\"22\" /> icon in the address bar. Click the icon to see a list of the blocked pop-ups.</li>\r\n<li>Click the link for the pop-up window that you\'d like to see.</li>\r\n<li>To always see pop-ups for the site, select \"Always show pop-ups from [site].\" The site will be added to the exceptions list, which you can manage in the Content Settings dialog.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>To manually allow pop-ups from a site, follow the steps below:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Click the Chrome menu <img class=\"null\" title=\"Chrome menu\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/SNP_9721C573E41777FBA43E1498AD084E3B160C_2696434_en_v2.png\" alt=\"Chrome menu\" width=\"29\" height=\"29\" /> on the browser toolbar.</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Settings</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Show advanced settings</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>in the \"Privacy\" section, click the <strong>Content settings</strong> button.</li>\r\n<li>In the \"Pop-ups\" section, click <a href=\"https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/3123708\"><strong>Manage exceptions</strong></a>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Allow all pop-ups</h3>\r\n<p>You can allow all pop-ups by disabling the pop-up blocker. Follow these steps:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Click the Chrome menu&nbsp;<img class=\"null\" title=\"Chrome menu\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/SNP_9721C573E41777FBA43E1498AD084E3B160C_2696434_en_v2.png\" alt=\"Chrome menu\" width=\"29\" height=\"29\" /> on the browser toolbar.</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Settings</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Show advanced settings</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>in the \"Privacy\" section, click the <strong>Content settings</strong> button.</li>\r\n<li>In the \"Pop-ups\" section, select \"Allow all sites to show pop-ups.\" Customize permissions for specific websites by clicking <a href=\"https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/3123708\"><strong>Manage exceptions</strong></a>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3 class=\"module moduleImage\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3 class=\"module moduleImage\"><a id=\"mff\"></a>Firefox (Mac)</h3>\r\n<div class=\"module moduleImage\">\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Firefox</strong> menu, select <strong>Preferences</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/FirefoxMac_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"403\" height=\"298\" border=\"1\" />&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Preferences </strong>window, choose the <strong>Content</strong> button and then uncheck <strong>Block Pop-up Windows</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/FirefoxMac_2.jpg\" alt=\"firefox\" width=\"403\" height=\"298\" border=\"1\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"module moduleImage\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3 class=\"module moduleImage\"><a id=\"mm\"></a>Mozilla (Mac)</h3>\r\n<div class=\"module moduleImage\">\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Mozilla</strong> menu, select <strong>Preferences</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/MozillaMac_1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"431\" height=\"228\" border=\"1\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>From the <strong>Privacy &amp; Security</strong> tab, choose Popup Windows. Uncheck <strong>Block unrequested popup windows</strong>, and click \"OK\"<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/MozillaMac_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"644\" height=\"476\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"modfloat right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3 class=\"modfloat right\"><a id=\"ms\"></a>Safari (Mac)</h3>\r\n<p class=\"modfloat right\">From the <strong>Safari</strong> menu, make sure <strong>Block Pop-Up Windows</strong> is unchecked.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/Safari_1.png\" alt=\"safari\" width=\"282\" height=\"300\" border=\"1\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"modfloat right\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"modfloat right\"><a id=\"yt\"></a>Yahoo Toolbar</h3>\r\n<div class=\"modfloat right\">\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Locate the Popup blocker icon and click the down arrow.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/Yahoo1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"418\" height=\"27\" border=\"1\" /><br /><br /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Uncheck <strong>Enable Pop-Up Blocker</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/Yahoo2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"232\" height=\"216\" border=\"1\" /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"txtd\">For more information on the Yahoo toolbar please go to <a href=\"http://toolbar.yahoo.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://toolbar.yahoo.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p class=\"txtd\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"txtd\"><a id=\"gt\"></a>Google Toolbar</h3>\r\n<div class=\"txtd\">\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Click on the Google logo on the Google toolbar and select <strong>Options.<br /></strong><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/Google_1.png\" alt=\"google\" width=\"278\" height=\"110\" border=\"1\" /><br /><br /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Uncheck <strong>Popup Blocker</strong>, and then click <strong>OK</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/Google_2.png\" alt=\"google\" width=\"446\" height=\"576\" border=\"1\" /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>For more information on the Google toolbar please go to <a href=\"http://toolbar.google.com/\" target=\"_blank\">http://toolbar.google.com</a>.</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><a id=\"at\"></a>AOL Toolbar</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Locate the Popup blocker icon.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/AOL_1.png\" alt=\"msn and aol\" width=\"448\" height=\"29\" border=\"1\" /><br /><br /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Click on it until it says <strong>Allowed</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/AOL_2.png\" alt=\"msn and aol\" width=\"433\" height=\"26\" border=\"1\" /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><a id=\"mt\"></a>MSN Toolbar</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Locate the Popup blocker icon and click the down arrow.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/MSN_1.png\" alt=\"msn and aol\" width=\"536\" height=\"27\" border=\"1\" /><br /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Check <strong>Allow Pop-ups</strong>.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/popups/MSN_2.png\" alt=\"msn and aol\" width=\"197\" height=\"111\" border=\"1\" /></li>\r\n</ol>', '2014-08-26 06:10:46', 'l7d23b', '2015-08-04 09:29:59', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on popup blockers for most browsers', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '#ie6#ie7#ie10#ff#gc#mff#mm#ms#yt#mt#at#gthttps://support.google.com/chrome/answer/3123708https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/3123708http://toolbar.yahoo.com/http://toolbar.google.com/'),
(292, 'Settlement Issue Troubleshooter', '<p><img src=\"upload/settlementtroubleshooter.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"467\" /></p>', '2014-09-06 16:00:08', 'l7d23b', '2014-09-06 16:00:08', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Settlement Issue Troubleshooter', '', 80007, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '');
