(293, 'UK Heat Usage Guide', '<p>Article Menu<a id=\"top\"></a></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=290#heatboard\" target=\"_blank\">Opening a Heatboard</a>&nbsp;(external article)</li>\r\n<li><a class=\"null\" href=\"#search\">Searching Heat</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#directaccess\">Opening an existing ticket</a></li>\r\n<li><a class=\"null\" href=\"#workingtickets\">Working with tickets</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#managing\">Managing Tickets</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Call Records</h2>\r\n<p>A Call Record (sometimes referred to as a Call Ticket) is comprised of the collective information about an individual issue. When a Call Record is created, the Call Log form opens, enabling you to document the caller and issue. Shortcuts keys are available to facilitate form data entry. A Call Record is made up of five forms (sometimes referred to as records) that are tabbed for easy access. Each form (or record) is stored as a table in the database. An Attachments tab is also displayed, allowing you to attach files to the Call Record.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a class=\"null\" href=\"#callLog\">Subset Form </a>- Appears at the top of the window and remains there regardless of which form is activated below it. The Subset contains profile data for the currently open Call Record.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#callLog\">Call Log Form </a>- Designed to give you an overview of the Call Record and provide the current status of the call.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#assignment\">Assignment Form </a>- The form in which you assign the issue to the party responsible for resolving the matter. There are three steps involved in Assignments: Assigning, Acknowledging, and Resolving. A Call Record can contain multiple Assignments.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#journal\">Journal Form </a>- Intended primarily as a memo field with room to record notes about the Call Record. A Call Record can contain multiple Journal entries. Reviewing these entries in chronological order is an effective way to understand the progress made on an issue.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"#attachment\">Attachments tab </a>- Use the functionality on this tab to attach files to the Call Record.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Searching Heat<a id=\"search\"></a></h2>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Each of the following fields validate against their respective entries in the database. You can enter data to any of the fields and hit the Tab key to perform a quick search.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/validFields.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"578\" height=\"122\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4 style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Using Wildcards</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">If you need to search using wildcards, use the % symbol.&nbsp;This can be performed from any of the validation fields.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;<img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/wildExample.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"317\" height=\"168\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Example: A search containing %HQ in the Postal Code field will return the following results:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/wildExampleRes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"318\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;\">The result set contains all Postal Codes <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">ending</span> in HQ. If you need to search the beginning of a field, the wildcard is not required. To search the middle of a field, surround the search phrase in percent signs: %searchstring%.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;\">To select a station in the result set, simply double click the entry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Using Simple Search</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Simple search is available from every field in heat that will accept a text input.&nbsp; <br /><br /><span style=\"color: #993366;\">Unlike the validation search, simple search will return tickets instead of sites.</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>To access simple search, right-click on any text field and select \"Simple Search\" from the menu.<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Simple search will use the currently selected field to search with and you will be presented with the following dialogue box.<br /><br /><img class=\"null\" style=\"align: center;\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/simpleSearch.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"531\" height=\"248\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>For standard searches, leave the operator as \"like\" and type in your search term in the \"Value\" box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click Run.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If entries were found you will have a new call group with your results.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/simpleSearchRes.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"384\" height=\"52\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">This search result (underlined in red)&nbsp;is from running a simple search on the solution description box looking for the word \"raised.\"</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">To navigate the ticket results, use the buttons highlighted below.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/callGroupNav.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"108\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Working With Tickets<a id=\"workingtickets\"></a></span></h2>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">When Heat opens you will be presented with the following screen:<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-left: auto; display: block; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/blankHeat.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"596\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;To access the sites and tickets you will need to hit <strong>Ctrl+N</strong> for a new ticket.<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-left: auto; display: block; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/blankHeatTkt.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"596\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 style=\"text-align: left;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Directly Accessing Tickets<a id=\"directaccess\"></a></span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">If you know the ticket number, you can use <strong>Ctrl+G</strong> on your keyboard or&nbsp;click the Jump button as illustrated below.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/jumpButton.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"406\" height=\"138\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Once you have this popup displayed, you can key in the ticket number and click OK.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/ctrlg.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"268\" height=\"114\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Once you\'ve opened an existing ticket, or populated a new ticket,&nbsp;the Heat window will look like this:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/callLog.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"778\" height=\"709\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ticket Subsets</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Heat separates major components of tickets by subsets.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/subsets.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"503\" height=\"23\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call Log\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contains the Problem Statement, call details, and completion information as seen below.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Detail\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Currently unused in the UK implementation.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Assignment\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provides the ability to assign tasks and tickets to yourself or other agents.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Journal\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contains all notes and updates to the ticket. This also includes old closing notes if the ticket has been reopened.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Web\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unused.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Attachments\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provides the ability to attach files to tickets.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Subset Navigation</strong></span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">A single menu is shared across all subset tabs.&nbsp;<br /><br />&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/journalNav.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"38\" /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Grid/Form View\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Toggles Between&nbsp;the list of entries&nbsp;or individual entries<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>New Entry\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Adds a new subset entry<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Abandon Record\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Abandons current journal entry data<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>First Journal Record\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shortcut: <strong>Ctrl + Shift + Page Up</strong></li>\r\n<li>Moves to the first record of the list<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Previous Record\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shortcut: <strong>Ctrl+ Page Up</strong></li>\r\n<li>Moves backwards 1 record<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Next Record\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shortcut: <strong>Ctrl + Page Down</strong></li>\r\n<li>Moves forwards 1 record<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Last Record\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shortcut: <strong>Ctrl + Shift + Page Down</strong></li>\r\n<li>Moves to the last record. (Most current)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Log Subset<a id=\"callLog\"></a></strong></span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">The Call Log form is common to all Customer Types and is designed to give an overview and the current status of the call. When you create a new Call Record, a blank Call Log form displays.</p>\r\n<div class=\"Normal\">&nbsp;<br /><img style=\"margin-left: auto; display: block; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/callLogSubset.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"743\" height=\"255\" /></div>\r\n<div class=\"Normal\">&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><br /><br />Call Log Form Fields</strong></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"Normal3\">Incident Log and Solution Information - These two fields are used to record the customer-described problem and the final solution. Entries provide a general understanding of the call.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />Call Status - The Call Status automatically defaults to Open when you create a new Call Record. Some other values for this field may include:<br /><br /></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"Normal3\">Closed - Triggers a system-generated stamp in the Closed By fields with the appropriate Call Logging user and date/time entries.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li class=\"Normal3\">Reopened - With appropriate rights, you can reopen a closed call. The previous closed information can remain, or you can move it to a Journal entry.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"Normal\">\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Record Type / Call Type / Category - Provides a way to classify the type of problem a customer is experiencing and is used extensively for reporting purposes. This value is used to determine which associated Detail form displays in the adjacent tab. You must provide a value in the Call Type field to save or close the call.<br /><br /><br /><br />\r\n<table class=\"null\" style=\"padding-left: 30px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Record Type:&nbsp;</span></strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Problem&nbsp;</span></strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Call Types:</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Comms</span></td>\r\n<t