1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Settlement Info</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Uncaptured Sale</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">VCS Billing Questions</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br />\r\n<table class=\"null\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Record Type:&nbsp;</span></strong></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Setup&nbsp;</span></strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Call Types:</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">UK RAMS Change</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Categories:</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Change of Owner</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Comms Deprovisioning</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Comms Provisioning</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td class=\"null\" style=\"border-bottom: 1px solid black;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt; font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-serif;\">Refresh - Gempay Install</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Priority - Often set to automatically populate using a default value, depending upon the Call Type selected. High or low relative urgency values (1 = highest priority) are preset but can be redefined according to business needs. The priority description auto fills when the priority is selected.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Tracker- Defaults to the current Login ID. You can use this value to identify the person responsible for the call.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Resolution Code / Cause Code - Allows the user to classify the solution. The Call Type you select determines the values that are available in the Cause drop-down list. The list of causes are established in a validation table for each Call Type. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Received By - This cluster of three fields (UserID, Date, and Time) indicates exactly when the Call Record was created. The values are automatically stamped according to the user Login ID and the date/time from the user&rsquo;s computer.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Updated - The last update that occurred to any of the Call Record forms is automatically system stamped into the Login ID, Date, and Time fields. Changes to a Call Record normally indicate someone is actively working on the call. Good call management may utilize these values for operational tracking of client responsiveness and staff performance.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Closed By - Similar to the Received by field cluster in that it uses automatic, system-stamped values upon closure of the Call Record. Note that Date and Time fields are used extensively to calculate call durations and other parameters.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"color: #993366;\">Note: Right-click the Call Log tab (or grid) to access shortcuts to commonly-used commands.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span><hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Assignment Form<a id=\"assignment\"></a></strong></span></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>The Assignment subset provides the ability to assign tasks and tickets to yourself or other agents.</p>\r\n<p>You can have multiple Assignments within one Call Record. This many-to-one relationship capability allows you to track delegated tasks. One person may not always be able to resolve an issue, in which case each assignee would have an Assignment within the Call Record. Use the Navigation arrow buttons at the bottom to view various Assignments. In addition, the grid view displays a list of all the Assignments for the Call Record. There are three stages to an Assignment: Create, Acknowledge, and Resolve.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Create a New Assignment</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">If the call taker cannot resolve an issue, it can be assigned to someone else to resolve. Depending on your protocol, you may assign a Call Record based on workload, knowledge, experience, or location. HEAT allows you to assign a Call Record to more than one group or technician, with each resolving a designated portion of the issue. Each Assignment and its associated assignments become part of the Call Record. This is especially useful when used in conjunction with the Resolve Assignments In Order option.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">To Assign a Call Record</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In an active Call Log form, select File&gt;Assignment/Journal&gt;New Assignment; or click the Assignment tab, right-click in the background of the Assignment form, and select New Assignment. The Assignment form automatically opens and fields in the Assignment Created By section of the Assignment header auto-fill with current Call Log information.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>From the Group drop-down list, select the appropriate group.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Contact field, select one of the listed contacts. Information about the technician such as Availability, Out of Office, Phone/Ext, Pager, and Email auto-fills the fields.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Comments field, type any comments or instructions about the Assignment.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select File&gt;Save Call Record.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>To assign this Call Record to another group or technician, right-click and select New Assignment. Repeat steps 2 through 5.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolve an Assignment</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">When you resolve an Assignment, you can record the resolution in the Call Record. Resolving an Assignment does not close a Call Record.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">If your system administrator has set the Enforce Acknowledge Before Resolve right, you are required to acknowledge the assignment before resolving it. If your system administrator has enforced that assignments be resolved in order, you must resolve assignments in chronological order. Assignments that must be resolved in order are identified by the active Resolve Assignments in Order icon in the Status bar.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">To Resolve an Assignment</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select File&gt;Go to Call ID. The Go to Call ID dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Type the Call ID of the appropriate Call Record, then click OK. The Call Record opens to the Call Log form.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Assignment tab. The Assignment form displays.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Resolve link. The Enter Value dialog box opens.<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note: You can also use shortcut keys to resolve Assignments: press Ctrl+Shift+F2. The Resolve Required Fields dialog box opens, prompting you to enter the Resolution and TotalAsgnmntTime (Time Spent field). Select each in turn, and click Edit Call, which places your cursor in the field to be updated. Then proceed to step 7.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Click Validate. The Validate from Resolve dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the appropriate resolution code, then click OK. On the Enter Value dialog box, click OK.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Comments field, type any additional information about the resolution.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select File&gt;Save Call Record.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>View Assignments</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">One Call Record can have multiple Assignments. The best way to view a comprehensive list of these Assignments is in grid view. Each row in the grid represents one Assignment for the selected Call Record. If you double-click an Assignment from the grid view, that Assignment displays in form view.<br /><br />In the grid view, you can drag and drop the column headers to re-sort the information. You can also drag and drop a column header to the area below the tabs (labeled Drag a column header here to group by that column), enabling you to sort and collapse information.</p>\r\n<p><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">To View Assignments in Grid View</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select File&gt;Go to Call ID. The Go to Call ID dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Type the Call ID of the appropriate Call Record, then click OK. The Call Record opens to the Call Log form.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Assignment tab.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select View&gt;Grid, or click the Grid/Form button in the toolbar at the bottom of the screen, which will toggle between grid and form view.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the grid view, all Assignments for the Call Record are listed. Double-click the Assignment you want to view. The selected Assignment displays in form view.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Note: In grid view, you can review the Assignments for an entire Call Group by using the navigation arrows on the toolbar.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Available Assignment Groups</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>UK Retail Technology\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contains members of UK Retail Technology Group\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Asif Rafiq</li>\r\n<li>Jacqui John</li>\r\n<li>John Mozie</li>\r\n<li>Martin Reynolds</li>\r\n<li>Neil Ralph<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>UK Vendor\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contains UK Vendors\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>BT Faults</li>\r\n<li>BT Service Center</li>\r\n<li>HTEC</li>\r\n<li>TNS UK<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>WS Tech Support\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contains all&nbsp;members of Valero Tech Support</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-left: auto; display: block; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/assignmentSubset.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"761\" height=\"388\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Journal Subset<a id=\"journal\"></a></strong></span></h4>\r\n<p><strong>Working with the Journal Form</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">The fourth Call Record tab displays the Journal form. This form is intended primarily as a memo field providing an area to document the chronological progression of the call resolution.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Like the Assignment form, the Journal form also has a many-to-one database relationship for each Call Record. Typically, you would create a Journal entry for each conversation and every major task you perform on behalf of the customer toward issue resolution. It is most helpful to display the Journal entries in chronological order, providing an organized view of the sequence of events performed to resolve the call. Options for displaying Journal entries in a specific order are found in the Call History section of user preferences (<strong>Edit&gt;User Preferences&gt;Grid Settings Tab</strong>).</p>\r\n<p>By selecting <strong>Edit&gt;User Preferences&gt;Grid Setting Tab</strong>, you can choose options for the Journal form:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Select the default view (Grid or Form) for Journal entries.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose a field used for the sort-order preference.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Choose ascending or descending for the sort order.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Grid lines can also be activated or disabled in the grid view.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Journal Form Fields</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Journal Created By - When a new Journal entry is created, the user ID, date, and time values are automatically populated in the Journal header.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Journal Type - The list of predefined Journal Types. The Journal Type field is validated, and you must add each new Journal Type to the validation table. This can be done by adding the record on the fly or in Table Maintenance.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Journal Entry - The body of the journal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Create Journal Entries</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">After the initial call, you should document follow up contacts or actions regarding an issue in the Journal form.</p>\r\n<p>To Create a Journal Entry:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select <strong>File&gt;Go to Call ID</strong>. The Go to Call ID dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Type the Call ID of the appropriate Call Record, then click <strong>OK</strong>. The Call Record opens to the Call Log form.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Journal tab.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>File&gt;Assignment/Journal&gt;New Journal Entry </strong>or <span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong>CTRL+J</strong></span>. An empty Journal form displays.<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note: HEAT automatically fills in the user, date, and time in the Last Modified area located in the Journal Information title bar.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>In the Journal Type drop-down list, select the correct type.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once&nbsp;the journal window is exited, the entry will automatically save and become non editable.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>View Journal Entries</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">One Call Record can have multiple Journal entries. The best way to view a comprehensive list of these entries is in grid view. Each row in the grid represents one entry for the selected Call Record. If you double-click an entry from the grid view, that entry displays in form view.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">In the grid view, you can drag and drop the column headers to re-sort the information. You can also drag and drop a column header to the area below the tabs (labeled Drag a column header here to group by that column), enabling you to sort and collapse information.</p>\r\n<p>To View Journal Entries in Grid View</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select File&gt;Go to Call ID. The Go to Call ID dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Type the Call ID of the appropriate Call Record, then click OK. That Call Record opens to the Call Log form.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Journal tab.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>View&gt;Grid</strong>, or click the Grid/Form button in the toolbar at the bottom of the screen, which will toggle between grid and form view.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In grid view, all Journal entries for the Call Record are listed. Double-click the entry you want to view. The selected entry displays in form view.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Note: In grid view, you can review the Journal entries for an entire Call Group by using the navigation arrows on the toolbar.<br />Abandon Journal Entries</p>\r\n<p>You can abandon an <strong>unsaved</strong> Journal entry.</p>\r\n<p>To Abandon a Journal Entry:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>With the Journal form open, select <strong>File&gt;Assignment/Journal&gt;Abandon Journal Entry</strong>, or click the <strong>Abandon Changes</strong> button.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Yes</strong> to confirm abandoning the changes to the current Journal entry.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Attachments Subset<a id=\"attachment\"></a></strong></span></h4>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">By default the subset will look like this when there are no attachments.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/attachmentBlank.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"781\" height=\"393\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">To attach files to a ticket, right-click in the whitespace of the Attachment subset and select Add Attachment</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/addAttachmentDiag.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"217\" height=\"209\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">The following box will be displayed. Click browse to locate your attachment.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/newAttach.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"501\" height=\"145\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Once your attachment is selected, click OK to add the attachment to Heat.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/attachmentWindowFilled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"501\" height=\"145\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">The Attachment subset will now look like this.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img class=\"null\" src=\"upload/articles/ukheat/attachment1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"777\" height=\"386\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;To access the attachment, double-click on the entry.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Closing Call Records</span></h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You can close a Call Record when the problem is resolved or otherwise becomes inactive. After you close records, you can track them to provide input for HEAT reports.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Close a Call Record</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In the Call Log form of a Call Record, type a description of how the issue was resolved in the <strong>Solution Description field</strong>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the Tab key to advance to the <strong>Resolution Code</strong> drop-down list. Select a resolution from the list.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Press the Tab key to advance to the <strong>Cause Code</strong> drop-down list. Select a cause from the list.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the close button at the upper-right of the <strong>Solution Description</strong> box.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #993366;\">Note: If you do not populate the required fields before closing, the Close Required Fields dialog box opens, listing the fields you must fill before you can close the call. Select Edit Call to populate those fields. You will also be prompted to fill in all fields required to save the Call Record, if those fields are still empty. Refer to \"Save Call Records\" for more information.</span></p>\r\n<p>When closed, the Call Status on that Call Record is changed to Closed. You cannot edit a closed Call Record without reopening the record. The Call Status would then change to Reopened.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Managing Tickets<a id=\"#managing\"></a></h2>\r\n<h3>Alarms</h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You can create an alarm and attach a Call Record to it to inform yourself of an urgent matter. Alarms either pop up or display in color in the Status bar.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Set an Alarm</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the Call Logging menu bar, select <strong>View&gt;Alarms</strong>. The Alarms dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>New</strong>. The Create Alarm dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If you want to attach the currently active Call Record to the alarm, select the Attach Current Call check box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Date field, select the date when you want the alarm to trigger (click the down arrow next to the Date field to activate the Date Selection tool, then select a date in the calendar).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Time scroll box, type or select the time when you want the alarm to trigger.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Subject field, type a brief subject for the alarm.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Note field, type the alarm message.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>OK</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Set Display Options for the Alarm</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Select<strong> Edit&gt;User Preferences&gt;SupportMail Tab</strong>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To View and Edit an Alarm</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Select the alarm in the Alarms dialog box, then click Edit. The Edit Alarm dialog box opens, in which you can modify your alarm parameters.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Delete an Alarm</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Select the alarm in the Alarms dialog box, then click Delete.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Respond to an Alarm</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>The Alarm dialog box provides a number of options for responding to the alarm.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Disable - Stops the alarm from executing.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Snooze - Delays the alarm (for about 5 minutes).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Reset - Opens the Edit Alarm dialog box, enabling you to change the alarm settings.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Go to Call - Opens the Call Record linked to the alarm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Hot Lists</h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">A Hot List is a special type of Call Group for which Boolean expressions are not used to pull specific Call Records according to defined criteria. Instead, the calls in a Hot List are manually added to the group. Any call can be added, including Call Records with different Customer Types. Hot Lists appear alongside other Call Groups in the Open Call Group dialog box.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Create a Hot List</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Group&gt;Add Call to Hot List&gt;New Hot List</strong>. The Create Hot List dialog box opens.<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note: You can also open the Create Hot List dialog box by selecting <strong>Group&gt;Open Call Group</strong>, then click the<strong> New Hot List</strong> button.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>In the <strong>Name</strong> field, type a name for the new Hot List.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the <strong>Description</strong> field, type a description of the Hot List.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Save the Hot List to the <strong>Personal</strong>, <strong>Team</strong>, or <strong>Global</strong> view. If you click <strong>Team</strong>, select the appropriate team from the drop-down list. All users assigned to that team have access to the Call Group.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>OK</strong>. The current call is added to the new Hot List.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add Call Records to Hot Lists</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Adding a Call Record to an existing Hot List links that call with the Hot List, as it is recorded in the database, as well as with the Call ID number. This is important because it means you can add a Call Record to many Hot Lists at the same time.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Add a Call Record to a Hot List</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Make sure the Call Record you want to add to the Hot List is the currently active call.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Group&gt;Add Call to Hot List. A list of existing Hot List groups displays.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the appropriate Hot List group from the list. The currently active call is added to the Hot List.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Remove Calls from Hot Lists</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You can permanently remove the active Call Record from the active Hot List. This option is available only when the Hot List is the currently active Call Group. Use this procedure to remove Call Records from both Hot Lists and My Hot List.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Remove a Call Record From a Hot List</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Make sure the Call Record you want to remove is the currently active call.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select Group&gt;Remove Call from Hot List. The Remove Call From Hot List dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the Don\'t show this dialog box again check box if you do not want to be prompted with the warning in the future.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click OK. The Call Record is permanently removed from the Hot List.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Delete Hot Lists</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">You can delete a Hot List if you are given security rights to do so by the HEAT administrator. Use caution when deleting a Hot List. Once a Hot List is deleted, you cannot restore it unless you recreate it.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #993366;\">Note: You cannot delete My Hot List.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To Delete a Hot List</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Group&gt;Open Call Group</strong>. The Open Call Group dialog box opens.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the view containing the Hot List you want to delete: <strong>Personal</strong>, <strong>Global</strong>, <strong>Team</strong>, or <strong>All</strong>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select the Hot List you want to delete.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Delete</strong>.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Yes</strong> to confirm the deletion. The Hot List is deleted from the list in the Open Call Group dialog box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Close</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"color: #993366;\">Note: This action deletes a Hot List Call Group, not the Call Records contained in the Hot List.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\"><a href=\"#top\">Return to top</a></span></p>', '2014-09-10 10:50:30', 'l7d23b', '2014-10-13 12:24:57', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on using and navigating UK Heat', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=290#heatboard#search#directaccess#workingtickets#managing#callLog#callLog#assignment#journal#attachment#top#top#top#top#top#top#top#top#top#top#top#top');
INSERT INTO `article` (`artid`, `arttitle`, `artbody`, `createstamp`, `usercreate`, `modstamp`, `usermod`, `pubflag`, `rfcflag`, `comment`, `usercomment`, `commentstamp`, `summary`, `triggers`, `chainid`, `rolename`, `encflag`, `linkdoctext`) VALUES
(294, 'Gempay Patch Information 9/16/14', '<ol>\r\n<li>Changes made to the AMC module to use remove the printing of the \'zero\' totals on the EOD printouts reverted EFT slips to Standard Font if the terminal is configured for Standalone and F75 linked.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to AMC module so the Pin pad idle message now states \'Please insert card\' if the terminal is stand-alone.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to AMC module to introduce a \'cancel\' message for the Indigo RetPOS if cancel button pressed when idle.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to the EFT module to change wording on EFT slips from \'I confirm that I received the goods...\' to \'Please debit my account.\'<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to EFT module to print the Star Rewards helpdesk number.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to EFT module to allow Split Payments.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to EFT Module to add a message on the POS screen if OPI linked saying \'Awaiting PIN Entry\' when terminal displays the PIN prompt.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to F75 module to correct issue initialising VBI POS .<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to F75 module to reduce the number of retries for sending transaction results .<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to Fuel Card module to Fix the issue causing some of the failed trickles to not go into the offline store (only into the general store, so they were sent only at resubmission.)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Changes made to Star Rewards module to not print the incorrect information on the ticket regarding the last balance update date and the points balance if not provided by the host. Added additional logging around the manual amount and volume entry and cap the product amount for manually entered loyalty transactions (non POS-linked.)</li>\r\n</ol>', '2014-09-16 09:13:25', 'l7d23b', '2014-09-16 09:14:28', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Patch information on gempay systems', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(295, 'Handling Wright Express Returns', '<p>n the room next to the accounting department (where the accounting printer is located), there are two Omni VX570 devices. The Wholesale Technical Support Department uses the Omni VX570 <strong>closest to the door</strong>.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>To process a refund on a Wright Express card, you will need the following information:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Card #, Expiration Date, Driver #, Vehicle #, Odometer #<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>On the Omni, select &ldquo;<strong>Refund/Return</strong>&rdquo;. Press the button next to that option to select it.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;<strong>Credit</strong>&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>WEX card #</strong> leaving off the &ldquo;690046&rdquo; at the beginning of the card number. Press &ldquo;Enter&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>expiration date</strong> (MM/YY). Press &ldquo;DONE&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the <strong>Vehicle #</strong>. Note: <strong>This has to be an 5 digit #, so you may need to enter a &ldquo;0&rdquo; prior to the driver # if it is only a 4 digit #</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Omni will ask for the &ldquo;<strong>Sequence #</strong>&rdquo;. Leave this field blank and press &ldquo;DONE&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The pin pad attached will prompt you to enter the following information. Enter all of this information and press the green button &ldquo;Enter&rdquo; on the pinpad on each one once entered:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Driver #</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Odometer #<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>product code # 400</strong>. Press &ldquo;DONE&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Leave the <strong>Refund Product #</strong> Press &ldquo;Done&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>dollar amount of refund</strong>, ex. &ldquo;80.00&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Omni will prompt you to enter tax amount, <strong>leave this blank</strong> and press &ldquo;DONE&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Omni will then give you a final screen showing &ldquo;<strong>REFUND</strong>&rdquo; at the top of the screen and the dollar amount. Press &ldquo;DONE&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once the Omni has completed the refund, it will say &ldquo;<strong>Please tear off receipt and give to customer</strong>&rdquo;. Tear off this receipt and press &ldquo;DONE&rdquo;.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Omni will then print out another receipt that is typically for the store. <strong>Tear this receipt off</strong> and press &ldquo;DONE&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Print a copy of your HEAT ticket and staple the receipts to the ticket and place in Staci Martinez&rsquo;s box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Submit an accounting adjustment request in Reflex to charge site for refund.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-09-17 14:39:33', 'l7d23b', '2014-10-09 12:30:08', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Handling WEX returns', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(296, 'Canadian Postal Codes Accepted at U.S. Gas Pumps', '<p align=\"left\">U.S. customers enjoy the convenience of paying at the pump for their fuel purchases using their zip code to help authenticate their identity. Effective 17 October 2014 Canadian customers that travel to the U.S. can enjoy this convenience as well by entering their postal code when prompted at U.S. pumps.</p>\r\n<p>Address Verification Service allows unattended terminals, such as gas pumps, to check a Visa&reg; cardholder&rsquo;s zip code with the card issuer. When prompted for a 5-digit numeric ZIP code at the pump, Canadians simply input the three numbers from their Canadian postal code, followed by two zeros.</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"null\" href=\"upload/AVS-Eh.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The full communication from Visa can be found here.</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-09-18 16:24:32', 'l7d23b', '2014-09-18 16:24:32', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Canadian Zip AVS', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(297, 'Information on EBT Payment Processing', '<p>If a station calls to inquire on processing EBT cards over the Valero network, please advise the following:</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>We are currently exploring the possibility of offering EBT card processing but no program is currently in place to process EBT cards.&nbsp; </em></strong></p>', '2014-09-24 08:11:42', 'l7d23b', '2014-09-24 08:11:42', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on EBT Payment Processing', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(298, 'UKCS Support Mailbox Setup', '<p>In Outlook, click the <strong>Tools</strong> menu and select <strong>Account Settings...</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/tools.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"229\" height=\"427\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once the <strong>E-mail Accounts</strong> window is open, select the <strong>Microsoft Exchange</strong> entry and click <strong>Change...</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/acctbox.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"623\" height=\"509\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the <strong>Change E-mail Account</strong> window, select <strong>More Settings...</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/change.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"634\" height=\"478\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On the <strong>Microsoft Exchange</strong> window, click the <strong>Advanced</strong> tab.</p>\r\n<p>Click the <strong>Add...</strong> button on the <strong>Advanced</strong> tab.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/advbox.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"354\" height=\"439\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In the <strong>Add Mailbox</strong> window, key in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">UKCS</span> and click <strong>OK</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/addbox.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"250\" height=\"134\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <strong>Microsoft Exchange</strong> window will now look like this. Click <strong>OK</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/advboxdone.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"354\" height=\"439\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On the <strong>Change E-mail Account</strong> window, click <strong>Next</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/changedone.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"634\" height=\"478\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Click <strong>Finish</strong> on the completion screen.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/vcsbox/finish.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"634\" height=\"478\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The new mailbox will be at the bottom of your <strong>Mail Folders&nbsp;</strong>list under <strong>Mailbox - UKCS.</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #993366;\"><strong>Warning: You will need to restart Outlook if you receive an error message stating the mailbox could not be accessed.</strong></span></p>', '2014-09-30 12:24:09', 'l7d23b', '2017-09-28 09:24:36', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to add the UKCS Support Mailbox to Outlook', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(299, 'UK Settlement Guide', '<p><strong>Sample Settlement Statement Guide</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a class=\"null\" href=\"upload/articles/documents/KP11%20Sample Valero Settlement Statement.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Click here for sample</strong></a></p>\r\n<p>The settlement reports replace the site polling report sent out by ATOS. Published on Monday every week, they provide details of all transactions taken on the site for the previous week.</p>\r\n<p>Like the polling reports that this replaces, the settlement report is vital to understanding the following:</p>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Transactions that have gone through the site<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When the transactions were taken<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When the settlement host received the transactions<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Settlement dates</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The settlement statement is also a vital tool for reconciling payments from the banks and other card issuers.</p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>1. Headings</h2>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/uksett/ukset1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"726\" height=\"126\" /></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p>The reports are explicit and include the site number and customer number, transaction date and settlement date, transaction count, etc. The settlement date and transaction date are vital for reconciliation. The transaction date (blue arrow above) tells the site the date the transaction was taken, whilst the settlement date is the day the transaction was actually settled. It is possible for transactions to be taken on the same day and <strong>*settled</strong> (* i.e. the day the transaction files are submitted to the bank/card issuers for payment in the agreed format, T+3) on different days, especially where the site performs end of day at different times of the day, or where there was a swap-out of the terminal without the end of day message to the host.</p>\r\n<p>The table below shows an example of transactions taken on different days with different settlement dates:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/uksett/ukset2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"604\" height=\"522\" /></p>\r\n<p>Site number is 123456, and the customer number 900001. The settlement file for the 13<sup>th</sup> (purple arrow) includes files for the 11<sup>th</sup> and 12<sup>th</sup> of September (see attached statement on appendix 1).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Hints</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Check the transaction dates on the settlement report and ensure the transaction totals are accurate.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Check payments against settlement dates. These should align with payments into site account, subject to agreed payment schedules advised by the card issuers.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>2. Data Presentation:</h2>\r\n<p>The card payments are consolidated by acquirer and issuer type, and brand type:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/uksett/ukset3.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"627\" height=\"304\" /></p>\r\n<p>The BMS debit payments will include Maestro for instance, and the UK Fuel cards include Euroshell, Fastfuel, BP, Fleet One and Texaco the Business for instance.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Transaction date totals</em></strong> are arrived at by adding up all transactions taken on the day, and arriving at a count that includes total value taken on the day:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/uksett/ukset4.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"612\" height=\"127\" /></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Settlement date totals</em></strong> refer to the transactions settled on the day, not what was taken:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/articles/uksett/ukset5.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"126\" /></p>\r\n<p></p>\r\n<h2>3. Exclusions:</h2>\r\n<p>The settlement report does not include Starrewards transactions (from the 1<sup>st</sup> of October 2014).</p>\r\n<p>The settlement report will also not include local account card totals, which are not taken on VCS infrastructure.</p>', '2014-10-01 09:07:35', 'l7d23b', '2014-10-14 12:06:14', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on UK settlement statements', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(300, 'Credit Card Refunds', '<h1>Credit Card Refurnds/Reversals/Returns</h1>\r\n<p>Credit card returns take <strong>3-5 <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">business</span> </strong>days to post to the customer\'s account. Durning this time the customer nor their bank will be able to see the refund while&nbsp;in process.</p>\r\n<p>Remember to communicate to customers that when a return or a reversal is done to their card at a store, it will take <strong>3-5 <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">business</span> </strong>days for them to see it at their bank.&nbsp; <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Especially</span> if it crosses over a weekend or banking holiday.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Credit card refund process</h1>\r\n<p>One of the key reasons that a credit card refund takes as long as it does is the number of steps involved in the refund process. When you initiate a refund, as when you return merchandise to a store, the seller requests a refund by beginning a new transaction request on the credit card network. The card company must receive this information, check it against your purchase history, confirm the merchant\'s request, clear the refund with its bank and transfer the credit to your account. The credit card\'s billing department must then issue a statement that shows the refund as a credit, which serves as the final step in the process. Each step is an opportunity for delays due to human or computer error, or due to waiting for a billing cycle to elapse</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"headline3 head mg-3\">Timeline</h2>\r\n<p>According to the TaxAct website, credit card refunds can take anywhere from two to 30 days before they are complete. The first 24 to 48 hours of this period involve the initial refund with the credit card company. But credit card companies use major banks to supply the funds they lend to cardholders to make purchases, which means that the credit card\'s policies as well as the bank\'s policies can delay the refund.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"headline3 head mg-3\">Billing Cycle</h2>\r\n<p>Customer billing cycles also control how long it takes to receive news of a credit card refund. For example, if you have an account that ends on the 29th day of each month, you may receive your card statement on the 5th day of the next month. If you return merchandise on the 30th, it will be the first transaction on your statement for the next billing cycle. In other words, five days after making the return you\'ll receive a statement that will not list the refund, though it will list the initial purchase. Your refund will appear on your next statement, which you\'ll receive 35 days after the date of the return. If you have online account access, you\'ll be able to see the refund as soon as it\'s processed instead of waiting for the next statement to arrive.</p>', '2014-10-15 07:11:56', 'l7d23b', '2014-10-15 07:12:11', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on credit card refunds', '', 50006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(301, 'ADSL Filter Information', '<p>TNS will ask at times to change the ADSL Line Filter.&nbsp; Please note that some Line Jack Units have the filter built in to the socket and do not have an external ADSL Filter.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/filter.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"515\" height=\"386\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Line Jack Unit Without Filter:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/lju.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"703\" height=\"636\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Check with the customer if there is a filter in place or if their Line Jack Unit has a socket that could take the RJ11 socket (smaller square&nbsp;connecter as visible on the filter picture above)&nbsp;on the Line Jack Unit.</p>', '2014-10-15 09:41:16', 'l7d23b', '2014-10-15 12:33:34', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on ADSL filters for Digi routers', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(302, 'VCS Additional POS and Terminal request process', '<p><strong>Request for additional POS: Retailer action</strong></p>\r\n<p>When a retailer acquires an additional POS, he will need a new terminal. The expectation is that the retailer raises a helpdesk ticket for:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>HTEC to supply a new terminal, and</li>\r\n<li>To have that terminal linked to the POS</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong><em>Please note</em></strong>: It is the retailer&rsquo;s responsibility to arrange the POS install date, and this is also at Retailer&rsquo;s cost. However soon as we are informed of the POS install date, it is VCS responsibility to arrange for terminal preparation and supply, and engineering support for the POS/Terminal linking.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Ordering the terminal: VCS action:</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>HTEC will be asked to provide the terminal and also provide the terminal ID.</li>\r\n<li>HTEC will also be asked to confirm engineering support on the date of POS install; this request will include instructions to HTEC on the type of link to terminal the site requires: OPI or F75.</li>\r\n<li>The request to HTEC for engineering support must allow a clear 5 days before the install date.</li>\r\n<li>The Valero analyst must also inform TNS of the new terminal, and where the link is OPI, the new POS IP address. This is vitally important because TNS will need to update the router config with the till and terminal information, or order a new router for the site. Allow between 5 and 7 days for this.</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Informing Barclays and FIS: VCS action</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Additional Terminals are almost treated like new site setups. Barclays and FIS should be told what the new terminal ID is:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Send email to the Barclays Account team quoting site name and MID</li>\r\n<li>Confirm when the installation will be completed</li>\r\n<li>Request Barclays to set the TID live against the MID</li>\r\n<li>FYI to FIS, quoting Valero site reference</li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Relevant Email addresses:</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>HTEC engineering request: <a href=\"mailto:InstallationRequest@htec.co.uk\">InstallationRequest@htec.co.uk</a></li>\r\n<li>HTEC TID request: <a href=\"mailto:InstallationRequest@htec.co.uk\">InstallationRequest@htec.co.uk</a> and <a href=\"mailto:callreg@htec.co.uk\">callreg@htec.co.uk</a></li>\r\n<li>TNS router update: <a href=\"mailto:jbarton@tnsi.com\">jbarton@tnsi.com</a></li>\r\n<li>Barclays: <a href=\"mailto:Paula.Jones@barclaycard.co.uk\">Paula.Jones@barclaycard.co.uk</a></li>\r\n<li>FIS: <a href=\"mailto:ccshelpdesk.uk@fisglobal.com\">ccshelpdesk.uk@fisglobal.com</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Additional POS</strong></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Request for additional POS will go into the VCS helpdesk</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Retailer will arrange for the POS installation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The VCS helpdesk will make the following assessments of the request and decide what support the retailer needs:</li>\r\n<li>Does the retailer need an additional terminal or terminals?</li>\r\n<li>Will the POS be OPI linked? If yes to A and B, raise a call with HTEC</li>\r\n<li>If the POS will be OPI- linked to the terminal, this will potentially require additional IP addresses on the router, or where the router cannot be configured, a new router:</li>\r\n<li>Helpdesk should put a request into TNS and allow up to 7 days</li>\r\n<li>Raise a call with HTEC for support</li>\r\n<li>Inform the retailer of process, timescales and costs</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Billing impact of additional POS and Terminal:</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>As mentioned earlier the retailer arranges and pays for the POS installation. There are however other billing outcomes that kick in at the deployment of an additional terminal:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Terminal supply: Valero will supply the terminal and Pinpad at no additional cost</li>\r\n<li>However, the additional terminal will attract a change to the scheme fee. VCS billing must amend the number of terminals and apply the additional VCS bill at the installation of the terminal. The request for additional terminal and deployment date should be copied to <a href=\"mailto:VCSbillingenquiries.GMB@valero.com\">VCSbillingenquiries.GMB@valero.com</a>, as a trigger to amend RAMS, and <a href=\"mailto:retailsupport@valero.com\">retailsupport@valero.com</a> to trigger VCS contract update.</li>\r\n<li>The HTEC engineer&rsquo;s visit to install the additional terminal (mostly on non-HTEC POS sites) will be charged back to the retailer as well&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Appendix 1: VCS charges:</strong></li>\r\n<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Fixed Charges</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p><strong>No of Terminals</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p><strong>Static Scheme Fee per month</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p>1</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p>&pound;95</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p>2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p>&pound;135</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p>3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p>&pound;170</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p>4</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p>&pound;205</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p>5</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p>&pound;240</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p>6</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p>&pound;275</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"153\">\r\n<p>7</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"215\">\r\n<p>&pound;310</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>*VCS engineering and service charges:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>*</strong>This section has been added for information purposes mostly, to assist with choosing appropriate costs that may apply either for installation of equipment, or replacement costs when lost, or at retailer exit from the service.</p>\r\n<p>For the purposes of additional POS and terminals, we should apply the costs as appropriate.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2014-10-16 07:00:04', 'dottij', '2016-04-29 09:31:56', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'VCS Additional POS and Terminal request process', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:InstallationRequest@htec.co.ukmailto:jbarton@tnsi.commailto:Paula.Jones@barclaycard.co.ukmailto:ccshelpdesk.uk@fisglobal.com'),
(303, 'Known Micros/Gempay Issues', '<h2>Issue 1</h2>\r\n<p>Description: When taking Star Rewards loyalty and fuel cards the retailer is prompted by the POS to swipe the card and on doing so receives an error.</p>\r\n<p>Solution: Even though the POS is prompting the cards need to be swiped on the Gempay. This is a training issue and would have been explained at the time of the Gempay installation.</p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>Issue 2</h2>\r\n<p>Description: Terminal freezes at the end of a transaction after swiping Star Rewards loyalty card.</p>\r\n<p>Solution: This is again a training issue and would have been explained at the time of the Gempay installation. The retailer needs to wait until the POS message advising that it is sending the loyalty prompt to the terminal is complete. Just waiting an additional second will resolve this issue. Note that this applies to both card and cash transactions.</p>', '2014-10-16 07:46:07', 'dottij', '2014-10-17 06:29:11', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Known Micros/Gempay Issues', '', 80007, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(304, 'UK Ticket Documentation', '<h2>Ticket Creation and Handling</h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Ticket Creation</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">When dealing with UK issues, please remember to only include <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">one</span> issue per ticket. If the site is calling in on multiple issues, open separate Heat tickets for each one.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Problem Statement</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Please enter a description of the issue the station is calling about only. Troubleshooting steps are entered in the solution description.</span><br /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Correct usage of&nbsp;the Problem Statement field.&nbsp;</span><br />&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/ukheatprob.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"371\" height=\"170\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Solution Description</h3>\r\n<p>For UK calls, the Solution Description field will be used as a way to report the \"Current Status\" of the ticket. This will serve to&nbsp;improve the reporting capabilities of Heat.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">All troubleshooting questions and steps <strong>must be documented </strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">and</span> have their corresponding answers or results documented as well.</span></p>\r\n<p>When working with new or existing tickets, enter the action you\'re taking in a <strong>journal&nbsp;entry</strong> and&nbsp;copy that to&nbsp;the <strong>Solution Description</strong> field following a date stamp. Ex: Raising a ticket with HTEC, reporting a fault with&nbsp;TNS,&nbsp;or&nbsp;waiting on an <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">immediate</span> callback from the staton.</p>\r\n<p>We ask that you keep the date stamp uniform and use the example below in green.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/solutiondescfilled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"368\" height=\"92\" /></p>\r\n<p>A typical solution descripton of a ticket:</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 401px; height: 5px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"373\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">30-June: Advised this might be because of the terminal replacement and the 2nd one wasn\'t able to be included. </span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">30-June: raised w/ htec incase there is something they need to do w/ the terminal they replaced.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">1-July: HTEC updated the site last night and are monitoring.&nbsp; Will contact the site for update. Called Gina who advised that the reconciliation report only shows one TID still.&nbsp; Updated Metro and asked HTEC to call site to investigate further. Emailed FIS to release funds on the slave terminal 25582106.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">2-July: Gina called back stating she hadnt heard from anyone yet on this. Looks like the Htec ticket was unable to get a hold of anyone at 9pm last night. I gave her the htec ref and the phone # as she wanted to contact them directly.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">2-Jul Fix applied, site to test and advise. Monitor till tomorrow.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">3-Jul. HTEC confirm the autmatic EOD worked last night. Comms between the two terminals was faulty and has now been resolved. Confirm.</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">3-Jul: Site will watch and we will discuss on Monday</span><br /><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">6-Jul: The automatic EOD is still not working. Take this up with the HTEC dev team and recall the terminal logs.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Ticket Closure</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Please stay diligent to keep open UK tickets to a minimum. All open UK tickets are monitored daily. It will be your responsibility to follow up or assign the ticket to the appropriate person.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If a call has been closed for more than a week you must open a new ticket rather than re-open the previous call.</span></li>\r\n</ul>', '2014-10-17 10:33:11', 'l7d23b', '2015-07-06 14:23:48', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instructions on ticket creation and handling for UK calls', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(305, 'UK Fuels Credit Requests', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>UK Fuels&rsquo; Credit Requests</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If a site has taken a transaction for a card they are not authorised to accept they can send a request for payment to UK Fuels as per the instructions below:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Send a copy of the receipt and an invoice for the invalid transaction in question:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>FAO James Cooper</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>UK Fuels Limited</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>Eurocard Centre</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>Herald Park</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>Herald Drive</em></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>Crewe CW1 6EG&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>UK Fuels will then make the decision on whether or not to credit the retailer. From a Retail Technology point of view we need to raise a request with HTEC to disable the ISO in question from the terminals.</p>', '2014-10-29 04:49:02', 'dottij', '2014-11-05 08:50:19', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Payment information for non authorized cards', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(306, 'Indigo and HydraPOS Issues', '<p>As a reminder, please do not log any HydraPOS or Indigo till issues with HTEC. You will need to refer retailers to the following numbers.</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>For HydraPOS issues:&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>08448567553&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>For Indigo issues:</td>\r\n<td>08448567584</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2014-10-31 10:02:51', 'l7d23b', '2014-10-31 10:03:47', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Contact number for Indigo and HydraPOS issues', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(307, 'Valero Fleet Portal', '', '2014-11-05 08:44:10', 'l7d23b', '2014-11-05 08:44:10', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on using the Valero Fleet Portal', '', 40008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(308, 'Valero Self Service (VSS)', '<p>Technical support for all Valero Internet sites will be&nbsp;provided by&nbsp;our department (phone and email).</p>\r\n<p>We currently support Jobbers and dealers on the Wholesale Portal and we have access to the Fleet online system, but the Consumer Self Service system is new to us.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Troubleshooting</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the customer is unable to sign into the Valero Self Serve website for their credit card, verify they are signing into on the correct page at <a href=\"http://www.valero.com\">www.valero.com</a>.&nbsp; Some customers will attempt to sign into the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Business Partners</span>\" sign-in, however, <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">this is incorrect</span>.&nbsp; The \"Business Partners\" sign-in is for our stations and jobbers.&nbsp; Valero credit card customers will need to click on the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Login Here</span>\" button located on the<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> left side of that same page</span></strong>.&nbsp; This will direct them to the credit card sign-in page for their credit card account.&nbsp;<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/vss-sign-in.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"165\" /></li>\r\n<li>If they are on the correct sign-in page, they may not be able to sign-in due to a&nbsp;pop-up blocker being active.&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=291\" target=\"_blank\">Article @291</a> in Reflex provides detailed instructions on how to disable those blockers in most of the environments you may encounter today.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Please do not modify any customer Firewall settings without getting approval from Israel, Karey or David</span>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>We will update the article as we discover new environments and solutions. If you are handling a different (new) type of issue not covered in the article, take good notes and if you are unable to resolve, escalate accordingly, first to your supervisor, then to someone &nbsp;in the IS Area (on call; schedule and contact numbers on the wall above David&rsquo;s phone).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Noting the Valero account</strong></p>\r\n<p>When a&nbsp;request for assistance&nbsp;is received concerning issues with VSS on a Valero credit card account, you will need to create a note on that customer\'s account in <strong>RAMS</strong> with your findings and the end result.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Depending on how the request was received will determine what kind of call cause code and entry type you will use.&nbsp; These codes and entry types including the following:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use</span><strong> NOTE</strong> </span>for emails</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Use</span><strong> ICAL </strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">for phone calls. </span></span>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>For <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">consumer accounts&nbsp;</span>use call cause code &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SELF</span></strong>&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>For<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> Fleet/Commercial accounts&nbsp;</span>use call cause code &lsquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>ONLN&rsquo;&nbsp;</strong></span></li>\r\n<li>Example ICAL:&nbsp;\"ICAL &ldquo;SELF&nbsp;&nbsp; Walked customer through the process to disable the pop up blocker in their Safari browser and transferred customer to queue #### to resolve the additional issue of&hellip;&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Transferring back to customer service for questions not pertaining to VSS support</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>When you receive a call from customer Support service, with a warm transfer or a dropped (cold) call in the queue, you may assume the customer&rsquo;s identity and rights to the account have been verified.&nbsp; Notes on the customer&rsquo;s account should bring you up to speed on the current issue.&nbsp; You can also assume that most of the customer&rsquo;s general maintenance issues have been handled too.&nbsp; If a new issue arises, however, during your conversation, you may need to transfer the customer back to their appropriate queue for additional account maintenance support after you have resolved their technical issue.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Advise the customer of the transfer back to customer service and the possible additional hold time.&nbsp; If they refuse, offer to send an e-mail.&nbsp; If they opt for the email:</p>\r\n<p><strong>For Consumer accounts:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Address an email to AMA-Mailteam (<a href=\"mailto:amamailteam@Valero.com\">amamailteam@Valero.com</a>)</li>\r\n<li>In the body include:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>SUBJECT LINE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>VSS Follow-up</em></li>\r\n<li>BODY OF EMAIL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em>Acct Name, Caller Name, Acct No and Phone No</em></li>\r\n<li><em>A brief description of what other needs the customer is requesting.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>For Fleet and Commercial accounts:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Address an email to rcscfleet</li>\r\n<li>In the body include:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>SUBJECT LINE&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>VSS Follow-up</em></li>\r\n<li>BODY OF EMAIL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Acct Name, Caller Name, Acct No and Phone No</em></li>\r\n<li><em>A brief description of what other needs the customer is requesting.</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Otherwise for a transfer (warm preferred (bring the answering agent up to speed), cold (drop the call in the queue if no one answers and you find yourself in the announcement loop).</p>\r\n<p><strong>For Valero Consumer accounts transfer to:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>4601 to the&nbsp; IVR for phone payments,</li>\r\n<li>5052 for simple maintenance and questions,</li>\r\n<li>5053 (Spanish) for simple maintenance and questions,</li>\r\n<li>5054 for more complex issues (collections, disputes, account status, etc.) or</li>\r\n<li>5055 for the Spanish queue for more complex issues.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>For Valero Fleet accounts, go ahead and handle anything that we are authorized to handle or:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Transfer back to the Fleet Queue (#5047).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>For EMAIL</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Same as by PHONE, above, but you will most likely need to contact the customer depending on the needs included in the email.</p>', '2014-11-05 08:48:48', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-13 12:23:48', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Valero Self Service support', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=291mailto:amamailteam@Valero.com'),
(309, 'Cornerstore Conversions', '<h3>Heat Changes</h3>\r\n<p>Due to the conversions, Heat has been modified and we will be unable to search for sites using the store number in the <strong>Store</strong> field in Heat. The store field will now have the jobber/dealer number for ALL sites, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">including</span> non-converted&nbsp;CST sites.</p>\r\n<p>You still have the ability to search other fields to locate the station. Please be aware the station name will change with the converted stores. When attempting to locate a station you may see multiple entries in heat.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/valeroconvert.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"768\" height=\"73\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Communications</h3>\r\n<p>Most sites will be using a prysm. Follow standard setup procedures when working with technicians to cut-over the sites.</p>', '2014-11-12 10:51:45', 'l7d23b', '2014-11-12 10:54:07', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on CST to Wholesale coversion sites', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(310, 'New Cornerstore Giftcards', '<p>New bin range for these cards will be: 603225010x</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/newcstgcfront.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"387\" height=\"500\" /><img src=\"upload/newcstfcfront.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"387\" height=\"500\" /></p>', '2014-11-12 13:45:59', 'l7d23b', '2016-02-29 14:34:27', 'lmvzw9', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'New Cornerstore Giftcards', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
