(312, 'UK On Call Process', '<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/alert2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"27\" />&nbsp;Please remember, on-call times are from 9am - 5pm GMT (3am - 11am CST)&nbsp;during the following days.<br />&nbsp; During business hours: M-F&nbsp;8am - 5pm GMT&nbsp;(2am - 11am CST) John Mozie ( <span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">07825 402 780</span></span><span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;)</span>&nbsp;will be the outage contact.&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #000000;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">After speaking with the emergency on call, please contact <strong>Debra Burnett</strong> at <strong>806 206 3606</strong>.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>In the first instance please call 2297 (01646 649297) / </u></strong><a href=\"mailto:VTOC@valero.com\"><strong>VTOC@valero.com</strong></a><strong><u>&nbsp; for the 24 hour Valero I/S helpdesk who will contact the on-call person if required.</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>If the issue is urgent and you are unable to get an answer you can also try 2298. In the rare event of a critical system being down, a terminal is unable to operate or if you are unable to raise the VTOC, please call Pembroke Security (+44 (0) 1646 649331) so they can alert the UK on call person.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Do not call the on-call mobile directly unless you have called the VTOC first</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><u>&nbsp;</u></p>\r\n<p>For any urgent issues</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call 2297 (+44(0)1646 649297)&nbsp;&nbsp; (or London: 3333/4444 or +44(0)207 513 3333)</li>\r\n<li>If not answered, leave a clear message about your urgent problem, including your name, location and the full phone number at which you can be contacted.&nbsp; Do not leave just an extension number.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The agent will call you back.&nbsp; If you do not receive a call back in what you consider an appropriate amount of time, you can also email <a href=\"mailto:VTOC@valero.com\">VTOC@valero.com</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em>Non-urgent issues outside of office hours should be reported to the helpdesk on the next business day between 08:00 and 17:00</em>.</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>UK Regional I/S On Call </u></strong><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n<table width=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"208\">\r\n<p><strong>Date</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"132\">\r\n<p><strong>Name</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"180\">\r\n<p><strong>Contact&nbsp; No.</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"208\">\r\n<p>From 08:00hrs 21<sup>st</sup> &ndash; 08:00hrs 26<sup>th</sup> December</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"132\">\r\n<p>Dom Edwards</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"180\">\r\n<p>+44 (0) 7770 475912</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"208\">\r\n<p>From 08:00hrs 26<sup>th</sup>&ndash; 08:00 31<sup>st</sup> December</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"132\">\r\n<p>Ian Remnant</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"180\">\r\n<p>+44 (0)7469 379301&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"208\">\r\n<p>From 08:00hrs 31<sup>st</sup> Dec &ndash; 08:00 hrs 4<sup>th</sup> January</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"132\">\r\n<p>Martin Reynolds</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"180\">\r\n<p>+44 (0)7469 379301&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>Links for On-Call person</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>For SME information, please refer to SME On Call contact list.</p>\r\n<p>Please check the procedures and the previous on-call summaries which are very likely to have solutions for issues that have happened before</p>\r\n<p><strong>Procedures can be found in </strong>\\\\nasukpmrf01\\Group\\Information Technology\\Procedures</p>\r\n<p>Previous on call email summaries can be found in the PEM Helpdesk inbox On Call folder (for instructions on how to add this to Outlook Click Here)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Contact numbers can be found in </strong><strong>UK IS Contact Information</strong><strong> in </strong>\\\\nasukpmrf01\\Group\\Information Technology\\On Call</p>\r\n<p>If you are unsure what the issue or solution is after checking the procedures and on call summaries, call the SME at the earliest possible opportunity, even if it&rsquo;s only for advice.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Martin Reynolds&nbsp;- <strong>07472 779 553</strong> or <strong>07768 294 201</strong></span></p>', '2014-11-24 05:18:57', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-21 08:16:54', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information for UK on call process', '', 80006, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:VTOC@valero.commailto:VTOC@valero.com');
