(315, 'RAMS / FAMS Payment Processing', '<p>When a customer now&nbsp;makes a payment to be processed/dated for the current date, it will immediately reflect in the account balance. This means the customer no longer has to wait until the system processes the payment to have those funds to become available.</p>\r\n<p>Unfortunately, at this time, this updated process <strong><em>DOES NOT</em></strong> include <strong><em>AUTOPAY</em></strong> payments. Those enrolled in AUTOPAY must wait until the payment is posted in RAMS..</p>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If a customer gives you a phone payment <strong><em>dated</em></strong> today, the amount of the payment will be released and available immediately.</li>\r\n<li>If a customer &nbsp;gives you a post-dated phone payment for Friday (11/28), the payment will reflect in the account balance on Friday at (12:01 am).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>FYI:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Payments made after business hours, holidays or weekends, will be available on the release date. &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Due to the immediate availability of funds, we should not have to issue TCLs for same day payments.</li>\r\n<li>The <strong>GTOT</strong> and <strong>AVCR</strong> commands will reflect current date payments.</li>\r\n<li>All unposted payments other than (autopay) will appear in the UNP field and the TX Screen. It will also appear in the PAY field in red. Because a payment will appear in both fields, please don&rsquo;t confuse with multiple payments being made. &nbsp;See screenshot below.</li>\r\n<li>This change is for both RAMS and FAMS.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2014-12-02 07:45:46', 'l7d23b', '2014-12-02 07:47:59', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how account payments are made in RAMS/FAMS', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(316, 'UK Outage - VCS Alert Procedure', '<p>\r\n<script>// <![CDATA[\r\njQuery(document).ready(function($) {\r\n    updateCountdown();\r\n    $(\'.message\').change(updateCountdown);\r\n    $(\'.message\').keyup(updateCountdown);\r\n});\r\n\r\nfunction updateCountdown() {\r\n    // 140 is the max message length\r\n    var remaining = 140 - jQuery(\'.message\').val().length;\r\n    jQuery(\'.countdown\').text(remaining + \' characters remaining.\');\r\n}\r\n// ]]></script>\r\n</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">How to send an alert</span></h3>\r\n<p>To send the alert you will need to establish a remote desktop connection to <strong>PEMWIN7VM05.</strong> This can be done a few different ways.</p>\r\n<p>Method 1:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"O:\\AMA-UK\\WTS\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to access</a>&nbsp;the folder containing a pre-configured remote desktop icon that will connect directly to <strong>PEMWIN7VM05</strong>. You can either drag the icon to your desktop or access it directly from the folder.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password for the account is <strong>Xp0BgNo#<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Click OK and Log On.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Method 2:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On your desktop click on your windows button.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the search type &ldquo;Remote&rdquo; and then select &ldquo;Remote Desktop Connection&rdquo; under the programs section.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Computer dialogue, type in <strong>PEMWIN7VM05 </strong>and click connect.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The username for the account is <strong>SVC0426</strong><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password for the account is <strong>Xp0BgNo#<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Click OK and Log On.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once Logged on you will see the following Icon on the desktop.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/alerticon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"79\" height=\"74\" /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Open Outlook on the desktop (<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">If Outlook is not open the Send SMS&nbsp;function will fail</span>).&nbsp;</span></h2>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Double Click this to launch the tool.<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>When you open the file it will automatically load the data required from SID (Site Information Database). This will pre-populate the contact email addresses and cell phone numbers in to the spreadsheet.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Select \"VCS Alert\" from the available options on the page that loads.<br /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Click the<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong> VCS Alert</strong> </span>button<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/alert-buttons.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"319\" height=\"278\" /></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #333399;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The Alert text box has a Maximum entry of 160 characters and, as you see, has an indication of the amount of characters next to the send button.</span><br /><br /><img src=\"upload/alertbox.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"528\" height=\"287\" /><br /><br /></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3><strong>System outage message templates - <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Copy and paste these messages as necessary.</span></strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Template 1: Confirmation of affected service and impact</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>We are experiencing an outage affecting transactions on xxxx cards. We are working with (named supplier) to resolve this update to follow.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Template 2: Update on the incident &ndash; use this after an&nbsp;hour and a half if not resolved</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>We continue to work with (named supplier) to solve the issue affecting transactions on xxxx cards.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Template 3: Confirmation that the issue has been resolved</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>The issue reported earlier has now been resolved and all Texaco sites should now be able to take card transactions.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Template 4: Confirmation that the issue is localised and on-going, with no end date in sight</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Please be aware that TNS have advised of an on-going network issue affecting sites in the (Insert area, post code or area code) area. Please ignore if this is not applicable to your site.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">Confirmation that the message has been sent:</span></h3>\r\n<p>After you have sent the email, please check the VCS Support mailbox. In the inbox should be a copy of the message that you have sent.</p>\r\n<p>If there is no message in the Inbox, please check the Drafts folder as there may be an issue in resolving an email or SMS number that is preventing the message from being sent.</p>\r\n<p>To correct this open the email from the drafts folder and perform a &ldquo;Ctrl &amp; K&rdquo; this is a keyboard shortcut for resolving the email addresses. The email address that is causing a problem will come up in dialogue box indicating that it has been unable to resolve. Locate this email address in the BCC field (you may have to go to options on the menu bar of the email and select BCC to make visible) and delete. This email address has been imported from the Site Information Database (SID) with errors. Please make a note of this email address and send and email to VCS Support with the email address in question so it can be corrected.</p>\r\n<p>Once you have corrected this issue press send on the email.</p>', '2014-12-22 08:47:00', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-12 12:58:50', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on sending a mass alert for UK outages/issues', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'O:\\AMA-UK\\WTS'),
(317, 'TNS Cease Orders', '<p>TNS cease orders will need&nbsp;to be signed by Andrew Cox. If a cease order is received from TNS in our group we must make sure the costs are for no more than 13 months. At that time&nbsp;Beth will need to get the order to Andrew for a signature.</p>', '2015-01-08 07:15:43', 'l7d23b', '2015-01-08 07:15:43', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Procedural Information on TNS cease orders', '', 80002, 'UK Support 2', 'N', ''),
(318, 'Gempay Software Release Package 1.0.7.6', '<p><span class=\"tier1\">Retail Technology has worked with HTEC to build package enhancements to the Gempay software in order to address some of the known issues as well as introduce changes to the existing and new card products. The following fixes and enhancements are included in this software release:</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Enhancements:</em></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Star Rewards</strong> Add validation to Star Rewards to link volume and spend to loyalty points and suppress printing the retailer copy of the Star Rewards receipt.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Shell CRT Card </strong>Add the Shell CRT fuel card range to the Valero fuel card scheme.</li>\r\n<li><strong>AllStar Chip and PIN </strong>Implement Chip and PIN on AllStar fuel cards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Fixes:</em></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Terminal Freezing Issues </strong>A fix to ignore card swipes on the POS during processing to prevent the terminal freezing.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Product Codes Data </strong>A fix to the product codes data sent to our transaction switching host, FIS, for AllStar Chip and PIN cards.</li>\r\n<li><strong>End of Shift Report </strong>A fix to change the printing pattern of End of Shift reports.&nbsp; If there is more than one shift during the day the last End of Shift report will be printed at the same time as the End of Day report.&nbsp; This will reduce paper waste.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Following vigorous tests the software is now ready to be piloted.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Deployment Approach</strong></p>\r\n<p>The deployment will be carried out as a phased approach commencing <strong>Monday 8<sup>th</sup> December 2014</strong> with <strong>six</strong> sites to run to the end of 2014 and through the first quarter of 2015. The remaining sites on the Valero estate will be deployed incrementally.&nbsp; Retailers at pilot sites will be contacted via email to advise when the software will be deployed to their sites.&nbsp;&nbsp; Following a successful pilot the software will be released to the remaining Valero estate.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Current</strong></span> pilot sites:</p>\r\n<table width=\"445\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>252510</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"381\">\r\n<p>QUEENS DRIVE SSTN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>886704</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"381\">\r\n<p>EDMONDS GARAGE</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>492266</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"381\">\r\n<p>AUTOLINE SERVICE STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>259801</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"381\">\r\n<p>V G MERCHANTS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>610857</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"381\">\r\n<p>NWF PEARCES</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>886830</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"381\">\r\n<p>PILTDOWN SERVICE STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width=\"280\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"61\">\r\n<p>887168</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"219\">\r\n<p>Kitchens</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"61\">\r\n<p>251208</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"219\">\r\n<p>Lenham</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"61\">\r\n<p>886621</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"219\">\r\n<p>Kilmington&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"61\">\r\n<p>257811</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"219\">\r\n<p>Shepton Mallet&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"61\">\r\n<p>251562</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"219\">\r\n<p>Elite Scotney</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"61\">\r\n<p>490534</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"219\">\r\n<p>Strensham NORTH</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"61\">\r\n<p>886495</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"219\">\r\n<p>Mangrove</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\