(319, ' VCS Telecoms Decommissioning Notice', '<p>Since Gempay deployment has completed,&nbsp;work is now being performed&nbsp;to cease or transfer all legacy telecoms lines on sites that were installed to originally&nbsp;support the Gemini solution.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&lt;div id=\"redblock\"&gt;The letter will be going out mid-week and is likely to generate additional calls from the retailers requesting an explanation.<br /><a href=\"upload/newsAssets/VCS Telecoms Decommissioning Notice V06 Mail Merge.docx\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to access the letter.</a>&lt;/div&gt;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In some cases, the retailers are likely to want to transfer the line into their own name as they are using it for other services and will disrupt their business if cancelled.&nbsp; In these cases the retailer will need to contact BT as described in the attached.&nbsp; In most cases BT will accept an email from us to the retailer giving permission for them to take ownership of the line.</p>', '2015-01-20 06:38:18', 'l7d23b', '2015-01-30 08:21:20', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on ISDN lines for Gemini system', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '\r\nValero Card Services16 January 2015Telecoms Decommissioning NoticeSite: MERGEFIELD Distributor_Name Distributor_NameSite No.: MERGEFIELD Site_Number Site_NumberSite: MERGEFIELD Address Address MERGEFIELD City City MERGEFIELD Province ProvincePost Code: MERGEFIELD Post_Code Post_CodeContact: MERGEFIELD Contact ContactTel:Email: MERGEFIELD Email EmailFollowing your recent installation of the Gempay terminals and associated telecoms infrastructure, a review of the telecoms lines at your site has been carried out which has identified the lines below. The new telephone line that has been installed at your site is solely to support Online Authorisation of your card acceptance solution.All lines listed below are the legacy lines that we hold on file for your site, which includes lines