(326, 'MFG MFL Overview', '<h2>VCS and MFG MFL Sites</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Valero Card Services enables Valero retailers to accept payment cards and ensure the secure processing and settlement of transactions<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In April 2015 78 Motor Fuels Limited (MFL) sites owned by the Motor Fuels Group (MFG) are joining the Valero network<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>MFL site names will be prefixed with the initials <strong>&ldquo;MFG&rdquo; or &ldquo;MFL&rdquo; </strong>in SID, RAM and Merlin<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>MFL sites will be using the Gempay 2 terminals as opposed to the Gempay 1 terminals currently used on the Valero estate<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The communications network at MFL sites is provided by <strong>Timico</strong> (Not TNS)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>All MFL sites will be using HTEC Indigo (RetPOS) tills and will be connected via OPI to the Gempay 2<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>FIS is the switching provider for all acquirers at MFG sites as per our standard setup</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><em><br />ALL Terminal, POS and Communications issues for MFG sites need to be logged with HTEC. </em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><em>TNS is </em></strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><em>not</em></strong></span><strong><em> involved in the MFL</em></strong><strong><em> communications</em></strong><strong><em> architecture</em></strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><strong><em>VCS Billing</em></strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>VCS Billing is based in Amarillo and deals with all VCS billing queries via a group mailbox<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VCS invoices include:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>VCS Scheme Fee <em>&pound;95 for a single POS site, &pound;135 for a two POS site; increases by &pound;40 per additional POS<br /><br /></em></li>\r\n<li>Credit Card merchant service charge<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Retailers can view, print and download their VCS invoices online via the E-Billing menu on Texaco &nbsp;&nbsp; Station:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Please note:</span> <br />At MFL sites, MFG Regional Managers will be granted access to read and download settlement reports for sites they are responsible for.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>VCS vs MFG MFL Site Support</h2>\r\n<table style=\"width: 835px; height: 370px;\" width=\"835\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #4f81bd;\" width=\"300\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #4f81bd;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><strong>Standard VCS</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #4f81bd;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><strong>MFG Sites</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>Terminal Type</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>Gempay 1</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>Gempay 2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>OPI Capability</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>HTEC HydraPOS</p>\r\n<p>Micros Iridium</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>HTEC HydraPOS</p>\r\n<p>Micros Iridium</p>\r\n<p>HTEC Indigo (RetPOS)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>Terminal Configuration</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>Two USB Hubs</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>One USB Hub</p>\r\n<p>One Mini-USB Hub*</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>Router Type</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>Digi WR44</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>Bintec</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>Communications Provider</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>TNS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>Timico via HTEC</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>POS Type</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>HTEC HydraPOS</p>\r\n<p>Micros Iridium</p>\r\n<p>Legacy POS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>HTEC Indigo (RetPOS)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>POS Support</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>Retailer&rsquo;s own</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>HTEC</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>Keyboards for Fuel Card Entry</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>UK Retail Technology</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px; background-color: #e9edf4;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>N/A</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"300\">\r\n<p>Billing</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"276\">\r\n<p>VCS Billing</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 257px; background-color: #d0d8e8;\" width=\"257\">\r\n<p>Combined VCS and Fuel Billing</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>MFG MFL Site Support<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/mfg/spider.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"636\" height=\"506\" /></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-04-09 08:35:09', 'l7d23b', '2015-04-09 08:43:29', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information for Motor Fuels Limited and Motor Fuels Group', '', 80002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(327, 'MFG MFL VCS Equipment', '<h2>Gempay 2 Terminal</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/mfg/gp2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"374\" height=\"503\" /><img src=\"upload/articles/mfg/gp2-pp.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"380\" height=\"503\" /></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/mfg/gp2on.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"378\" height=\"407\" /></p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Bintec Router</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/mfg/442982-routers-funkwerk-rs230a-5510000221.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"799\" height=\"195\" /></p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>MFG MFL Network Topology</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/mfg/topo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"802\" height=\"481\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-04-09 08:58:07', 'l7d23b', '2015-04-09 08:58:43', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information for Motor Fuels Limited and Motor Fuels Group Equipment', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(328, 'TNS EU Broadband Escalations', '<p><a href=\"upload/docs/EU Broadband Escalation Document.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">EU Broadband Escalation Document.pdf</a></p>', '2015-04-09 09:19:52', 'l7d23b', '2015-04-24 09:04:20', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'TNS EU Broadband Escalations', '', 80001, 'Administrator', 'N', ''),
(329, 'Wholesale Customer Portal Password Reset', '<p>IdM will provide Support Analysts the ability to clear security questions, unlock external accounts, and reset external account password for Wholesale Customer Portal users.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Navigating to IdM</h1>\r\n<p>IdM can be accessed by navigating to the Valero hope page, selecting \"Service Center\" at the top and selecting \"IDM Home\" under the Popular Destinations section on the lower right.</p>\r\n<p>Alternately, you can <a href=\"https://fipwd.valero.com/sap/bc/webdynpro/sap/zid_idm_home\" target=\"_blank\">click here to access IdM</a>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>New password guidelines</h2>\r\n<p>hen creating a new password, please choose one that cannot be easily guessed. Passwords that include your first name, last name, username, the company you work for, or words like &ldquo;password&rdquo; cannot not be used. Passwords must be at least eight (8) characters long and must meet 3 of the 4 requirements below:</p>\r\n<p>Include at least one(1) lower case character (a-z)<br />Include at least one(1) upper case character (A-Z)<br />Include at least one(1) number (0-9)<br />Include at least one(1) special character (#,$,@)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>How to Assist Users&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the IdM Homepage Under IdM Tools click on \"Helpdesk Screen\".<br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/idm/idm1.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"733\" height=\"543\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Search for the user who needs assistance<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Review the User information\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/idm/idm3.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"758\" height=\"383\" /></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><br /><br />Verify specific account information such as Name, Email Address, and Phone Number. Proceed to <strong>Actions</strong> when you are ready to move forward.</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">If any information needs to be updated or corrected, please send the request via <a style=\"color: #3366ff;\" href=\"help.valero.com\" target=\"_blank\">help.valero.com</a>&nbsp;to have the information corrected.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/idsearch-idm.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"802\" height=\"191\" /></p>\r\n<p>Some other changes in terms of the display of a user&rsquo;s account are that you will be able to view their XNET logon alias (under Login ID), last logon time (under Last Login), and the user picture will be a gold color instead of a blue signifying it is an external account.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1>Actions</h1>\r\n<p>There are&nbsp;2 options that you will be using for Wholesale Password Reset:<br /><br /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unlock External Account <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Reset External Account Password</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>UNLOCK EXTERNAL ACCOUNTS</h2>\r\n<p>If a user has locked their account due to bad password attempts you can unlock it using the tool in IdM under Actions.</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/idm/idm7.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"810\" height=\"146\" /></span></strong></span></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you click Unlock External Account you will receive confirmation and your task is complete.</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/idm/idm8.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"313\" height=\"116\" /></span></strong></span></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>RESET EXTERNAL ACCOUNT PASSWORD</h2>\r\n<p>Users often forget their password and may not remember their Security Questions to use the password reset tool, so they may call in for a password reset. You can reset the password by using the tool in Idm under Actions.</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><img src=\"upload/pwresetopt-idm.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"816\" height=\"98\" /></span></strong></span></strong></span></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you click Reset External Account Password you will receive confirmation and your task is complete.</p>\r\n<p><strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong><strong><span style=\"font-size: large;\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/idm/idm10.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"516\" height=\"77\" /></span></strong></strong></span></strong></span></strong></strong></p>\r\n<p>An email communication will be sent to the user to the address we have on file. The email will include a new temporary password.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Additional Resources</h2>\r\n<p>If you require help using the tool please contact one of following for assistance:</p>\r\n<p>Viraj Mehta&mdash;IS Wholesale Portal Support</p>\r\n<p>210-345-4601</p>\r\n<p>Carmen Leal&mdash;Data Security</p>\r\n<p>210-345-4370</p>', '2015-04-16 09:40:30', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-28 12:17:44', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Wholesale Customer Portal Password Reset', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'https://fipwd.valero.com/sap/bc/webdynpro/sap/zid_idm_homehelp.valero.com'),
(330, 'Portal Mobilization Project', '<p>The Portal Mobilization project will provide users with easier access to applications such as Allocation Viewer, MSR reports and general program content via their mobile devices (phones, tablets, etc). Mobilization functionality is being applied to both the Branded (distributor and dealer) and Unbranded portals.&nbsp; Also, the existing content has been redesigned and reorganized to accommodate the new mobilization format.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Important launch info:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Changeover date:</strong> Monday, April 20, at 8:00 PM central through Tuesday, April 21, 2:00 AM central<strong>. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The Portal will be unavailable during this time</span>.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Customers will be notified of the outage, the new mobilization functionality and the redesign via email, DTN messages as well as messages on the current Portal.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>New security protocol is also part of this project. <strong>The first time users log in after the changeover, they&rsquo;ll be prompted to update their Portal passwords.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>A user&rsquo;s guide is attached.&nbsp; It will be mailed to customers and posted on the Portal.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Users will need a browser of Internet Explorer 9 or higher</strong> to view the redesigned Portal. Other browser options include Google Chrome, Mozilla Firefox and Apple Safari, which can all be downloaded for free.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin: 5px;\" src=\"upload/alert5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" /><a href=\"upload/docs/Portal Training Guide BRANDED.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Portal Training Guide</a></p>', '2015-04-17 08:17:56', 'l7d23b', '2015-04-17 08:20:08', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Portal Mobilization Project', '', 40007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(331, 'Wholesale Customer Support', '<p>The Mail Team will be handling all Customer Relations issues that were being forward to San Antonio.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>For non-escalated issues such as cash price, rude clerks/employees, dirty bathrooms, car wash issues, pump issues, etc:</em></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Advise the customer you will forward their concern to the appropriate department and they will be contacted (screen prints are no longer needed).</li>\r\n<li>Send an email the Mailteam at <a href=\"mailto:customersupport@valero.com\">customersupport@valero.com</a>.</li>\r\n<li>In the subject line indicate the issue for example &ldquo;rude clerk&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Include the account number and customer&rsquo;s name in the body of the email.</li>\r\n<li>Document the issue with specific details in your ICAL.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>For escalated calls such as customer is extremely upset or they are claiming fuel damages:</em></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Connect the call to <strong>5990</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>Document the issue with specific details in your heat ticket.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions, see your Supervisor.</p>', '2015-04-17 14:15:53', 'l7d23b', '2015-05-21 09:01:48', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Wholesale Customer Support', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:customersupport@valero.com'),
(332, 'Contactless PINPads', '<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Performing a Contactless Transaction</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>If a transaction is below &pound;20. It will eligible for contactless payment, the transaction will be passed from the POS to the terminal in the usual way. The PinPAD message will change from &lsquo;Please Insert Card&rsquo; to &lsquo;Present Card&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>The Customer taps the symbol on the PinPAD with their payment card and it authorises. There will no PIN Prompt and the customer will not be required to be enter a PIN (Occasionally a random check of the PIN will take place)</p>\r\n<p>The purpose of a contactless transaction is speed, therefore there will be no Customer receipt printed. A receipt can be printed from the GemPAY on request</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Printing a Contactless Transaction receipt</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>A customer receipt can be printed on request to complete this action carryout the following</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press Menu key on the GemPAY (Middle button on top row)</li>\r\n<li>Arrow down to the Applications Option followed by Enter</li>\r\n<li>Arrow down to HappEFT Option followed by Enter</li>\r\n<li>Press Enter on Print Cless Cardholder Receipt</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Trouble shooting known issues </span></strong></p>\r\n<p>There is an issue where on occasions the terminal will fail to read a contact (chip &lsquo;n&rsquo; pin) card if the amount is below &pound;20. If this occurs request the customer leaves the card in the PinPAD and press the Cancel key on the terminal. This will cancel the transaction and pass the sale back to the POS. Press the EFT button on the POS and pass the sale back to the terminal, the card should now recognise the card and prompt for the PIN.</p>\r\n<p>On rare occasions if the above doesn&rsquo;t work after 3 attempts then press the Cancel key on the terminal. Reboot the terminal and try again once it is at the idle screen.</p>\r\n<p>The PinPAD displays &lsquo;please present one card&rsquo;. Request the customer ensure there are no other contactless cards or devices (such as phone) near the PinPAD</p>', '2015-05-01 05:07:43', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-04 08:06:06', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Contactless PINPads', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(333, 'Accepting Texaco Fuel Cards with PIN', '<p>The Texaco fuel cards will work exactly how they work now, except that there will be a requirement for the customer to enter a PIN number when prompted.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>The process:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/texpin.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"426\" height=\"498\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>With PIN:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Swipe card</li>\r\n<li>Enter vehicle registration and Odometer readings</li>\r\n<li>Prompt for PIN <strong>(only allows 3 attempts until card is blocked for 24 hrs)</strong></li>\r\n<li>Customer to enter PIN on the PIN Entry device/Card reader</li>\r\n<li>Finish</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Without PIN:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Swipe Card</li>\r\n<li>Enter Vehicle registration and Odometer readings</li>\r\n<li>Prompt for PIN &ndash; PIN number not known</li>\r\n<li><strong>Customer</strong> must press<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> cancel</span> on the terminal to default to signature</li>\r\n<li>Prompt for signature appears</li>\r\n<li>Customer to Sign</li>\r\n<li>Finish.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>NB: Signature Default is only active until July 1<sup>st</sup> 2015, thereafter PIN only function will be available</strong></p>', '2015-05-01 05:12:34', 'l7d23b', '2015-05-01 05:12:34', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Accepting Texaco Fuel Cards with PIN  Fastfuel and The Business cards', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '');
