(334, 'Gempay Software Release Package 1.1.0.1', '<p>We are piloting a new software release, <a href=\"upload/docs/Gempay Software Release 1.1.0.1  Plan-1.docx\" target=\"_blank\">Release Package 1.1.0.1</a>.&nbsp;&nbsp;This release contains the following fixes and enhancements:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Contactless</strong> A fix for the contactless payment functionality for the Gempay 1 terminal and contactless P5 PINpad.&nbsp; Customers will be able to pay via Contactless for transactions below &pound;20.&nbsp; Contactless transactions do not require a PIN (Unless a random security check is requested) and customer receipts are only produced on request.&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=332\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for article 332</a>&nbsp;for additional information.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Valero Fuel Cards PIN</strong> </span>Enable PIN for Valero fuel cards; Texaco FastFuel and Texaco the Business.&nbsp; Please note that this has previously been in pilot at four sites.&nbsp; Retailers were advised of this deployment by Karen Goane on 1<sup>st</sup> April.&nbsp; Until the 1<sup>st</sup> July all card transactions will default to signature if the customer doesn&rsquo;t know their PIN number. &nbsp;Sites have been provided with a counter top display advising customers of this change.&nbsp;&nbsp;The following documents have more information on this.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=333\" target=\"_blank\">Accepting Texaco Fuel Cards with PIN</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"upload/docs/Do u have yr PIN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PIN Flyer</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"upload/docs/PIN Fuels Cards Texaco Site Brief 1st April .docx\" target=\"_blank\">Letter to Dealer</a><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>FIS Settlement Data</strong> A fix to the file configuration for Texaco the Business and StarRewards settlement file build.&nbsp; This fix will be transparent to retailers; the main beneficiary is FIS.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The pilot will adopt a two-pronged approach which is described in more detail in the attached Plan document:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Continue to test the Value Fuel Cards PIN software from 5<sup>th</sup> to the 10<sup>th</sup> May at:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 758px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" width=\"585\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p><strong>No</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p><strong>Site Ref</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p><strong>Site name</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p><strong>POS Type</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>1</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>887083</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>Royal Blue Service Station</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Micros</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>2</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>887002</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>MORLEY SERVICE STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Hydrapos</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>3</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>887084</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>BRIDGE GARAGE</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Micros</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>4</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>251221</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>LANGTON GREEN S/STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Micros</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>5</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>492130</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>PASTURE ROAD F/STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Tokheim</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>6</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>492186</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>PENSARNAU FILLING STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td w