\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>16</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>886763</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>DYFFRYN SERVICE STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Casio</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>17</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>886999</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>BEATRICE SERVICE STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Micros</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>18</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>886998</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>ST ERTH SERVICES</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Indigo</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>19</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>887000</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>SCORRIER SERVICE STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Micros</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"64\">\r\n<p>20</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"71\">\r\n<p>886920</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"303\">\r\n<p>LLANINA FILLING STATION</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"148\">\r\n<p>Hydrapos</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>Re-commence the Contactless pilot on two sites.&nbsp; Following a successful review the pilot will be extended to a further 10 sites.&nbsp; The two initial sites are:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>253299 Lancashire Hill Service Station</li>\r\n<li>886399 Tates Crawley Service Station</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From a support point of view, you may be called with regards to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>PIN &nbsp;- PIN not known or has not been received by the customer, or PIN functionality is not working (Refer to &ldquo;<a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=333\" target=\"_blank\">Gempay PIN Process for Texaco Fuel Cards</a>&rdquo;)</li>\r\n<li>Contactless &ndash; Contactless functionality Is not working (Refer to &ldquo;Contactless on Valero Sites&rdquo;)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please Jacqui&nbsp;John or John Mozie if you have any further questions.</p>', '2015-05-01 05:24:26', 'l7d23b', '2015-05-01 08:19:36', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Gempay Software Release Package 1.1.0.1', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '\r\n   Gempay Software Release Plan for package 1.1.0.1Contents TOC \\o \"1-3\" \\h \\z \\u 1.Purpose PAGEREF _Toc418006227 \\h 12.Assumptions/Constraints/Risks PAGEREF _Toc418006228 \\h 12.1Assumptions PAGEREF _Toc418006229 \\h 12.2Constraints PAGEREF _Toc418006230 \\h 22.3Risks PAGEREF _Toc418006231 \\h 22.4Release Approach PAGEREF _Toc418006232 \\h 22.5Rationale PAGEREF _Toc418006233 \\h 22.6Release Strategy PAGEREF _Toc418006234 \\h 22.7Release Content PAGEREF _Toc418006235 \\h 22.8Release Schedule PAGEREF _Toc418006236 \\h 22.9Release Impacts PAGEREF _Toc418006237 \\h 32.10Key success Criteria: PAGEREF _Toc418006238 \\h 32.11Release Notification PAGEREF _Toc418006239 \\h 42.12Release Management PAGEREF _Toc418006240 \\h 4PurposeThis plan guides the release of the Gempay software enhancements developed by HTEC for use on Valero retail sites. This document refers to developments contained in release 1.1.0.1.This plan will include release strategy, pilot sites, roll back plan and pilot exit criteria.Assumptions/Constraints/Risks Assumptions The package contains a crucial fix and software being released into pilot:Fix for contactless for the Gempay 1 terminal and P5 PINpad.PIN for Valero fuel cards.File config fix for Texaco The Business and Starrewards settlement buildPackage Content:HAppEFT.01.00.04.0185.WW00Added a check for a Star Rewards Daily Volume Limit to perform the validation only if the value is &gt; 0 (meaning the check is enabled)HLibF75.01.02.00.0022.WW00Fixed sending a response back to the till in some specific failure scenariosAMC.01.24.02.0159.WW00Changed to stop ECR, ICC and TIME background tasks when Star Rewards card swiped in idle and also MAG task if key pressed in idleChanged to not start contactless pre-processing if ICC card is already insertedFixed sending a response back to the till in some specific failure scenariosFixed the issue causing terminal to occasionally open the main menu after the transaction (standalone terminals)Fuelcards_8583.01.02.00.0058.WW00Added PIN fallback to signature for TTB cardsChanged the Euroshell card verification to support CRT cardsAdded a support for DKV cardsChanged to send loyalty transaction for TTB cards automatically without prompting for a loyalty cardAdded a check for a Star Rewards Daily Volume Limit to perform the validation only if theThe software has also gone through an internal UAT by Valero and signed off by the Valero IS Change Advisory board as fit to go into pilot on Valero sites.ConstraintsThe software has been vigorously tested and presents no known risksRisksThere is a minimal risk that the software may behave differently in live than it did in testRelease ApproachThe  Release Plan provides an outline of activities necessary to ensure that the projects product is available for use by its end-users as originally planned.RationaleThe essence of the plan is to provide a managed and steadied approach to the deployment, and avoiding as much as practically possible, any incidents that may create new issues, or exacerbate existing issues on retail sites.Release StrategyThere is a 2-pronged approach to this release:Continue the testing on the Valero PIN for a further week on 20 sites between the 5th and 10th of May. Re-start pilot on the contactless PIN on 2 sites on the 5th of May, and review. The pilot will then be extended to a further 10 sites with varying technology after that.Release ContentThe release content is as detailed in this document and driven by Valero requirements.Release ScheduleThe schedule includes:The two contactless sites:Lancashire Hill 253299Tates Crawley 886399The additional sites that will form part of the PIN pilotNoSite RefSite namePOS Type1887083Royal Blue Service StationMicros2887002MORLEY SERVICE STATIONHydrapos3887084BRIDGE GARAGE Micros4251221LANGTON GREEN S/STATIONMicros5492130PASTURE ROAD F/STATIONTokheim6492186PENSARNAU FILLING STATIONMicros7886037CROSSROADS SERVICE STATIONTokheim8491747SEEDLEY ROAD S/STNMicros9886597STOOPS GARAGEEdacom10886921PADARN SERVICE STATIONHydrapos11886565LARKHILL SERVICE STATIONHydrapos12491099CHARLEMONT STREET SERVICE STNHydrapos13887179SPAR FILLING STATIONMicros14887037Victoria Filling Station Micros15254114SCRUBS LANE S/SMicros16886763DYFFRYN SERVICE STATIONCasio17886999BEATRICE SERVICE STATIONMicros18886998ST ERTH SERVICESIndigo19887000SCORRIER SERVICE STATIONMicros20886920LLANINA FILLING STATIONHydraposTable 1: Pilot site listRelease ImpactsAs detailed in the contentsKey success Criteria:Pilot on any of the functionality does not raise any critical issuesThe software does not adversely affect existing functionality, or create new issuesThe participating sites are supported with HTECs premium care package throughout the software pilot periodRelease NotificationSites involved in the pilot will be advised by Valero of the software update and specific issues they have raised it will be addressing. Release ManagementPlanned software update, managed and staggered using existing TMS capabilities:HTEC Helpdesk Manager will manage and report on deploymentProject development team will provide technical support Valero Helpdesk will be primed and ready to pick up on any issues and escalate both within Valero and HTEC if the response is inadequate.Appendix A: References index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=332index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=333\r\n 1st April 2015    Dear CustomerTexaco Fastfuel and The Business cards are PIN enabled from 1st MAY 2015!Valero are delighted to announce that we are enabling PIN on the Texaco network for the Texaco Fastfuel and The Business cards. This is a welcome move to increase security; making the Texaco branded fuel cards a safe option for our customers.We have run a successful pilot across a number of sites and are confident that this will be a smooth transition for you and our cardholder(s).Texaco Fastfuel and The Business cardholder(s) will receive their PIN numbers from our card issuer prior to May 1st and will be ready with their PIN numbers when making their fuel card transactions.  (Pin numbers cannot be changed)GO LIVE DATES from the 1st May 2015 onwardsThere will be a gradual roll out across the Texaco network starting 1st May 2015, with the aim to complete all Texaco sites by May 31st 2015. You will know that your site has been upgraded when the first Fastfuel or The Business card is presented that day and prompts for PIN.  Signature Default FunctionUntil the 1st July 2015 all card transactions can default to signature if the customer doesnt know their PIN number.  A step by step guide has been produced and is attached for your reference.  Please ensure this is placed in the sales area for all your staff to refer to. Tates Consumables will send out a counter top display card week commencing 6th April, advising customers of the need to have the PIN number available from May 1st onwards. Please ensure this is displayed as soon as you receive it.If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to contact me 0207 513 3181 or email karen.goane@valero.com. Yours faithfullyKaren GoaneCards ManagerValero Energy Limitedindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=333'),
(335, 'Gift Card Replacement Procedure', '<p>All bad mag stripe replacements either from a customer or from a station will require apprvoal from David Cantor.</p>\r\n<p>The following information will be required to have the gift card replaced</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Card holder\'s first and last name</li>\r\n<li>The full card number of the Gift/Fuel card having issues</li>\r\n<li>Date of original purchase</li>\r\n<li>Location of original purchase</li>\r\n<li>Original card value</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a href=\"mailto:david.cantor@valero.com&amp;subject=Gift/Fuel Card replacement%20&amp;body=Ticket:%20XXXXXXX%0D%0A%0D%0A&bull;Card holder\'s first and last name:%0D%0A&bull;Gift/Fuel card number:%0D%0A&bull;Date of original purchase:%0D%0A&bull;Location of original purchase:%0D%0A&bull;Original card value:%0D%0A\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to email the information to David</a></p>', '2015-05-06 05:45:25', 'lbfb2t', '2015-05-06 08:58:31', 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on replacing gift cards with bad magnetic stripes', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:david.cantor@valero.com&amp;subject=Gift/Fuel Card replacement &amp;body=Ticket: XXXXXXX%0D%0A%0D%0A&bull;Card holder\'s first and last name:%0D%0A&bull;Gift/Fuel card number:%0D%0A&bull;Date of original purchase:%0D%0A&bull;Location of original purchase:%0D%0A&bull;Original card value:%0D%0A'),
(336, 'Phone Payment Procedure (RAMS)', '<p>Valero credit card customers have the option of making a payment on their account via a phone payment using their checking/savings account.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>General Information:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>When a customer makes a payment to be processed/dated for the current date, it will <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">immediately reflect in the account balance</span>. This means the customer no longer has to wait until the system processes the payment to have those funds to become available.</p>\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If a customer gives you a phone payment <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><em>dated</em></strong>&nbsp; </span>today, the amount of the payment will be released and available immediately.</li>\r\n<li>If a customer gives you a post-dated phone payment for Friday, the payment will reflect in the account balance on Friday at (12:01 am).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>FYI:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Payments made after business hours, holidays or weekends, will be available on the release date. &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Due to the immediate availability of funds, we should not have to issue TCLs for same day payments.</li>\r\n<li>The <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>GTOT</strong> </span>and <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>AVCR</strong> </span>commands will reflect current date payments.</li>\r\n<li>All unposted payments will appear in the UNP field and the TX Screen.&nbsp; It will also appear in the PAY field in red. Because a payment will appear in both fields, please don&rsquo;t confuse with multiple payments being made. &nbsp;See screenshot below.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Accessing the Phone Payment Screen</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Customer Information</span>\" screen in RAMS/FAMS, enter \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">VA</span>\" on the Command line.&nbsp; This screen&nbsp;shows all previous payments and will allow you to select&nbsp;the customer\'s banking information to make a new phone payment.&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Processing a&nbsp;phone payment&nbsp;</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">While in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">VA</span>\" screen, type an \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">S</span>\" on the yellow line on the left hand side of the bank information the customer wants to use in order to select it.&nbsp;</span> <br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/rams-ppay-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"748\" height=\"234\" /></strong></span><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If prompted to verify for \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Authorized Signer</span>\":<br /><br /></span></span>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Ask if the&nbsp;customer is an authorized signer on the bank account being used.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the customer is <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>not</strong> </span>an authorized signer, then you are unable to process the payment and can <strong>F3</strong> to exit the screen.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Y</strong></span>&rdquo; in the <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>AUTHORIZED SIGNER</strong> </span>field at the top left hand side of the <strong>VB</strong> screen.&nbsp; <br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The <strong>A SIGNER</strong> field will populate with &ldquo;<strong>Y</strong>&rdquo; on the <strong>VA</strong> screen under the release date.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Enter the payment amount and verify payment date:&nbsp; <br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Pending Date field</strong> </span>on the <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Phone Payment Entry </span>screen will populate with today\'s date.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the customer is making a post-dated payment, you must change the date accordingly.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Press <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Enter<br /><br /></strong></span></li>\r\n<li>The system will automatically set a <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>PTP</strong> </span>on the account for all phone payments.&nbsp; The $15.00 has been removed from the <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>FEE</strong> </span>field since we are not applying phone payment fees at this time.&nbsp; <br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/rams-ppay-2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"770\" height=\"355\" /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><br /></span>&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Changing info/deleting a pending phone payment</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If a customer calls back to change the bank account number on a phone payment that has not been processed, follow these steps in order to change the information:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If they want to <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>change</strong> </span>the information on the payment: <br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ask the customer if they are an authorized signer on the bank account:<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If yes, type &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>C</strong></span>&rdquo; next to the appropriate payment and make necessary changes (amount and/or date)&nbsp;and press enter.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If no, <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">advise customer we are unable to make the change</span>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Document the change in your <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>ICAL</strong></span> and include that the customer is an authorizer signer.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If they want to <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">delete</span> </strong>the payment: <br /><br /></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Type \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">D</span>\" next to the payment.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When prompted, press \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">F5</span>\" on your keyboard to confirm.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Document the change in your <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">ICAL</span> </strong>that the payment has been deleted.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Adding a checking/savings account </strong></span></p>\r\n<p>If the customer does not a bank account on file or is needing to add a new one, we can do that in RAMS when the customer wants to make a phone payment.&nbsp; To add a new checking/savings account to the customer\'s account:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Customer Information</span>\" screen on the customer\'s account, type in \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">VB</span>\" on the Command field.&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the customer is a \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Authorized Signer</span>\", type \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Y</span>\" in that field.&nbsp; <br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If the customer is not an \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Authorized Signer</span>\", advise the customer they can not make a phone payment.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Type in the bank routing number in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Bank Routing</span>\" field.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Type in the bank&nbsp;account number in the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Bank Account</span>\" field.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>For the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Acct Type</span>\", type in \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">C</span>\" for checking and \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">S</span>\" for savings.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/rams-ppay-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"705\" height=\"335\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>', '2015-05-06 08:22:08', 'lbfb2t', '2017-06-17 12:59:55', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Procedure for taking phone payments on RAMS accounts.', '', 90003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
