(342, 'Datawire Setup on NCR Radiant', '<p>Datawire is a First Data owned&nbsp;piece of communications software that is built in to the Radiant POS system. This product will use a broadband connection to communicate.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The configuration for credit is as follows:</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 140px;\" width=\"351\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>ApplicationID</td>\r\n<td>RADIANTEPSLNMUW2&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>MerchantID</td>\r\n<td>JDXXXXXXXX</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Service ID</td>\r\n<td>XXX</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>TerminalID</td>\r\n<td>XXX</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>URL1</td>\r\n<td>https://staging1.datawire.net/sd</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>URL2</td>\r\n<td>https://staging2.datawire.net/sd</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>UseSessionConnection</td>\r\n<td>YES</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-06-01 06:21:35', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-01 06:21:35', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information for setting up a Datawire connection on a Radiant POS', '', 30008, 'Archive', 'N', ''),
(343, 'ADM Remote Access Certificate Instructions', '<p><strong>Create new user certificate, stored in Internet Explorer</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Browse to https://catxsawh03.corp.valero.com/certsrv, select <strong>Request a certificate<br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/ADM/adm1.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"685\" height=\"347\" /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>User Certificate</strong>, select <strong>Submit</strong> button<br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/ADM/adm2.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"483\" height=\"255\" /></li>\r\n<li>The certificate will be installed into Internet Explorer, <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">on this desktop<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/ADM/adm3.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"523\" height=\"290\" /></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Export new user certificate to y: drive</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In Internet Explorer (on the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">same desktop</span> as above!), go to <strong>Tools</strong> -&gt; <strong>Internet Options</strong> menu choice</li>\r\n<li>In Internet Options, go to <strong>Content</strong> tab, select <strong>Certificates</strong> button</li>\r\n<li>From the list of certificates, select the certificate you just created (the expiration date should be one year from today), and choose <strong>Export</strong> button, to enter the Certificate Export Wizard</li>\r\n<li>Ensure <strong>Yes, export the private key</strong> is selected, then choose <strong>Next</strong> button</li>\r\n<li>In Export File Format, check the box for &ldquo;Include all certificates in the certification path if possible&rdquo; and choose <strong>Next</strong></li>\r\n<li>In Password part of wizard, type and confirm a password and choose <strong>Next</strong> button, <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">whilst ensuring you will have this password available later</span></strong> (at home/on the road); you should avoid emailing your password to yourself, as email isn&rsquo;t considered secure/encrypted; one option is to write the password on paper, and store this in your billfold or purse</li>\r\n<li>In the File to Export portion, choose a location to save your new user certificate (one suggestion is your Y: drive), and choose <strong>Save</strong></li>\r\n<li>Choose <strong>Finish</strong>, and <strong>OK</strong> buttons, to complete the Export</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rename and email your certificate to yourself</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Go to the certificate file you just exported, and add the .txt extension to the filename (i.e. L_Number.pfx.txt), to avoid Outlook and other email services blocking the pfx filetype</li>\r\n<li>Right click the certificate file just renamed, and choose <strong>Send To</strong> -&gt; <strong>Mail Recipient</strong>, and send this file to an email address convenient for you to access at home/on the road</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Import your new user certificate on your home computer/road laptop</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Note: on each computer you&rsquo;ll use to access the SSL VPN, you&rsquo;ll need to install the new user certificate</li>\r\n<li>On your home computer/laptop, download your new user certificate to your local filesystem, rename it back to its original name (i.e. L_Number.pfx)</li>\r\n<li>Double click on the pfx file, starting the Certificate Import Wizard, and choose <strong>Next</strong> button</li>\r\n<li>Choose <strong>Next</strong> button again, accepting the default name</li>\r\n<li>Type the password to decrypt your certificate private key, choose <strong>Next</strong> button</li>\r\n<li>In Certificate Store, accept default of &ldquo;Automatically select the certificate store based on the type of certificate&rdquo;, and choose <strong>Next</strong> button</li>\r\n<li>Choose <strong>Finish</strong> button, to complete Certificate Import Wizard; you&rsquo;re now able to authenticate to remote access using this new user certificate!</li>\r\n<li>Note: the new user certificate for remote access is now installed <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">on this computer</span> (the import steps here will need to be performed on each computer)</li>\r\n</ol>', '2015-06-01 09:37:50', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-01 09:53:24', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'ADM Remote Access Certificate Instructions', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(344, 'Verifone RubyCi Setup on TNS Link', '<h3>Important Information:</h3>\r\n<p>Please note that dashes should <strong>never</strong> be entered as part of the merchant ID. To verify the correct Merchant ID was entered, check the merchant ID from an EPS configuration report to confirm it was entered correctly.</p>\r\n<h3>Commander /&nbsp;CI&nbsp;Settings and Connections:</h3>\r\n<table style=\"height: 129px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 59px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 81%; height: 59px;\" colspan=\"6\">\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ruby CI&nbsp;IP Setup information for TNS Cisco 881</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 27%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Isolated Payment NIC</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Device Specific Routes</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 29%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Buypass Config</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">IP&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 17%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">172.16.21.12</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Route Type</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">Host</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 13.88%; height: 13.62px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Connection Mode&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15.11%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">IP</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Gateway</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 17%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">172.16.21.1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Destination</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">204.194.125.9</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 13.88%; height: 13.62px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">IP</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15.11%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">204.194.125.9</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.62px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13.62px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Netmask</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 17%; height: 13.62px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">255.255.255.0</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Gateway</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 13.62px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">172.16.21.1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 13.88%; height: 13.62px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Port</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15.11%; height: 13.62px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">7735</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 17%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ebecf0;\">Netmask</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">255.255.255.255</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 13.88%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 15.11%; height: 13px; border-bottom-color: grey; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/ci-cisco.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"787\" height=\"731\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-06-01 10:07:35', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-23 08:12:36', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'RubyCI Setup on TNS Link', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '');
