(345, 'Heat Guide', '<p>The Valero Wholesale Technical Support department uses the Heat ticketing system to document, record and track calls that come in from stores, customers and jobbers. With each ticket, you can insert journal entries, customer and store data and attach documents such as PDF files and emails.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421025998\"></a>Understanding Heat Ticket Structure</h1>\r\n<p>Heat is structured to help WTS document issues concerning Valero stations, customers, jobbers/distributors and UK Texaco locations. Each option is structured differently when it comes to the selectable fields and information available.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Heat ticketing system allows 4 different types of tickets to be created:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Consumer</strong> &ndash; this is used for customers.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Facility</strong> &ndash; this is used for jobbers.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Store</strong> &ndash; this is used for Valero stations</li>\r\n<li><strong>UK Store</strong> - this is used for Texaco UK locations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here is an example of each ticket type you&rsquo;ll be working with:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a name=\"_Toc421025999\"></a><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Store tickets</span></strong><strong>:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>This ticket shows the store&rsquo;s contact information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><a name=\"_Toc421026000\"></a><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer tickets</span></strong><strong>:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>This ticket type has one section for customer contact information and another section for the store contact information.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong><a name=\"_Toc421026001\"></a><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Facility (jobber) tickets</span></strong><strong>:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>These tickets show the Facility ID (jobber #) and its contact info.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a name=\"_Toc421026002\"></a><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">UK tickets</span></strong><strong>:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>These tickets are easily identifiable due to the red header. The UK Heat tickets are the only ones that have a different color than the other ticket types.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Using the appropriate ticket type is important for cataloging and documenting any issues or problems that may arise. Here&rsquo;s a further explanation of each ticket type:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Customer ticket</strong> &ndash; used if the customer calls us in regards to any issue.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Store ticket</strong> &ndash; used if the store calls us concerning all issues.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Facility ticket</strong> - used if the jobber calls us regarding a issue with the jobber itself.</li>\r\n<li><strong>UK ticket</strong> &ndash; this ticket type should be used for all call reasons in regards to a UK Texaco location.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026003\"></a>Creating a new ticket</h1>\r\n<p>To open a new ticket in Heat, follow these steps:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>In Heat, hold &ldquo;Ctrl&rdquo; and press &ldquo;N&rdquo; on your keyboard (or go to &ldquo;File&rdquo; then select &ldquo;New call record&rdquo;).</li>\r\n<li>If a new &ldquo;store&rdquo; ticket does not open, hold &ldquo;Ctrl&rdquo; and press &ldquo;T&rdquo; on the keyboard. You will then select either &ldquo;Consumer&rdquo;, &ldquo;Facility&rdquo;, &ldquo;Store&rdquo; or &ldquo;UK Store&rdquo; as the customer type. See example below.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Example: </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you click on your desired customer type, click &ldquo;<strong>OK</strong>&rdquo; to create a new ticket in Heat. This will bring up the appropriate template in Heat and we can then start to fill out the information that we are researching.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here&rsquo;s an example of a newly opened &ldquo;Store&rdquo; ticket:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026004\"></a>Store tickets &ndash; in detail</h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The first ticket type we will examine is the &ldquo;Store&rdquo; ticket type. Of all the ticket types available, this type is used the most frequent. Store&rsquo;s can call in for reasons such as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Network issues &ndash; unable to process credit</li>\r\n<li>Out of balances</li>\r\n<li>Chargeback inquiries</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026005\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Site contact </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">information fields </span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The first part we will review is the top part of the Heat ticket, the <strong>site contact entry fields</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The top part of a Heat ticket host the fields for the store&rsquo;s address, phone number, jobber/dealer numbers, site name and site&rsquo;s contact name.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026006\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ticket Organization Fields</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The bottom part of a Heat ticket is what hosts the notes, organization fields, initial problem statement and resolution fields and the ticket organization tabs.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ticket Organization Tabs</strong></span> host each page of the ticket in Heat:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call Log tab- main page of the ticket, which is depicted above.</li>\r\n<li>Detail tab - is an additional page that has separate questions to ask depending on the issue at hand.</li>\r\n<li>Assignment tab - create an assignment for yourself or another co-worker to look at this ticket. The</li>\r\n<li>Journal tab - troubleshooting and work notes are held here.</li>\r\n<li>Web tab &ndash; Not used by Wholesale Technical Support.</li>\r\n<li>Attachments tab &ndash; attach PDF, Word docs, images, etc. to the ticket</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Problem Statement field</strong></span> is where the initial notes for the call are placed. This field should be kept with brief statements about why the customer is calling. This field is just so we know what the call is about.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Organization fields</strong></span> are what we use to categorize the ticket. The selections we have are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Record Type- the 3 selections for this field are &ldquo;problem&rdquo;, &ldquo;project&rdquo; and &ldquo;request&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Call Type &ndash; this field will vary depending on what &ldquo;record type&rdquo; you chose previously.</li>\r\n<li>Category &ndash; this field will vary depending on what &ldquo;call type&rdquo; you chose previously.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Priority &ndash; the priority can range from:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1 (emergency),</li>\r\n<li>2 (elevated),</li>\r\n<li>3 (standard) and</li>\r\n<li>4 (scheduled).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For the purposes of Wholesale Technical Support, we always use <strong>level 3</strong>.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Source &ndash; this is always defaulted to &ldquo;phone&rdquo;. Other options include &ldquo;voicemail&rdquo;, &ldquo;email&rdquo; and &ldquo;letter&rdquo;. You will only change this if you receive an email, letter or voicemail from a customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Resolution field</strong></span> is where the ticket resolution notes should be placed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026007\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How to pull up a Valero site in Heat</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you have a new ticket created, you can now pull up the location you need.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are a number of ways to pull up a location in Heat, which include the store&rsquo;s phone number, address, jobber/dealer # or store name.</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026008\"></a>Phone Number</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a site by their phone number, type in the store&rsquo;s phone number in the &ldquo;Phone&rdquo; field and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026009\"></a>Store Address</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a store by their address, type in the store&rsquo;s address in the &ldquo;Address&rdquo; field and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard, Heat will bring up another box asking you to select the site. If the address is correct, click on &ldquo;<strong>OK</strong>&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: If the site has had a change in their jobber/dealer #, it may show two different sites. You&rsquo;ll want to select their current jobber/dealer #</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026010\"></a>Jobber/Dealer Number</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a store by their jobber/dealer number, type in the store&rsquo;s jobber/dealer number in the &ldquo;*Store&rdquo; field and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026011\"></a>Store name</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a store by their store name, type in the store&rsquo;s name in the blank field at the top of Heat and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026012\"></a>Customer Tickets &ndash; in detail</h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Customer tickets are used when a customer calls in concerning reasons such as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Gift card orders</li>\r\n<li>Gift card balance inquiry</li>\r\n<li>Store errors</li>\r\n<li>Store locations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026013\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer contact </span><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">information fields </span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The first part we will review is the top part of the Heat ticket, the <strong>customer contact entry fields.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>The top part of a Heat ticket host the fields for the customer&rsquo;s first and last name, phone number, address and email address. The second half of the customer ticket hosts the fields for the store (jobber/dealer #), phone number, address and merchant # (BP #).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026014\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ticket Organization Fields</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The bottom part of a Heat ticket is what hosts the notes, organization fields, initial problem statement and resolution fields and the ticket organization tabs</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ticket Organization Tabs</strong></span> host each page of the ticket in Heat:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call Log tab- main page of the ticket, which is depicted above.</li>\r\n<li>Detail tab - is an additional page that has separate questions to ask depending on the issue at hand.</li>\r\n<li>Assignment tab - create an assignment for yourself or another co-worker to look at this ticket. The</li>\r\n<li>Journal tab - troubleshooting and work notes are held here.</li>\r\n<li>Web tab &ndash; Not used by Wholesale Technical Support.</li>\r\n<li>Attachments tab &ndash; attach PDF, Word docs, images, etc. to the ticket&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Problem Statement field</strong></span> is where the initial notes for the call are placed. This field should be kept with brief statements about why the customer is calling. This field is just so we know what the call is about.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Organization fields</strong></span> are what we use to categorize the ticket. The selections we have are:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Record Type- the 2 selections for this field are &ldquo;Customer relations - comment&rdquo; and &ldquo;Wholesale &ndash; comment&rdquo;. We always use &ldquo;Wholesale &ndash; comment&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Call Type &ndash; You will either choose &ldquo;Gift card&rdquo; or &ldquo;Transaction&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Category &ndash; this field will vary depending on what &ldquo;call type&rdquo; you chose previously.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Priority &ndash; the priority can range from\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1 (emergency),</li>\r\n<li>2 (elevated),</li>\r\n<li>3 (standard) and</li>\r\n<li>4 (scheduled).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the purposes of Wholesale Technical Support, we always use <strong>level 3</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Source &ndash; this is always defaulted to &ldquo;phone&rdquo;. Other options include &ldquo;voicemail&rdquo;, &ldquo;email&rdquo; and &ldquo;letter&rdquo;. You will only change this if you receive an email, letter or voicemail from a customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Resolution field</strong></span> is where the ticket resolution notes should be placed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026015\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How to pull up a customer in Heat</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On customer tickets, you can pull up customers that have already called in by their phone number or last name.</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026016\"></a>Phone Number</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a customer by their phone number, type in the customer&rsquo;s phone number in the &ldquo;Phone&rdquo; field and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026017\"></a>Customer&rsquo;s last name</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you are unable to pull up a customer by their phone number, you can attempt their last name as well. Type in the customer&rsquo;s last name in the second box of the &ldquo;Name&rdquo; field and press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you enter their phone number or last name, it will populate with the customer&rsquo;s first name and either their last name or phone number. To access any ticket history for the customer, click on the &ldquo;Caller History&rdquo; icon. The ticket history window will pop-up for that customer:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>At this point you can double click on the ticket # you want to access and Heat will bring up that ticket.</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026018\"></a>Creating a new customer in Heat</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you are unable to locate the customer in Heat via their phone number or last name, you can create a log history for that customer by creating a new customer profile.</p>\r\n<p>First, click the &ldquo;New&rdquo; button:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This will start the new customer wizard in Heat. The first dialogue box that appears is the &ldquo;First Name&rdquo; field. Enter the customer&rsquo;s first name here and then click &ldquo;OK&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Next, enter the customer&rsquo;s last name and click on &ldquo;OK&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Lastly, enter the customer&rsquo;s phone number and click on &ldquo;OK&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This will establish the customer&rsquo;s information in Heat and we can now access their information for future reference if needed.</p>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026019\"></a>Facility tickets &ndash; in detail</h1>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Facility (jobber) tickets are used when distributors call us for reasons such as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Settlement issues</li>\r\n<li>Valero Portal issues</li>\r\n<li>Billing inquires</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026020\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Facility contact information fields</span></h2>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>The top part of a Heat ticket hosts the fields for the Facility ID (jobber #), phone number and address. The second half of the customer ticket hosts the contact name field.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026021\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ticket Organization Fields</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The bottom part of a Heat ticket is what hosts the notes, organization fields, initial problem statement and resolution fields and the ticket organization tabs.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ticket Organization Tabs</strong></span> host each page of the ticket in Heat:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call Log tab- main page of the ticket, which is depicted above.</li>\r\n<li>Detail tab - is an additional page that has separate questions to ask depending on the issue at hand.</li>\r\n<li>Assignment tab - create an assignment for yourself or another co-worker to look at this ticket. The</li>\r\n<li>Journal tab - troubleshooting and work notes are held here.</li>\r\n<li>Web tab &ndash; Not used by Wholesale Technical Support.</li>\r\n<li>Attachments tab &ndash; attach PDF, Word docs, images, etc. to the ticket</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Problem Statement field</strong></span> is where the initial notes for the call are placed. This field should be kept with brief statements about why the customer is calling. This field is just so we know what the call is about.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Organization fields</strong></span> are what we use to categorize the ticket. The selections we have are:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Record Type- the 2 selections for this field are &ldquo;Customer relations - comment&rdquo; and &ldquo;Wholesale &ndash; comment&rdquo;. We always use &ldquo;Wholesale &ndash; comment&rdquo;.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call Type &ndash; You will either choose &ldquo;Gift card&rdquo; or &ldquo;Transaction&rdquo;.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Category &ndash; this field will vary depending on what &ldquo;call type&rdquo; you chose previously.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Priority &ndash; the priority can range from:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1 (<strong>emergency</strong>)</li>\r\n<li>2 (<strong>elevated</strong>),</li>\r\n<li>3 (<strong>standard</strong>)</li>\r\n<li>4 (<strong>scheduled</strong>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the purposes of Wholesale Technical Support, we always use <strong>level 3</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Source &ndash; this is always defaulted to &ldquo;phone&rdquo;. Other options include &ldquo;voicemail&rdquo;, &ldquo;email&rdquo; and &ldquo;letter&rdquo;. You will only change this if you receive an email, letter or voicemail from a customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Resolution field</strong></span> is where the ticket resolution notes should be placed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026022\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How to pull up a Jobber in Heat</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On facility tickets, you can pull up their information in Heat by their phone number, jobber # or the jobber name.</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026023\"></a>Facility ID (Jobber #)</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a jobber by their facility ID, type in their jobber # in the &ldquo;Facility ID&rdquo; field and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you enter the Jobber #, Heat will bring up a dialogue box asking you to confirm the correct jobber:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Double click on this jobber if it is correct and Heat will populate the ticket with their information.</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026024\"></a>UK Tickets &ndash; in detail</h1>\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n<p>Texaco locations in the UK (United Kingdom) call the Valero help desk typically in regards to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Settlement issues</li>\r\n<li>Credit processing issues</li>\r\n<li>Transaction inquiries</li>\r\n<li>Peripheral issues</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026025\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">UK contact information fields</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The top part of a Heat ticket hosts the fields for the J/D #, phone number and address and site #. The second half of the customer ticket hosts the contact name field.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026026\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Ticket Organization Fields</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The bottom part of a Heat ticket is what hosts the notes, organization fields, initial problem statement and resolution fields and the ticket organization tabs.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ticket Organization Tabs</strong></span> host each page of the ticket in Heat:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Call Log tab- main page of the ticket, which is depicted above.</li>\r\n<li>Detail tab - is an additional page that has separate questions to ask depending on the issue at hand.</li>\r\n<li>Assignment tab - create an assignment for yourself or another co-worker to look at this ticket. The</li>\r\n<li>Journal tab - troubleshooting and work notes are held here.</li>\r\n<li>Web tab &ndash; Not used by Wholesale Technical Support.</li>\r\n<li>Attachments tab &ndash; attach PDF, Word docs, images, etc. to the ticket</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Problem Statement field</strong></span> is where the initial notes for the call are placed. This field should be kept with brief statements about why the customer is calling. This field is just so we know what the call is about.</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Call Organization fields</strong></span> are what we use to categorize the ticket. The selections we have are:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Record Type- the 3 selections for this field are &ldquo;UK - Problem&rdquo; and &ldquo;UK - Request&rdquo; and &ldquo;UK &ndash; Setup&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Call Type &ndash; this field will vary depending on what &ldquo;record type&rdquo; you chose previously.</li>\r\n<li>Category &ndash; this field will vary depending on what &ldquo;call type&rdquo; you chose previously.</li>\r\n<li>Priority &ndash; the priority can range from:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1 (<strong>emergency</strong>)</li>\r\n<li>2 (<strong>elevated</strong>),</li>\r\n<li>3 (<strong>standard</strong>)</li>\r\n<li>4 (<strong>scheduled</strong>).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>***Note:</strong> It is extremely important to use the appropriate priority levels for UK calls.&nbsp;&nbsp; For a further explanation of the priority types, please see the &ldquo;UK Call Priority&rdquo; section***</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Source &ndash; this is always defaulted to &ldquo;phone&rdquo;. Other options include &ldquo;voicemail&rdquo;, &ldquo;email&rdquo; and &ldquo;letter&rdquo;. You will only change this if you receive an email, letter or voicemail from a customer.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026027\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">UK Call Priority</span></h2>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026028\"></a><strong>Critical</strong></h3>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat Priority: 1 - Emergency</strong> <strong>Ops Log&nbsp;Priority: High</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Issue&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Description&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Response Timeframe</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Escalation&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Comments&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Total communications failure on site</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Loss of DSL and GPRS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 24 hours</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>TNS Account Manager, TNS service Manager, TNS delivery Team Lead</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Cannot take any cards</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Cannot take all cards</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 6 hours</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>HTEC, FIS Account Manager, TNS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Where it is not easily apparent where the fault has arisen from, there will be a period of analysis to help identify the failing service</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Cannot take Visa cards</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Site cannot take visa credit or debit cards</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 6 hours</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Barclays, FIS, HTEC</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Due payments over 3 days late</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Settlement to sites over 3 days late&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact site and Area Manager</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Relevant supplier contact</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Requests to support fraud investigations</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Requests from Police or other relevant organisation to support a fraud investigation on site</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Immediate</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Cannot accept Allstar cards</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Allstar transactions failure</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact site, raise a fix request. Request turnaround within 6 hours</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Relevant supplier contact</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h4><em>&nbsp;</em></h4>\r\n<h4><em>&nbsp;</em></h4>\r\n<h4><em>&nbsp;</em></h4>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026029\"></a>Medium</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat Priority:&nbsp;2 - Elevated</strong> <strong>Ops Log&nbsp;Priority: Medium</strong></p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Issue&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Description&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Response Timeframe</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Escalation&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Comments&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>ADSL down/GPRS UP</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>ADSL or PSTN down on a site</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact TNS, request fix in 48 hours</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>TNS Account Manager, TNS service Manager, TNS delivery Team Lead</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Fuel Card not accepted</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Any scheme outside Allstar</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact site, raise issue, request fix 48 hours</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Card issuer, relevant supplier</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Single terminal failure</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Single terminal on a 2/more terminal site</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>VCS helpdesk, raise with HTEC, initial assessment, terminal delivery within 5 days</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>HTEC</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Reconciliation Issues</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Site unable to reconcile transactions</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Contact site, provide reports/access to reports within 5 days</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026030\"></a>Low</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat Priority:&nbsp;3 - Standard</strong> <strong>Ops Log&nbsp;Priority: Low</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Issue&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Description&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Response Timeframe</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Escalation&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Comments&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>PINpad failure</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>VCS helpdesk, request PINpad</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>VCS helpdesk, request PINpad</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Keyboard failure</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>VCS helpdesk, request Keyboard</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>VCS helpdesk, request Keyboard</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Back Office issues</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Back office</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Raise with supplier</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Site must have a contract with the supplier</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>POS issues</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>POS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Raise with supplier</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Requests for configuration changes (cashback, for example)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>POS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Raise with supplier</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Solution Description field</strong></span> is where the ticket notes should be placed:</p>\r\n<p>***<strong>Note</strong>: UK sites are noted differently than tickets for the U.S. For all UK tickets, notes should be made in the &ldquo;<strong>solution description</strong>&rdquo; field. Notes should always start with the date the note was entered and then the note. ***</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 1 June: HTEC called site and were advised that manager will call HTEC today&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026031\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">How to pull up a UK site in Heat</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On UK tickets, you can pull the store&rsquo;s information in Heat by their phone number or their Site #.</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026032\"></a>Phone number</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a UK site by their phone number, type in their phone # in the &ldquo;Phone&rdquo; field and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc421026033\"></a>Site ID #</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a UK site by their site number, type in their site ID # in the &ldquo;Site #&rdquo; field and then press &ldquo;Tab&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026034\"></a>Assignments in Heat</h1>\r\n<p>Assignments are used to assign a ticket to a particular agent. Some agents, like Terry Dunham and the UK group, use these thoroughly to work through tickets that need to be worked.</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026035\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Creating a new assignment in Heat</span></h2>\r\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&nbsp;</span></h2>\r\n<p>To create a new assignment, click on the &ldquo;<strong>Assignment</strong>&rdquo; tab:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once on the assignment screen, right click on the empty area and select &ldquo;<strong>New Assignment</strong>&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This will bring up the assignment creation entry fields. This is where you will input the data for the assignment:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To begin, you&rsquo;ll select options from the &ldquo;<strong>Group</strong>&rdquo; dropdown box, the &ldquo;<strong>Assignee</strong>&rdquo; dropdown box and makes notes in the &ldquo;<strong>Assignment Notes</strong>&rdquo; field:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Group</strong>: WTS uses one of two options for this selection &ndash;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>WS Tech Support</strong> &ndash; this is the most standard selection when creating a ticket. This includes everyone on the WTS team at the Valero Payment Services Center.</li>\r\n<li><strong>UK Retail Technology</strong> &ndash; this includes everyone in the UK Group that is located in the UK. This is used while working on UK calls, if needed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Assignee</strong>: this selection box includes each person&rsquo;s name depending on what &ldquo;group&rdquo; category you chose.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Assignment Notes</strong>: this field is where you&rsquo;ll put in notes for the agent you are creating the assignment for.</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026036\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Completing assignments in Heat</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you work an assignment that was created for you in Heat, you will need to &ldquo;complete&rdquo; the assignment before the ticket can be closed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From the assignment tab on the ticket, fill out the &ldquo;<strong>Completion Notes</strong>&rdquo; and click on &ldquo;<strong>Complete</strong>&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Heat will auto-populate the &ldquo;<strong>Resolution</strong>&rdquo;, &ldquo;<strong>Date and time</strong>&rdquo; and &ldquo;<strong>Completed by</strong>&rdquo; fields.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026037\"></a>Reviewing Ticket history</h1>\r\n<p>Once you have the customer, store, facility or UK site pulled up in Heat, you have the ability to review all logged tickets for them. To review ticket history in Heat, you can click on the &ldquo;Caller History&rdquo; icon or you can access it via the &ldquo;Customer&rdquo; tab.</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026038\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;Caller History&rdquo; icon</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When you place your cursor over the icon, it will display an information box. This is the most frequent and easiest way of reviewing ticket history.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026039\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer Tab</span></h2>\r\n<p>Alternatively, you can access the ticket history by going to the &ldquo;Customer&rdquo; tab in Heat and selecting &ldquo;Call History&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026040\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Review list of tickets for the location</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once the call history log appears, you&rsquo;ll see something like this. You will have to use the screen bar at the bottom of the screen to scroll over to the right and see the ticket details.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you scroll over to the right, you&rsquo;ll see the following columns:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Category</strong> &ndash; this is from the &ldquo;Category&rdquo; field on the ticket.</li>\r\n<li><strong>CallDesc</strong> &ndash; this is the &ldquo;Problem Statement&rdquo; field in the ticket.</li>\r\n<li><strong>RecvdBy</strong> &ndash; agent who opened the ticket.</li>\r\n<li><strong>RecvdDate</strong> &ndash; date ticket was opened.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you have found the ticket you want to see, <strong>double click</strong> on that line and Heat will open that ticket up:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc421026041\"></a>Noting Heat Tickets</h1>\r\n<p>Whenever we work on a Heat ticket, in addition to using the &ldquo;problem statement&rdquo; and the &ldquo;close description&rdquo;, we use &ldquo;<strong>journal</strong>&rdquo; entries to make notes when there is an update or action taken on the issue concerning the store and/or customer.</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026042\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">The importance of establishing clear and precise notes</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Getting into the habit of creating clear and precise notes is essential in establishing solid ticket structure. Some issues that the Wholesale Technical Support department works on require multiple notes that could possibly span over the course of a few days. When these issues arise it is possible that several agents will be updating or working the ticket. The necessity of making a note on the Heat ticket that is understandable to anyone who may see it is crucial. If the notes on the ticket do not provide a logical progression or summary of what you have done then this may cause the next agent to be unable to decipher what you have done. Making your notes clear and logical saves time for not only yourself but also for the next agent should someone else come across your ticket.</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc421026043\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Using Journal Entries</span></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Journal entries are the main format we use in order to make notes on a ticket. Using journal entries establishes a well-structured Heat ticket that provides a central location for all of your notes. Once the journal entry has been saved it can&rsquo;t be deleted by any other agent. This eliminates a note being deleted accidently.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Whenever you create a new journal entry, you must select a &ldquo;Journal Type&rdquo; which is a list of the following selections:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Action/Troubleshooting</strong> &ndash; this is used when we troubleshoot equipment.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Approved Emergency</strong> &ndash; not used by WTS</li>\r\n<li><strong>Approved Out of Scope</strong> &ndash; not used by WTS</li>\r\n<li><strong>Attachment Added</strong> &ndash; can be selected if an attachment is added to the ticket</li>\r\n<li><strong>Left Message</strong> &ndash; can be used if you leave a voicemail for a customer.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Note</strong> &ndash; this is the primary journal type used by WTS. Used for any updates or notes.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Received Documents</strong> &ndash; can be used if documents are received for the ticket.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Received Status Inquiry</strong> &ndash; can be used if store or customer calls or sends a status inquiry.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Shipped Package</strong> &ndash; not used by WTS.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Update from AM/ZM</strong> &ndash; can be used if we receive an update from Area Manager or Zone Manager.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Update from Assignee</strong> &ndash; can be used if update is received from assignee (from the assignment tab).</li>\r\n<li><strong>Update from Customer</strong> &ndash; can be used if update is received from customer.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Update from Vendor</strong> &ndash; used if we receive an update typically from TNS or Spacenet concerning an active issue.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The main &ldquo;journal types&rdquo; we use are &ldquo;<strong>Action/Troubleshooting</strong>&rdquo;, &ldquo;<strong>Note</strong>&rdquo; and &ldquo;<strong>Update</strong> <strong>from Vendor</strong>&rdquo;.</p>', '2015-06-05 09:57:19', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-05 10:01:53', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Training and usage guide for Heat ticketing system', '', 40003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(346, 'TNSLink Information', '<p>The Cisco 881 is a device provided by TNS to support stations with IP based POS equipment as the Fusion Point Express (FPX) cannot handle IP based communications.</p>\r\n<p>For all new TNSLink orders, the Cisco 881 device will expect the IP POS payment NIC to be configured as follows:</p>\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">IP POS</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Port 0</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">172.16.21.12 (this applies to Fiscal TravStar 1, Gilbarco Passport, NCR RPOS, Verifone Commander, and Wayne Nucleus)&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">VX520&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Port 0</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">172.16.21.13 (for sites with more than one, the second device will use 172.16.21.14)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">EZR&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Port 2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">DHCP</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Netmask</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">255.255.255.0 (All Setups)</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Gateway</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">172.16.21.1 <span style=\"font-size: small;\">(All Setups)</span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/881front.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"474\" height=\"113\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/881rear.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"454\" height=\"72\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Port layout:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/881connections.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"644\" height=\"213\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-06-08 10:23:53', 'l7d23b', '2017-02-15 09:24:14', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on TNSLink\'s Cisco 881 communication device', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(347, 'Current Internal Maintenence Notice', '<p>Information Systems will be performing system maintenance Thursday, June 25th, 2015 10:00 PM to Friday June 26th, 2015 1:00 AM (CDT).</p>\r\n<p><strong>During the maintenance the following systems will be unavailable:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Business-to-business data transfer (B2B)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Valero Internet web site (<a href=\"http://www.valero.com/\">www.valero.com</a>)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>US Wholesale Portal</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>MLP Internet web site (<a href=\"http://www.valeroenergypartners.com/\">www.valeroenergypartners.com</a>)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Diamond Green Diesel Internet web site (<a href=\"http://www.diamondgreendiesel.com/\">www.diamondgreendiesel.com</a>)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Credit Card Center Internet web site (ccc.valero.com)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Canadian Wholesale Portal</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>UK home heat web site (texaco.co.uk)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Ireland home heat web site (texaco.ie)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>UK Business Online (texacodistributors.co.uk)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Texaco Station (texacostation.com)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Star Rewards (<a href=\"http://www.starrewards.co.uk/\">www.starrewards.co.uk</a>)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Texaco Children&rsquo;s Art (texacochildrensart.com)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Remote access via go.valero.com</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Email synchronization on mobile devices (VSync)</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Supplier Conversion Portal</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>External collaboration web site</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you have any questions regarding this system unavailability, please contact the IS Customer Support Center at (210) 345-4357 or (800) 483-0045. We apologize for any inconvenience this may cause.</p>', '2015-06-23 10:54:06', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-23 10:54:06', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Current Internal Maintenence Notice', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'http://www.valero.com/http://www.valeroenergypartners.com/http://www.diamondgreendiesel.com/http://www.starrewards.co.uk/'),
(348, 'UK Alternate Communications Platforms', '<p>We have&nbsp;3 sites that do not have ADSL lines installed and use satellite for carrying card transactions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Hybeam Satellite&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>Strensham Services (490534) - Hybeam Reference <strong>HYB350</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">Worsted Service Station (886695) - Hybeam Reference <strong>HYB367</strong></span><strong>&nbsp;No longer Texaco branded</strong></p>\r\n<p>Harbledown (251269) - Hybeam Reference <strong>HYB387</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Support tickets can be raised by contacting the following Telephone Number <strong>0844 264 6574</strong></p>\r\n<p>Or Email <strong><a href=\"mailto:support@hybeam.co.uk\">support@hybeam.co.uk</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Airband DSL</h2>\r\n<p>Newtown Cross Garage (492261)</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Postcode: HR8 2TZ<br />Name on account: Martin Reynolds<br />Company: Valero Energy</p>\r\n<p>Airband Technical Service Line - 01905 676 484</p>', '2015-06-24 06:48:16', 'mjreyn', '2017-07-21 08:28:07', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Contact Details for data providers other than TNS/BT', '', 80006, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:support@hybeam.co.uk');
