(349, 'Gempay General Information', '<p>The Gempay and Gempay 2 devices are made by verifone but run HTEC software. The Gempay 2s are used in the MFL sites. The menus between the two devices are the same.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/mfg/gpgp2info.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"350\" /></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=239\" target=\"_blank\">This article covers the functionality of the general menu button on the Gempay/2</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Troubleshooting</h3>\r\n<p>Note: If a pinpad needs to be replaced for any reason (tamper/security warning, dead buttons, blank screen, etc...) the station may use the chip card slot on the <strong>Gempay/2 </strong>(<span style=\"color: #800080;\">designated in purple above) <span style=\"color: #000000;\">to run chip cards</span></span><strong>. <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">The pinpad must be disconnected from the Gempay for this to work.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=265\" target=\"_blank\">Information on clearing a Large log file.</a> <br />This can also be used if the terminal is running slowly <strong>and as a general troubleshooting step</strong>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=170\" target=\"_blank\">Correcting time on Gempay due to daylight savings</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=241\" target=\"_blank\">Dialing a site in after a configuration change.</a>&nbsp;<br />This step can sometimes be skipped by HTEC if they\'re pushing software changes to a site.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong>General Information</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=334\" target=\"_blank\">Information on the latest Gempay software</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=193\" target=\"_blank\">Gempay Manuals</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=327\" target=\"_blank\">Gempay 2 and Pinpad Images</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=274\" target=\"_blank\"> Pinpad extension cables</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=262\" target=\"_blank\">Product codes for Gempay</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=242\" target=\"_blank\">Manager Password for Gempay</a></p>', '2015-06-25 08:18:03', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-25 08:30:40', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Repository of Information for the Gempay system', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=239index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=265index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=170index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=241index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=334index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=193index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=327index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=274index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=262index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=242'),
(350, 'Valero EMV Program', '<p>Update 6/7/16</p>\r\n<p>The attached letter was mailed to all distributor and direct dealers reminding them of our EMV Incentive Program. Alisa will follow up with an email communication to all of our customers later this week.</p>\r\n<p>Key Points:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Valero will provide an incentive of up to $3,000 per site to assist in the transition to EMV capable POS systems that are <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">installed</span></strong> by December 31, 2016.</li>\r\n<li>Inside transaction liability will continue to be covered by Valero until December 31, 2016.</li>\r\n<li>We are already seeing delays in the availability of hardware and installation technicians. Reminder your distributors to not delay.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Distributors can contact Valero Wholesale Technical Support at 866-4Valero for questions about EMV, or the EMV Incentive Program.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/Reminder - EMV Upgrade Reimbursement Program Letter.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Attachment can be found here.</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Valero has updated the equipment offered through the Managed Services Program with VeriFone&rsquo;s newest hardware offerings all of which are EMV ready.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>RubyCi</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Ruby2/Commander</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Topaz/Commander</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Commander Site Controller</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Verifone MX 915 Pinpad - this is currently the only pinpad that has been certified through Valero. There are other EMV compliant pin pads but the 915 is the only <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Valero</span> certified one.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Verifone&rsquo;s Managed Services program allows our customers to lease a brand new POS system for a monthly fee. The program also includes annual software maintenance (ASM), 24x7 Help Desk support, and on-site maintenance and repair. More information can be found on the Verifone page of the Wholesale Portal.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Distributors who sign up sites under our managed services program are eligible for the $3,000 incentive if they complete the other program requirements. Installation costs for this program are also eligible for 100% reimbursement through BDP ( if available).</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/Managed Services.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Letter to distributors and dealers</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/Valero Managed Services Order Form.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Order form available on the portal for dealers/distributors</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/Valero EMV Reimbursement Program v2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for the information packet</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-06-25 09:07:10', 'l7d23b', '2016-11-08 09:31:17', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Valero EMV Program', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(351, 'Wincanton Order Book Closure SMS Messages', '<p>Wincanton will notify the WTS Helpdesk&nbsp;to send a message to customers notifying them that the order books are closed.</p>\r\n<h3>To access the server to send the mass SMS:</h3>\r\n<p>Method 1:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"file:///O:/AMA-UK/WTS\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #3a4e80;\">Click here to access</span></a>&nbsp;the folder containing a pre-configured remote desktop icon that will connect directly to <strong>PEMWIN7VM05</strong>. You can either drag the icon to your desktop or access it directly from the folder.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password for the account is <strong>Xp0BgNo#<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Click OK and Log On.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Method 2:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On your desktop click on your windows button.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the search type &ldquo;Remote&rdquo; and then select &ldquo;Remote Desktop Connection&rdquo; under the programs section.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Computer dialogue, type in <strong>PEMWIN7VM05 </strong>and click connect.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The username for the account is SVC0426<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password for the account is <strong>Xp0BgNo#<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Click OK and Log On.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>After accessing the remote server:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Open Outlook on the desktop if it is not already running (If Outlook is not open the Send SMS&nbsp;function will fail).&nbsp;<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Double Click this to launch the tool.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/alerticon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"79\" height=\"74\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>When you open the file it will automatically load the data required from SID (Site Information Database). This will pre-populate the contact email addresses and cell phone numbers in to the spreadsheet.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Click the<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong> Order Book Alert </strong></span>button<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/alert-buttons.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"319\" height=\"278\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter the dates that have been communicated to you by Wincanton in the &ldquo;Closed For&rdquo; and &ldquo;Next Del Date&rdquo; dialogue boxes.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/orderbookbox.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"372\" height=\"232\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on the Send Order Book Update button.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Confirm that you want to send the message.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once you send message <em><strong>do not</strong></em> resend message even if you get an error. It will send another message.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2015-06-25 13:31:11', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-12 13:02:25', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Wincanton Order Book Closure SMS Messages', '', 80001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'file:///O:/AMA-UK/WTS'),
(352, 'El Dorado Casino', '<p>We may start receiving calls from customers claiming to have received a $200.00 Prepaid Fuel card from the El Dorado Casino in Shreveport, Louisiana (LA) and there are funds missing from it they did not spend or redeem.&nbsp; They may refer to the open ticket number <strong>1422890</strong>. <br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Do not update this ticket with customer call information except as noted below.</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Open a Customer type ticket for the caller.&nbsp;<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Obtain their phone number, full name, full original card number and mailing address.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Using Value Link&rsquo;s card query, confirm the transactions they made.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Subtract the total of those from the $200.00 original balance to find the amount we owe them.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If there are still funds on their card, &ldquo;destroy active&rdquo; their original card in Value Link.&nbsp;<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Use store # &lsquo;02011819998&rsquo; and<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Note your ticket number in the memo field.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Do not forget to check the remove funds box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Advise your customer you are mailing them a replacement, working (please test it) Fuel Prepaid card; be sure and record the replacement card number that you are mailing in the resolution of your ticket along with their mailing address.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Please instruct your caller that once they receive it, they will need to call our Service Center again, referring to your ticket number, &nbsp;to have the card <strong>activated</strong> for the amount you calculated, and the customer &nbsp;they agreed with.&nbsp; If you and your customer are not able to&nbsp;agree on an amount, forward the ticket&nbsp;number to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:david.cantor@valero.com\" target=\"_blank\">David</a>&nbsp;and advise that&nbsp;he will call back after&nbsp;the activity is analyzed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If all in agreement, and you&rsquo;re mailing the replacement, please add a note to&nbsp;the ticket number above [ <strong>1422890</strong> ]&nbsp;and input the customer&rsquo;s name, city of residence, full original card number, the mailed replacement card number, your ticket number and the amount to activate the card for on their return call.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you are taking a return call from one of these customers.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Verify their identity by matching the ticket number and original full card number. You should also confirm the card number of the replacement card mailed to them.&nbsp; If they elect to obtain a replacement card locally, be sure to verify how they received their original card (from the El Dorado Casino in Shreveport, LA), and the original amount on the original card ($200.00).&nbsp; If verification fails, escalate the ticket to your supervisor.&nbsp; If all checks out, Activate the replacement card using &lsquo;02011819998&rsquo; for the store number in Value Link (this is important).&nbsp; Then note and close your ticket.&nbsp; Please leave my ticket open.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2015-06-25 13:45:33', 'l7d23b', '2015-06-25 13:56:04', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Gift Cards ordered from this location', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:david.cantor@valero.com'),
(353, 'Dealer/Jobber Portal Problems', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">If you notice that there is a component of the&nbsp;Jobber/Dealer portal that is not working, please contact Viraj Mehta @ <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">210-345-4601.&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\"> Also please let Karey or Israel know so that we can post an update as soon as possible.</span></span></p>', '2015-07-01 08:21:38', 'lbfb2t', '2015-07-01 08:22:32', 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to resolve problems with portal components.', '', 60002, 'User', 'N', ''),
(354, 'Insta Credit QR Program', '<p>The new version of Instacredit via QR code is now&nbsp;available to our&nbsp;stations.</p>\r\n<p>If a station calls to order a kit, send an email to Israel Herrera&nbsp;with the store information.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Portal Information:</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #9c9c9c; height: 279px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; background-color: #edf5ff;\" border=\"1\" width=\"725\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Valero Insta-Credit Program <!-- page heading -->\r\n<div class=\"row row-page-heading\">\r\n<div class=\"col-md-9\">\r\n<div class=\"field-short-description\">Turn your loyal customers into Valero Credit Card holders with the in-store Insta-Credit program.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"col-md-3\">\r\n<div class=\"tag-line\"><!-- Summary Title -->\r\n<h3 class=\"field-summary-title\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<!-- Summary Body -->\r\n<p class=\"field-summary-body\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<!--/page heading --> <!-- Video --> <!-- /video -->\r\n<div class=\"body\"><!-- Callout -->\r\n<h2 class=\"field-callout\">Approved Insta-Credit applicants can start shopping in your store immediately with their Temporary Shopping Pass.</h2>\r\n<!-- Long Description -->\r\n<h3 class=\"field-long-description\" style=\"display: none;\">&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<div class=\"body-contents\">\r\n<div id=\"ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_ctl10_label\" style=\"display: none;\">Page Content</div>\r\n<div id=\"ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_ctl10__ControlWrapper_RichHtmlField\" class=\"ms-rtestate-field\" style=\"display: inline;\">\r\n<p><span class=\"ms-rteFontSize-3\">Switching customers to the Valero Credit Card through Insta-Credit shifts them to credit transactions that are free for you. Plus, it can earn them up to an 8 cent per gallon rebate every month. It\'s easy for consumers to apply and get an instant application decision. </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span class=\"ms-rteFontSize-3\">Customer takes an Insta-Credit envelope from the display at the counter.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"ms-rteFontSize-3\">Customer can scan the QR code located on the envelope to start the application process right on their smart phone.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"ms-rteFontSize-3\">Customer completes and submits the application, and waits for the application decision.</span></li>\r\n<li><span class=\"ms-rteFontSize-3\">If the application receives an instant approval, the Temporary Shopping Pass located in the envelope will be activated, and the consumer can begin using it for purchases at the pump and in your store immediately.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span class=\"ms-rteFontSize-3\">Contact the Valero Wholesale Technical Support desk at <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">866-482-5376</span> (866-4VALERO)&nbsp;to request an&nbsp;Insta-Credit kit for your grand opening or other special event.</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/2016-insta-credit-program-flier-final.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Insta-Credit Flyer from Valero portal (Click for PDF)</a></p>', '2015-07-02 13:42:06', 'lbfb2t', '2017-07-03 15:23:52', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Insta Credit QR program', '', 10009, 'User', 'N', ''),
(355, 'RAMS Fleet Guide', '<p>The Valero Wholesale Technical Support department assists the Fleet department with their calls after the Fleet department has closed for the day. These hours are typically Monday through Thursday 6 PM to 8 AM and Friday starting at 3 PM until Monday morning at 8 AM.</p>\r\n<p>For Fleet account maintenance, the Wholesale Technical Support department handles aspects of the account such as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Phone payments</li>\r\n<li>Balance inquiries</li>\r\n<li>Lost/stolen cards</li>\r\n<li>Replacement cards</li>\r\n<li>Limit changes on drivers</li>\r\n<li>Temporary credit line increases (ESTR).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc399850099\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Pulling up an account in RAMS</span></h2>\r\n<p>To pull up an account in RAMS, follow the following steps:</p>\r\n<p>When you sign into RAMS, you&rsquo;ll see this first screen, &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Retail Account Management System</span></strong>&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet1.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"426\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;From this screen, type &ldquo;<strong>d</strong>&rdquo; in the function field. This will take you to the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer Account Maintenance</span></strong>&rdquo; screen.</p>\r\n<p>On the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer Account Maintenance</span></strong>&rdquo; screen, type &ldquo;<strong>k</strong>&rdquo; in the function field. This will take you to the &ldquo;Customer Information&rdquo; screen:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet2.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"601\" height=\"352\" /></p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer Information</span></strong>&rdquo; screen is the initial screen where we will pull up a Fleet account:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet3.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"610\" height=\"293\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>With Fleet accounts, the account number you may be provided with may be two different numbers.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The 1<sup>st</sup> is called the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fleet Number</span></strong>&rdquo; and starts with 3062, see example below.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>To pull up a Fleet account in RAMS, you&rsquo;ll want to type in the account # into the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Command</span></strong>&rdquo; field. :</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet4.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"496\" height=\"22\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>The account number we need from this 3062 number is the <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">six digits prior to the final digit</span></strong>:<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet%20images/fleet5.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"499\" height=\"31\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>Copy this number and delete the full 3062 number from the command field. You&rsquo;ll then paste the number you just copied into the command field to pull up the account in Rams and press &ldquo;Enter&rdquo; on your keyboard:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet6.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"497\" height=\"27\" /></p>\r\n<p>The 2<sup>nd</sup> is the actual <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">6 or 8&nbsp;digit account number</span></strong>.</p>\r\n<p>This account # can vary on the beginning number. If the customer gives you a 6 or 8&nbsp;digit account number, simply type that into the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Command</span></strong>&rdquo; field and press &ldquo;<strong>Enter</strong>&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fleet Account Maintenance</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Once you press &ldquo;Enter&rdquo; on your keyboard to pull up the account, Rams will bring up the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer Information</span></strong>&rdquo; screen for the account:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet%20images/fleet7.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"601\" height=\"422\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Customer Information</span></strong>&rdquo; screen is the main screen for any account.</p>\r\n<p>This is where you can find information such as:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Business name</li>\r\n<li>Mailing address</li>\r\n<li>Phone numbers</li>\r\n<li>Statement balance</li>\r\n<li>Payment history</li>\r\n<li>Payment due date</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: If you happen to reach a different screen on the account, simply type &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">k</span></strong></span>&rdquo; in the command field and it will bring you back to this main screen.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc399850100\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Verifying Information</span></h1>\r\n<p>Whenever you have someone calling on behalf of the fleet account, we need to verify information to verify their identity. The information we verify is:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Phone number</li>\r\n<li>Mailing address</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: It is important to know that if the person calling is not listed as the &ldquo;contact name&rdquo; on this screen or is not listed in the account notes screen (F12) we will not be able to provide information such as: balance, available credit and driver pin #s.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet%20images/fleet8.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"607\" height=\"379\" /></p>\r\n<p>If the person calling has verified the address and phone number for the account, you can now enter the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">verf</span></strong>&rdquo; (short for verify) in the command field:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet9.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"592\" height=\"409\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;The &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">verf</span></strong>&rdquo; command indicates on the account that you have asked and verified information on the account.</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc399850101\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Making phone payments</span></h1>\r\n<p>Fleet customers will often call in after Fleet department hours to make a payment over the phone. Whenever they make a phone payment, they have two options to make the payment: <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">IVR (Valerie)</span> or via a <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">phone representative</span>.</p>\r\n<p>To enter the <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">phone payment screen</span></strong>, type in &ldquo;<strong>va</strong>&rdquo; in the command field and press &ldquo;Enter&rdquo; on your keyboard:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet10.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"657\" height=\"488\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fleet Account Maintenance</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>On the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">va</span></strong>&rdquo; screen, you&rsquo;ll see the payment information along with the bank information:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bank Routing #</li>\r\n<li>Bank account #</li>\r\n<li>Bank name</li>\r\n<li>Account type (C or S)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet11.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"647\" height=\"209\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">checking account</span></strong>&rdquo; number is automatically masked out by default. If you see this bank information, verify the last 3 digits of the checking account number. <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">In order for the customer to use the bank information we have on file, they must verify the last 3 digits.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you have verified that information, type in &ldquo;<strong>s</strong>&rdquo; on the yellow line next to the payment information:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet12.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"614\" height=\"148\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you have selected the bank account you want to use, the screen to enter the payment amount and payment date will appear:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet13.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"648\" height=\"250\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Type in the payment amount in the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">amount</span></strong>&rdquo; field</li>\r\n<li>Enter in the payment date in the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">date</span></strong>&rdquo; field (mm/dd/yy) and then press &ldquo;<strong>Enter</strong>&rdquo;.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you press &ldquo;<strong>Enter</strong>&rdquo;, you will be taken back to the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">VA</span></strong>&rdquo; screen where the payment you just processed will be pending:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet14.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"648\" height=\"261\" /></p>\r\n<p>The payment will show your RAMS initials (see example above) if you are the one that processed the payment. If the customer processed the phone payment with the IVR, it will show #IV instead.</p>\r\n<p>You can also give the customer a &ldquo;confirmation number&rdquo; for their payment. The confirmation number will be where it says &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">CONF/PIC</span></strong>&rdquo; (see example above).</p>\r\n<h1><a name=\"_Toc399850102\"></a><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Performing an ESTR (temporary credit line increase)</span></h1>\r\n<p>Sometimes Fleet accounts can reach their credit line causing the cards to be declined for no available credit. If the account reaches the credit line and the account administrator calls in a payment over the phone we can perform an ESTR &ndash; which will temporarily increase their credit line for 24 hours.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: The temporary credit increase we can give in an ESTR is <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">20% of their current credit line</span></strong>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Example</strong>: 20% of a $5000 credit line is $1000.00. Thus, their temporary credit line would be $6000.00.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">K</span></strong>&rdquo; screen in RAMS:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Type &ldquo;<strong>ESTR</strong>&rdquo; in the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Command</span></strong>&rdquo; field.</li>\r\n<li>Tab over to the &ldquo;<strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Amount</span></strong>&rdquo; field and type in the amount that you want the credit line to be in the format of &ldquo;xxxx.xx&rdquo; and press &ldquo;Enter&rdquo;.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet15.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"575\" height=\"317\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Fleet Account Maintenance</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The ESTR you just performed will appear as well in the notes screen, &ldquo;F12&rdquo;:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/fleet images/fleet16.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"574\" height=\"386\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note</strong></span>: ESTR&rsquo;s will remain on the account until the next business day. The credit analysts for the Fleet department work reports on a daily basis (Monday through Friday) and remove the ESTR the next day.</p>', '2015-07-06 09:10:55', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-27 13:34:49', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'RAMS Fleet Guide', '', 90003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(356, 'Skimming Information', '<p>If you receive a call from a station concerning a found skimmer:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Gather the following information\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Site Information</li>\r\n<li>Site contact\'s name and phone number</li>\r\n<li>Law enforcement information (Case Number, etc.)</li>\r\n<li>If the site has not contacted law enforcement yet, advise them to do so.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Create and close a heat ticket with the information gathered.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"mailto:debbie.knox@valero.com?CC=craig.sperry@valero.com;laneshia.jones@valero.com&amp;Subject=Skimmer%20Notification&amp;Body=A%20skimmer%20was%20identified%20at%20the%20following%20location%3A\">Send an email by clicking here</a>. The email group consists of:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Debbie Knox</li>\r\n<li>Laneshia Jones</li>\r\n<li>Craig Sperry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ol>', '2015-07-07 09:05:32', 'l7d23b', '2017-01-03 08:38:45', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Skimming Information', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:debbie.knox@valero.com?CC=craig.sperry@valero.com;laneshia.jones@valero.com&amp;Subject=Skimmer Notification&amp;Body=A skimmer was identified at the following location%3A'),
(357, 'Test Card Mailing for IIN Card acceptance', '<p>If someone from a&nbsp;station (dealer, manager, etc)&nbsp;is calling to ask about the validity of the letter and process, confirm the letter is from our office and advise them&nbsp;to follow the directions and report the results to you now or they can call back with the results; follow steps 1-2 and 4-9 below (skip step 3) and give your caller the ticket number so they can call back&nbsp;to report the results later.&nbsp; Leave your ticket open in this case.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If someone is calling back with the results and gives you their ticket number.&nbsp; Perform step 3 below, verify the ticket is coded exactly as required, then close the ticket.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Create a new Heat ticket for the store<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the [Problem statement] &nbsp;box type: &ldquo;<strong>Test card results</strong>&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the [Solution Description] box, enter the item that they circled: <em>either <strong>2b, 2c, 2d1 or 2d2</strong><br /><br /></em></li>\r\n<li>In [Record Type] select \"<strong>4 Wholesale &ndash; Problem</strong>\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In [Call Type] choose&nbsp; \"<strong>Unsupported</strong>\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the [Category:] field there will be no options, so simply type \"<strong>IIN Letter Results</strong>\" in the empty box.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>For [Priority] choose <strong>4</strong><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>For [*Resolution Code:] select \"<strong>Reported</strong>\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>For [*Cause Code:] select \"<strong>Software/Application Error</strong>\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Close your ticket, only after the test results are recorded (see step 3).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">IMPORTANT</span></h2>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #b8b8b8; height: 91px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; background-color: #ffe9c9;\" border=\"1\" width=\"786\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>When the store tests the card, have them check the error message for that pump on the register.&nbsp; If they get an L1 decilne, no further action is needed. Verify this against clientline.</p>\r\n<p>If they get \"Invalid Card\" or \"Card Not&nbsp;Accepted\" then they need to have a tech go out to have the correct card deck loaded.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Card Table</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Unfortunately this setting can be overlooked quite easily during the install. When installing on the GemPro an option labeled \"<strong>Default Setting</strong>\" will need to be changed to \"<strong>Valero</strong>.\" This will install the Valero card table.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>We need the tickets coded in exactly this manner for reporting purposes.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Before opening a new ticket, verify there isn&rsquo;t already a ticket as described above still open, ([f5], click on the [Call History] tab and review the last items in the resulting ticket history list).</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #bababa; height: 417px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; background-color: #e0e0e0;\" width=\"685\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a id=\"letter\"></a>Dear Merchant:</p>\r\n<p>At Valero, our goal is to help you meet your customer\' needs and make their experience at your store as efficient as possible. It has come to our attention that there are some locations that may have an outdated card table in their POS system that can cause issues for customers attempting to purchase at the pump with their Valero credit card.</p>\r\n<p>To insure that your store is not one of the locations with this issue, please validate the card table in your system by following the instructions attached below. This validation test will only take a couple of minutes. After completing the validation test, please report your findings by calling us toll free per the instructions.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your assistance.</p>\r\n<p>Valero Payment services</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please use the attached test card and do the following actions:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Slide card in payment card acceptor at any of your outside dispensers.</li>\r\n<li>Follow the prompt at the pump.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If the zip code is required - enter 79108</li>\r\n<li>if the prompt says: SEE CASHER\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Circle this item (b) and go on to item 3</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If the prompt says: CARD NOT ACCEPTED\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Circle this item (c) and go on to item 3</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If the prompt says: SELECT DEBIT or CREDIT (please select CREDIT)\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Cicle this item (d1) and go on to item 3</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If the prompt says: BEGIN FUELING\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Cancel the transaction, circle this item (d2) and go on to item 3.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Please contact us at <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">866-482-5376</span>, option 3, to report your results</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #a6a6a6; height: 143px; float: right; background-color: #ffffff;\" width=\"295\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Physical Card Attached</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Station Name<br />Station Address<br />City State Zip</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2015-07-08 09:23:13', 'l7d23b', '2015-08-13 09:49:02', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information for IIN test cards sent to sites', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(358, 'Valero Self Serve & Fleet Portal Access Issues', '<h3>When receiving calls concerning portal access, follow these steps.</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Obtain customer\'s account number.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Before</strong> recommending a different browser, check to see if customer\'s current version of Internet Explorer / Safari&nbsp;is configured correctly.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Note the customer\'s account in RAMS.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><br />Windows Internet Explorer</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To check IE&nbsp;browser version, have the customer click the cogwheel on the upper right of the Internet Explorer window.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\"><img src=\"upload/ieicons.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"118\" height=\"56\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click <strong>About Internet Explorer</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\"><img src=\"upload/aboutie.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"268\" height=\"324\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The following window will display version information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\"><img src=\"upload/aboutwindow.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"387\" height=\"326\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If a customer is running Internet Explorer version&nbsp;9 or above and is receiving the error: Page cannot be displayed:<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the cogwheel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\"><img src=\"upload/ieicons.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"118\" height=\"56\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Click Internet Options.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\"><img src=\"upload/ieopts-3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"269\" height=\"324\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Verify the security settings match what is highlighted in green below.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\"><img src=\"upload/iesettings.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"423\" height=\"541\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\"><span style=\"color: #0000ff;\">Please note:&nbsp;<strong>All</strong> versions prior to and <strong>some</strong> versions of&nbsp;IE&nbsp;9 will not have the options: <strong>Use TLS 1.1</strong> and<strong> Use TLS 1.2 </strong>will not be present in the list. If the customer has IE9 <strong>without</strong> the options, they will need to use an alternate browser as their version of Windows OS will need to be upgraded to support a more current version of IE.</span></p>\r\n<h4 style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&nbsp;Have the customer click OK and restart their browser.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Mac OS</h2>\r\n<p>There are no settings to change for Safari. If the customer is running an outdated version, they will have to upgrade their OS to get a current browser. If OS is prior to what is listed below, the customer will have to use an alternate browser.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>iOS (iPhone/iPad):&nbsp;Safari 6 or later<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>OSX (desktop):&nbsp;Safari 7 or later (OSX 10.9.5 Mavericks is the oldest OSX version that will run Safari 7)<br />To access version number:</li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Open Safari by clicking on the Safari icon in the dock.</li>\r\n<li>Click on <em>Safari</em> in your Safari menu, located at the top of your screen.</li>\r\n<li>A drop-down menu will now appear. Choose the option labeled <em>About Safari</em>.</li>\r\n<li>A dialog box will now appear containing the browser\'s version number. The first number, located outside of the parenthesis, is the actual version of Safari.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Definitions:</span></h4>\r\n<p><span class=\"_Tgc\"><strong>SSL</strong> (<strong>Secure Sockets Layer</strong>) is the standard security technology for establishing an encrypted link between a web server and a browser. This link ensures that all data passed between the web server and browsers remain private and integral.</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"_Tgc\"><strong>TLS</strong> (<strong>Transport Layer Security </strong>) is a protocol that ensures privacy between communicating applications and their users on the Internet. When a server and client communicate, <strong>TLS</strong> ensures that no third party may eavesdrop or tamper with any message. <strong>TLS</strong> is the successor to the Secure Sockets Layer (SSL).</span></p>', '2015-07-08 10:10:36', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-07 07:35:33', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Valero Self Serve & Fleet Portal Access Issues', '', 40008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(359, 'CST Non-Valero Stores Procedure', '<p>We are now taking support calls for CST Non-Valero (Shell and Sunoco), TX stores and Nice \'n Easy (unbranded), NY stores.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/Non-Valero%20Sites.xlsx\">Click here to access the spreadsheet that contains the non-Valero sites.</a>&nbsp;This can also be accessed via the quick links on the front page of Reflex.</p>\r\n<p>As you will see from the spreadsheet, most of the Shell branded stores in Texas are Gilbarco Passport sites, while the Nice &lsquo;n easy locations in New York state are Retalix.&nbsp; There are also some Wayne Nucleus sites branded Sonoco, also in NY.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Included in the spreadsheet are maintenance numbers listed for each of the sites, one for POS support (reboot Retalix, etc.), and one for Hardware Support (equivalent to CST&rsquo;s Maintenance departments).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>These sites will not be listed in RAMs nor HEAT, so you cannot make tickets on them.&nbsp; Perform your troubleshooting efforts as you do for other CST sites as per the <strong>Amarillo Overnight</strong> article in Reflex.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If your results are to call maintenance or to reboot a system we are not familiar with, use the POS or Hardware maintenance number in the spreadsheet to contact someone to assist in those endeavors, or the resolution.</p>\r\n<p>Until we have a better process in Reflex, create an e-mail&nbsp; as you would with the description in the normal CST Overnight ticket and send it to <a href=\"mailto:servicedesk@cstbrands.com\">servicedesk@cstbrands.com</a> (please copy Debra and&nbsp;David on all emails).&nbsp; Make sure you clearly identify the unbranded location in your e-mail. This will alert The CST Helpdesk to the issue that you worked on when they open in the morning.</p>\r\n<p>Please let your supervisor know if you have any questions.</p>', '2015-07-08 11:00:24', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-04 11:52:47', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Informat