(361, 'Gempay Scheme Fee', '<p>As part of the Gempay project, Retailers with only 1 Point of Sale were issued with a spare (back up) Gempay terminal at Valero&rsquo;s expense.&nbsp; The decision was taken to deploy these spare terminals in lieu of a maintenance contract with HTEC.&nbsp; Sites that have more than 1 Point of Sale who experience an issue with their terminal, would still be able to carry out transactions on their other Point of Sale whilst a replacement terminal was being organised.</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #c7c7c7; height: 172px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" border=\"1\" width=\"325\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;No. of Terminals</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">Static Scheme Fee per month</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;1 + 1 backup</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&pound;95</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">2</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&pound;135</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">3</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&pound;170</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">4</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&pound;205</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">5</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&pound;240</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">6</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&pound;275</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">7</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&pound;310</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-08-10 09:16:51', 'l7d23b', '2015-08-10 09:25:07', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information for Gempay scheme fees', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(362, 'Barclaycard contingency system test', '<p>Barclay\'s will&nbsp;be undertaking a scheduled switch to their contingency system on Sunday 13<sup>th</sup> September 2015 between 02:00 and 03:00BST. We will remain on the contingency system for one week changing back to our primary on Sunday 20<sup>th</sup> September 2015 between 02:00 and 03:00BST.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>BST (British Summer Time)= GMT+1</p>\r\n<p>Local hours impacted&nbsp;19:00 - 20:00 CST</p>\r\n<p><strong>PLEASE NOTE: - As it is impossible to predict the exact time of switchover of the systems they have allowed an hour&rsquo;s window to accommodate this piece of work &ndash; in normal circumstances the actual switch should take less than 15 minutes and during this time you will experience a loss of the authorisation service</strong>.</p>\r\n<p>Should you experience any problems outside of the aforementioned windows or require further information please contact the BB Technical Helpdesk on 01604 529655</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-08-10 10:23:10', 'l7d23b', '2015-09-04 08:42:04', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Barclaycard contingency system test', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(363, 'UK Outage - Voicemail Procedure', '<table style=\"width: 825px; border-color: #002878; background-color: #1f287a; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; height: 16px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"15\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\">Please note. This article contains 2 procedures to follow when enabling and disabling the outage message.</span></h3>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Enabling the outage message locally</h3>\r\n<p>Press the UK OUTAGE button</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/ukOutage.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"389\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Enabling the Voicemail message on the UK switch</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Dial<strong> 9 011 44 207 513 3444<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>You&rsquo;ll be now asked for your ext. Please press<strong> <strong><strong>* 3805 #</strong>&nbsp;<br /><br /></strong></strong></li>\r\n<li>Enter Password: <strong>12345 #<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Enable the voicemail meessage<br /><br /></strong>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Choose Setup Options: <strong>Option 4<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Change Greetings: <strong>Option 1<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>To Record in UK english: <strong>O</strong><strong>ption 2<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Press 1. This enables the outage message and allows customers to leave messages. <br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Login to the voice mail system</strong><br /><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Click this link: <a href=\"https://ucmukldhq01/ccmuser\">https://ucmukldhq01/ccmuser</a><br /><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-roman;\">\r\n<li>If you encounter the following page:<br /><img src=\"upload/securitypage.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"574\" height=\"242\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click:<br /><img src=\"upload/securitypage1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"320\" height=\"27\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The following page will display:<br /><img style=\"margin-right: 20px; margin-left: 20px;\" src=\"upload/securitypage2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"361\" height=\"237\" /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /><br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Login with:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Username = <strong>TXAMCC</strong></li>\r\n<li>Password = <strong>12345<br /><br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The following page will display:<br /><img src=\"upload/cisco1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"150\" /><strong><br /><br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>To enable the voicemail forwarding, select <strong>Voicemail</strong> from the dropdown.<img src=\"upload/cisco2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"466\" height=\"136\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Press Save.</strong><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a id=\"disable\"></a>Disabling the outage message locally</h3>\r\n<p>Press <strong>LOGOUT</strong></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><img src=\"upload/outageLogout.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"600\" height=\"389\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Disabling the Voicemail message on the UK switch</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Login to the voice mail system<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Click this link: <a href=\"https://ucmukldhq01/ccmuser\">https://ucmukldhq01/ccmuser</a><br /><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-roman;\">\r\n<li>If you encounter the following page:<br /><img src=\"upload/securitypage.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"643\" height=\"271\" /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Click<br /><img src=\"upload/securitypage1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"320\" height=\"27\" /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><br /><br /></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The following page will display:<br /><img src=\"upload/securitypage2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"361\" height=\"237\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Login with:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Username = TXAMCC</li>\r\n<li>Password = 12345<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Now you&rsquo;ll see the following page pop up.<img src=\"upload/cisco1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"150\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>To disable forwarding, please enter the ext <strong>85014626</strong> and press <strong>save</strong>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li><strong>Disable the Voicemail message and check messages.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Dial&nbsp;<strong>9 011 44 207 513 3444<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>You&rsquo;ll be now asked for your ext. Please press <strong>* 3805 #&nbsp;<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Enter Password: <strong>12345 #<br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Choose Setup Options: <strong>Option 4<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Change Greetings: <strong>Option 1<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>To Record in UK english: <strong>O</strong><strong>ption 2<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Press 2. </strong>This disables the outage message and prevents customers from leaving messages.<strong> <br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Check, log, and respond to any voicemails that are left on the system.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2015-08-12 10:48:48', 'l7d23b', '2015-08-20 14:50:57', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to enable the outage message for UK outages', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'https://ucmukldhq01/ccmuserhttps://ucmukldhq01/ccmuser'),
(364, 'Identifying Points of Failure', '<h4><img style=\"margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px; float: right;\" src=\"upload/ukoutagemap1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"155\" height=\"420\" /></h4>\r\n<h2>Identifying the location of the issue</h2>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Till to Terminal Issues</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Identifying</strong> - errors such as \"till link failed\" or \"EFT Unavailable\" point to a till to terminal issue.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Testing -</strong> If the site is unable to initialize sales from the till, have the site run a manual sale on the Gempay. If the sale is successful, this indicates an issue between the till and terminal.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sometimes rebooting the till and terminal can re-establish communications between the two.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If issue is on all tills/terminals, it could indicate an issue with the switch or the router.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Terminal to Communications Provider Issues</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Identifying</strong> - Failure to connect to the network is less intuitive to identify than other issues as network connectivity problems can still generate a \"Decline\" message on the Gempay even if the transaction is not hitting the switch.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Testing - </strong>If a communication test fails, begin with checking out the Digi WR44.<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Make sure the Digi has power. The power connector to the Digi has a twist-lock plug. If the plug is not twisted back into place, it can fall out. Reconnect power and advise call of the twist-lock.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the Digi has power: Check the status of the DSL light on the Digi. If the light is red, the router is not connected to the DSL. Before calling TNS (for non-MFL sites) check to make sure the line from the DSL port on the back of the Digi to the wall is connected securely.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the DSL light is red and cabling has been checked: Check the signal lights on the front of the Digi. If the site has 1 bar, they may have trouble connecting out over the backup system. There are aerials (antennas) on the back. Attempt to adjust these to get at least 2 lights.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If everything looks as it should be working, but is not: This could indicate an issue with the communication provider or beyond.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Communications Provider Issues</span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Identifying</strong>- There can be issues that affect the OLA Switch or authorizers and their card types. These issues usually present themselves as a site not being able to authorize a specific type of card or group of cards.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Testing</strong> - If a communications test passes, this could indicate an issue with the OLA Switch or the authorizers.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The chart below shows which card types are processed by which authorizers. This can be used to quickly reference if there is an issue with a specific card authorizer.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If a station or stations are reporting one specific card type declining, e.g. FleetOne, there may be an issue between UK Fuels and FleetOne.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/ukoutagemap - Copy 2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"703\" height=\"572\" /></p>\r\n<h4>To properly test communications, have the site dial the terminal in.</h4>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press the Menu button. Button in the center at the top of the keypad.</li>\r\n<li>Select Maintenance</li>\r\n<li>Select Download</li>\r\n<li>Select Connect</li>\r\n<li>This will display: Scenario 00000</li>\r\n<li>Press the OK button on the keypad.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>The Gempay will now display \"Connecting to TMS.\" After this message you will either receive \"Connection Made\" or \"No Connection.\"</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Connection Made -</strong> This will prove that the route from the terminal to the communication provider is functional.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>No Connection -</strong> This denotes an issue between the terminal and the communication provider.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">More Information</span></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Issues with specific card acceptance across multiple sites could indicate an issue between the card authorizer and card companies.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Any failure of the Communication Provider, or any node past, will cause a multi-site outage.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>*Add in manual sale procedure</p>\r\n<p>*fix typo in chart MyFuel</p>\r\n<p>*add to faq article</p>\r\n<p>*define outage severity - isolated incident</p>\r\n<p>*look up area in google maps - isolated incident</p>\r\n<p>*</p>', '2015-08-13 09:40:21', 'l7d23b', '2015-08-18 10:03:21', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how to identify an outage or point of failure at a UK site', '', 80001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(365, 'Temporary Shopping Pass Acct Lookup', '<p>If you need to get the account number for a customer that is using a temporary shopping pass. Use the following steps:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Log in to RAMS.</li>\r\n<li>Select \"H - System Control\" from the menu.</li>\r\n<li>Select \"C - ACCT NO / REF NO / TSP NO\" from the next menu.</li>\r\n<li>Enter the last 10 digits of the temporary shopping pass number 70003801<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>3025364302 </strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">in the TSP field.</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Customer number will be the last 8 digits in the account number field.</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2015-08-19 10:55:41', 'lbfb2t', '2015-08-19 14:20:57', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Method for looking up an account number for temporary shopping passes', '', 90003, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(366, 'UK Document Links', '<p>Please use this to log all chargeable requests that need to be charged back to the retailer.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://intranet.valero.com/IS/UKI1TeamSite/RetailTechnology/Shared%20Documents/34%20VCS%20Monthly%20Chargebacks%202015.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">VCS Monthly Chargebacks</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Jacqui has started to compile a list of mini keyboard requests in Sharepoint.&nbsp; Primarily so&nbsp;she can maintain a list of those that are awaiting keyboards but also so that we can keep statistics on the keyboards we provide.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://intranet.valero.com/IS/UKI1TeamSite/RetailTechnology/Shared%20Documents/33%20Mini%20Keyboard%20Request%20List.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">Keyboard Replacement Requests</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-08-24 07:35:05', 'l7d23b', '2015-08-24 07:35:05', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'UK Document Links', '', 80002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'http://intranet.valero.com/IS/UKI1TeamSite/RetailTechnology/Shared Documents/34 VCS Monthly Chargebacks 2015.xlsxhttp://intranet.valero.com/IS/UKI1TeamSite/RetailTechnology/Shared Documents/33 Mini Keyboard Request List.xlsx'),
