(370, 'Allstar One Acceptance Information', '<p>A new Allstar card has been introduced into the field called the Allstar One card. BIN: 471530.</p>\r\n<p>This is a dual-use card meaning when you swipe the card it generates a KeyFuels ISO and when you use Chip and PIN it generates an AllStar ISO.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The following issue has been resolved.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\"><strong>If the station runs linked terminals:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">The card should not have issues running on&nbsp; a linked till/terminal system. If there merchant is receiving an \"Invalid Card\" error, a ticket needs to be raised with HTEC.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left; padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\"><span style=\"color: #ccffff; text-decoration: line-through; background-color: #000000;\">22 Oct: There may have been&nbsp;a recent update that is affecting sites ability to accept this card. The card may decline immediately after swiping. Raise the issue with HTEC.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\"><strong>If the station runs standalone terminals:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">The merchant must use a different set of product codes for sales on Allstar One cards run on a standalone terminal. The product list can be found below. This issue should not affect sites that have linked tills/terminals.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: line-through;\">This may be a temporary issue that is addressed in the future.&nbsp;This article will update to reflect any new information or changes that are provided to us.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #909696; height: 740px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"224\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">101</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Unleaded&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">101</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Unleaded Regular&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">102</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Unleaded Premium</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">102</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Unleaded Super</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">104</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Unleaded Type 2</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">105</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Unleaded Type 3</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">109</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">LRP&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">121</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Regular Diesel</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">122</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Premium Diesel</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">126</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Gas Oil</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">126</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Red Diesel</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">141</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">LPG</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">301</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Lubes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">301</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Oil</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">301</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Oil 