style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">350</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Parts</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">350</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Repairs</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">380</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Service</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">391</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Car Hire</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">410</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Car Wash</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">832</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Goods Standard Rate</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">833</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #d8e2e3;\">Goods Zero Rate</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">872</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #c4cecf;\">Goods Reduced Rate</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2015-09-04 09:47:08', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-01 10:18:40', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Allstar One acceptance and product coding', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(371, 'Triple DES non-compliance', '<table style=\"border-color: #a9ffa3; height: 321px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; background-color: #d4ddff;\" border=\"1\" width=\"779\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><strong>IMPORTANT</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Update 01 Dec: </strong>We\'ve confirmed stations are receiving a 4R error as the result of the change.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><strong>Update 29&nbsp;Nov</strong>: Beginning Monday, 30th November,&nbsp;single DES&nbsp;DUKPT will be removed at the network causing anyone without triple DES pin pads to stop taking pin debit for inside sales only.&nbsp;There are about 320 sites that we were unable to contact or have not received confirmation of contact. If you receive a call inquiring about the issue please advise the site the following:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><em>\"Due to PCI compliance regulations, the encryption type&nbsp;currently used by your inside pin pad(s) has been removed from our network\'s system. Most debit cards can be run as credit until you have&nbsp;a compliant pin pad installed.\"</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">If a station advises they were not notified of the issue:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: trebuchet ms,geneva;\"><em>\"Multiple notices have been sent to your station and your distributor in the last several weeks as well as a notification on the Valero dealer portal.\"</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">If you receive a call concerning this issue, please log your call in heat with the following setup:</span></p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 112px;\" width=\"722\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>[Record Type]</td>\r\n<td><strong>6 Wholesale Request</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>[Call Type]</td>\r\n<td><strong>POS Info Request</strong></td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>[Category]</td>\r\n<td><strong>Single DES Cutoff</strong></td>\r\n<td>(please key this manually as it is not a drop down selection)</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n<p>Everything else can be coded as normal</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Associate your ticket to the Heatboard: <strong>SDES End of Life Tickets</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Update 23 Oct: First Data has granted Valero an extension to extend the SDES to TDES compliance effort to November 30th.</span></p>\r\n<p>A Letter,&nbsp;<a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Procedures\\Tripple DES Compliance\\Visa Mandate PCI-TDES Compliance Standards Update.docx\" target=\"_blank\">Visa Mandate PCI-TDES Compliance Standards Update</a>, was mailed to 748 sites and their distributors on 09/08/15.</p>\r\n<p>The distributors need to work with the sites to get their PIN pads inside switched to TDES by reprogramming the PIN pads or ordering new ones.&nbsp;If a PIN pad was injected with both DUKPT/TDES - (AKEY-PCS-BUY-06-20), a technician should be able to switch to the engine with TDES.&nbsp; If the PIN pad was injected with single des -&nbsp;(AKEY-PCS-BUY-06), a new PIN pad will need to be ordered.&nbsp; The sites are not required at this time to upgrade their entire POS system.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/pinpadbottom.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"700\" height=\"515\" /></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 90px;\">Label on pin pad showing the encryption type.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The sites that were contacted can be found in: <a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Procedures\\Tripple DES Compliance\\Valero Single DES Sites_09072015.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">Valero Single DES Sites_09072015.xlsx</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To see the sites, double click on the number to the right of the Distributor Name to get the list of their non-compliant locations that received the letter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Like the IIN&nbsp;card testing, we&rsquo;ve been asked to track all stores&nbsp;and jobbers&nbsp;that call in with questions on this letter.</p>\r\n<p>Create your ticket as follows:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>[Record Type] = <strong><em>6 Wholesale Request</em></strong></li>\r\n<li>[Call Type]&nbsp;=<strong> <em>POS Info Request</em></strong></li>\r\n<li>[Category]&nbsp;= <strong><em>Triple DES</em> </strong>(please key this manually as it is not a drop down selection).&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Everything else can be coded as normal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If the location is calling about the <strong>10/12/15</strong> cutoff date, you may offer them a special cutoff of <strong>10/21/15</strong> since they took the trouble to call in, but that is the final date for compliance.&nbsp; <strong>Note that request was made in your ticket.</strong></p>\r\n<p>If they ask about CRInDs and what is needed for their site, advise them that we are researching that and we will get back to them with the information for their installation. Please note that in your ticket as well.&nbsp;If&nbsp;a site does inquire about the CRInDs,<strong> leave the ticket open.</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you have further questions, please see David.</p>', '2015-09-11 08:03:41', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-01 07:03:07', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Triple DES non-compliance', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(372, 'Weekly VCS Alert Tool Test', '<p>Method 1:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"file:///O:/AMA-UK/WTS\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #3a4e80;\">Click here to access</span></a>&nbsp;the folder containing a pre-configured remote desktop icon that will connect directly to <strong>PEMWIN7VM05</strong>. You can either drag the icon to your desktop or access it directly from the folder.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password for the account is <strong>Xp0BgNo#<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Click OK and Log On.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Method 2:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On your desktop click on your windows button.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the search type &ldquo;Remote&rdquo; and then select &ldquo;Remote Desktop Connection&rdquo; under the programs section.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Computer dialogue, type in <strong>PEMWIN7VM05 </strong>and click connect.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The username for the account is SVC0426<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Password for the account is <strong>Xp0BgNo#<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Click OK and Log On.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>After accessing the remote server:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Open Outlook on the desktop if it is not already running (If Outlook is not open the Send SMS&nbsp;function will fail).&nbsp;<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Double Click this to launch the tool.<br /><img src=\"upload/vcsTestIcon.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"82\" height=\"107\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on the Tool tab to launch the form.<br /><img src=\"upload/vcsTestTool.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"188\" height=\"62\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click \"Send Alert\"<br /><img src=\"upload/vcsTestMessage.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"526\" height=\"285\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>To confirm the message was sent, the VCS mailbox will receive a copy of the alert.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once this process is completed, successfully or not, click this to send notification to management.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2015-09-17 09:05:52', 'l7d23b', '2015-09-17 09:54:12', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Instruction on how to perform the weekly VCS Alert tool test', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'file:///O:/AMA-UK/WTS'),
