of parts that come with MX 915 Pin Pads when order through Valero Direct Purchase', '', 10008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(374, 'Irate or Abusive UK Calls', '<p>If you have a call that degenerates to an unacceptable and/or&nbsp;abusive state, the helpdesk analyst should advise the retailer that they are being unprofessional, and please advise (<strong>using a professional tone of voice</strong>) at least <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">twice</span></strong> to &ldquo;please refrain from such language.&rdquo;&nbsp; If the behaviour continues advise the caller they should now speak with their Area Manager, and drop the line.</p>\r\n<p>If you are in a situation that you must do this, please email Debra with the details.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-09-24 09:44:47', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-22 09:21:48', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to handle escalated, irate, or abusive callers', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(375, 'FAMS Screen Changes - Revolving Terms', '<p><strong>Changes to &ldquo;K&rdquo; Screen (Customer Information Screen SCR6863)</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/fams1.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"620\" height=\"460\" /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Offered Discount is deducted from the TOTAL account balance and not the Minimum Payment Due.</li>\r\n<li>Government and OPIS accounts will not display the UPR field as they are not under Revolving Terms.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Changes to the &ldquo;B&rdquo; Screen (History Screen SCR6836)</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/fams2.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"618\" height=\"462\" /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Offered Discount is deducted from the TOTAL account balance and not the Minimum Payment Due.</li>\r\n<li>Government and OPIS Min Due balance will continue to reflect the ODIS (if applicable) as these accounts are not under Revolving Terms.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Changes to the &ldquo;VB&rdquo; Screen (Phone Payment Entry &ndash; SCR3958)</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/fams3.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"615\" height=\"457\" /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the account is past its due date &ndash; you will not see the NEW BAL LESS DISC field as the account is no longer eligible for the ODIS.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>NEW Screen &ldquo;UD&rdquo;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/fams4.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"619\" height=\"461\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Business Rules/Other Information&hellip;</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the past due amount is $100 or less, a late fee will not be assessed.</li>\r\n<li>If an account has a Min Due less than $25, the Min Due will be &ldquo;Forced&rdquo; to $25 and if the account is past due, a late fee will not be assessed.</li>\r\n<li>If an account is past due and has a returned payment, only one of the fees will be assessed at billing (greater amount).</li>\r\n<li>At charge-off, if any type of fees (late payment fee, returned check fee, interest charge, etc) applies, they will be assessed at billing.</li>\r\n<li>Total Balance minus Min Due equals UPR.</li>\r\n<li>The DBT command may not work properly due to the revolving terms when accounting applies returned payments to the accounts.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The DBT command may not debit the returned payment amount to the appropriate aging buckets on a new or an inactive account.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>o&nbsp;&nbsp; If there is more than one payment within the same billing cycle, and one of the payments is returned, the DBT command may not debit the returned payment amount to the appropriate aging buckets.</p>', '2015-10-01 06:51:07', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-01 06:51:07', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on changes to FAMS revolving terms screens', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(376, 'UK FAX/SMS Management System Change ', '<p><strong>What is happening?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The system that manages incoming and outgoing faxes and SMS messages is being upgraded.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Why?</strong></p>\r\n<p>The system that manages incoming and outgoing faxes and SMS messages needs to be upgraded in order to work correctly and to be supported by the vendor as part of the new Microsoft Exchange email system has been deployed in London and Pembroke.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>When?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tuesday 6<sup>th</sup> October &ndash; 04:00PM &ndash; 07:00PM <strong>Note</strong>: FAX / SMS service during this period will be intermittent<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>What is affected?</strong></p>\r\n<p>Anyone or any application that sends or receives FAX or SMS messages may find that the FAX or SMS takes a longer time than normal to be sent or to arrive. <strong>Note</strong>: This only affects FAX and SMS messages sent from computer systems, it does not affect any of the physical FAX machines or SMS messages sent via your mobile phone.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>What do I need to do? </strong>Unless you have a pressing need to send or receive either a FAX or SMS message in this change window then there is nothing that you need to do.&nbsp; If you do have to have access to FAX or SMS during this time period the please contact Simon Bowler on 8-585-3902.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have any issues with these after the change, please call the IS UK Helpdesk on <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">x2297<a style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: x2297\" href=\"#\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: x2297\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"\" /></a></span></p>', '2015-10-05 11:19:53', 'lbfb2t', '2015-10-05 11:19:53', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Changes to Fax/SMS UK  Systems', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(377, 'Verifone Commander on TNS Link', '<p><strong>Commander / Ruby CI&nbsp;Settings and Connections:</strong></p>\r\n<table class=\"null\" style=\"width: 757px; height: 83px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Commander IP Setup information for TNS Cisco 881</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n<table style=\"height: 78px;\" border=\"0\" width=\"168\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Isolated Payment Nic</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>IP&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.12</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Gateway</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Netmask</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;255.255.255.0</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<table style=\"height: 123px;\" width=\"221\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Device Specific Route</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Route Type&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Host</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Destination</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;204.194.125.9</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Gateway</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Netmask</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;255.255.255.255</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n<table style=\"height: 103px;\" width=\"228\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Buypass Config</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Connection Mode&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;IP</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>IP</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;204.194.125.9</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Port</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;7735</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All Commander solution installs should include a Cybera EZR</li>\r\n<li>The Isolated Payment NIC will function independently of the Cybera EZR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left; padding-left: 60px;\">o&nbsp;&nbsp; Meaning, the site can pull a table load or process credit without the Cybera EZR being online</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The Cybera Zone Router has to be configured for DHCP</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 60px;\">o&nbsp;&nbsp; The TNS Cisco router (FE2) is configured to issue an IP to the EZR</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If site is unable to pull a table download, please have the tech confirm &ldquo;SSL Enabled&rdquo; is not selected in the Commander EPS Global Configuration</li>\r\n<li>Zoom data/fax modem has to be connected to the console/aux port on the Cisco 800 series router and powered on before the Cisco router is powered on so they can synchronize</li>\r\n<li>If a site is unable to pull a parameter download (PDL), please have the tech confirm the merchant ID.&nbsp; The letters in the merchant ID have to be uppercase.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Commander&nbsp;Connections to TNS Cisco 881</h3>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/commander-cisco.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"792\" height=\"772\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Ruby CI Connections to TNS Cisco 881</h3>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/ci-cisco.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"787\" height=\"731\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-10-06 09:03:46', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-23 08:19:20', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on connecting a Commander to a TNS Link', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '');
