(380, 'Gempay How-to Videos', '<p>Completing an End of Day:</p>\r\n<p><video controls=\"controls\" width=\"820\" height=\"410\">\r\n<source src=\"upload/vids/end of day process.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" /></video></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pin pad replacement and pairing:</p>\r\n<p><video controls=\"controls\" width=\"820\" height=\"410\">\r\n<source src=\"upload/vids/Pin pad replacement &amp; pairing.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" /></video></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Terminal support and swap out process:</p>\r\n<p><video controls=\"controls\" width=\"820\" height=\"410\">\r\n<source src=\"upload/vids/Terminal Support and Swap Out Process.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" /></video></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Terminal Maintenance:</p>\r\n<p><video controls=\"controls\" width=\"820\" height=\"410\">\r\n<source src=\"upload/vids/Terminal Maintenance.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\" /></video></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-10-13 08:56:31', 'l7d23b', '2015-10-14 07:51:31', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Gempay How-to Videos', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(381, 'UK Closures/ Date changes', '<p>If you receive a call for an extension of a closure to their location (or a date change for anything), please refer them to their Area Sales Manager. We can open a ticket on our end stating we&rsquo;ve referred them and then close it afterwards please.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As there are multiple parities involved which all rely on having the same date set and &nbsp;the site may also have some contractual obligations to complete.</p>', '2015-11-05 08:00:29', 'l7d23b', '2015-11-05 08:00:29', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'UK Closures/ Date changes', '', 80001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(382, 'SageNet Satellite Change Over', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 18pt;\"><strong>SageNet Satellite Change Over</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"> Sagenet will no longer be using their satellite AMC 6. It has reached end of life. A Sagenet tech will be going out to our sites to re-point the store&rsquo;s dish to the new satellite. While the technician is there, he will upgrade the Prysm Pro to the most recent PCI compliant software as well as perform a quality assurance check of the full installation including a dial backup test.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">To facilitate credit card processing during the re-point, the technician will put the site in dial back-up mode. It is critical that the store&rsquo;s phone line is available for this time period. There will be a window of approximately 20 minutes (could be up to 60 minutes if dial backup line is not available) during the PrysmPro update that their credit terminals will not be connected to the network. The technician will work to minimize this disruption.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Once configuration is complete, the store&rsquo;s system will be back online and the technician will perform quality assurance tests to make sure everything is operating properly. &nbsp;An authorization letter is being sent out by Valero Wholesale giving Sagenet technicians authorization to complete the re-point and upgrade at no cost to the stores. &nbsp;The technicians will have this letter with them and will present it to the store.&nbsp; You can find a copy of the authorization letter <strong><a href=\"upload/spacenet-authorization-letter.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. </strong>You can find a copy of the flyer that was sent out by Sagenet <strong><a href=\"upload/sagenetvalerorepoint110215a.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Below are the steps the Sagenet Technician will do:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The technician will call and schedule the time he/she will be on-site.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Once on-site the technician will put your site into Dial backup in preparation of the re-point.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The technician will re-point the satellite antenna to the new satellite and confirm operation.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The technician will then upgrade your PrysmPro to the latest software. To expedite this procedure, we swap out the existing PrysmPro with a pre-configured unit.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The PrysmPro will communicate via the re-pointed VSAT and pull your site-specific configuration. During this time the site will not be able to process credit over dial backup or VSAT. We expect this time to be approximately 20 minutes (could be up to 60 minutes if dial backup line is not available).</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Once the PrysmPro has the specific configuration loaded the technician will perform tests to ensure normal operation.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The final step will be to perform a quality assurance check of your site.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">If the sites have any questions they can call <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">1-800-478-2722</span> or email questions to <a href=\"mailto:valero@sagenet.com\">valero@sagenet.com</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Heat Ticket Creation</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">When you get a call from a SageNet technician re-pointing a dish, please make the ticket as follows below. This is important because we will be pulling reports weekly and this will make things easier when we run the searches for the tickets.&nbsp;&nbsp; If you have any questions, please ask David.</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Record Type </strong>= Select &ldquo;6 &ndash; Wholesale &ndash; Request&rdquo;.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Call Type</strong> = Select &ldquo;Pos Info Request&rdquo;.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Category </strong>= Select &ldquo;Network Compliance&rdquo;.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Priority</strong> =Select &ldquo; Scheduled&rdquo;.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>FAQs:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Why is the satellite being retired?</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Satellites are launched into space with a defined usable life. Typically this life span is 15 years. The satellite you are operating on today is AMC6. The new Satellite is SES 2 and has a designed lifespan to 2026.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Why must I have a dial line dedicated to the network?</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">The core service is VSAT-Satellite service and the PrysmPro has an integrated dial modem to provide maximum availability. If the VSAT were to fail or have an outage, the dial modem will connect to the network so that store credit operations will continue. The switch between VSAT and Dial is controlled by the PrysmPro automatically. It is recommended the dial line be dedicated to the PrysmPro for highest availability.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong>Why do I have to upgrade my PrysmPro software?</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">PCI compliance mandates, and the Valero branded program requires, that devices pro&shy;cessing or passing credit data operate with the most recent software version. This new software meets the current requirement of PCI compliance and has enhanced monitoring capabilities.</span></p>', '2015-11-05 13:16:48', 'lbfb2t', '2017-03-23 09:00:14', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'SageNet project to repoint dishes to a new satellite.', '', 30010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:valero@sagenet.com'),
(383, 'Pre-Screen Possible Match', '<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/possible-match.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"780\" height=\"228\" /></p>\r\n<p>If you see this screen when processing a pre-screen application,</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Take down the application number and <strong>last four</strong> of the social security number and press Enter.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Read the pended script:<strong>Thank you for submitting your application; You should receive a letter within 7-10 days with detailed information about our credit decision as well as contact information for the credit reporting agency used.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li>Shift+F6 to get to the application notes screen.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the function field, type \"<strong>A</strong>\" to add a note.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the note, include the following: \"Pended, possible match, read script.\" You must include the <strong>application number</strong> and the<strong> last 4</strong> of the social.<br /><br /><img style=\"float: left; margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px;\" src=\"upload/alert5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"28\" height=\"28\" />The pended application number may begin with a 92. This denotes an old account and should be listed in your note.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<h4><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><img style=\"margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px; float: left;\" src=\"upload/alert2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"27\" />Every pended account requires a note. &nbsp;Debra receives an email on every pended&nbsp;application that does not have a note.<br /><br /><br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: 10px; margin-left: 10px; float: left;\" src=\"upload/alert2.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"27\" />Do not include the full social security number in your note.<br /></strong></span></h4>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-11-05 13:46:03', 'l7d23b', '2016-05-11 08:18:42', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on handling Possible Matches in RAMS', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(384, 'Parameter Download/Encryption Problem', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">First Data has made a change to how our profiles work.&nbsp; Basically this change is forcing everyone away from single des encryption inside.&nbsp;&nbsp; The way they have done this is when you go to set a PDL, if the site is set to DKPUT, you will get an error when you set the PDL.&nbsp; You have to set encryption to Dual Pin or Triple Des to get the flag to set.&nbsp;&nbsp; The problem with this is that it will not allow to set back to single des which could break debit if the store does not have triple des equipment.&nbsp; Mitzi is working with First data to get this changed back as this was not supposed to happen until November 30.&nbsp; So at this time, please be aware and make techs aware that if we change it, it could break debit at the site.&nbsp;&nbsp; When we get the notification this has been changed back we will let you know or provide a work around.</span></p>', '2015-11-06 08:51:10', 'lbfb2t', '2015-11-06 08:52:39', 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'First Data changed how parameter downloads are set which could break Debit.', '', 40002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(385, 'Continuous Ping', '<p>Click the Start menu and select Run or type CMD into the search box as the bottom of the Start menu.</p>\r\n<p>Alternatively, hold down the windows key on the keyboard and press the \"R\" key and type in CMD.</p>\r\n<p>This should bring up a black window.</p>\r\n<p>Type in: <strong>ping google.com -t</strong></p>\r\n<p>This will ping until stopped. To stop use: Ctrl + C.</p>', '2015-11-13 11:09:31', 'l7d23b', '2016-01-08 09:10:47', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to perform a continuous ping to test for packet loss', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(386, 'Gilbarco Passport on TNS Link', '<h3>Network Settings</h3>\r\n<table class=\"null\" style=\"width: 583px; height: 73px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Passport IP Setup information for TNSLink -&nbsp;Cisco 800 Series</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n<table style=\"height: 60px;\" border=\"0\" width=\"240\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">RV042 (Router) Settings</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>WAN IP&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.12</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>WAN Gateway</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>WAN Netmask</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;255.255.255.0</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<table style=\"height: 35px;\" width=\"267\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Passport Settings</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Connection Type</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;VSAT</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Host IP Address</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;204.194.125.9</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>IP Port</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;7735</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"Default\">Notes</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Make sure the tech uses an uppercase \"L\" in the MID on the Passport.&nbsp; ex..&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">L</span>348XXXXXX001<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=346\" target=\"_blank\">TNSLink </a>will connect to the <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=128\" target=\"_blank\">Linksys RV042</a> via the Internet port. This will connect to FE LAN 0 on the TNSLink.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Passport FPX to TNSLink cutover steps<br /></strong>Follow these steps for&nbsp;an almost&nbsp;zero downtime cutover.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Connect TNSLink to Internet.</li>\r\n<li>Call ICC to confirm connectivity after OK and VPN lights are green.</li>\r\n<li>Connect TNSLink to RV042.</li>\r\n<li>Program RV042.</li>\r\n<li>Program Passport settings and save when there\'s no credit being passed.</li>\r\n<li>Once Passport settings are saved, it should switch to the TNSLink with&nbsp;no interruption.</li>\r\n<li>The FPX can now be removed.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p class=\"Default\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"Default\">Connection Configuration</h3>\r\n<p class=\"Default\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/passport-cisco.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"770\" height=\"463\" /></p>', '2015-11-20 13:52:27', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-23 08:17:35', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on connecting a Passport to a TNS Link', '', 10006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=346'),
(387, 'Contactless Pin Pad Information', '<table style=\"height: 97px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"642\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #dee8ff;\" colspan=\"2\"><strong>Campaign Documents</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #dee8ff;\">Letter to stations:</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #dee8ff;\"><a href=\"upload/docs/Contactless Payments.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Contactless Payments.pdf</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #dee8ff;\">FAQs to station:</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #dee8ff;\"><a href=\"upload/docs/Contactless%20Payment FAQs JM.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Contactless Payment FAQs JM.pdf</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #dee8ff;\">Internal Spreadsheet</td>\r\n<td style=\"background-color: #dee8ff;\"><a href=\"http://intranet.valero.com/IS/UKI1TeamSite/RetailTechnology/Shared%20Documents/Forms/AllItems.aspx?RootFolder=%2FIS%2FUKI1TeamSite%2FRetailTechnology%2FShared%20Documents%2FContactless%20Pinpads&amp;FolderCTID=0x0120001165C34A38806A46A5C77AC14E2D525C&amp;View={136500BB-A5ED-48F4-B4E7-B90C309142E4}\" target=\"_blank\">Contactless.xlsx</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong>: Any site that participated in the pilot for the contactless rollout will not be charged the&nbsp;&pound;150.00 +VAT for the enabling fee. Please see the table at the bottom of the article&nbsp;to see the sites exempted from the fee.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.&nbsp; Create a Heat ticket with the following info:</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #bdbdbd; height: 97px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"844\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;Problem Statement:&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 350px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Site calling to request contactless pin pad(s). <br /></span></span>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Requested By:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Contact Phone:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Current # of contactless pads already on site: </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Requested # of pin pads:</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Advise site of a one time fee of &pound;150.00 +VAT&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">per pin pad to be installed or activated</span>.</strong></span></span><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><br /></span></strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;Record Type:</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">11 UK - Request</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;Call Type:</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">UK Term Req</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;Category:</span></td>\r\n<td><strong><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Contactless</span></strong></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">This will need to be keyed&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;Priority:</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Standard 3</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">&nbsp;Solution Description:</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Date Month Initials:&nbsp;Request email sent.</span></td>\r\n<td><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Only add&nbsp;after the email has actually been sent.</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2. Open a ticket with HTEC detailing same information.</p>\r\n<p><br />3.&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:Major, Chris?CC=VCS Support&amp;Subject=Contactless%20Order&amp;Body=Ticket%20Number%3A%20%0A%0ASite%20ID%3A%20%0A%0ARequested%20By%3A%20%0A%0AContact%20Phone%3A%20%0A%0A%23%20of%20contactless%20pads%20already%20on%20site%3A%20%0A%0ARequested%20%23%20of%20pin%20pads%3A%20%0A\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to send the request email</a>.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<p>4.&nbsp; Leave your ticket open.</p>\r\n<p><br />5.&nbsp; <strong>Advise the site that contactless deployment will start in</strong> <span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Jan 2016</strong></span>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>These sites will not be charged the fee to enable.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 317px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"589\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 64px; background-color: #dedede;\" width=\"64\">CallID</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 64px; background-color: #dedede;\" width=\"64\">Soldto</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 64px; background-color: #dedede;\" width=\"80\">SiteID</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 64px; background-color: #dedede;\" width=\"198\">Site Name</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447053</td>\r\n<td>431006</td>\r\n<td>886039</td>\r\n<td>NORTHWICK SERVICE STATION</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447055</td>\r\n<td>431007</td>\r\n<td>886054</td>\r\n<td>GENERAL GARAGE</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447056</td>\r\n<td>431351</td>\r\n<td>887011</td>\r\n<td>WESTGATE SERVICES</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447057</td>\r\n<td>431005</td>\r\n<td>886286</td>\r\n<td>CHELTENHAM S/STN</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447061</td>\r\n<td>430906</td>\r\n<td>251645</td>\r\n<td>MALVERN SPRINGS S/S</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447065</td>\r\n<td>430925</td>\r\n<td>254644</td>\r\n<td>LEDBURY ROAD</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447066</td>\r\n<td>430907</td>\r\n<td>252315</td>\r\n<td>ST. STEPHENS S/STN</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447069</td>\r\n<td>430924</td>\r\n<td>251466</td>\r\n<td>COMMANDERY S/STN</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1447070<