(388, 'Prysm Configuration Login Information', '<ul>\r\n<li>IP 192.168.86.1</li>\r\n<li>Port 8182</li>\r\n<li>Subnet 255.255.255.0</li>\r\n<li>Gateway 192.168.86.2&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>User ID: admin</li>\r\n<li>Pass: p@$$w0rd</li>\r\n</ul>', '2015-12-01 10:04:25', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-23 09:00:29', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Prysm Configuration Login Information', '', 30010, 'Tech Support 2', 'N', ''),
(389, 'Pin Pad Encryption Information', '<ol>\r\n<li>For Mx8xx series PINpads they would be running RFS18 OS and they should have been injected with RSA key pairs at factory needed for remote key injection. If these PINpads have been in use for a while it is very unlikely neither has happened. So in this case on site key loading cannot be done by a VASC.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>For the Mx9xx on-site key loading can be done by a VASC<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>For PP1000SE on-site key loading to 3DES cannot be done and the unit has to be swapped.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2015-12-01 10:06:41', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-01 10:06:41', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Pin Pad Encryption Information', '', 10008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(390, 'Buypass Peak Season Freeze', '<p>The FDC Peak Season Freeze is required to stabilize our production environments during our busiest time of the year, in order to provide the best service possible to our customers. Therefore it is necessary to enforce limits on change activity in the production environments.\\</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The 2015 peak season freeze period runs from November 20th 2015 through January 4<sup>th</sup> 2016.&nbsp; During this period we will have very limited ability to make network changes.&nbsp; The following dates are &ldquo;Hard Freeze&rdquo; zones and there will be no Network changes allowed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>** Peak Season No Change Periods **</p>\r\n<p><strong>November 25 through November 30 </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>December 18 through December 26</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As a result of the First Data 2015 Freeze schedule, Bank FIID changes are affected by the freeze schedule. Please see below for a description of the impacted changes and dates of impact. There will be changes scheduled through the change window but suspended during the NO CHANGE Period.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>BANK ODFI Updates</em></strong> - All adds and changes to bank FIID\'s including DFA acquirer ID&rsquo;s, changes or additions of encryption keys and any other change to the BANK FIID.</p>\r\n<p>Merchant profile updates and Bank FIID Conversions. This also includes BANK FIID conversions on merchant profiles or mass updates for merchant profiles.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please see below for change dates through the freeze period including the deadline for submitting changes to Data Managers via Service Desk RRs. The request deadlines are fixed and there will be no exceptions. For any BANK FIID conversion requests outside the change windows, the request must be completed by building a new merchant profile on the correct FIID. Any updates to merchant profiles outside the change windows must be completed via BOS/AIS or Buypass Tools</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Dates for Weekly FIID updates </strong></p>\r\n<p>11/16/2015 (Monday) &ndash; BANK ODFI &amp; Extproc updates (Request deadline Wednesday, 11/11/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>11/16/2015 (Monday) - Merchant Updates and FIID Conversions (Request deadline Friday, 11/13/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>11/23/2015 (Monday) &ndash; NO CHANGES</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>11/30/2015 (Monday) &ndash; BANK ODFI &amp; Extproc updates (Request deadline Wednesday, 11/18/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>11/30/2015 (Monday) - Merchant Updates and FIID Conversions (Request Friday, deadline 11/20/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12/07/2015 (Monday) &ndash; BANK ODFI &amp; Extproc updates (Request deadline Wednesday, 12/02/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12/07/2015 (Monday) - Merchant Updates and FIID Conversions (Request Friday, deadline 12/04/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12/14/2015 (Monday) &ndash; BANK ODFI &amp; Extproc updates (Request deadline Wednesday, 12/09/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12/14/2015 (Monday) - Merchant Updates and FIID Conversions (Request deadline Friday, 12/11/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12/21/2015 (Monday) &ndash; NO CHANGES</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>12/28/2015 (Monday) &ndash; NO CHANGES</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>01/04/2016 (Monday) &ndash; BANK ODFI and Extproc updates (Request deadline Wednesday, 12/16/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>01/04/2016 (Monday) - Merchant Updates and FIID Conversions (Request deadline Friday, 12/18/2015 11:00 am CT)</p>', '2015-12-01 10:20:35', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-01 10:20:35', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Buypass Peak Season Freeze', '', 40002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(391, 'VeriFone Vx520 Installation Instructions', '<p><a href=\"upload/docs/Vx520_VALERO.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Full reference guide for VX520 can be found here.</a></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Verify the dealer has received all supplies, which should include the following:</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>VeriFone Vx520 Terminal and power cord<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Verify the address that is printed on the VeriFone Vx520 terminal receipt paper is the dealer you are speaking with on the phone<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Verify the 13 digit merchant id number matches with the merchant id in the RAMS system. The 13 digit merchant id number is located on the merchant/dealer to alias cross reference field (format is <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">JS</span>XX XXXXXX 001)<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Instruct dealer to print &lsquo;system configuration report&rsquo; (<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">page 42</span> of the Reference Guide)&nbsp;<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/5204.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"440\" height=\"510\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Instruct dealer to perform an &ldquo;end of day&rdquo; close before disconnecting the Omni 3750 or Vx570 terminal (page 44 of the Reference Guide)&nbsp;<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/5202.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"442\" height=\"549\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Instruct dealer to write their new 6 digit merchant id number on sticker located on bottom of the new Vx520 terminal<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Assist the dealer with connecting the new VeriFone Vx520 terminal<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Please follow the steps below in order to setup the Vx520 to work with SageNet &amp; TNS:&nbsp;<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SageNet Prysm</span><br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>HOST 204.194.125.009</li>\r\n<li>PORT#7735</li>\r\n<li>TERM <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">192.168.0010<a style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 192.168.0010\" href=\"#\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 192.168.0010\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></a></span>.020\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>***For sites with a second terminal, the TERM IP is 192.168.001.021***</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>GWAY 192.168.001.254</li>\r\n<li>MASK 255.255.255.000<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">TNSLink<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>HOST 204.194.125.009</li>\r\n<li>PORT#7735</li>\r\n<li>TERM 172.016.021.013\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>***For sites with a second terminal, the TERM IP is 172.016.021.014***</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>GWAY 172.016.021.001</li>\r\n<li>MASK 255.255.255.000<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Attach the power cable to the Vx520 terminal, and then connect the other end to a wall outlet.</li>\r\n<li>Go into &lsquo;Manager Function&rsquo;</li>\r\n<li>Password is 123456</li>\r\n<li>Go into &lsquo;Tech Setup&lsquo;</li>\r\n<li>Password is 53484C (to get the C, press 2 and the alpha key 3 times)</li>\r\n<li>Look for &lsquo;Comm Configuration&rsquo;</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow key to the right of &lsquo;Comm Configuration&rsquo;</li>\r\n<li>Look for &lsquo;COMBO&rsquo;.</li>\r\n<li>Press the arrow key next to &lsquo;COMBO&rsquo;</li>\r\n<li>Press the key next to &lsquo;IP ADDRESS&rsquo; and follow the prompts</li>\r\n<li>Connect the CAT-5 cable to the ETH on the back of the Vx520. Connect the other end of the cable to LAN 1 port of the Prysm or Port 0 of the Cisco 881 router.</li>\r\n<li>Then press the red X key twice to return to main menu<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Instruct dealer to follow these steps to perform a comm test.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/5203.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"441\" height=\"564\" /></li>\r\n<li>Instruct dealer to set up fuel prices (page 48 of the Reference Guide)&nbsp;<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/5204.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"442\" height=\"700\" /></li>\r\n<li>After installation is complete, please instruct the dealer to place the Vx570 terminal, PINpad, power cord and cables in the box the new equipment came in. UPS will be by within 3 to 5 working days with call tag in hand to pick up the old equipment.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2015-12-01 10:56:32', 'l7d23b', '2017-09-25 08:56:11', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'VeriFone Vx520 Installation Instructions', '', 10012, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '');
