(393, 'VPS System Guide', '<p>The Wholesale Technical Support (WTS) department receives the signed receipts (hard copies) by mail, email and/or fax from the Valero fuel stations.&nbsp; Once they are received, the agents on the &ldquo;swing shift&rdquo; log and record the receipt into the appropriate log spreadsheet.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Often times the fuel station that sent in the signed receipt will call the WTS help desk to verify if it was received or to see why it was requested.&nbsp; Previously, the WTS department used RAMS to look up a retrieval request and verify if it was marked as received.&nbsp; Beginning in July 2015, that system was moved to an in-house online database for quicker and easier look-up and documenting.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Of the VPS System, the WTS department primarily uses the &ldquo;Chargeback and Retrievals&rdquo;/Dispute Details section.&nbsp; This is where the details and notes for a retrieval request can be located.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776695\"></a>Explanation of hardcopies</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Whenever a customer makes an inside purchase at the fuel station the receipt that is produced is referred to as a &ldquo;hardcopy&rdquo;.&nbsp; Valero fuel stations are required to obtain a signature on all inside credit transactions that are $25.00 and above.&nbsp; If the sale is less than $25.00 then the store is not required by Valero Payment Services to obtain a signature.&nbsp; The $25.00 limit is referred to as the &ldquo;Small Credit Amount&rdquo;.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Hardcopies (may also be referred to as &ldquo;retrievals&rdquo; by the WTS department) are requested by our processor, First Data, or the issuing bank of the card.&nbsp; The retrievals are entered systematically into VPS and the request is sent to the distributor (jobber) for that station. The reasons may vary on why VPS is receiving the hardcopy request but typically the reasons are the customer is disputing the sale or the customer is requesting a copy for their records.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Accessing the System</h2>\r\n<p>In order to access the retrieval system, you must be on your PC workstation located in the WTS department.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From your PC:</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/desktop_icon.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"59\" height=\"73\" /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Navigate to your desktop</li>\r\n<li>Double-click the RAMS_VPS desktop icon</li>\r\n<li>If you receive a page that says &ldquo;There is a problem with this website&rsquo;s security certificate&rdquo;, click on &ldquo;Continue to this website (not recommended).&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" width=\"80%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If you do not have the desktop icon, please speak with your supervisor.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You should now be on the login page for the VPS Retrieval System:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/signin_page.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"272\" height=\"245\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you are on your workstation PC, the &ldquo;Username&rdquo; field should already be populated with your L number.&nbsp; If the L number in the Username field is correct, click on &ldquo;Sign In&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You will now be directed to the VPS System home page.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From the home screen you can choose from one of the three pages under the VPS Navigation bar on the left:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Chargeback and Retrievals<img style=\"float: right; margin-right: 20px; margin-left: 20px;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/navbar.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"251\" height=\"113\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Merchant Account Maintenance-Research only<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VPS Reporting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2>VPS Navigation &ndash; Chargeback and Retrievals</h2>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776698\"></a>Introduction</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;Chargeback and Retrievals&rdquo; section is the main part of the system that WTS uses in dealing with chargebacks and retrievals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This page has five different tabs which house different information:<img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/chargebackscreen.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"528\" height=\"154\" /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Dispute Batches<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Batch Review<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Dispute Details<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Dispute Entry<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Dispute Recap</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Dispute Batches Screen</h3>\r\n<p>This screen is a summary of the files that Valero Payment Services receives from First Data (Clientline) and American Express for credit card chargebacks and hardcopy requests.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Files for each date are referred to as a &ldquo;batch&rdquo; and include their own batch number.&nbsp; You can click on each row in the table to view details for that date.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Batch Review Screen</h3>\r\n<p>The Batch Review Screen is connected to the Dispute Batches Screen.&nbsp; Once you click on a batch from the Dispute Batches screen it will take you to this screen.&nbsp; This screen shows you the masked card numbers and invoice details.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Dispute Details Screen</h3>\r\n<p>This is the main screen used by WTS to research credit card chargeback and retrieval request details.&nbsp; This screen includes search criteria and credit card transaction details for each chargeback and retrieval.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><em>How to locate retrieval information</em></span></h3>\r\n<p><strong>Step # 1</strong>: Enter your search criteria in the Search Criteria field.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The search criteria allows up to 4 filters to narrow your search for the chargeback/retrieval you are researching:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Required Criteria (Batch date, Invoice date, Rtrvl request date, Settlement Date)</li>\r\n<li>Criteria 2, 3, and 4 (see table below)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\" width=\"638\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Search Criteria Options</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"213\">\r\n<p><strong>Option</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p><strong>Selection</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p><strong>Explanation</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td rowspan=\"4\" width=\"213\">\r\n<p><strong>Required Criteria</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>(this field must be filled in)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Batch Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Batch date that the chargeback occurred on.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Invoice Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Date the transaction occurred</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Rtrvl Rqst Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Date VPS requested the hard copy from the station</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Settlement Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Settlement Date the charge paid to the Valero station</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td rowspan=\"17\" width=\"213\">\r\n<p><strong>Criteria 2, 3 and 4</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Account (%)</p>\r\n<p>Example search:</p>\r\n<p>%1234&nbsp;&nbsp; - or &nbsp; - 1234%</p>\r\n<p>4%0061 &ndash; or &ndash; 42%</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>The % symbol can be used as a wildcard search query. If the full card # is not known then using the % will allow you to search with just the partial card #. &nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Batch Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Batch date of chargeback</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Card (%)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Card # (<strong>Valero cards only</strong>)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Card Type (%)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Visa, MasterCard, etc.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Dealer (%)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Store&rsquo;s dealer #</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Dispute Amount</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Amount being disputed</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Dispute Status</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Status is posted or unposted. If dispute is still in an &ldquo;unposted&rdquo; status, the accounting group can make adjustments or changes. Once it is under &ldquo;posted&rdquo; no adjustments can be made.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Invoice Amount</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Transaction amount</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Invoice Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Date of transaction</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Invoice Number (%)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Transaction invoice #</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Last action</p>\r\n<p>Example: chargeback, reversal request, etc.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Last action taken on the dispute</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Merchant (%)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Jobber #</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Merchant ID (%)</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Bypass # or Alias #</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Operator ID</p>\r\n<p>Example: Operator ID for First Data is #FD</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 199px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>ID of who ordered hard copy</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Rtrvl Rqst Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Date hard copy request was submitted by VPS</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Rtrvl Status</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226px; background-color: #dae6ed;\" width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Requested, Accepted, Rejected, Reissued, and Closed</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"226\">\r\n<p>Settlement Date</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"199\">\r\n<p>Settlement Date of the transaction</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you have entered your search criteria, click on &ldquo;search&rdquo;.&nbsp; The system will bring up all results that match your criteria:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/search criteria example.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"744\" height=\"175\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Helpful Hints</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In the &ldquo;Required Criteria&rdquo; field, it&rsquo;s better if you choose a &ldquo;From&rdquo; and &ldquo;Thru&rdquo; date just to broaden your search query.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The % symbol can be used as a wildcard search query. &nbsp; &nbsp; If only a partial number of your search query is known (i.e. account #, jobber #, Bypass #, etc) then the % symbol can be used to search with just the partial number.</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If you use the Settlement Date in the Required Criteria field, search under the previous business date instead of the Settlement Date that appears on the MSR&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; All headers (InvDate, Account, etc) allow searching by ascending/descending order by clicking on that header.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step # 2</strong>: Select the correct transaction from the populated results</p>\r\n<p>From the results that populate on the right side of the search criteria, left click on the row that contains the information you are trying to locate.&nbsp; Each row is highlighted in a shade of light blue when you hover over it.&nbsp; The search results show columns for:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Invoice Date<img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/search results.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"555\" height=\"213\" /><br /></strong>&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Account (card #)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Invoice Number<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Amount<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Merchant ID<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Merchant<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Dealer #<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Act (action taken)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Status</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step # 3</strong>: Review chargeback details and notes</p>\r\n<p>Once you have selected your desired transaction, full details including recently added notes and actions will appear on the notes section of the page:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/notes section.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"790\" height=\"327\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>This section includes all details concerning the chargeback/dispute (invoice number, invoice date, masked account number, etc.) and information regarding the station (jobber/dealer number, site address and phone number and processor number).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The lower right hand box stores the last actions taken on the chargeback/dispute.&nbsp; This will show all actions from the initial dispute to the chargeback and/or reversal.&nbsp; To expand the notes on each action, left click on that row and it will display a pop-up box with information concerning that action:</p>\r\n<p><em><br /></em><em><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/dispute action.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"352\" height=\"276\" /></em></p>\r\n<h4><em>&nbsp;</em><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/action%20highlighted.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"413\" height=\"210\" /></h4>\r\n<h4>&nbsp;</h4>\r\n<h4><span style=\"font-size: 24pt;\"><em>&nbsp;&gt;</em></span></h4>\r\n<h4><em>&nbsp;</em></h4>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;Oper&rdquo; ID column displays who entered the action.&nbsp; The standard codes are:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 23px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" border=\"1\" width=\"658\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 624px; background-color: #284c99;\" colspan=\"5\" width=\"624\">\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><strong>Operator ID</strong></span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"137\">\r\n<p><strong>#AX</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\">\r\n<p><strong>#FD</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"137\">\r\n<p><strong>SYS</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"118\">\r\n<p><strong>L Number</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"128\">\r\n<p><strong>Initials</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"137\">\r\n<p>American Express</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\">\r\n<p>First Data</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"137\">\r\n<p>System Generated</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"118\">\r\n<p>Agent&rsquo;s L#</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"128\">\r\n<p>Agent&rsquo;s initials</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you have reviewed the information from the dispute action, click on &ldquo;cancel&rdquo; to navigate back to the notes screen.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><em>Entering a note</em></h4>\r\n<p>To enter a note on the dispute details screen, click on the &ldquo;Enter Dispute Note&rdquo; button:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/dispute%20button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"385\" height=\"79\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You will be presented with the following screen:</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/create%20a%20note.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"526\" height=\"254\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For the purpose of WTS the &ldquo;Retention Code&rdquo; will always be &ldquo;Temporary&rdquo;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If the store calls in with an update (unable to locate receipt, for example) then WTS can enter the note here. Updates posted here are purely for noting purposes for the accounting group records.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once you have finished typing in your note in the description field click on &ldquo;Submit&rdquo;.&nbsp; You can also click on &ldquo;Cancel&rdquo; should you need to exit the note without saving.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once a note is submitted it cannot be changed or deleted.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><a name=\"_Toc435776704\"></a><em>Attaching a PDF or Image</em></h4>\r\n<p>If you have a document (PDF or Image only) that you would like to attach to the chargeback/dispute, click on the &ldquo;Attach Dispute Document&rdquo;.&nbsp; This will bring up the attach dispute document window:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/attach button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"389\" height=\"77\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/vps/attach screen.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"677\" height=\"385\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To attach a document: select attachment source &gt; WTS.&nbsp; On the attachment type select your desired type, which are Data Warehouse Query, Bank Docs, and Transaction history.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Enter your description (if needed) and then select Add Files &gt; choose your document &gt; click on OK &gt; select Start Upload.&nbsp; Once the upload is complete click on close. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; WTS does not use the &ldquo;Edit Dispute Detail&rdquo; button or the &ldquo;Select an Action&rdquo; menu.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><em>Accessing Merchant Account Maintenance from the Dispute Details Screen</em></h4>\r\n<p>If you wish to review the Merchant Account Maintenance screen of the jobber/dealer that you currently have pulled up in the Dispute Details screen, click on the link for either the jobber number or the dealer number that are both underlined. Clicking on the jobber number pulls up the jobber record and clicking on the dealer number pulls up the dealer record.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To get back to the Dispute Details screen, use the back arrow &nbsp;on the top left hand corner.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><em>Current list of chargeback codes</em></h4>\r\n<table width=\"643\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\" width=\"643\">\r\n<p><strong>Chargeback Codes (article # 126 in Reflex)</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\" width=\"643\">\r\n<p><strong>Valero Sales Guide Violations</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p>Code #</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"245\">\r\n<p><strong>Reason</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"319\">\r\n<p><strong>Explanation</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"245\">\r\n<p>Late Presentment</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"319\">\r\n<p>Any invoice presented more than 25 days after transaction date.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>2</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"245\">\r\n<p>Insta-Credit Invoice Violation</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"319\">\r\n<p>Insta-credit invoice does not contain required informatio