ction posted as a purchase.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>67</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\" width=\"565\">\r\n<p>Non-fuel purchase on a Fuel only card</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>68</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\" width=\"565\">\r\n<p>Terminated Vehicle</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>69</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\" width=\"565\">\r\n<p>Invalid Vehicle</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>82</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\" width=\"565\">\r\n<p>Voyager Cost Plus Pricing</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>88</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\" width=\"565\">\r\n<p>Outside EMV Counterfeit Card</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>89</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\" width=\"565\">\r\n<p>Outside EMV Lost/Stolen Card Non-receipt</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"4\" width=\"643\">\r\n<p><strong>Crind Transactions</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>90</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"251\">\r\n<p>CRIND Transaction - Preauth Limits</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"313\">\r\n<p>CRIND transaction exceeding preauthorization limits.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>91</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"251\">\r\n<p>CRIND Transaction - Software</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"313\">\r\n<p>CRIND transaction for failure to update POS software.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>95</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"251\">\r\n<p>Outside EMV Counterfeit Card</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"313\">\r\n<p>Valero Responsibility</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>96</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"251\">\r\n<p>Outside EMV Lost/Stolen Card Non-receipt</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"313\">\r\n<p>Valero Responsibility</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>98</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"251\">\r\n<p>CRIND Transaction - Skim/Clone Card</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"313\">\r\n<p>CRIND transaction on a skim/clone card - Valero responsibility.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">\r\n<p><strong>99</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\" width=\"251\">\r\n<p>CRIND Transaction - Valero</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"313\">\r\n<p>CRIND chargebacks that are the responsibility of Valero.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"79\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td width=\"245\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td width=\"6\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td width=\"313\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Dispute Entry Screen</h3>\r\n<p>The Dispute Entry Screen is used by the accounting department to enter chargebacks and/or retrieval requests.&nbsp; WTS does not use this screen.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Dispute Recap Screen</h3>\r\n<p>The Dispute Recap Screen is a recap of all the chargebacks and reversals for that day&rsquo;s batch.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>VPS Navigation - Merchant Account Maintenance</h2>\r\n<p>The Merchant Account Maintenance Screen details all information for the jobber and/or dealer.&nbsp; This screen is the same information as it is from the RAMS application.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Note:</strong></p>\r\n<p>The Merchant Account Maintenance Screen is &ldquo;View only&rdquo;, no changes can be made.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776710\"></a>Merchant Information Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Merchant Information Screen is the equivalent of the Merchant Account Screen in the VPS application.&nbsp; This screen displays the jobber or dealer&rsquo;s information, including:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jobber name/Dealer name</li>\r\n<li>Company address</li>\r\n<li>Company phone number and</li>\r\n<li>Settlement Method (if on DTN, for example)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776711\"></a>Notes Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The notes screen shows all the notes from the RAMS application.&nbsp; Merchant notes still have to be created from the RAMS application and not in VPS.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776712\"></a>History Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The History Screen shows batch totals for jobber.&nbsp; You can double-click on the date you would like to see details for in the populated table.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><a name=\"_Toc433966014\"></a><a name=\"_Toc430088125\"></a><strong>Figure </strong><strong>12: History Screen Expanded</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776713\"></a>Discount &amp; Fees Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Discount &amp; Fees shows the discount and fees amounts from that store&rsquo;s MSR.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776714\"></a>Cross Reference Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This screen shows all the stores merchant numbers (BC0 number, WEX MID, MID (TP/L3/VX) and Bypass number.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776715\"></a>Memo Summary Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Memo Summary screen shows all sales for the jobber under that memo date.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776716\"></a>Transmittal History Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This screen is the equivalent of the Merchant Transmittal History screen in the RAMS application.&nbsp; This screen shows any adjustments or billings (VSAT billing, Vlink billing, CTE charges, etc).&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776717\"></a>M-T-D Sales Screen</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This screen shows a summary and breakdown of sales for the jobber for the month.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><a name=\"_Toc435776718\"></a><em>How to pull up a jobber/dealer in the Merchant Account Maintenance Screen</em></h4>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To pull up a jobber/dealer on this screen:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Type in your jobber/dealer number in the &ldquo;Command&rdquo; field as one complete number with no spaces or special characters.</li>\r\n<li>Click on &ldquo;Submit Command&rdquo;.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong> <a name=\"_Toc433966015\"></a><a name=\"_Toc430088126\"></a>Figure 13: MTD Command Line</strong></p>\r\n<table width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p><strong>Helpful Hints</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Format for entering in the jobber/dealer number is: jobberdealer, ex. 4750010146</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If you are searching for just the jobber, enter in the dealer number as all zero&rsquo;s.&nbsp; Example: 4750000000 &ndash; five digits for the jobber number and five digits for the dealer number.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc435776719\"></a>VPS Navigation &ndash; VPS Reporting</h2>\r\n<p>The VPS reporting screen is used by the VPS Accounting group to pull reports concerning chargebacks/disputes.&nbsp; The Wholesale Technical Support department does not use this screen currently.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"_Toc435776720\"></a>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776721\"></a>What is a hardcopy?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A hardcopy is the receipt from a fuel station for an inside transaction.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776722\"></a>Do all transactions require a signed receipt?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>No.&nbsp; Valero Payment Services does not require fuel stations to have a signed receipt for anything under $25.00.&nbsp; This is called the &ldquo;Small Credit Amount&rdquo;.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776723\"></a>Why are we receiving hardcopy requests?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The primary reasons for Valero Payment Services to receive a hardcopy request on a transaction is typically because a) the customer is disputing the sale or b) the customer needs a copy of the receipt.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776724\"></a>Why is a sale charged-back?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There are multiple reasons why a sale would be charged-back by VPS.&nbsp; The most common reasons are:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>No hardcopy received</li>\r\n<li>Manually entered sale with no imprint obtained</li>\r\n<li>Duplicate charge</li>\r\n<li>Crind limit violation</li>\r\n<li>AVS non-compliant (pump did not prompt for zip code)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For a full list of chargeback reasons, see &ldquo;<a href=\"#_Current_list_of\">Current list of chargeback codes</a>&rdquo;.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"_Toc435776725\"></a>What credit cards do not currently appear in the VPS System?&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The following cards are not currently available in the system:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fuelman</li>\r\n<li>Fleet One</li>\r\n<li>Proprietary/Fleet</li>\r\n</ul>', '2015-12-01 12:48:48', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-01 13:38:39', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'VPS System Guide', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '#_Current_list_of'),
(394, 'Debit 4R Declines on Sapphire', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp; There has been a problem identified with some sites getting 4R Declines after TDes&nbsp; pin pads have been installed.&nbsp;&nbsp; VeriFone has a patch that will fix this issue.&nbsp; The tech will need to call and advise them of this issue.&nbsp; VeriFone should be able to remote in and apply patch to resolve issue.&nbsp;</span></p>', '2015-12-02 14:22:05', 'lbfb2t', '2016-01-07 08:44:58', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on 4R declines with TDes pin pads and Sapphire systems', '', 10002, 'User', 'N', ''),
(395, 'Site Debrands', '<ol>\r\n<li>On the date of <strong>DEBRAND</strong>, you will change the status on RAMS to show deactivated.</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>On the command line type in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">MDEL</span></li>\r\n<li>Tab over to the code line type in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">D</span>.</li>\r\n<li>Press the enter key.&nbsp;<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>If there is an Vx570 and/or Satellite billing, make the deactivation date the last date of the billing cycle.</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>On the command line type in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">DVDD</span>.</li>\r\n<li>On the date line use the debrand date.</li>\r\n<li>Press the enter key.<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"mailto:deric.thames@firstdata.com; Gail.Gonzalez@firstdata.com?CC=Kristy.Croshaw@firstdata.com; Barbara.Hockenberry@firstdata.com; susan.torres@firstdata.com; karey.black@valero.com; mitzi.land@valero.com; israel.herrera@valero.com &amp;Subject=Valero%20Inactive%20Site&amp;Body=Please%20change%20the%20following%20site%20profile%20to%20inactive%3A%0A%0ABP%3A%20%0AJ/D%3A%20%0ASite%20Name%3A%20%0AAddress%3A%20%0ACity/State/Zip%3A%20%0APhone%3A%20%0A%0AThanks%21\">Click here to email the request to First Data.</a></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-12-03 08:39:37', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-13 09:38:57', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how to debrand a site', '', 40014, 'Tech Support 2', 'N', 'mailto:deric.thames@firstdata.com; Gail.Gonzalez@firstdata.com?CC=Kristy.Croshaw@firstdata.com; Barbara.Hockenberry@firstdata.com; susan.torres@firstdata.com; karey.black@valero.com; mitzi.land@valero.com; israel.herrera@valero.com &amp;Subject=Valero Inactive Site&amp;Body=Please change the following site profile to inactive%3A%0A%0ABP%3A %0AJ/D%3A %0ASite Name%3A %0AAddress%3A %0ACity/State/Zip%3A %0APhone%3A %0A%0AThanks%21'),
(396, 'Site Name Change', '<ol>\r\n<li>On the date of <strong>NAME CHANGE</strong>, you will change the name in RAMS.</li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>On the command line type in <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">MNAM</span></li>\r\n<li>Press the enter key.</li>\r\n<li>Input new name on Merchant/Station Name line.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=397\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to order a new plate</a>.&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Update the name on the profile in Clientline under Merchant Setup &ndash; Search Merchant and click update. Then you will need to go to Terminal Setup and set the site for a table load.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Make a copy of the email and attach to the back of the 1089 or CRM request.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-12-03 08:51:29', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-03 09:08:49', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on changing a station name', '', 40014, 'Tech Support 2', 'N', 'index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=397');
