d Gateway will be used.&nbsp; The migration will consist of updating the AMG with the Processor Connections applications, disconnecting the Gilbarco Passport from the FPX device, updating the POS with an IP &amp; host information for First Data, and then connecting the POS system to the AMG.&nbsp; The site will be using broadband primary with 4G for failover.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Site Details:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Jobber&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 85020</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Dealer&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 64568</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Address&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 969 E IH 10&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Seguin&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; TX&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 78155</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Cisco RV042 Settings:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">IP POS&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 172.16.21.12</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">GW&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 172.16.21.1</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Mask&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 255.255.255.0</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Passport Settings:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Connection Type&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; VSAT (setting is used for IP connectivity)</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">IP Address&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 204.194.125.9</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #808080;\">Port &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 7735</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-12-22 06:47:39', 'l7d23b', '2016-03-28 06:02:35', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Acumera pilot sites', '', 30007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(409, 'Weather Closing Procedure - Telephones', '<p>Recording an&nbsp;Outage Message</p>\r\n<p>From a supervisor or the outage phone do the following:</p>\r\n<p>To check the announcement, dial 5339.</p>\r\n<p>To record the announcement:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Dial the announcement access code #4. You will hear a dial tone.</li>\r\n<li>Dial the announcement&nbsp;extension, 5339. You will hear a dial tone.</li>\r\n<li>Dial 1 to begin recording</li>\r\n<li>Speak the announcement into the phone. Your message is being recorded.</li>\r\n<li>Hang up the phone to end recording.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Note: The announcement record the sound of the receiver returning to the phone. Hang up gently, press the drop button, or depress the switch hook with your finger.</p>\r\n<p>You have to wait 15 seconds before you can dial the extension 5339 to listen to your announcement.</p>\r\n<p>Scripts&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Inclement Weather Script:<em> <strong>Our offices are temporarily closed due to inclement weather. If you have a critical situation that requires immediate attention, please stay on the line and you will be prompted to leave a voicemail. Please&nbsp;leave your name and phone number and we will return your call as quickly as possible.</strong></em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2015-12-22 09:58:53', 'l7d23b', '2015-12-22 14:11:22', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Telephone Procedures', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(410, 'Valero Cards Discounting', '<p><strong>Consumer</strong></p>\r\n<p>A four cent ($.04) per gallon Gas Rebate will be applied to every gallon of fuel purchased using your Valero creditcard if the total gallons received for billing during the billing cycle are at least 50.0 gallons or more, up to 74.9 gallons. An eight cent ($.08) per gallon Gas Rebate will be applied to every gallon of fuel purchased on your Valero credit card if the total gallons received for billing during the billing cycle are at least 75.0 gallons or more, up to a maximum of 110.0 gallons received for billing during any billing cycle of the Program.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Commercial Accounts (No Drivers)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pay the cash price at the gas station where available.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Fleet Accounts</strong></p>\r\n<p>Valero Fleet Account Discounts are available to Fleet Accounts at participating locations (where the Valero Fleet Discount Site sign is displayed) and will be earned only when balances due are paid within terms.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Discount Table</strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 238px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" border=\"1\" width=\"275\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>GALLONS PURCHASED</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>PROMPT PAY DISCOUNT&nbsp;per GALLON*</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>300-499</td>\r\n<td>$.01</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>500-1,499</td>\r\n<td>$.015</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1,500-2,499</td>\r\n<td>$.02</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>2,500-3,999</td>\r\n<td>$.03</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>4,000-4,999</td>\r\n<td>$.04</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>5,000-9,999</td>\r\n<td>$.05</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>10,000-19,999</td>\r\n<td>$.06</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>20,000-49,999</td>\r\n<td>$.07</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>50,000 and over</td>\r\n<td>$.08</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2016-01-04 07:20:35', 'l7d23b', '2016-01-04 07:23:52', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on discounting for fleet, commercial, and consumer accounts', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(411, 'TNS Work Request Lead Times', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 134px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" border=\"1\" width=\"664\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"3\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"105\"><strong>Work Type</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"104\">Minor <br />5 Business Days</td>\r\n<td width=\"104\">Substantial <br />7 Business Days</td>\r\n<td width=\"111\">Major <br />12 Business Days</td>\r\n<td width=\"158\">Responsible Group</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"105\">WAN Update</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>X</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"111\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"158\">ICC</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"105\">New LVC</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>X</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"111\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"158\">IP Implementations</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"105\">LVC Change</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>X</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"111\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"158\">IP Implementations</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"105\">LAN Update</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>X</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"111\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"158\">ICC</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"105\">Testing Support</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"104\"><strong>X</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"111\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"158\">ICC/IP Implementations</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>A work request is used by TNS to initiate some sort of change that is requested. The requested change is submitted to the TNS Client Management Team (Laurie&rsquo;s Team: PaymentsClientSupport@tnsi.com), with the details and the target date. When a work request is created, the Client Manager will pass along the Work Request ID and the first available date based on the standard lead times. When ready to initiate the change, Valero along with the site will call into the TNS ICC and reference the Work request for the change to be processed. A work request ticket is only valid for 30 days.&nbsp; After 30 days, the ticket will automatically be changed to a Rescheduling Status.&nbsp; The ICC will not work on a ticket in this status.&nbsp; If a ticket goes to Rescheduling Status, the site will need to provide TNS Client Management a new date for the work and it will have to go back into the ICC work queue with the appropriate advanced notice.</p>\r\n<p><strong>WAN Update</strong> &ndash; This will be the most common and will make a change to the Broadband WAN IP&rsquo;s currently configured on the router. For Example: The site submitted the order with Dynamic DHCP routing, but they now need to use specific Static IP&rsquo;s. Or &ndash; the site initially gave us incorrect Static IP&rsquo;s and they want to use something different.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New LVC (Logical Virtual Circuit)</strong> - This will be to add routing that does not already exist in on the router. For example: the site moves to Fiscal; they will need LVCs added to route to allow access to Fiscal.</p>\r\n<p><strong>LVC Change</strong> &ndash; This should be rare, but would be to make a change to an LVC that is already built on a router</p>\r\n<p><strong>LAN Update</strong> &ndash; this should also be rare or non-existent since we are using the same 172 address for all sites (except for the first pilot sites where some have a 192).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Testing Support</strong> &ndash; Scheduling a resource to help review or test</p>\r\n<p>-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>\r\n<p><strong>Client Management </strong>= <a href=\"mailto:PaymentsClientSupport@tnsi.com\">PaymentsClientSupport@tnsi.com</a></p>\r\n<p><strong>The TNS Installation Center (ICC)</strong> is open Monday-Friday 8:30 am &ndash; 6:30 pm Eastern.&nbsp; 800-816-2273.</p>\r\n<p>If you are on hold and want to just have someone check the router and run a dbu test for basic installation, you can also try emailing them. If one of the technician&rsquo;s has a break in their call, they may be able to check the router for you and respond to the email:&nbsp; FPICC@tnsi.com</p>', '2016-01-06 10:07:15', 'l7d23b', '2016-01-06 10:11:36', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Timeframes for changes to TNSLink devices', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:PaymentsClientSupport@tnsi.com'),
(412, 'Fleet Voice Approvals', '<p>Occasionally, station attendants will call and request a &ldquo;voice approval&rdquo;.&nbsp; Usually, this is because the POS equipment is not working properly or because a customer&rsquo;s credit card was declined and the customer is requesting that they call us.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The customer must be present at the store location in order to authorize a voice approval.&nbsp; If the customer is not present, advise the clerk that we are not able to authorize the voice approval.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>To process a request for a voice approval:</em></strong><strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Ask the clerk for the card number and the customer&rsquo;s name<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Ask the clerk to let you speak to the customer</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Verify all account information with customer<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>Is the account open and not more than 30 days delinquent?</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If YES, ask the customer to let you speak to the clerk and go to step 4. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>If NO, forward the call to Level 2 and make and <strong>ICAL</strong> on the account.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>Ask the attendant</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>for his/her name</li>\r\n<li>the station name</li>\r\n<li>what the customer is buying<br /><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;1. If the customer is buying merchandise, connect the call to a Credit Analyst for approval and make an <strong>ICAL</strong>&nbsp;the&nbsp;account.<br /></em><em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;2. If the customer is buying fuel only, continue with the procedures.</em></li>\r\n<li>total price of the sale<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>Give the attendant the approval code as the last four numbers of the customer&rsquo;s account number backwards and your RAMS Operator Initials. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>Example: Account number is 9212346558 and your initials are ABC, approval number would be 8556ABC.<br /><br /></em></li>\r\n<li>Make a <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">permanent ical</span> on the account<br /><br /></li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>COMMAND: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>ICAL</strong></span></li>\r\n<li>RETN: <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>P</strong></span></li>\r\n<li>Enter Call Cause Code <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>VAPP</strong> </span>on the first line</li>\r\n<li>Document customer&rsquo;s inquiry on the second line and include the following:</li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>customer name</li>\r\n<li>attendant name</li>\r\n<li>store name</li>\r\n<li>sub (card) number being used</li>\r\n<li>type of purchase (fuel, merchandsie)</li>\r\n<li>total amount purchased</li>\r\n<li>approval code</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong><em>If a voice approval is being requested and the account is closed and/or 30 days or more delinquent:&nbsp;</em></strong><strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Tell the customer that we are not able to authorize a voice approval since the account is closed and/or 30 days or more past due.</li>\r\n<li>If the customer insists, and the account is open and gives a <strong>PTP, </strong>then authorize the voice approval.</li>\r\n<li>If the customer insists and the account is closed, forward the call to a Credit Analyst</li>\r\n<li>Make an <strong>ICAL</strong> on the account.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong><em>If a voice approval is being requested and the account is closed:</em></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Tell the customer that we will need to review the account for reinstatement in order to authorize a voice approval.</li>\r\n<li>Refer to <em>Reinstatement Procedures</em>.</li>\r\n<li>If qualifies for reinstatement, then authorize the voice approval.</li>\r\n<li>If does not qualify for reinstatement, advise the customer the account does not qualify for reinstatement and will need to deny the voice approval.</li>\r\n<li>Make an <strong>ICAL</strong> on the account.</li>\r\n<li>If customer insists on getting a voice approval, forward to a Supervisor.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong><em>If the sale is for merchandise:</em></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>A voice approval can be given for merchandise purchases up to $75.00.</li>\r\n<li>If the merchandise is over $75.00, connect the call to a Supervisor.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong><em>If a voice approval is being requested and the account does not qualify for a voice approval or the merchandise amount is over $75.00:</em></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If customer has no other means to pay, give voice approval.</li>\r\n<li>Make an <strong>SCAL</strong> on the account.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-01-07 07:53:34', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-18 11:26:25', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Fleet Voice Approvals', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '');
INSERT INTO `article` (`artid`, `arttitle`, `artbody`, `createstamp`, `usercreate`, `modstamp`, `usermod`, `pubflag`, `rfcflag`, `comment`, `usercomment`, `commentstamp`, `summary`, `triggers`, `chainid`, `rolename`, `encflag`, `linkdoctext`) VALUES
(413, 'Changing Print Size on VX520', '<ol>\r\n<li>Press F2 &amp; F4 at the same time.</li>\r\n<li>Enter SYSTEM MODE ENTRY PASSWORD.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Press 1 then alpha, alpha, 66831 and enter (Green Button)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Press 1 for Edit Parameters.</li>\r\n<li>Change the Group ID from 1 to 2.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Press 2 and enter (Green Button)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Enter GID 2 Password.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Press 1 then alpha, alpha, 66831 and enter (Green Button) twice.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Scroll down to Parameter: PRINTSIZE.</li>\r\n<li>Press 3 to change the value from 0 to 1 to make the font large on the receipt printing.</li>\r\n<li>To change Value:\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Press Backspace (Yellow Button) one time and enter 1.</li>\r\n<li>Press Enter (Green Button).</li>\r\n<li>Press Exit (Red Button).</li>\r\n<li>Press 3 to reboot to main menu.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/vx520-layout.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"461\" height=\"438\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-01-14 11:51:13', 'lbfb2t', '2016-01-14 15:52:07', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to change the print size on a VX520 terminal.', '', 10012, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(414, 'TNSLink Legacy Sites', '<p>The following sites have TNSLink routers that support the 192.168.1.X IP scheme.&nbsp; These sites were configured prior to the IP scheme change.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>vlr0800182735</li>\r\n<li>vlr2646047027</li>\r\n<li>vlr2646049528</li>\r\n<li>vlr2820010374</li>\r\n<li>vlr4092510599</li>\r\n<li>vlr3200110457</li>\r\n<li>vlr2922010516</li>\r\n<li>vlr5680010621</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700099703</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700099696</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700099702</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700099701</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700099698</li>\r\n<li>vlr6625065383</li>\r\n<li>vlr6625070011</li>\r\n<li>vlr6625070318</li>\r\n<li>too00001v (TootNTotum Lab)</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700081125</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700010132</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700081133</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700081919</li>\r\n<li>vlr7700097477</li>\r\n<li>vlr7857010361</li>\r\n<li>vlr7857010418</li>\r\n</ol>', '2016-01-20 05:12:14', 'l7d23b', '2016-01-20 05:12:14', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on TNSLink sites that use the old IP addressing information', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(415, 'Allsup\'s Station Information', '<p>Valero has now branded 130 Allsup sites.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Allsup&rsquo;s had an active satellite agreement with AstrumSat for services provided by SageNet.&nbsp; AstrumSat is a reseller for SageNet.&nbsp; Valero worked with AstrumSat and SageNet to modify the configuration of the Prysm to support routing for credit card transactions to First Data and connectivity for the Verifone EZR.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>If a site experiences issues with satellite service or the EZR, the sites will call the Allsup&rsquo;s help desk at 1-800-282-8409.&nbsp; The Allsup help desk personnel will work directly with AstrumSat and SageNet to resolve satellite service issues.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Allsup sites may call the Valero help desk for inquiries on transactions, proprietary cards, or merchant setup.</p>', '2016-02-03 10:57:15', 'l7d23b', '2017-03-23 09:00:39', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Allsup\'s Station Information', '', 30010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(416, 'EMV Reversals', '<p>On 02/04/16 IS did a<strong> reversal </strong>&nbsp;of the c/b 50 and 52 that were issued to the stations for Counterfeit/chip liability chargeback&rsquo;s. &nbsp;It appears they &ldquo;look&rdquo; like chargeback&rsquo;s on the MSR but they are truly a reversal and the money has been given back to the station.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>These transactions will appear as <strong>chargeback 35</strong> in the VPS system which is a Valero chargeback similar to 99&rsquo;s which the station <strong>will not see</strong>.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/emvrev.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"432\" height=\"311\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-02-05 08:41:44', 'l7d23b', '2016-02-05 08:41:44', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Info on 2/4/16 EMV reversals', '', 50005, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(417, 'Configuring MX915 for a Nucleus', '<p>If a tech is installing a Wayne shipped MX915 (the encryption label will read TDES086 instead of AKEYPCSBUY 20) and they\'re getting an encryption error, follow these steps.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Hold 1-5-9 together on the keypad</li>\r\n<li>Enter password: 166832</li>\r\n<li>Go to the Administration tab</li>\r\n<li>Go to&nbsp;the Config tab</li>\r\n<li>Select config.user1</li>\r\n<li>Scroll down the list and find: KSN PREFIX LEN</li>\r\n<li>Change this variable from 0 to 1</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-02-05 09:59:35', 'l7d23b', '2016-02-05 09:59:35', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Configuring MX915 for a Nucleus', '', 10007, 'Tech Support 2', 'N', ''),
(418, 'MasterCard Reported Product Code Errors', '<p>On Thursday 02/04/16, we mailed letters (<a href=\"upload/docs/Fuel Code Errors Letter.docx\" target=\"_blank\">copy attached</a>) for 73 locations and their Distributors that were reported by MasterCard&nbsp;as sending the wrong product codes for billing information (<a href=\"upload/docs/Valero Review_January 2016.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">Spreadsheet Attached</a>). &nbsp;These errors are affecting all Fleet billing companies, including Valero. There are already tickets created under a Heat Board for all these locations.&nbsp; When/if they call in, based on their POS system, take the following actions:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Gilbarco Passport<br /><br /></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Use <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=166\" target=\"_blank\">Article #166</a>&nbsp;to walk the location through checking and correcting the Network Product codes.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>VeriFone and Wayne Systems:</strong>&nbsp;<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hopefully it will be a technician calling.</li>\r\n<li>Do test transactions for all the different fuel products they sell to make sure the product tab in the ClientLine transaction records have the correct product codes.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>If not, advise the technician calling in where the errors are and have him/her call in again to test when corrected.&nbsp; .</li>\r\n<li>If it is&nbsp; not the technician calling in advise your caller that it will be better if the technician on site calls in for verification before he/she leaves.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you find specific situations that are not addressed adequately in this article, please let your Supervisor know and we will attempt to keep these instructions updated with all new information&nbsp; as it is discovered and verified.</p>\r\n<p>Please update the Solution Description for the ticket with who you spoke to, that person&rsquo;s contact phone number and the date and time the corrections were completed).&nbsp; Indicate whether or not &nbsp;you were able to verify the corrections.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Spreadsheets have been created from the Data warehouse for each ticket that shows historical data at the bottom of the data set that you can review if the technicians require assistance in identifying the errors that are occurring.&nbsp; These spreadsheets are located in this folder:<a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Projects\\Prod Code Errors\\Voyager 1st6 Qtr 2016\" target=\"_blank\"> O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Projects\\Prod Code Errors\\Voyager 1st6 Qtr 2016</a></p>', '2016-02-05 12:01:17', 'l7d23b', '2017-07-05 13:51:14', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'MasterCard Reported sites with Product Code Errors for Valero to get corrected.', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '\r\n DATE  \\@ \"MMMM d, yyyy\"  \\* MERGEFORMAT March 18, 2015RE:  Product Code Error NotificationM Spiegel &amp; Sons, Inc.10 E Village Rd.Tuxedo Park, NY 10987Site Name:   FILLIN  \"Store Name\" \\* MERGEFORMAT Pegasus Automotive3981 Hylan Blvd.Staten Island, NY 10308-3429 FILLIN  \"Store Name\"  \\* MERGEFORMAT  This location has been identified as incorrectly reporting product codes on various fleet credit card transactions. Diesel is being reported as Unleaded Premium (90 or 91 octane)This error needs to be remediated as soon as possible to avoid possible chargebacks or fines on these transactions.  The correction for this error is dependent on the Point of Sale (POS) system you have installed at this site.  Below is a guide on how to resolve this error based on your POS system.Gilbarco PassportPlease call the Valero Technical Support Help Desk at (866) 482-5376 and an agent will walk you through the changes required to resolve this issue.Verifone Systems (Ruby, Topaz, Sapphire, etc.)A certified VeriFone technician will need to be on site to resolve this issue if you do not have a VeriFone maintenance contract or you may contact the VeriFone Help Desk if you do have a maintenance contract.  We require the technician on site or the VeriFone Help Desk to contact us at (866) 482-5376 to test the changes and ensure the issue has been resolved.Wayne NucleusA certified Wayne technician will need to be on site to resolve this issue if you do not have a Wayne maintenance contract or you may contact the Wayne Help Desk if you do have a maintenance contract.  We require the technician on site or the Wayne Help Desk to contact us at (866) 482-5376 to test the changes and ensure the issue has been resolved.If you have any questions regarding this issue, please contact the Valero Help Desk.  As always, we appreciate your business and thank you for your continued support of the Valero branded program.Sincerely, Carolyn J. AllenSenior Manager, Wholesale Brandsindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=166O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Projects\\Prod Code Errors\\Voyager 1st6 Qtr 2016'),
(419, 'Merchant Settlement Reports/DTN 2/16/16', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">There was a problem this morning getting MSR information to DTN.&nbsp;The issue has been resolved and Jobbers should start seeing these reports coming through.</span></p>', '2016-02-16 08:37:06', 'lbfb2t', '2016-02-16 08:37:06', 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'DTN issue with MSR\'s 2/16/16', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(420, 'NCR Installs Information', '<p>We will be migrating Six Hubbell Valero from TNS FPX to Acumera Processor Connections on February 16th for credit card processing.&nbsp; If the site calls in to report issues, please open a ticket, then transfer the customer to Acumera at 512-687-7401.&nbsp; This is Valero&rsquo;s second site to test the Processor Connections offer from Acumera.&nbsp; The migration will consist of:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Acumera installing the AMG with the Processor Connections applications and an 8-port managed switch</li>\r\n<li>POS tech de-installing the Verifone Sapphire and installing a Verifone Commander</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>o&nbsp;&nbsp; updating the POS with an IP &amp; host information for First Data</p>\r\n<p>o&nbsp;&nbsp; Connecting the isolated payment NIC to the managed switch</p>\r\n<p>o&nbsp;&nbsp; Connect the EZR to the managed switch</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The site will be using broadband primary with 4G for failover.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Site Details:</p>\r\n<p>Jobber&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3450</p>\r\n<p>Dealer&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 45997</p>\r\n<p>Site Name&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Six Hubbell Valero</p>\r\n<p>Address&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 14530 W McNichols, Detroit, MI 48235</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Here are the details for the POS:</p>\r\n<p>IP POS&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 172.16.21.12</p>\r\n<p>GW&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 172.16.21.1</p>\r\n<p>Mask&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 255.255.255.0</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Please contact me with any questions.</p>', '2016-02-17 09:11:32', 'l7d23b', '2016-02-17 09:11:32', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'NCR Installs Information', '', 10011, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(421, 'Super Stop 465 Looping Transactions', '<p>You may start receiving calls from disgruntled customers in relation to the looping transactions that occurred last week at SuperStop #465 in Fort Smith AR:</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;1) <strong>This statement was provided today to the Jobber Colson Oil:</strong></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo; Again, please accept our apologies for the length of time it has taken for our third party processor to complete the corrections to your customer\'s accounts.&nbsp; By the end of today, 7,000 corrections for the American Express and Discover transactions that looped within your store\'s POS system, will be completely uploaded to those two card companies.&nbsp; This has been an ongoing manual process since Monday 02/22.&nbsp; Your customers should start seeing those corrections applied to their accounts on Friday.&nbsp; That next posting process, to the customer accounts, is totally outside our control, so we cannot guarantee completion on Friday.&nbsp; As for a phone number, the customers can call their card issuing company via the phone number on the back of their cards to check on the status of their refund (whether it has been posted to their account or not).&nbsp; They can also contact us at <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">1-866-482-5376</span> and we can explain the issue and try to provide reassurance that the issue is being resolved.&nbsp; </em></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>2)&nbsp; </em><strong>If the question arises of &ldquo;&hellip;what caused this to happen?&hellip;&rdquo;You may respond with:</strong></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;<em>There was either a software or hardware glitch in the store&rsquo;s&rsquo; electronic POS (Point of Sale) system that caused a rapid transmission of duplicate transactions across the network in a very short time.&nbsp; This caused multiple charges to your credit card account. The exact cause was never determined so an installation of &nbsp;all new updated equipment and software resolved the issue late in the day on 02/18.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;<strong>3)</strong>&nbsp; </em><em><strong>As for the corrections:</strong></em>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;once the issue was resolved and the transactions all finalized, we submitted all the duplicate transactions to our third party processor to correct customer credit card accounts.&nbsp; These 7,000 transactions had to be manually processed starting on Monday (02/22).&nbsp; Those corrections will be completed and uploaded to the billing card companies by the end of today (02/24).&nbsp; Totally outside of our control, those billing companies process the corrections under their timeframes and policies and it may be as early as Friday (02/26) or later for the corrections to start appearing on customer accounts.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;<strong>4)&nbsp; </strong></em><strong><strong>If a customer requests compensation in the form of funds or interest refunds:</strong><em>&nbsp;</em></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>&ldquo;Any compensation or interest adjustments will need to be addressed with your credit card company through the dispute process&rdquo;.</em></p>\r\n<p><strong><strong>&nbsp;5)&nbsp; In your closing with your caller, please include the following statement:</strong></strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;&ldquo;Valero recognizes how important and impacting this event has been for you and we are truly sorry this has occurred. We are working to the best of our ability with our third party partners and your local store team to make the necessary corrections to your accounts as quickly and accurately as possible.&nbsp; After all the corrections are applied to your account and if there remain any discrepancies, please call us back, referencing your ticket number from this call, for us to review and correct any outstanding transaction issues.&rdquo;</em></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Remember, do not try to give callers all of this information (except #5).&nbsp; Only answer the questions they ask. Please let me know if any new questions not addressed here come up in your conversations with your callers.</strong></span></p>', '2016-02-25 09:43:11', 'lbfb2t', '2016-02-25 09:46:50', 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on assisting customers that were affected by the looping transaction issue', '', 50006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
