(424, 'Unbranded Portal Help', '<p>For unbranded customers that have questions about reporting on the Portal that we are unable to answer (after we make the attempt), you can refer them to the email address provided by Sarah Jackson below.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Toll free number: <strong><span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">1-877-825-7225<a style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 1-877-825-7225\" href=\"#\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 1-877-825-7225\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></a></span></strong></li>\r\n<li>Email: customerservice_wholesalemktg@valero.com</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>', '2016-03-29 13:32:57', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-19 12:04:52', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Unbranded Portal Help', '', 40007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(425, 'Passport Setup for Acumera', '<p class=\"Default\" style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; box-sizing: border-box;\">Network Settings</span></p>\r\n<ul style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">\r\n<li class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Buynet setting does not matter for Passport/Acumera setups as it is IP&nbsp;based.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">Passport Settings</p>\r\n<ul style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<div class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Passport set for Connection Type:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"font-weight: bold; box-sizing: border-box;\">VSAT (Not VSAT w/ DIAL BACK UP)<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" /></strong></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<div class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Host IP: 204.194.125.9</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<div class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">IP Port: 7735</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">Make sure the tech uses an uppercase \"L\" in the MID on the Passport.&nbsp; ex..&nbsp;<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: #ff0000; box-sizing: border-box;\">L</span>348XXXXXX001</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"Default\" style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">Router Settings</p>\r\n<ul style=\"font: 17.33px/24.76px \'PT Serif\', serif; color: #333333; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 10px; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; box-sizing: border-box; widows: 1; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<div class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;WAN IP: 172.16.21.12</div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<div class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;WAN Net Mask: 255.255.255.0<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<div class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;WAN Gateway:&nbsp;172.16.21.1<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">\r\n<div class=\"Default\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\">&nbsp;WAN DNS: 10.5.48.1</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '2016-04-12 14:05:30', 'l7d23b', '2016-04-12 14:05:30', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Setup instructions for Gilbarco Passport on the Acumera Merchant Gateway', '', 10006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(426, 'Verifone Commander on Acumera MG', '<p><strong>Commander / Ruby CI&nbsp;Settings and Connections:</strong></p>\r\n<table class=\"null\" style=\"width: 757px; height: 83px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"3\">\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Commander IP Setup information for Acumera Merchant Gateway</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n<table style=\"height: 78px;\" border=\"0\" width=\"168\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Isolated Payment Nic</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>IP&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.12</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Gateway</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Netmask</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;255.255.255.0</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<table style=\"height: 123px;\" width=\"221\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Device Specific Route</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Route Type&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>Host</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Destination</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;204.194.125.9</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Gateway</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;172.16.21.1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Netmask</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;255.255.255.255</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"vertical-align: top;\">\r\n<table style=\"height: 103px;\" width=\"228\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Buypass Config</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Connection Mode&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;IP</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>IP</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;204.194.125.9</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Port</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;7735</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All Commander solution installs should include a Cybera EZR<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The Isolated Payment NIC will function independently of the Cybera EZR<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Meaning, the site can pull a table load or process credit without the Cybera EZR being online<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The Cybera Zone Router has to be configured for DHCP<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The TNS Cisco router (FE2) is configured to issue an IP to the EZR<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If site is unable to pull a table download, please have the tech confirm &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">SSL Enabled</span>&rdquo; is not selected in the Commander EPS Global Configuration<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Zoom data/fax modem has to be connected to the console/aux port on the Cisco 800 series router and powered on before the Cisco router is powered on so they can synchronize<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If a site is unable to pull a parameter download (PDL), please have the tech confirm the merchant ID.&nbsp; The letters in the merchant ID have to be <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">uppercase</span>.</li>\r\n</ul>', '2016-04-13 09:47:59', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-18 10:55:02', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Settings for Commander and Ruby CI on Acumera Merchnat Gateway', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
