td>\r\n<td width=\"167\">\r\n<p>Topaz Sapphire</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"198\">\r\n<p>6.02.09</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"206\">\r\n<p>6.02.13</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"139\">\r\n<p>Verifone</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"167\">\r\n<p>VX570</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"198\">\r\n<p>7.00.04</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"206\">\r\n<p>7.00.04</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"139\">\r\n<p>Wayne</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"167\">\r\n<p>Nucleus</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"198\">\r\n<p>7.01AF</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"206\">\r\n<p>8.00AC</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-04-20 08:58:16', 'l7d23b', '2017-10-12 10:30:12', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on latest software versions for POS systems', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(428, 'Test', '<div class=\"dropdown\"><button class=\"dropbtn\">Dropdown</button>\r\n<div id=\"myDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-content\"><a href=\"#\">Link 1</a> <a href=\"#\">Link 2</a> <a href=\"#\">Link 3</a></div>\r\n</div>', '2016-04-27 07:40:21', 'lc9782', '2016-04-27 07:44:55', 'lc9782', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(429, 'Insta-Credit Ordering ', '<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Insta-Credit Order Process</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">When call is received, open a heat ticket under Facility (jobber).&nbsp; Please make sure to get the caller\'s name and a good contact number.<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">For your Heat ticket, select the following categories:<br /><br /></span>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Record Type:</strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Wholesale &ndash;Request Merchant Info</span> </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Call Type:</strong> <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">(blank)</span></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Category:</strong> manually type <strong>&ldquo;</strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Instacredit</span><strong>&rdquo;</strong>&nbsp; </span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Priority:&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">3</span><br /><br /></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">In the ticket journal, please include the site information as in the example below.&nbsp; Please make sure to verify jobber and dealer number.<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Email the ticket number to <a href=\"mailto:Israel.herrera@valero.com\">Israel.herrera@valero.com</a> so that the request can be processed and leave your ticket open. Once the information has been processed Israel will close your ticket.<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Mitzi will arrange to have orders shipped out.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Ex.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Jobber-Dealer</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Store name</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Store Address</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Store phone</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><strong>Note if we need to ship to site, dist, or other. If other please include address in the journal. </strong></span></p>', '2016-05-13 16:00:11', 'lbfb2t', '2017-06-18 10:52:59', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Procedure for Ordering Insta-Credit Kit ', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:Israel.herrera@valero.com'),
(430, 'Prysm Pro 4.0 Patching Information', '<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">SageNet will be applying patches to PrysmPro 4.0 systems daily between the hours of 1 AM and 4AM local store times.&nbsp; The referenced spreadsheet lists all the sites that will be patched. The schedule for this weekend is not completed yet.&nbsp; The updates take a total of about 5 minutes and the sites should recover without any intervention.&nbsp; Over 400 have been completed already with no issues.&nbsp; The problems encountered early Friday morning (5/13) were caused by something else entirely.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;Click <a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\ValerSites_TimeZone_5-13-16.xlsx\">here</a><strong>&nbsp;</strong>for site listings.</span></p>', '2016-05-13 16:34:48', 'lbfb2t', '2017-03-23 09:00:47', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Details on Sagenet Patching Prysm-Pro 4.0 Sites', '', 30010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(431, 'Manual Voucher Addresses', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 565px; height: 400px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" border=\"1\" width=\"610\" cellpadding=\"2\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Organisation</td>\r\n<td>Address for submitting manual vouchers</td>\r\n<td>Comment</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Barclays</td>\r\n<td>RR Donnelly<br />Open Sort and Distribute<br />Leicester<br />LE87 2BB<br />Mail Area 113</td>\r\n<td>Use this when the vouchers have not been keyed into the terminal</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Allstar</td>\r\n<td>PO Box 1463 Windmill Hill<br />Swindon<br />SN5 6PS<br /><a href=\"mailto:networkmanagement@allstarcard.co.uk\">networkmanagement@allstarcard.co.uk</a><br />08708423250</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>BP Routex / Fastfuel / Texaco The Business</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>FAO Data Entry<br />Eurocard Centre<br />Herald Park<br />Herald Drive<br />Crewe<br />CW1 6EG&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Legacy Sites</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;1 Trinity Court<br />Wolverhampton<br />WV10 6UH</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;All other cards</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;As advised by the card issuers</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;Retailer to contact the issuer and confirm manual process</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-05-27 08:45:13', 'l7d23b', '2016-05-27 08:45:13', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Addresses for stations to send manual vouchers to', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:networkmanagement@allstarcard.co.uk'),
(432, 'Gilbarco Passport EMV', '<p>Sites upgrading to Gilbarco&rsquo;s Passport EMV Software Version 11.01C will require a change in Clientline to enable EMV for the merchant ID.&nbsp; First Data is enabling all Gilbarco sites, but in the event a site is missed and you receive a call reporting issues related to processing EMV cards, please check the EMV indicator in Clientline to ensure &nbsp;it is set to &ldquo;YES&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/gilEmv.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"383\" height=\"426\" /></p>', '2016-05-27 11:14:09', 'l7d23b', '2016-05-27 11:14:09', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Gilbarco Passport EMV', '', 40002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(433, 'Outage Wrap-up Email Example', '<p>Example of an outage wrap-up email</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 236px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" width=\"538\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>Beginning at approximately 09:15 CST/ 15:15 GMT, &nbsp;1<sup><span style=\"font-size: small;\">st</span></sup> April, our helpdesk received a call reporting extremely slow credit card processing times that sometimes resulted in declined transactions. Shortly after that call, the helpdesk began to receive similar calls at a steady pace. I contacted TNS to check if they were having any network issues. TNS checked multiple sites, all which had strong signals and nothing to indicate connectivity issues. By 15:40, the stations that we were currently engaged with began to report successful, fast transactions.</p>\r\n<p>At 16:00 we began to receive the same type of call, albeit at a slightly lower volume. As we were receiving calls from both standard and MFL sites (ruling out TNS,) we reported the issue to FIS at 16:20. Calls were handled appropriately by helpdesk staff resulting in low hold times and minimal call buildup. Incoming calls began to dwindle shortly after we spoke to FIS.</p>\r\n<p>At 16:35 FIS closed their ticket as resolved. We contacted FIS to enquire on the reason for the service interruption. FIS stated that the issue was due to an application spike on one of their servers and they were currently checking as to why the issue occurred. Calls concerning the issue stopped at approximately 16:25. We followed up with a few affected sites and confirmed the issue was resolved.</p>\r\n<p>A total of 18 calls were logged and associated to a heat board between 15:15 and 16:24 for this issue.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2016-06-06 08:04:56', 'l7d23b', '2016-06-06 08:04:56', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Outage Wrap-up Email Example', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(434, 'Unlocking WTS Agent Fleet Portal Access', '<p>In the event that a WTS agent gets locked out you can unlock the account from&nbsp;RAMS.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Log in to rams.</li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>D</strong>, press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>J</strong>, press enter.</li>\r\n<li>In the <span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\">last name </span>field enter an <strong>S</strong>, press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Enter an <strong>S</strong> on one of the results and press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>E</strong> on the <span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\">command</span> field, press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>B</strong> in the <span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\">function</span> field and the agent\'s L-number in the&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">user id</span> field, press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Change the<strong> B</strong> in the <span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\">function</span> field to a <strong>P</strong>, press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Type <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>valero</strong> </span>in the password field, press enter.</li>\r\n<li>This will reset the user\'s password to <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>valero</strong> </span>and prompt for a change once they log in to the fleet portal.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2016-06-06 08:24:02', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-18 10:39:07', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Unlocking WTS Agent Fleet Portal Access', '', 40008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(435, 'Enhanced Zone Router Installation Information', '<p>It is very important that during the installation of the Commander/RubyCI the VASC contact Verifone to confirm remote support functionality via the EZR.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>All Valero sites with Commander/RubyCI should have an EZR.</p>\r\n<p>There is currently an issue with any Cybera Zone Routers running software version prior to 1.3.1 that is preventing them from working correctly on our network. The Cybera must be replaced with one running a current software.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/EnhancedRouterInstallGuide_1Dec2015.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">The guide can be found here.</a></p>', '2016-06-09 05:28:39', 'l7d23b', '2017-07-05 13:44:43', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Cybera EZR install information', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(436, 'Gift Card Ordering Procedure Change', '<p>Effective 6/23/16, all new Gift Card orders that are the results of order requests via email from our clients please follow these new instructions:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Change the source to &ldquo;email&rdquo; in your HEAT ticket</li>\r\n<li>Immediately after pasting the order information in the notes<strong>, copy and paste the full contents of your customer&rsquo;s email body to the Assignment Notes of your ticket</strong></li>\r\n<li>Alternatively, you may copy and paste the email contents into a Journal note (or &ldquo;Received Documents&rdquo; Journal entry) or you may save the email as a &ldquo;.msg&rdquo; and attach a copy to the ticket (Attachments tab and [right-click] select &ldquo;Add Attachment&rdquo;).&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>If you have any questions, please contact David Cantor.</p>', '2016-06-24 12:44:52', 'lbfb2t', '2016-06-24 14:10:38', 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Changes to Gift Card Ordering Procedures Effective 06/23/16', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(437, 'Early Site De-Branding Notification', '<p>If you have a site, technician or customer call in and state that a particular site has de-branded but we still show them active in RAMS, we need to send an email to Sarah Jackson (sarah.jackson@valero.com) detailing the store information and what was relayed to us.&nbsp; She is the supervisor over contract administration and will get this to the correct contract administrator so they can make contact with the site.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>When the correct requests have been sent, Mitzi will de-brand the site. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\">Do not make any changes to the store&rsquo;s profile in Clientline or in RAMS</span>. </span></strong></p>', '2016-06-24 13:00:07', 'lbfb2t', '2017-07-05 16:10:27', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'What to do if you receive information that a site is de-branding early.', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(438, 'Gaining Access to texacostation.com', '<ol style=\"list-style-type: upper-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Request new roles via IDM.</li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://inside.valero.com/irj/servlet/prt/portal/prtmode/preview/prtroot/pcd!3aportal_content!2finsideValero!2ftools!2fiViews!2fcom.vlo.iv.IDM_HOME?sap-config-mode=true\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to access IDM.</a><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Helpdesk Screen</span> under IDM Tools on the right.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/idmtools.png\" alt=\"\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Search Terms</span>, enter your L-Number. Click Search.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/search.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"353\" height=\"117\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Your profile should display. Click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Select Identity</span>.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/select.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"123\" height=\"85\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Under your profile picture, click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">My Current Access</span>.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/mycurrentaccess.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"159\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Actions</span> in the upper right of the access window. Then click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Request Access For</span>.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/requestaccess.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"202\" height=\"112\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>On the next window. Click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Skip to Search</span>.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/skip.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"328\" height=\"277\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Keywords</span> field, enter <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">A1229</span> </strong>and click the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">magnifying glass</span>.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/keywords.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"406\" height=\"46\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The following entry will display if the role was found.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/1229.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"785\" height=\"123\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Add to Req</span>. The entry will then display like this:<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/1229after.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"408\" height=\"34\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Remove the A1229 from the Keywords field.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Keywords</span> field enter <strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">AD7221</span> </strong>and click the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">magnifying glass</span>.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/7221.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"786\" height=\"122\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Add to Req</span>. The entry will then display like this:<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/7221after.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"502\" height=\"32\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Submit for Approval</span> once the two roles have been added.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/submit.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"298\" height=\"150\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enter a reason for your request (customer service)&nbsp;and click <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Submit Request</span>.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/submitrequest.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"754\" height=\"314\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>You will receive a message stating the requests have been created.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/texacostationsupport/created.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"205\" height=\"27\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>After the roles have been approved you will receive an email with a temporary password.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Go to <a href=\"http://texacostation.com\" target=\"_blank\">texacostation.com</a><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Close out any running <strong>programs</strong> or <strong>browser windows</strong>&nbsp;that you may have open <strong>including this page</strong>. Texacostation.com must be the only thing running on your computer.<br /><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">This is extremely important as the password reset process can corrupt browser sessions and the ability to access websites.<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Log in with your L-number and temporary password and follow the password reset procedure.<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">After the password reset procedure, you<strong> must log out of windows and log back in</strong>.</span></li>\r\n</ol>', '2016-06-29 09:19:44', 'l7d23b', '2016-06-29 09:27:17', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on setting up your access to texacostation.com', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'http://inside.valero.com/irj/servlet/prt/portal/prtmode/preview/prtroot/pcd!3aportal_content!2finsideValero!2ftools!2fiViews!2fcom.vlo.iv.IDM_HOME?sap-config-mode=truehttp://texacostation.com');
INSERT INTO `article` (`artid`, `arttitle`, `artbody`, `createstamp`, `usercreate`, `modstamp`, `usermod`, `pubflag`, `rfcflag`, `comment`, `usercomment`, `commentstamp`, `summary`, `triggers`, `chainid`, `rolename`, `encflag`, `linkdoctext`) VALUES
(439, 'FIS Service Now Portal', '<p>The portal can be found at <a href=\"https://fisglobalprod.service-now.com/\">https://fisglobalprod.service-now.com/&nbsp;</a></p>\r\n<p>Login Details:<br />Username: <a href=\"mailto:vcssupport@valero.com\">vcssupport@valero.com</a><br />Password: .Valero1</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/Service NOW Training MPS Clients June16 v3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">User guide PDF can be found here.</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Guide for filling out ticket data is as follows:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Short description</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>This should be used to be able to identify the issue and link it to the HEAT call, so the HEAT Call ID, site name and number need to be incorporated into this, the suggested format is as follows:</p>\r\n<p>HEAT Call ID - Short Description &ndash; Site Name &ndash; Site Number</p>\r\n<p>e.g. &lsquo;01412345 - Incorrect Amex MID at Strensham S/Stn #490534&rsquo;.</p>\r\n<p><strong><em>Please describe your issue</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>Use this field to provide the issue in detail. Providing as much detail as possible will help FIS triage and resolve the issue more efficiently.</p>', '2016-07-21 10:24:17', 'l7d23b', '2016-09-01 06:25:52', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'FIS Service Now Portal Info', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'https://fisglobalprod.service-now.com/mailto:vcssupport@valero.com'),
(440, 'Pre-Qualified Phone Application Procedures', '<h2><a href=\"#limit\">Credit Limit Increase</a>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Scripts</strong></span></h2>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #828282; width: 100%; height: 299px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"10\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">Greeting:</span> </span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>&ldquo;Thank you for calling to apply for a Valero Credit Card issued by DSRM National Bank, my name is _____.&nbsp;</em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\">Income 1: </span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;Federal law </span></em><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">requires that we collect income information to determine your ability to pay.&rdquo;&nbsp;</span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\">Income 2:</span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">Alimony, child support or separate maintenance need not be revealed if you do not wish it to be considered as a basis for repaying this obligation.&rdquo;</span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\">Email: </span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>&ldquo;If you provide an email address, we may use it to contact you about your account or to send you information about products and services you might find useful.&rdquo;</em> </span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\">Cellular Phone: </span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;If you provide a cell phone number, you agree to receive calls or messages at this number. Normal cell phone charges may apply.&rdquo; </span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\"><a href=\"#admin\">Administrator:</a> </span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;If this application is approved, unless you tell us otherwise, an Additional User may assist in the administration of your Account and this credit card account may also appear on the additional user&rsquo;s credit file.&rdquo;</span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">DOB/SSN</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">: </span></span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;For credit reporting purposes, we are required to obtain the SSN and DOB of the Additional User.&rdquo; </span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">No DOB/SSN:</span>&nbsp;</span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">\"</span><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">By not providing this required information, you understand information relating to this Account will not be furnished to the credit bureaus.&rdquo;</span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\"><a href=\"#pended\">PENDED: </a></span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;</span><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">Thank you for submitting your application; You should receive a letter within 7-10 days with detailed information about our credit decision as well as contact information for the credit reporting agency used&rdquo;. </span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\">REJECT DUE TO ERS OR DTI:</span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;Thank you for submitting your application; however, at this time we are unable to approve your application. You should receive a letter within 7-10 days with detailed information about our credit decision as well as contact information for the credit reporting agency used.&rdquo;</span></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\">APPROVED: </span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>&ldquo;Congratulations, your application has been approved and you should receive your card(s) within 7-10 days. Important information, including the terms and conditions of your account will accompany the credit card(s). Use of the card(s) constitutes acceptance of the terms and conditions. Upon receiving your new credit card(s), we invite you to register at <u>valero.com/newcard</u> to activate your card(s) and manage your account. Thank you for calling and welcome to Valero. Is there anything else I can help you with today?&rdquo;</em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.42%;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #000000; font-size: 12pt;\">CREDIT REPORT: </span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 78.84%;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;Due to changes to the original offer information, we will perform our standard credit investigation&rdquo;</span></em></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Spanish Calls should be transferred to (5055).</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Read the following greeting:<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #ffffff; font-size: 12pt; background-color: #000000;\">Greeting: </span><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">&ldquo;Thank you for calling to apply for a Valero Credit Card issued by DSRM National Bank, my name is _____.&nbsp;</span><br /><br /></em>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><em>What state do you live in?&rdquo;</em>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If applicant responds with Vermont, advise we are unable to process a phone or internet application for Vermont applicants.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Ask the customer if they received a Pre-Qualified Certificate,</li>\r\n<li>If yes, advise they must complete, sign and mail to us.</li>\r\n<li>If no, advise we can mail them a regular application, complete the <strong>Reflex Item</strong> for paper application request. (If you don&rsquo;t have access to Reflex, send an email to the Mail Team with the customer&rsquo;s name and complete address and they will mail it.)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If applicant responds with a state other than Vermont, continue processing the phone application (enter the state abbreviation in the D/License Field).<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>&ldquo;<strong>A</strong>&rdquo; APPLICATION PROCESSING<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>&ldquo;<strong>A</strong>&rdquo; INTIAL APPLICATION ENTRY<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Ask the applicant if they have a Pre-Qualified Customer Number and is the certificate issued in their name. (This number is located on the right hand side of the letter and also above the name and address of the certificate portion).<br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If the applicant has a Pre-Qualified Customer Number, follow procedures below.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the applicant does not have a Pre-Qualified Customer Number, follow the normal Phone Application Processing Procedure.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If you are not trained to process Phone Application, transfer the call to 3904.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If the person calling is not the pre-qualified applicant, update all necessary fields and process the application (<strong>Changes will require a credit report.</strong> Follow the Ordering a Credit Report Process Section).<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Caller ID</strong> - Agents will make every effort to capture the Caller ID number that accompanies each call and enter it on the Caller ID line. If there is no Caller ID displayed, ask for the number they are calling from and enter it.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Certificate No</strong><strong> &ndash; </strong>Ask the applicant for the Pre-Qualified Customer Number. Enter the Pre-Qualified Customer Number and Press the <strong>ENTER </strong>key<strong>. </strong>(This will pre-populate some of the applicant&rsquo;s information). <em>If you receive the message &ldquo;customer number already exists&rdquo;, escalate the call to the Mail Team Supervisor.&nbsp;<br /><br /></em></li>\r\n<li><strong>Verify applicant&rsquo;s full name (Ask Applicant for their full name):</strong></li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If the information populated does not match the information given by the applicant, enter the correct information. (<strong>Changes will require a credit report.</strong> Follow the Ordering a Credit Report Process Section).&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li><strong>Date of Birth-</strong> Enter the date of birth.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>D/License - Enter the State it was issued in and enter the license number.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>MAIL ADD:</strong>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Ask the applicant to verify their mailing address.</li>\r\n<li>If the address is a PO Box, the physical address is also <strong><em>required</em></strong>. (no credit report is needed). Make a NOTE &ldquo;<em>pre-qualified offer was sent to PO Box, updated physical address</em>&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>If the information populated does not match the information given by the applicant or they request to change the mailing address from a physical address to a PO Box, enter the correct information. (Changes will require a new credit report, follow the Ordering a New Credit Report Process Section).</li>\r\n<li>If the address populates with symbols (#, . , - etc), remove the symbols to prevent credit bureau reporting corruption.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Street Add &ndash; If the street address is the same as the mailing address, leave as the default. (Follow formatting above).<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>SSN &ndash; Ask the applicant for their Social Security Number. The SSN provided by applicant should match the pre-populated last 7 digits in the File SSN Field. If the pre-populated 7 digits do not match exactly, verify the full SSN again.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>File SSN &ndash; Pre-populated SSN.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Gross Annual Inc &ndash; Enter the gross (before taxes) annual income which can be an approximate amount.</strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the applicant inquires why we need that information or whether child support, alimony, etc. should be included read the scripts below:<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong><em>Income Script:</em></strong></span><em> &ldquo;Federal law </em><em>requires that we collect income information to determine your ability to pay.&rdquo;&nbsp;<br /><br /></em></span><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong>Income Script: </strong></span>&ldquo;Alimony, child support or separate maintenance need not be revealed if you do not wish it to be considered as a basis for repaying this obligation.&rdquo;</span><br /><br /></em></li>\r\n<li><em><em>If an applicant indicates they rely on another form of income (i.e. spouse income, assets, or separate maintenance):<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #ff6600;\"><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\">Other Income Script:</span> </strong>&ldquo;Are the funds accessible to you&rdquo;?</span><br /></span></em></em><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If applicant says <strong>NO</strong>, advise we are not able to consider that specific income.</li>\r\n<li>If applicant says <strong>YES</strong>, update income amount.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Own/Buy &ndash; If owns or is buying their home, enter &ldquo;Y&rdquo; on OWN/BUY. If they do not, enter &ldquo;N&rdquo;.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Rent &ndash; If rents, enter &ldquo;Y&rdquo;. If they do not, enter &ldquo;N&rdquo;.<br /></strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If neither rents nor owns, enter &ldquo;Y&rdquo; on OWN/BUY and &ldquo;N&rdquo; on RENT.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Rent Amt &ndash; Enter monthly rent amount in whole dollars (example 350).<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>EMP Code - Enter FON.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Service &ndash; leave blank.<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n<li><strong><strong>Email Add - Ask for an email address and enter it. If an email address is provided, read the following script:<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\">Email Script:</span> </em></span></strong></strong><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>&ldquo;If you provide an email address, we may use it to contact you about your account or to send you information about products and services you might find useful.&rdquo;</em></span><strong><strong> <br /><br /></strong></strong><em><br /></em></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the customer objects to the use of their email address for marketing purposes, advise the customer that if approved, a Privacy Notice will be mailed with their cards and they may opt out of this process.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Phone Pri# - </strong>Enter the primary phone number along with indicator for (C)ell or (L)and. If a cell (C) phone number is given, read the following script:<strong><br /><br /></strong><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong>Cell Script:</strong></span> &ldquo;If you provide a cell phone number, you agree to receive calls or messages at this number. Normal cell phone charges may apply.&rdquo; </span><br /><br /></em></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the customer objects to the use of their cell phone for marketing purposes, advise the customer that if approved, a Privacy Notice will be mailed with their cards and they may opt out of this process.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Sec# - </strong>Enter the secondary phone number (if no # provided, leave field blank and do not attempt to enter any numbers as this will cause an error message) along with indicator for (C)ell or (L)and. If a cell (C) phone number is given, read the following:<strong> <br /><br /><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><em><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\">Cell Script:</span> </em></span></strong><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><em>&ldquo;If you provide a cell phone number, you agree to receive calls or messages at this number. Normal cell phone charges may apply.&rdquo; </em></span></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the customer objects to the use of their cell phone for marketing purposes, advise the customer that if approved, a Privacy Notice will be mailed with their cards and they may opt out of this process.<br /><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>Cards Req</strong><strong> &ndash; </strong>Enter a minimum of 01 card and a maximum of 99 cards. Card #2 will automatically have the additional user&rsquo;s name (if listed) and any additional cards beyond that will be issued in the account owner&rsquo;s name.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If applicant requests cards in names other than the applicant or additional user, increase the card count and document the names on your phone sheet for later reference.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>User Name</strong><strong> &ndash; </strong>Enter the full name of the additional user. <strong><u>NOTE:</u></strong><u> We will data furnish trade info on additional users over the age of 16 as long as we have both DOB and full SSN; but, we cannot guarantee what the credit reporting agencies will report.</u> Read the script below:<br /><br /><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong><a id=\"admin\"></a>Admin Script:</strong></span> &ldquo;If this application is approved, unless you tell us otherwise, an Additional User may assist in the administration of your Account and this credit card account may also appear on the additional user&rsquo;s credit file.&rdquo;</span></em><em><br /><br /></em>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If customer agrees to credit reporting and administration of the account, read the script below:<br /><br />\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; font-size: 12pt; background-color: #000000;\"><strong><em>DOB/SSN Script</em></strong></span><em><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\">:</span> &ldquo;For credit reporting purposes, we are required to obtain the SSN and DOB of the Additional User.&rdquo;</span> <br /><br /><strong>User DOB</strong> &ndash; Enter Additional users date of birth. (Field required for credit reporting). The system will not allow a DOB younger than 16 years of age at time application is entered. If additional user is under 16 read the script below:<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong>Age Script:</strong></span> &ldquo;Additional User must be 16 years of age or older.&rdquo;</span><br /><br /></em></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If under the age of 16, we will not data furnish Additional User.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>User SSN</strong> &ndash; Enter Additional Users full social security number. (Field is required for credit reporting)&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If customer agrees to <strong>credit reporting and administration</strong> of the account, read the script below:<br /><br /><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong>SSN DOB&nbsp;Script:</strong></span> &ldquo;For credit reporting purposes, we are required to obtain the SSN and DOB of the Additional User.&rdquo; <br /></span></em></li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\"><em>&nbsp;</em></span></p>\r\n<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If customer is unable to provide either DOB or under the age of 16 or SSN for Additional user, read script below:<br /><br /><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong>No DOB/SSN Script:</strong></span></span>&nbsp;<span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">\"</span><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">By not providing this required information, you understand information relating to this Account will not be furnished to the credit bureaus.&rdquo;<br /><br /></span></em></li>\r\n<li><em>Increase card count.<br /><br /></em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Increase the card count for card holder</li>\r\n<li>If application is approved - Make <strong>PERM NOTE</strong> on account, &ldquo;Per account owner (name), (additional user&rsquo;s name) is authorized on account, but does not want credit reporting.&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Skip User DOB and User SSN fields (not credit reporting)</li>\r\n<li>Increase card count.<br />&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">&nbsp;</span></em></li>\r\n<li><em>If the customer agrees to credit reporting but does <strong>NOT</strong> agree to &ldquo;<u>administration of the account</u></em>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>Add name to User Name field and fill in DOB and SSN (as above).</em></li>\r\n<li><em>If application is approved, make a <strong>PERM NOTE</strong> on the account, leave name in SNAM field. Example Note: &ldquo;Per account owner, SNAM/(name) for credit reporting only, is not authorized on the account.&rdquo;</em></li>\r\n<li><em>Increase card count.<br /><br /></em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If the customer does <strong>NOT</strong> agree to credit reporting but <u>agrees</u> to <u>&ldquo;administration of the account&rdquo;</u>, <strong>remove</strong> name from <strong>User Name</strong> field.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong>App Type</strong><strong> - </strong>&ldquo;<strong>P</strong>&rdquo; for promo application will pre-populate.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Promo</strong><strong> - </strong>Will pre-populate with current promo code.<br /><strong>&nbsp;</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Manual Routing</strong> &ndash; leave blank.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Dealer</strong><strong> -</strong> May be pre-populated, if not populated leave blank.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><strong>Track ID</strong> - This field will be blank unless there is a Special Promotion.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>If all information <strong><em>matches</em></strong> the information provided by the pre-qualified offer, press enter.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li><em>The Application Status Screen will populate. Refer to Approved or Reject due to DTI.</em></li>\r\n<li>If you get an error message &ldquo;ADDRESS NOT FOUND&rdquo; at the bottom of the page:\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Ask the customer to verify the address again including city, state, zip.</li>\r\n<li>If the address is correct, tab back to the &ldquo;OVERRIDE&rdquo; Field and type &ldquo;<strong>Y</strong>&rdquo; and enter.</li>\r\n<li>Refer to Approved or Reject due to DTI.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If some of the information <em>does not match</em> (name, address, SSN) or changes are requested, DO NOT PRESS ENTER. A new credit report must be ordered. <em>Follow the Ordering a Credit Report Process.</em> Once the credit report is pulled, a screen will appear indicating the status of the application which could be a Possible Match, Pended, Rejected or Approved. Follow the appropriate steps for the status indicated. &nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Possible Application&nbsp;Results</strong></span></h2>\r\n<h3><strong>Possible Match</strong></h3>\r\n<p>This screen will populate the records in RAMS that are associated with the SSN or name of the new application.<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/rams.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"622\" height=\"139\" /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If you get to this screen,\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Write down the possible match numbers (<strong>S or</strong> <strong>C</strong>) that begin with &ldquo;<strong>92</strong>&rdquo;&nbsp;or the <strong>4 digit</strong> code associated with the <strong>F </strong>and press enter.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>At the non-scored application entry screen, the status code field will be listed as &ldquo;D&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Read the following script:<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #ffffff; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #000000;\">PENDED SCRIPT</span>: </strong></span><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">&ldquo;</span><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">Thank you for submitting your application; You should receive a letter within 7-10 days with detailed information about our credit decision as well as contact information for the credit reporting agency used&rdquo;. </span><br /><br /></em></li>\r\n<li><strong>Shift F6</strong> to get to the application notes screen.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the function field, type &ldquo;<strong>A</strong>&rdquo; to add a note.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the note, include the following: &ldquo;pended, possible match, read script&rdquo;. (Be sure to include the possible match numbers but do not include full SSN in your NOTE, just last 4 digits).&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><strong><a id=\"pended\"></a>PENDED </strong></h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>At the Application Results Script Screen, if the application status shows PENDED:<br /><br /></strong>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Read the following script:<br /><br /><span style=\"color: #ffffff; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #000000;\">PENDED SCRIPT</span>: </strong></span><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">&ldquo;</span><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">Thank you for submitting your application; You should receive a letter within 7-10 days with detailed information about our credit decision as well as contact information for the credit reporting agency used&rdquo;. <br /><br /></span></em></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000; background-color: #ffffff;\">Press Enter.</span></li>\r\n<li>Shift F6 to get to the application notes screen.</li>\r\n<li>In the function field, type &ldquo;A&rdquo; to add a note.</li>\r\n<li>In the note, include the following: &ldquo;pended, read script&rdquo;.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h3><strong>REJECT DUE TO SCORE OR DTI</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>At the Application Results Script Screen, if the application status shows<strong> REJECTED:</strong>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Read:<br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\">REJECT DUE TO ERS OR DTI SCRIPT:</span></strong> <span style=\"color: #3366ff;\">&ldquo;Thank you for submitting your application; however, at this time we are unable to approve your application. You should receive a letter within 7-10 days with detailed information about our credit decision as well as contact information for the credit reporting agency used.&rdquo;</span></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h3><strong>APPROVED</strong></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>At the Application Results Screen, if the application status shows <strong>APPROVED</strong>:</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Read:<br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\"><strong>APPROVED SCRIPT</strong>:</span> <span style=\"color: #3366ff;\"><em>&ldquo;Congratulations, your application has been approved and you should receive your card(s) within 7-10 days. Important information, including the terms and conditions of your account will accompany the credit card(s). Use of the card(s) constitutes acceptance of the terms and conditions. Upon receiving your new credit card(s), we invite you to register at <u>valero.com/newcard</u> to activate your card(s) and manage your account. Thank you for calling and welcome to Valero. Is there anything else I can help you with today?&rdquo;</em></span></span><br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>If the applicant requested additional cards with different names other than the one listed on the SNAM:\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>From the Application Results Script Screen,</li>\r\n<li>Shift F6 to get to the application notes screen.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>In the function field, type &ldquo;A&rdquo; to add a note.</li>\r\n<li>In the note, include the following: &ldquo;requested additional cards for Tim Smith and Laura Smith&rdquo;. Copy note to be placed on account side.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Shift F5 to the Account Card Screen and make necessary name changes to the card(s).\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Command: <strong>Card</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Code: <strong>(sub number)</strong></li>\r\n<li>Command: <strong>Note</strong> (paste note from application side)</li>\r\n<li>RETN: <strong>P<br /><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If additional cards requested, but card count not increased, send email to Trainer and Mail Team supervisor advising of error. Clearly note application as to action needed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If applicant requests &ldquo;additional&rdquo; cards <strong><u>after</u></strong> approval,\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Advise they will need to make that request when they call to activate their new cards upon receipt.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><a id=\"limit\"></a>If customer requests higher credit limit: <strong>(NOTE: this is for pre-qualified only!!)</strong></li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li><a href=\"mailto:Mary.Donlon@valero.com;%20Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com;%20Faye.Jackson@valero.com;%20Danny.Valverde@valero.com;%20Luz.Smart@valero.com;%20Laneshia.Jones@valero.com;%20Beverly.Adcock@valero.com?Subject=New%20Customer%20-%20Credit%20Limit%20Increase%20Request&amp;Body=Account%20%23%3A%0ARequested%20Amount%3A\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to send an email to AMA_Supervisors. Enter the account number and requested limit in the email.</a></li>\r\n<li>Add a Note in the Application Notes Screen\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Shift[F-6]</li>\r\n<li>Function [A]: and enter the following note &ldquo;Customer requests a credit line increase to $____ Emailed AMA_Supervisors to review&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If you are unable to get to the Application Notes Screen\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Pull up the new account in RAMs</li>\r\n<li>Shift [F-2] to go to the Application</li>\r\n<li>Shift [F6] to go to the Application Notes Screen</li>\r\n<li>Continue with 5.b.2. Above.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ordering a Credit Report Process</strong></span></h2>\r\n<p>A credit report is required when information is different from the Pre-Qualified Offer. Examples include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Address change, change from physical address to PO Box (ADDING a physical address with no PO Box change does not require a new credit report).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Social Security number not matching.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Any significant name change.<br /><br /><strong>Changes requiring credit report<br /></strong>Examples: Laura Perez to Laura Jackson, Teresa Bailey to Amy Bailey, John Jones to John Murphy, Jim Jones to Phillip Jones, Joe Dokes Jr to Joe Dokes Sr.<br /><br /><strong>Changes <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">not</span> requiring credit report<br /></strong>Examples: Johnathan Jones to Jon Jones, Robert Smith to Rob Smith.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>To order a credit report:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Read the following script to the applicant.<em> <br /></em><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff; background-color: #000000;\">CREDIT REPORT SCRIPT:</span><span style=\"color: #3366ff;\"><em> &ldquo;Due to changes to the original offer information, we will perform our standard credit investigation&rdquo;<br /></em></span></span>go to Step 2.<br /><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>If the customer does not wish for a new credit report to be pulled, advise we will not be able to complete the application process without doing so, F3 to exit the application.</li>\r\n<li>If customer agrees to pull credit report, go to Step 2.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li><em>If the applicant asks if we will run a credit report as part of the standard credit investigation, it is acceptable to answer &ldquo;Yes&rdquo;.</em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>In the &ldquo;APP TYPE&rdquo; Field, change P to &ldquo;<strong>O</strong>&rdquo; (letter &ldquo;O&rdquo;. This will <u>O</u>rder a credit report) and press enter.</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li><strong><em>If the SSN is different, <u>the system will require you to retype the full 9 digits and press enter.<br /></u></em></strong>&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<li>If you get an error message &ldquo;ADDRESS NOT FOUND&rdquo; at the bottom of the page:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><em>Ask the customer to verify the address again including city, state, zip.</em></li>\r\n<li>If the address is correct, tab back to the &ldquo;OVERRIDE&rdquo; Field and type &ldquo;<strong>Y</strong>&rdquo; and enter.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>The Application Results Screen will populate. Press enter.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>If the application is approved, an account number is assigned. Read the &ldquo;Approved Script&rdquo; on the Application Results Script Screen.</li>\r\n<li>If the application is rejected due to score or DTI, the system will send a letter. Read the &ldquo;Rejected Script&rdquo; on the Application Results Script Screen.</li>\r\n<li>Shift F6 to make a NOTE in the Applications Notes Screen.\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>On the Function Field, type &ldquo;<strong>A</strong>&rdquo; and press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Type &ldquo;ordered credit report due to change and include changes you made.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>If the application &ldquo;Pends&rdquo;</li>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Read the \"Pended Script\":<br /><span style=\"color: #ffffff; font-size: 12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"background-color: #000000;\">PENDED SCRIPT</span>: </strong></span><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">&ldquo;</span><em><span style=\"color: #3366ff; font-size: 12pt;\">Thank you for submitting your application; You should receive a letter within 7-10 days with detailed information about our credit decision as well as contact information for the credit reporting agency used&rdquo;. </span></em>&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>From the Application Results Script Screen, F11 to the Non-Scored Application Entry Screen:&nbsp;\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Shift F6 to enter a note.&nbsp;\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>In the&nbsp;Applications Notes Screen:&nbsp;\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Function: <strong>A</strong> and press enter.</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #000000;\">In the notes field, type &ldquo;ordered credit report due to change in pre-qualified certificate, include information you changed, application pended.&rdquo;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-07-22 09:04:39', 'l7d23b', '2017-08-16 08:19:52', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Pre-Qualified Phone Application Procedures', '', 60003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '#limit#admin#pendedmailto:Mary.Donlon@valero.com; Nerybel.Garcia@valero.com; Faye.Jackson@valero.com; Danny.Valverde@valero.com; Luz.Smart@valero.com; Laneshia.Jones@valero.com; Beverly.Adcock@valero.com?Subject=New Customer - Credit Limit Increase Request&amp;Body=Account %23%3A%0ARequested Amount%3A'),
(441, 'Accounting VX MID\'s', '<p>Wholesale VX: 283589</p>\r\n<p>Retail/CST VX: 283587</p>\r\n<p>Giftcard VX: 283586</p>', '2016-07-25 09:51:45', 'lbfb2t', '2017-01-30 12:59:57', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Merchant ID\'s for the Accounting VX Terminal at Valero Payment Center', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(442, 'Seven Eleven/Acumera Update', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Today the first SEI site was migrated away from the TNS FPX device to the Acumera Gateway (AMG).&nbsp; Below is the basic configuration which will be updated in the next few days to include diagrams.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Connect the AMG&nbsp;coming off of&nbsp;Port 1 (RS-232 port) on the AMG to&nbsp;Comm 2 on the Sapphire.&nbsp;Cable is proprietary&nbsp;and the tech will supply it.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">POS will need to be set to Enhanced Hughes VSAT.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">You will need to have the tech use 77090001&nbsp;for the dial phone numbers</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Buypass profile will need to be set to&nbsp;931699 as well.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">You will need to call Acumera to make sure all is registered and working correctly.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">If you have any questions, please let Israel know.&nbsp;</span></p>', '2016-08-18 17:09:10', 'lbfb2t', '2016-08-26 16:44:38', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Update on ASYNC connectivity issue between Acumera AMG and the Sapphire', '', 10002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
