(446, 'Notification of 2017-2018 TNS Network Moratorium', '<p>In an effort to continue to provide a stable and reliable network for our customers during the peak retail season, TNS will be implementing a Network Moratorium from <strong>November 22, 2017 through January 4, 2018</strong>.&nbsp; During this freeze period there will be limitations on approved requests processed, keeping our focus on minimizing changes that could potentially impact our customers.&nbsp; Any requested changes or additions will be reviewed and considered by the TNS Seasonal Review Board.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>There will be no changes allowed for the Dial, SSL and MPE/Tokenization platforms during the freeze period.&nbsp; Only emergency maintenance to repair network events will take place during this period.&nbsp; In the event emergency maintenance is required, TNS will make every effort to notify our customers prior to any changes made and conduct these changes during non-peak times.</p>\r\n<p>TNS has also requested that any vendor related maintenance be minimized during this moratorium</p>\r\n<p>For the TNS IP based products, there will be limitations in regards to when and what tasks can be performed during the freeze period.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/tns-moratorium.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"545\" height=\"570\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Yellow: </strong>Indicates lower risk dates.&nbsp; New and Change LVCs will process as usual.&nbsp; LVC Disconnects will not be processed.&nbsp; All changes approved, but may require additional lead time.&nbsp; No expedites will be accepted.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Orange</strong>: Indicates moderate risk dates.&nbsp; New and Change LVCs will process as usual.&nbsp; LVC Disconnects will not be processed.&nbsp; New circuits will be installed and LVC Hot Swap changes are approved, but may require additional lead time.&nbsp;&nbsp; Any other changes are not approved.&nbsp; No expedites will be accepted.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Red</strong>: Indicates highest risk dates. New and Change LVCs will process as usual but may require additional lead time.&nbsp; LVC Disconnects will not be processed.&nbsp; LVC Hot Swaps are approved, but will be limited and require additional lead time.&nbsp; Any other changes are not approved.&nbsp; No expedites will be accepted.</p>\r\n<p>Please <a href=\"upload/tns-payments-support-and-escalation-laurie.docx\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for TNS Escalation Guide.</p>', '2016-09-10 18:29:15', 'lbfb2t', '2017-09-20 16:31:43', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on what changes can be requested during the TNS Moratorium 2017-2018', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '\r\nIn an effort to continue to provide a stable and reliable network for our customers during the peak retail season, TNS will be implementing a Network Moratorium from November 22, 2017 through January 4, 2018. During this freeze period there will be limitations on approved requests processed, keeping our focus on minimizing changes that could potentially impact our customers. Any requested changes or additions will be reviewed and considered by the TNS Seasonal Review Board. There will be no changes allowed for the Dial, SSL and MPE/Tokenization platforms during the freeze period. Only emergency maintenance to repair network events will take place during this period. In the event emergency maintenance is required, TNS will make every effort to notify our customers prior to any changes made and conduct these changes during non-peak times. TNS has also requested that any vendor related maintenance be minimized during this moratoriumFor the TNS IP based products, there will be limitations in regards to when and what tasks can be performed during the freeze period. Yellow: Indicates lower risk dates. New and Change LVCs will process as usual. LVC Disconnects will not be processed. All changes approved, but may require additional lead time. No expedites will be accepted.Orange: Indicates moderate risk dates. New and Change LVCs will process as usual. LVC Disconnects will not be processed. New circuits will be installed and LVC Hot Swap changes are approved, but may require additional lead time. Any other changes are not approved. No expedites will be accepted.Red: Indicates highest risk dates. New and Change LVCs will process as usual but may require additional lead time. LVC Disconnects will not be processed. LVC Hot Swaps are approved, but will be limited and require additional lead time. Any other changes are not approved. No expedites will be accepted.6223028575TNS Operations Support and Escalation00TNS Operations Support and Escalation5. Chief Network OfficerMark ColeUSA: +1 703 453 83354. Network Operations DirectorUSA:  +1 703 814 8072EUR:  +44 114 292 0181AUS:  +61 2 9959 08723. Network Operations ManagerUSA: +1 703 814 8073EUR: +44 114 292 0173AUS: +61 2 9959 0832. Duty Shift SupervisorEscalate via support numbers belowPSD Support Center(Payments Services)PSDNOC@tnsi.comUSA: +1 703 453 8500EUR: +44 114 292 0246 Opt.1CAD Support Center(Broadband Access)CADNOC@tnsi.comUSA: +1 703 453 8501EUR: +44 845 111 2037Escalations can be invoked by the customer at any point in time, either by calling the above numbers, or by calling the related support center and requesting escalation.  When a customer escalates via the support center, they will receive the ticket ID and name of the Director/Manager/Supervisor that will be handling the escalation while on the initial call.Client Management / Service DeliveryTNS ContactDetailsReferenceLaurie AylwardClient ManagerOffice: 703-592-1250Mobile: 703-939-0750Email:  laylward@tnsi.comPrimary ContactClient Management GroupEmail: PaymentsClientSupport@tnsi.comBackupIrvin Hayes IIDirector, Global Client Services  Office: 703-667-4664Mobile: 703-862-3819Email:  ihayes@tnsi.com1st Level EscalationMark ColeChief Network OfficerOffice: 703-453-8335Mobile: 703-615-7095Email: mcole@tnsi.com    2nd Level Escalation'),
