(449, 'TNS Call Tags', '<p>If you&nbsp;are requesting call tags for a site that is needing to send back&nbsp;TNS equipment, please follow this procedure.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Debranding/debranded:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If the site states they are debranding, or have recently debranded (as still showing active in RAMS), click&nbsp;the corresponding analyst\'s name below&nbsp;to send an email to confirm closure of the site. <br /><br />\r\n<table style=\"height: 120px;\" width=\"342\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Territories</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Name</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;515, 330, 355</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:kristy.donaho@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand%20confirmation%20request&amp;Body=Hello%2C%20can%20you%20confirm%20that%20the%20following%20site%20has%20either%20debranded%20or%20in%20the%20processing%20of%20debranding%3F%20The%20site%20is%20requesting%20call%20tags%20to%20return%20their%20TNS%20equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite%20Name%3A%0A%0AThank%20you%21\">Kristy Donaho</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;529, 292, 306,112, 295</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:debbie.kiker@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand%20confirmation%20request&amp;Body=Hello%2C%20can%20you%20confirm%20that%20the%20following%20site%20has%20either%20debranded%20or%20in%20the%20processing%20of%20debranding%3F%20The%20site%20is%20requesting%20call%20tags%20to%20return%20their%20TNS%20equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite%20Name%3A%0A%0AThank%20you%21\">Debbie Kiker</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;523, 240, 300, 391, 530</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:laura.macrae@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand%20confirmation%20request&amp;Body=Hello%2C%20can%20you%20confirm%20that%20the%20following%20site%20has%20either%20debranded%20or%20in%20the%20processing%20of%20debranding%3F%20The%20site%20is%20requesting%20call%20tags%20to%20return%20their%20TNS%20equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite%20Name%3A%0A%0AThank%20you%21\">Laura Macrae</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;519, 442, 439, CST</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:myrta.solis@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand%20confirmation%20request&amp;Body=Hello%2C%20can%20you%20confirm%20that%20the%20following%20site%20has%20either%20debranded%20or%20in%20the%20processing%20of%20debranding%3F%20The%20site%20is%20requesting%20call%20tags%20to%20return%20their%20TNS%20equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite%20Name%3A%0A%0AThank%20you%21\">Myrta Solis</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>&nbsp;230, 340, 510, 517</td>\r\n<td>&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:emily.wakeman@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand%20confirmation%20request&amp;Body=Hello%2C%20can%20you%20confirm%20that%20the%20following%20site%20has%20either%20debranded%20or%20in%20the%20processing%20of%20debranding%3F%20The%20site%20is%20requesting%20call%20tags%20to%20return%20their%20TNS%20equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite%20Name%3A%0A%0AThank%20you%21\">Emily Wakeman</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once you receive confirmation from the analyst, or the site is showing debranded in RAMS,&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:laylward@tnsi.com?CC=denise.arispe@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Request%20for%20Call%20Tags&amp;Body=The%20following%20site%20has%20requested%20call%20tags%20to%20return%20their%20TNS%20equipment.%20We%27ve%20confirmed%20the%20site%20has%20either%20debranded%20or%20is%20in%20the%20process%20of%20debranding.%0A%0ASite%20ID%3A%0ASite%20Address%3A%0ARecipient%20Name%3A%20%0A%0AThank%20you%20for%20your%20assistance.\">you can then send the call tag request to Laurie Aylward at TNS by clicking here.</a>&nbsp;Be sure to fill out the detail in the email.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the analyst has not received proper paperwork for the de-brand, they will contact the distributor to verify status.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Upgraded to TNS Link:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the site is needing to return their FPX due to a TNS-Link install or has extra they need to send back: <a href=\"mailto:laylward@tnsi.com?CC=denise.arispe@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Request%20for%20Call%20Tags&amp;Body=The%20following%20site%20has%20requested%20call%20tags%20to%20return%20their%20TNS%20equipment.%0A%0ASite%20ID%3A%0ASite%20Address%3A%0ARecipient%20Name%3A%20%0A%0AThank%20you%20for%20your%20assistance.\">Click here and enter the information required in the email.</a>&nbsp; Please make sure to include the reason they are needing a call tag.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp; </span>For VLINK (FPX) equipment returns in particular, TNS encourages&nbsp;that the FedEx label be sent via&nbsp;email so the customer can use their own box.&nbsp; Please be sure to obtain the following information:&nbsp;<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Name</li>\r\n<li>Phone number</li>\r\n<li>Email address and</li>\r\n<li>Address where they will be shipping from.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note</strong> </span>&ndash; whomever is receiving the label would need to be able to access Fedex.com and print the label.\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;For TNSLinks &ndash; we can still continue to send boxes and packaging materials as requested.</p>', '2016-09-16 08:30:04', 'l7d23b', '2017-07-28 10:15:52', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Procedure for requesting call tags from TNS', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:kristy.donaho@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand confirmation request&amp;Body=Hello%2C can you confirm that the following site has either debranded or in the processing of debranding%3F The site is requesting call tags to return their TNS equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite Name%3A%0A%0AThank you%21mailto:debbie.kiker@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand confirmation request&amp;Body=Hello%2C can you confirm that the following site has either debranded or in the processing of debranding%3F The site is requesting call tags to return their TNS equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite Name%3A%0A%0AThank you%21mailto:laura.macrae@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand confirmation request&amp;Body=Hello%2C can you confirm that the following site has either debranded or in the processing of debranding%3F The site is requesting call tags to return their TNS equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite Name%3A%0A%0AThank you%21mailto:myrta.solis@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand confirmation request&amp;Body=Hello%2C can you confirm that the following site has either debranded or in the processing of debranding%3F The site is requesting call tags to return their TNS equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite Name%3A%0A%0AThank you%21mailto:emily.wakeman@valero.com?CC=wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Debrand confirmation request&amp;Body=Hello%2C can you confirm that the following site has either debranded or in the processing of debranding%3F The site is requesting call tags to return their TNS equipment.%0A%0AJobber/Dealer%3A%0ASite Name%3A%0A%0AThank you%21mailto:laylward@tnsi.com?CC=denise.arispe@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Request for Call Tags&amp;Body=The following site has requested call tags to return their TNS equipment. We%27ve confirmed the site has either debranded or is in the process of debranding.%0A%0ASite ID%3A%0ASite Address%3A%0ARecipient Name%3A %0A%0AThank you for your assistance.mailto:laylward@tnsi.com?CC=denise.arispe@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com&amp;Subject=Request for Call Tags&amp;Body=The following site has requested call tags to return their TNS equipment.%0A%0ASite ID%3A%0ASite Address%3A%0ARecipient Name%3A %0A%0AThank you for your assistance.'),
(450, 'Gulf RAMS Guide', '<table style=\"height: 254px; float: left;\" width=\"620\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<h3><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">First time&nbsp;Gulf login<br /><br /></span></h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Double click the gulf icon <img src=\"upload/gulficon.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"72\" height=\"67\" />&nbsp;on your desktop. If you do not have it, <a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Reflex\\Apps\">click here in Internet Explorer</a>&nbsp;or right <a href=\"upload/apps/Gulf_Production.rsdm\">click here and select \"Save Link As\" in chrome</a>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>On the initial login screen the USERID will be your L-number and password will be RAMS.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>On the next screen type in GULF and hit enter.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Hit enter again.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>On this screen enter your initials and then enter the password according to the table on the right.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>RAMS will prompt you to change it after you enter it. Don\'t forget what you entered!<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once you\'ve logged in and successfully updated your password, <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>click below&nbsp;to send an email confirming you\'ve followed the steps and have logged in successfully to change your temp password.</strong></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<table style=\"height: 192px; float: right;\" width=\"232\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>Agent</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Temp Password</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Brent</td>\r\n<td>USERBPH</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Don</td>\r\n<td>USERDWL</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Israel</td>\r\n<td>USERIJH</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Jason</td>\r\n<td>USERJEY</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Nate</td>\r\n<td>USERNFB</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Stacey</td>\r\n<td>USERSGG</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Chris</td>\r\n<td>VALERO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Justin</td>\r\n<td>VALERO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Mary</td>\r\n<td>VALERO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Sharon</td>\r\n<td>VALERO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Suzanne</td>\r\n<td>VALERO</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan=\"2\">Please note, if you are not on this list, you are already an active Gulf user and can disregard this procedure.</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a href=\"mailto:debra.burnett@valero.com?Subject=I%27ve%20completed%20the%20Gulf/RAMS%20Sign-in%20procedure.\">Click here to send an email to confirm you\'ve set up your Gulf access.</a></h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-09-16 11:00:09', 'l7d23b', '2016-09-19 09:08:38', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on using the Gulf RAMS', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:debra.burnett@valero.com?Subject=I%27ve completed the Gulf/RAMS Sign-in procedure.'),
(451, 'IIN Rollout Information', '<p><strong>IIN Rollout</strong></p>\r\n<p>On October 4<sup>th</sup>, we started replacing Commercial Credit Cards with our IIN cards.&nbsp; By issuing these new cards, our transactions will no longer be going thru our 3<sup>rd</sup> party vendor and we will be saving on the cost of processing the transactions.</p>\r\n<p>The process will start by replacing cards in the San Antonio area and we will gradually replace our entire portfolio. Fleet Accounts will be replaced sometime in the near future once all Commercial accounts have been converted.</p>\r\n<p>Information regarding the changeover:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Approximately 670 accounts containing at least 3200 cards will be replaced.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cards will be replaced with the same sub numbers.</li>\r\n<li>After a certain number of days, the old cards will be cancelled by the system. The time frame has not been determined by management yet.</li>\r\n<li>The account number on the card is different. The card will start with &ldquo;810&rdquo; and then it will list the true account number and will include the &ldquo;90&rdquo;.</li>\r\n<li>In RAMS, on the <strong>I </strong>screen, the IINA filed will indicate a <strong>N.</strong> (N=new IIN, O=old card).</li>\r\n<li>A NOTE will be on the account if the cards were reissued: <strong>IRIS&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; REISSUED DUE TO NEW IIN</strong></li>\r\n<li>There are locations that have not converted their systems to accept our new IIN cards. We do not know which locations have converted at this time.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If a new IIN card is being declined at a location that has not been updated, we will not be able to see the declines reason in Unposted.</li>\r\n<li>Make sure that the customer is trying to use a new IIN card,</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ask for the account number on the credit card, the new IIN cards start with 810.</li>\r\n<li>If it&rsquo;s an IIN card, give a voice approval for the charge.</li>\r\n<li>Email the Fleet Supervisor the following information,</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Station Name, Address, City and State</li>\r\n<li>The Fleet Supervisor will contact Mitzi Land to reach out to the station and ask that they update their system.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Insert being sent with credit cards:<br /><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/iinaddin.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"181\" height=\"357\" /></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '2016-10-05 12:11:01', 'l7d23b', '2016-10-05 12:11:01', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'IIN Rollout Information', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(452, 'Android and Apple Pay', '<p>If you have a site or technician calling concerning any NFC payment types, direct them to their POS Vendor so the vendor can assist with the process of setting it up.</p>', '2016-10-14 09:53:47', 'l7d23b', '2016-10-14 09:53:47', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on Android and Apple pay', '', 10008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(453, 'T+1 Settlement Process', '<p>Any requests for a Retailer&rsquo;s settlement chain to be changed to Transaction + 1 day settlement (T+1) for credit and debit cards should be made by Area Sales Managers. The ASMs should hold a discussion with Retailers and confirm the additional charges for T+1 Settlement as set out in the VCS User Agreement, Appendix 1, Part 2, 2. Variable Charges.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>ASMs request the changes via email to VCS Support. The email should be for the attention of VCS Support Admin (Beth) and the VCS Helpdesk.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VCS Support Admin will email the request to the Barclays Merchant Services account manager quoting the sites MID. Once VCS Admin receives confirmation from BMS that the site&rsquo;s MID is on the T+1 Chain, VCS support will confirm to the ASM.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>VCS Helpdesk will amend the site&rsquo;s billing in RAMS so that the site is billed the monthly T+1 Settlement fee and increased MSC&rsquo;s in their VCS monthly invoice.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sites Mid-term: The amendment may be parked by the Amarillo Helpdesk so that it takes effect on the correct month&rsquo;s billing cycle in order that the retailer is not billed prematurely for their T+1 Settlement (based on the monthly billing cycle dates).</li>\r\n<li>New contract: The settlement chain will be notated on the sites Merlin record and the VCS Tracker. The Amarillo helpdesk will update RAMs for the charges to take effect on the first invoice.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Once the update in RAMs has been made by the VCS Helpdesk, the Helpdesk will confirm the update to VCS support Admin.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>This process will be tracked by VCS Admin on a T+1 billing tracker based on the Retail Technology Share Point site.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The billing will then be checked by VCS Admin on the site&rsquo;s respective VCS invoice.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2016-10-21 10:39:19', 'l7d23b', '2016-10-21 10:39:36', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how a site is setup on the T+1 settlement process', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(454, 'Emergency Procedure - Accident or Illness', '<p>A new system has been put in place to notify us, via the backdoor line, if anyone in the building dials 911.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Our group has extra responsibilities regarding this change. </strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>You will need to read the attached PDF and familiarize yourself with the new procedure.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Please see below.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>From the article:</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><em>When a 9-1-1 call is placed using a landline within our facility, a notification is also initiated on the Wholesale Technical Support (WTS) &lsquo;Back Door&rsquo; line. <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>(1.)</strong></span>The WTS phone display will reflect the name and number of the extension that placed the 9-1-1 call.<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> <strong>(2.)</strong></span>The WTS agent(s) retrieving the 9-1-1 call will immediately proceed to the location of the individual who placed the 9-1-1 call to assure they have assistance, then proceed towards the front of the facility to greet emergency personnel and alert a member of management<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">(3.)</span></strong>. </em></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>You <strong>must</strong> record the name of the individual that shows up. Only answer the line after you have obtained the name. The line will be dead air but will continue to ring until answered.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>There will be 2 agents involved&nbsp;in this process. <br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The first will proceed to the location of the individual who placed the 9-1-1 call. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>The second will notify a member of management. If Debra or David are here, notify them first. If they are not, notify a member of management <strong>on your way up to the front</strong> to meet emergency personnel.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Once a member of management has relieved you at the front desk your responsibility has been fulfilled. Proceed back to your desk at this time.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/Emergency - Accident or Illness.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Emergency - Accident or Illness.pdf</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2016-11-02 13:28:03', 'l7d23b', '2016-11-02 13:54:21', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Emergency Procedure - Accident or Illness', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(455, 'EMV Liability Communication to Jobbers', '<p>Wholesale sent a communication out to Jobbers in reference to the EMV Liability shift that happens on December 31, 2016 and the losses they could potentially incur if their sites have not become EMV compliant. Wholesale would like for our distributors to understand their potential liability.</p>\r\n<p>We have a spreadsheet showing the potential loss for each jobber located <a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Reflex Articles\\EMV by Store-YTD Oct 2016.xlsx\">here</a>. Please give them the total amount under the &ldquo;total&rdquo; column on the sheet for the sites in question.&nbsp; When you create the ticket, please select:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Record Type: </strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">WholesaleRequest</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Call Type: </strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Merchant Info Request</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Category: </strong>Type &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">EMV</span>&rdquo; in field</p>\r\n<p><strong>Priority:</strong> <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">3</span>.</p>\r\n<p>If you have any questions please see David or Debra.</p>', '2016-11-08 09:42:01', 'lbfb2t', '2017-06-18 10:13:13', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on potential losses due to EMV non-compliance.', '', 50005, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
