(462, 'EMV Chargebacks', '<p>Beginning <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">January 1</span>, some stores are being held responsible for chargebacks of transactions for EMV capable Bankcards for inside sales. The VPS system identifies these chargebacks based on the original dispute code for Visa (0062), MasterCard (4870 or 4871), and Amex (F30 or F31). Discover chargebacks are identified by the dispute code (UA01), but these are processed manually.</p>\r\n<p>The following chargeback codes apply to these chargebacks:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>33 &ndash; Counterfeit Card &ndash; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Store responsible</span></li>\r\n<li>34 &ndash; Lost/Stolen Fraud &ndash; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Store responsible</span></li>\r\n<li>35 &ndash; Counterfeit Card &ndash; Valero responsible</li>\r\n<li>36 &ndash; Lost/Stolen Fraud &ndash; Valero responsible</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Note:</span></strong> We have no recourse to dispute these transactions with the issuer, so copies of the receipt are not necessary.</p>\r\n<p>Chargebacks with a 33 or 34 code are charged to the store on their settlement. VPS will use one of these codes if the store has an EMV responsibility date in RAMS and the transaction date is after that date. If a station does not have a date set on the day a chargeback is processed, the 35 or 36 chargeback code is used. This will also be true if the station has a date set, but the transaction date for the disputed transaction is before the date. 35 and 36 code chargebacks are not charged to the station.</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Responsibility Dates</span>&rdquo; are currently being updated manually based on the weekly file we receive from First Data. The following criteria are used:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Stores with a Gilbarco POS and some Verifone devices were responsible starting 1/1 or the date of the file showing the update to the device. The following Hardware codes are sent on the file:<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Pass</li>\r\n<li>R</li>\r\n<li>R H</li>\r\n<li>RS</li>\r\n<li>RS H</li>\r\n<li>RST</li>\r\n<li>RSTH</li>\r\n<li>S</li>\r\n<li>ST</li>\r\n<li>STH<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Currently GPM and East End Marketing stores are not being held responsible. They do not have a date.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>CST wants to handle their chargebacks at a corporate level, so their stores do not have dates set either.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>RAMS will show a store with an EMV responsibility date set (far right, middle of the screen). Accessible with <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">shift+F4</span> on the main screen.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/emv-rams.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"717\" height=\"436\" /></p>\r\n<p>The date also shows up on the screen of the chargeback in VPS:</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/emv-vps.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"735\" height=\"518\" /></p>', '2017-01-19 09:29:42', 'l7d23b', '2017-06-17 15:13:21', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Info on EMV Chargebacks', '', 50005, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(463, 'Verifone Service ID', '<p>Sites that don\'t know their Service ID can e-mail <u><a href=\"mailto:petroservices@verifone.com\">petroservices@verifone.com</a></u> OR navigate to CSR Functions menu of their register, select Maintenance, and then select \"13. Check for VRSD Updates\". Service ID will be displayed in pop-up screen.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" src=\"upload/srvid.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"593\" height=\"326\" /></p>', '2017-01-19 13:47:25', 'l7d23b', '2017-01-19 13:47:25', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on finding the Verifone Service ID', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(464, 'VPS Reports', '<p>From the main VPS screen, select <strong>VPS Reporting.</strong></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reporting/1.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"216\" height=\"107\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>On the next screen, select <strong>Public Reports.</strong></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reporting/2.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"484\" height=\"242\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Then select <strong>WTS Reports</strong> at the bottom of the list.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reporting/3.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"563\" height=\"345\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The following page will list the available reports. They will have the same input as the old reporting system.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reporting/4.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"301\" height=\"245\" /></p>', '2017-02-03 11:31:15', 'l7d23b', '2017-02-03 11:31:15', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information VPS Reports', '', 40009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(465, 'UPS Transit Times Map', '<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/map_0470.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"546\" height=\"353\" /></p>', '2017-02-06 08:45:35', 'l7d23b', '2017-02-06 08:45:35', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'UPS Transit Times Map', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(466, 'Sagenet S1 Ticket Process', '<p>If SageNet deems that an S1 ticket will be necessary to get a site back online, a quote will be sent to the group box <a href=\"mailto:wts-ama@valero.com\">wts-ama@valero.com</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>It will be the responsibility of the agent monitoring the box to notify the agent who opened the initial S3 ticket.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The agent who opened the S3 will then be responsible for contacting the site for approval of the necessary charges.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The agent will need to receive acknowledgement, either verbal or written, from someone from the site who is authorized to approve charges.&nbsp; This will typically be either the site owner or the manager on duty.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If/When verbal acknowledgement is obtained, please notify David Cantor of the ticket number and the time of the call so that the recorded call may be archived for future reference if required.&nbsp; If written acknowledgment is requested, please use the template located at <a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Spacenet\">here</a>.&nbsp; Please email Melissa Morgan (<a href=\"mailto:Melissa.Morgan@SageNet.com\">Melissa.Morgan@SageNet.com</a>)&nbsp;at Sagenet with the authorization information.</p>', '2017-02-23 17:14:11', 'lbfb2t', '2017-03-23 09:00:54', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'New process for handling S1 tickets', '', 30010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:wts-ama@valero.com'),
