(468, 'New BP Fuel Cards Design', '<p align=\"LEFT\">BP have launched a new card design which will start to appear as new accounts are opened and they renew expired cards on existing accounts.</p>\r\n<p>BP will <strong><span style=\"font-family: Calibri,Calibri;\">not </span></strong>be replacing all cards immediately which means that there will be a 3 year deployment of the new design for customers&rsquo; cards as they are replaced. Therefore, the existing design should continue to be accepted during this time. The new design cards have the same ISO 700676 and therefore no development is required on the Gempay.</p>\r\n<p>Below are images of the new BP Plus card designs and the current card image:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 21px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 241px;\"><img src=\"upload/bp-int.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"275\" height=\"178\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 241px;\"><img src=\"upload/bp-uk.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"282\" height=\"173\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 241px;\"><img src=\"upload/bp-existing.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"269\" height=\"174\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 241px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">UK Issued BP Plus Card (UK and International use)</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 241px; text-align: center;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">UK Issued BP Plus Card (UK use only)</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 241px; text-align: center;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">UK Issued BP Plus Card (existing design)</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-05-09 05:45:09', 'l7d23b', '2017-05-09 05:46:28', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on the new BP Fuel Cards Design', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', ''),
(469, 'MasterCard 2-Series Cards', '<h4><strong>12/19/17 Update&nbsp;</strong></h4>\r\n<p>We&rsquo;ve been granted an additional extension on the new 2-series MasterCard. Previously we communicated sites had until December 31, 2017 to be</p>\r\n<p>compliant. However, now our Valero sites have until <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>June 30, 2018</strong> </span>to upgrade hardware and/or software to support the new 2-series MasterCard. Failure to accept the new card will result in fines from MasterCard.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4><strong>11/14/2017 Update</strong></h4>\r\n<p>Our Marketing team will be mailing letters this week to 248 distributors (2943 sites) that have sites with POS systems installed that are <strong>unable</strong> to accept the new 2-series MasterCard. <a href=\"upload/docs/Mastercard2series_POS_update_ltr v2.docx\" target=\"_blank\">The letter can be found here.</a> <a href=\"upload/docs/MasterCard 2Series nonCompliant final.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">The list of sites, here.</a></p>\r\n<p>If you receive calls from distributors or sites inquiring about Commander software upgrades, please remind the site that if a working EZR is installed, that the software upgrade can be performed remotely.&nbsp; <a href=\"upload/docs/Sales Bulletin_FD_EMV Transition Team Valero v2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">You can view&nbsp;the letter that we emailed previously about Verifone&rsquo;s EMV Assistance Team here.</a>&nbsp;This defines the process for requesting a software download and EMV configuration assistance.&nbsp; Our Marketing team will send a reminder email this week to our distributors about Verifone&rsquo;s EMV Assistance Team.</p>\r\n<p>You may receive calls from sites installed with Gilbarco Passport inquiring on current version installed&nbsp; To identify the software version currently running, please follow these steps.</p>\r\n<p>From the Cashier screen:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>select More</li>\r\n<li>select Stats</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The Passport version line will show:&nbsp; Server version number / Maintenance pack / Brand or Network</p>\r\n<p>Example software version format:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 11.01.23.01X VALERO</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>MasterCard is releasing a new consumer credit card that is referred to as the 2-series BIN.&nbsp; All Valero sites&nbsp;will be required to&nbsp;accept this new card.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Failure to accept the new card may result in fines from MasterCard.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Valero sites have until December 31<sup>st</sup>&nbsp;2017 to upgrade hardware and/or software of non-compliant systems.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The table below gives information on which systems and software versions will work with the card.</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 621px; height: 119px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #3592cc; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><strong>Vendor</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #3592cc; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><strong>System</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #3592cc; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"color: #ffffff;\"><strong>MasterCard 2-Series</strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">FISCAL</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Trav Star 1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Supported in v10.00.01-3565</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Gilbarco</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Passport</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Supported in v10P&nbsp;and higher</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">NCR</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Radiant</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Will be supported in EMV&nbsp;version</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #eb9d9d; height: 13px;\">Verifone</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #eb9d9d; height: 13px;\">Ruby</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #eb9d9d; height: 13px;\">Not Supported</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Verifone</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Ruby Ci</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Supported in v3.02.34</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Verifone</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Ruby 2 w/Commander</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Supported in v3.02.34</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Verifone</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Topaz w/Commander</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #e8e8e8; height: 13px;\">Supported in v3.02.34</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Verifone</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Ruby Sapphire</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Supported in v6.02.13</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Verifone</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Topaz Sapphire</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Supported in v6.02.13</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 83px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Wayne</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 154px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Nucleus (Fusion)</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 354px; background-color: #a8f0b4; height: 13px;\">Supported in v8.00AG_patch02</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2017-06-01 09:56:36', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-19 14:51:49', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on MasterCard \'2-Series BIN\' Cards', '', 10008, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '\r\nNovember 13, 2017RE: MasterCard 2-Series BINs Dear Valero Distributor/Dealer:We previously communicated that MasterCard is releasing a new series of BINs to accommodate growth. The new series of BINs begin with 2 (range 222100-272099) and will work exactly the same way as the current 5-series BINs do today. In order to support the new 2-series BINs, sites are strongly encouraged to upgrade POS hardware and/or software by January 1, 2018. If sites are unable to accept the new 2-series BINs starting January 1, 2018, MasterCard will impose fines per incident starting at $2,500 for the first 30 days and will increase the fines after that. Weve attached a list of your non-compliant sites that will not support the new BINs and will require a software and/or hardware upgrade. For Gilbarco Passport systems running v10, please check the patch version. Only Passport v10p will support the new MasterCard.For your convenience, the chart below shows which software version is needed by POS type to accept the MasterCard 2-Series BINs.For questions regarding this information, please contact Valero Wholesale Technical Support at 866-482-5376 (866-4VALERO). As always, thank you for your business. Sincerely, Carolyn J. AllenDirector, Wholesale Brands'),
(470, 'TNS Zoom Modem', '<p>The Zoom modem is the Dial Backup option that comes with the TNS Link.&nbsp; This device will allow sites to still run credit cards over their analog phone line in case there is an issue with their internet connection.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Front of Zoom Modem:</strong></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/front-zoom-modem.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"358\" height=\"87\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Description of lights:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Pwr</strong>: Power</li>\r\n<li><strong>TD</strong>: Transmit Data - data is being sent to modem</li>\r\n<li><strong>RD</strong>: Receive Data - data is being received from modem</li>\r\n<li><strong>OH</strong>: Off-Hook - Zoom modem is using the phone line\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>***This is the main indicator light that the Valero Help Desk will look for.&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">If this light is on it means that the site is processing on DBU</span>***</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>CD</strong>: Carrier Detect - modem is talking to another modem</li>\r\n<li><strong>TR</strong>: Terminal Ready - modem is ready to send data</li>\r\n<li><strong>AA</strong>: Auto Answer - modem will automatically answer incoming calls</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Back of Zoom Modem:</strong></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/zoom-modem.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"449\" height=\"134\" /></p>\r\n<p><strong>Connections:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>TNS Cable type # 125 connects from COM port on Zoom modem to \"Console\" port on TNS Link.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Analog phone line needs to be connected to the \"Line\" port.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Troubleshooting:</strong></p>\r\n<p>If site will not recover on DBU -</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Verify the phone line is connected to the \"Line\" port on the Zoom modem</li>\r\n<li>Verify TNS Cable type # 125 is connected to the COM port on the Zoom modem and the other end is connected to the \"Console\" port on the TNS Link</li>\r\n<li>If the \"OH\" light will not come on -\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Power down the Zoom modem and TNS Link for about 30 seconds</li>\r\n<li>Power up the Zoom modem first and wait about 1 min</li>\r\n<li>Power up the TNS Link</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Once Zoom modem starts to connect you will hear a loud dial-up noise.&nbsp; Once it has made&nbsp;a connection you will see the \"OH\" light come on.&nbsp; If not, go through troubleshooting steps above.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>If it will still not work, verify dial tone on the phone line and verify that it is a analog line.&nbsp; Digital phone lines will not work on the Zoom modem.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-06-04 12:17:49', 'ln524h', '2017-06-19 11:45:05', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Zoom Modem Overview', '', 30009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(471, 'Gift Card FedEx Shipping', '<p>If a customer requests expedited shipping for a gift card order, we can accommodate that request by obtaining a quote from the FedEx website and provide the customer the shipping quote.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.fedex.com/ratefinder/home?cc=US&amp;language=en&amp;locId=express\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a> to access the FedEx \"Get Rates &amp; Transit Times\" page.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note:</strong></span> If you are submitting a gift card order with expedited shipping please email the gift card agent with the order number and the shipping quote you obtained.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #000000; width: 828px; height: 512px; background-color: #ffffff;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 51px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 17.35px; height: 51px;\">1.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 111.69px; height: 51px;\"><strong><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">From</span></strong><br />Amarillo Office Zip - <strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">79110</span></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 676.96px; height: 193.19px;\" rowspan=\"7\"><img style=\"float: left;\" src=\"upload/fedexmain.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"671\" height=\"502\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 45px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 17.35px; height: 45px;\">2.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 111.69px; height: 45px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>To</strong><br /></span>Customer&rsquo;s Zip</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 31px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 17.35px; height: 31px;\">3.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 111.69px; height: 31px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>No. of packages</strong><br /></span>Enter 1</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 3px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 17.35px; height: 3px;\">4.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 111.69px; height: 3px;\">&nbsp;\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Weight</strong><br /></span>Use <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Ship Weight</strong> </span>from order form in Reflex</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 17.35px; height: 17px;\">5.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 111.69px; height: 17px;\">&nbsp;\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Pickup/Dropoff</strong><br /></span>Use an already scheduled pickup</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 20.19px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 17.35px; height: 20.19px;\">6.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 111.69px; height: 20.19px;\">&nbsp;\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Ship Date</strong><br /></span>Set this to <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>2</strong> </span><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">business days</span> </strong>after order</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 26px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 17.35px; height: 26px;\">7.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 111.69px; height: 26px;\">Finally, Click <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Get detailed quote</strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 830px; height: 300px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 20.01px;\">8.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 109.29px;\">\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Package Type</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Choose \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>FedEx Small Box</strong></span>\"</span></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 678.7px; height: 3.36px;\" rowspan=\"2\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/fedexpackagetype.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"632\" height=\"290\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 20.01px; height: 13px;\">9.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 109.29px; height: 13px;\">Click \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Continue</strong></span>\"</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 828.83px; height: 230px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.94px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 18px; height: 13.94px;\">10.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 108px; height: 13.94px;\">\r\n<p>FedEx will provide shipping quotes and estimated time of delivery.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Advise the customer of these options available.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 681.83px; height: 13.94px;\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/fedex-quote.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"640\" height=\"221\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 831px; height: 194px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 183.94px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 19.09px; height: 183.94px;\">11.</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 108.46px; height: 183.94px;\">Enter the shipping quote total you obtained from the FedEx website in the \"<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Shipping Cost</span></strong>\" field in the Reflex order.&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 681.45px; height: 183.94px;\"><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/reflex-shipping-field.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"428\" height=\"183\" /></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-06-07 15:19:56', 'ln524h', '2017-06-10 15:14:46', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to submit an expedited shipping request for a gift card order', '', 40010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'https://www.fedex.com/ratefinder/home?cc=US&amp;language=en&amp;locId=express');
