(472, 'Gempay 3 Guide', '<p>Quick Menu</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 100%; height: 15px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 4px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.23%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#functionkeys\">Function Keys</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.93%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#menustructure\">Menu Structure</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 7.79%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#preauth\">Pre-Auth</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 14.79%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#fuelcard\">Fuel Card Transactions </a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.35%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#troubleshooting\">Troubleshooting</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 4.11px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.23%; height: 4.11px;\"><a href=\"#eft\">EFT Transactions</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.93%; height: 4.11px;\"><a href=\"#refunds\">Refunds</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 7.79%; height: 4.11px;\"><a href=\"#eoseod\">EOD and EOS </a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 14.79%; height: 4.11px;\"><a href=\"#download\">Downloads</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.35%; height: 4.11px;\"><a href=\"#star\">Star Rewards (loyalty)</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 4px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.23%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#time\">Time Change</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.93%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#brightness\">Terminal/Pin Pad Brightness</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 7.79%; height: 4px;\"><a href=\"#reboot\">Soft Reboot</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 14.79%; height: 4px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 11.35%; height: 4px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>Introduction</h3>\r\n<p>GemPAY3 is HTEC\'s payment terminal solution specifically designed to meet the payment processing requirements for credit, debit, and fuel cards. HTEC GemPAY3 can be linked to various Point-of-Sales systems, including HTEC\'s HydraPOS and RetPOS systems. It can also be operated as a standalone terminal. The software runs on a proven hardware platform manufactured by Ingenico, the world leader in payment terminal technologies.</p>\r\n<p>When the GemPAY3 is powered on, it displays the HTEC logo and connection information (top left), time and date (top right), and function buttons. Looking at the color of the connection icon will give you the status of the connection.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/gp1.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"508\" height=\"292\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Installing printer paper</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/gp2.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"661\" height=\"181\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a id=\"functionkeys\"></a>Function Key Layout</strong></span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #000000; width: 266px; height: 69px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 43.52px;\">F1</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 209.47px;\">Manual Sale</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 43.52px;\">F2</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 209.47px;\">Pre-authorisation</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 43.52px;\">F3</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 209.47px;\">Print Contactless Receipt</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 43.52px;\">F4</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 209.47px;\">Call TMS</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Keyboard Layout</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>On the main alphanumeric keypad, the right hand side keys are for decisions taken against the chosen options or to control software flow. A detailed description is listed below</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #000000; width: 512px; height: 74px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px;\">Function</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.91px;\">Key</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 155.08px;\">Key Description</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px;\">Call&nbsp;Menu</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.91px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/white button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"28\" height=\"30\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 155.08px;\">Menu</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px;\">Cancel option or go back to Main Screen</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.91px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/red button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"25\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 155.08px;\">Cancel</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px;\">Clear a typed character or go back in Menu</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.91px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/yellow%20button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"28\" height=\"30\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 155.08px;\">Clear/Back</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 300px;\">Confirm selection or press for YES</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39.91px;\">&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/green button.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"30\" height=\"31\" /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 155.08px;\">Select/Yes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Rebooting the terminal</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Hold down the Clear/Back (yellow) key and press the decimal/point key on the keypad. This will initiate a soft reboot of the terminal.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Connectivity</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>White - No cable connected<br />Orange - No connection<br />Green - Online</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>GemPay Physical Connections</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>The GemPay3 has no On/Off switch. This function is performed by connecting/disconnecting the transformer from the power source. The diagram below shows ports where Ethernet cable, PIN pad, USB, and power transformer can be connected.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/gp3.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"519\" height=\"433\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Pin Pad: Lane/5000</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Lane/5000 model offers contact and contactless reader functionalities for Chip &amp; Pin, contact, and contactless cards.</p>\r\n<p>Note: During terminal installation, if&nbsp;a PIN pad is detected, the \"PP\" icon will be displayed on the terminal screen. If the \"PP\" icon is not shown, disconnect the PIN pad, reboot the terminal, then reconnect the PIN pad.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/gp3/gp4.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"167\" height=\"222\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Pin Pad physical connections</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>The customer pin pad has a single cable that splits in two. One end will connect to the terminal, the other will connection into a power supply box.<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><br /><img src=\"upload/line5k-wire.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"315\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To reboot the pin pad, disconnect the power supply connector for 30 seconds.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Pin pad power supply.<br /><img src=\"upload/line5k-psu.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"302\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Pin pad power supply connected to pin pad cable.<br /><img src=\"upload/line5k-connected.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"500\" height=\"244\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a id=\"menustructure\"></a>Menu Structure</strong></span></p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #000000; width: 469px; height: 606px;\" border=\"1\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 125.93px; height: 221px; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"17\">\r\n<h4><strong>Control Panel</strong></h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 52px;\" rowspan=\"4\">Application Reports</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Transaction</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Calls Planning</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Diagnosis</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Batch Data Capture</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 39px;\" rowspan=\"3\">Software Management</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Evolution</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">View Configuration</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Removal</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 78px;\" rowspan=\"6\">Terminal Information</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Shortcuts</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Legal Information</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Application Version</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">SDK Information</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Firmware PCIPTS</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Hardware Information</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 52px;\" rowspan=\"4\">Terminal Settings</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">General Settings</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Human Interface</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">ECO Mode</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Communication Means</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 125.93px; height: 39px; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"3\">\r\n<h4><strong>Contactless</strong></h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 26px;\" rowspan=\"2\">ICC Debug</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Enable ICC Debug</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Disable ICC Debug</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 13px;\">Detailed Logging</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 125.93px; height: 38.34px; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"3\">\r\n<h4><strong>EFT</strong></h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 25.34px;\" rowspan=\"2\">ICC Debug</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Enable ICC Debug</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 12.34px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 164.25px; height: 12.34px;\">Disable ICC Debug</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 13px;\">Detailed Logging</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 125.93px; height: 26px; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"2\">\r\n<h4><strong>Fuel Cards</strong></h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 13px;\">Check Card</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 13px;\">Detail Logging</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 125.93px; height: 182px; text-align: center;\" rowspan=\"14\">\r\n<h4><strong>AM</strong></h4>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 52px;\" rowspan=\"4\">Transactions</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Manual Sale</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Pre Auth</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Refund</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">End of Shift&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 39px;\" rowspan=\"3\">Duplicates</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Transactions</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">End of Shift</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">End of Day</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 13px;\">Maintenance</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Call TMS</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 65px;\" rowspan=\"5\">Terminal</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Terminal Attributes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">TMS ID</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">TMP IP Settings</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">POS Link Setup</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">Detailed Logging</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"border: 1px solid black; width: 156.82px; height: 13px;\">Engineer</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 164.25px; height: 13px;\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><a id=\"download\"></a>TMS Download</h3>\r\n<p><strong>Download</strong><br />To perform a TMS download:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>White</strong> key</li>\r\n<li>Choose <strong>AM</strong> tile</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Maintenance</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Call TMS</strong></li>\r\n<li>Press the green button</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"preauth\"></a>Pre-Authorisation Process</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Fuel Card (Keyed and Swiped) - Stand Alone or Manual</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><br />To access the Pre-Authorisation menu:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>white key</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select the <strong>AM</strong> tile</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Transaction menu</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Pre-Auth<br /><br /></strong><strong>OR</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Press the <strong>F1 </strong>button on the GemPay idle screen.<br /><br />After this step, the GBP 1.00 PRESENT CARD message will be displayed.<br />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Connecting to Host</strong><br />When a fuel card is pre-authorised, the card is connected to the card issuer for host pre-validation. For example, if the card is a UK Fuels card, the message on screen will ready: \"<strong>CONNECTING TO UK FUELS RT</strong>.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Host Connected</strong><br />Once the terminal is connected to the host, the screen will read: \"<strong>CONNECTED</strong>.\"<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Product Allowed</strong><br />On a successful pre-authorisation, the products allowed for the fuel card are printed on a receipt as well as the pre-auth validation code for the merchant.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Pre-Auth Receipt</strong><br />After the Pre-validation receipt is printed, the terminal will return to the idle screen.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Product Allowed</p>\r\n<p>On a successful pre-authorisation, the products allowed for the fuel card are printed on the receipt as well as a pre-auth validation code for the merchant.<img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/gp3/gp5.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"276\" height=\"343\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"fuelcard\"></a>Fuel Card&nbsp;Transaction Process&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Fuel Card (Keyed and Swiped) - Stand Alone or Manual</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><br /></strong>To access the Manual Transaction menu:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>white key</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select the <strong>AM</strong> tile</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Transaction</strong> menu</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Manual Sale</strong><br /><br /><strong>OR<br /></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Press the <strong>F2 </strong>button on the GemPay idle screen.<br /><br />After this step, the amount prompt is displayed. Enter a zero amount and continue, this will trigger a card prompt.<br /><br />To key a card number in, press the white key and choose <strong>Manual Entry</strong>.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Enter Product Codes</strong><br />A message is displayed to let the operator manually enter a product code or press the white key to choose from a list of products.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If the white key is pressed on the <strong>ENTER PRODUCT CODE</strong> screen, a list of all product categories <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">available on the card</span> are displayed.<br />Select a category by pressing on it on the screen. Once highlighted, the green key will select the category.</li>\r\n<li>Once a category is selected, the list of products available and their product codes will be displayed.</li>\r\n<li>Select a product by pressing on screen to highlight and press the green button.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Enter Amount</strong><br />This screen will prompt for GBP amount to be entered.<br /><br />Note: If a zero amount is entered, an invalid value error message is displayed, and the operator will be prompted again.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Enter Volume</strong><br />Once a product is chosen, there are multiple screens shown to capture more data regarding this product.<br /><br />Note: If dry goods are selected, <strong>ENTER VOLUME</strong> is replaced by <strong>ENTER QUANTITY</strong>. If \"0\" is entered, the terminal will display an&nbsp;<strong>INCORRECT VALUE</strong> message and will re-prompt for quantity or volume.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Additional Product Sales</strong><br />After volume or quantity has been entered, the&nbsp;customer will be asked if they want more products. If <strong>YES</strong> is selected, the terminal will return to the prompt for product code (step 1 above). If <strong>NO</strong> is selected, the transaction will proceed to the next step.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Enter Mileage</strong><br />This screen will prompt for vehicle mileage if the card requires it. Some schemes require value of mileage to be greater than zero or one.<br />Mileage can be entered on the keypad or via an on screen&nbsp;keyboard.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Enter VRN</strong><br />This screen prompts for the customer\'s vehicle registration number. VRN can be entered on the keypad or via an on screen keyboard.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Card Verification - PIN/Signature<br /></strong>If the card is a Chip &amp; PIN card, the terminal will prompt for a PIN. If the card is a magnetic strip card, the terminal will either ask for the&nbsp;PIN or the operator to verify the signature.<br />Note:<strong><br /></strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If the PIN entered is incorrect, the terminal will display the message: INCORRECT PIN.</li>\r\n<li>If the cardholder entered the PIN incorrectly twice, the terminal will display: LAST PIN TRY.</li>\r\n<li>If the terminal is left idle for more than 20 seconds, it will display the message: PIN NOT ENTERED.</li>\r\n<li>If the PIN is canceled or the&nbsp;third attempt failed, the transaction will be canceled.</li>\r\n<li>If the pin is correct, the terminal will proceed to the next step.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Additional Data Entry</strong><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Vehicle ID&nbsp;</strong><br />Specific schemes may require entering of vehicle ID data. This is controlled by card.<br />This will be prompted on the PIN pad for customer entry.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Driver ID</strong><br />Specific schemes may require entering of&nbsp;driver ID data. This is controlled by card.<br />This will be prompted on the PIN pad for customer entry.<br /><br />Driver ID and Vehicle ID prompts are mutually exclusive to each other.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Host Connection<br /></strong>If the host connection is successful, the <strong>CONNECTED</strong> message screen is displayed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Transaction Approved<br /></strong>Once the transaction is approved, the <strong>COMPLETED REMOVE CARD</strong> message will be displayed.<br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If PIN process was not performed, the application will ask operator to verify signature.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Signature Verification</strong><br />Once all of the information has been entered, merchant copy is printed, and the operator&nbsp;is prompted to verify signature.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Fuel Card Swiped &amp; Keyed Transaction Process (POS-Linked)</strong></p>\r\n<p>OPI Protocol</p>\r\n<p>When the GemPay3 terminal is POS-linked, the operator&nbsp;can start a fuel card transaction on the POS by selecting the relevant fuel or goods that need to be sold as well as the amount from the POS. After these steps, the operator will need to select the method of payment on the POS. After the method of payment is selected on the POS, the POS will send a message to the GemPay3 to prompt to present card.</p>\r\n<p>Although the request for authorisation will be performed on the GemPay, some prompts will still be displayed on the POS. Some for these prompts include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Prompt for Mileage</li>\r\n<li>Vehicle Registration</li>\r\n<li>Call Auth Centre (Card Issuer for Authorization)</li>\r\n<li>Auth Code</li>\r\n<li>Signature Check</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"eft\"></a>EFT Transaction Process</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>EFT Transaction - Standalone or Manual</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>To access the Manual Transaction menu:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>white key</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select the <strong>AM</strong> tile</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Transaction</strong> menu</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Manual Sale</strong><br /><br /><strong>OR<br /></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Press the <strong>F2 </strong>button on the GemPAY idle screen.</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">After this step, the amount prompt is displayed.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Enter Amount</strong><br />The sale amount can be entered at this point. If a zero amount is entered, the amount prompt will be displayed again after presenting the card. (This is not applicable for contactless cards)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Card Prompt</strong><br />The customer can now&nbsp;insert, swipe, or tap card on the PIN pad. To key a card number, press the <strong>white key</strong> and select <strong>Manual Entry. </strong>If Manual Entry is the only option available, then it will be displayed automatically.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Cash Back Prompt</strong><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Enter PIN</strong><br />After inserting card, the next screen will prompt for a PIN on the pin pad. The terminal will display \"<strong>AWAITING PIN ENTRY</strong>\" until a valid pin is entered. The PIN OK screen should be displayed if a valid PIN is entered.<br />Note: If an invalid PIN is entered, \"<strong>INCORRECT PIN</strong>\" will be displayed. If pin prompt times out or is canceled, the transaction will be voided.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Connecting to Host</strong><br />Depending on the acquirer, a connecting to host message will be displayed. In our case, it will display \"<strong>CONNECTING TO BMS</strong>.\"<br /><br />During this process the PIN pad will display:<br /><strong>PLEASE WAIT</strong> if card is inserted<br /><strong>DO NOT REMOVE CARD</strong> in all other cases<br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Host Connected</strong><br />After the terminal connects to the host, the <strong>CONNECTED</strong> message will be displayed.<br /><br />During this process, the PIN pad will display:<br /><strong>PLEASE WAIT</strong> if card is inserted<br /><strong>DO NOT REMOVE CARD</strong> in all other cases<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>No Host Connection</strong><br />If the host cannot be reached, the terminal will display \"<strong>RECONNECTING TO BMS</strong>\" followed by \"<strong>CONNECTING TO BMS</strong>.\" This will repeat up to 3 times.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Authorization&nbsp;Result</strong><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Transaction Approved<br /></strong><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Signature Validation</strong><br />If the transaction was Chip &amp; Signature, swiped, or keyed in, then <strong>\"IS SIGNATURE VALID?\"</strong> will be displayed, and a receipt with a signature line will be printed. Operator then confirms if the signature is valid by pressing <strong>YES</strong>. <strong>PLEASE WAIT</strong> will be displayed as the customer\'s receipt is printed. If<strong> NO</strong> is selected, the transaction will be declined.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Chip &amp; PIN Transaction</strong><br />If the transaction&nbsp;was chip &amp; pin, then no additional validation needs to be performed. <strong>APPROVED REMOVE CARD</strong> message will be displayed on both terminal and pin pad, and receipt will be printed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Transaction Declined<br /></strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If the transaction was not approved or signature was rejected, <strong>NOT AUTHORISED</strong> is displayed on the terminal, and <strong>DECLINED</strong> is displayed on the pin pad. If a chip card was used, <strong>DECLINED REMOVE CARD</strong> is displayed instead. Declined receipt will be printed.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>POS Linked Transaction<br /></strong>The operator will need to process the sale on the POS as normal. After sending the sale from the POS to the terminal, \"<strong>PRESENT CARD</strong>\" will be displayed on the GemPAY3.<br />After the card has been inserted, swiped, or keyed, the steps will be exactly the same as in the EFT Transaction instructions&nbsp;above.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"refunds\"></a>Refunds</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Refund Transaction - Standalone or Manual</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>To access the Refund menu:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>White</strong> key</li>\r\n<li>Choose <strong>AM</strong> tile</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Transactions</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Refund</strong></li>\r\n<li>Enter supervisor password</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Enter Amount</strong><br />If the supervisory password entry is successful, the amount prompt will be displayed. An amount should be entered and the green button pressed. This will trigger the card prompt. If a zero amount is entered, then the amount prompt will be displayed after presenting the card. This is not applicable to contactless cards.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Present Card</strong><br />When the card is inserted, swiped, or keyed, \"<strong>PLEASE WAIT</strong>\" will be displayed.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Check Signature</strong><br />Once all of the information has been entered, a merchant copy will be printed, and the operator will be prompted to verify the cardholder signature. Operator will be presented with the following options:\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>OK</strong> - Completes transaction</li>\r\n<li><strong>NO</strong> - Displays a \"<strong>TEAR OFF RECEIPT</strong>\" message, followed by a \"<strong>DECLINED</strong>\" message</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3><a id=\"eoseod\"></a>End of Shift (EOS) and End of Day (EOD) Reports</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Standalone EOS and EOD Report</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>End of Shift</strong><br />To perform an End of Shift on terminal:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>White</strong> key</li>\r\n<li>Choose <strong>AM</strong> tile</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Transactions</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>End of Shift</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>End of Day</strong><br />To perform an End of Shift on terminal:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the <strong>White</strong> key</li>\r\n<li>Choose <strong>AM</strong> tile</li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>Transactions</strong></li>\r\n<li>Select <strong>End of Day</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If <strong>EOD</strong> is chosen before <strong>EOS</strong> has been performed, the terminal will automatically perform<strong> EOS</strong> first before <strong>EOD</strong>.</li>\r\n<li>When terminals are inter-linked (i.e. connected on&nbsp;a single LAN segment by IP), each terminal will perform its own local <strong>EOS</strong> when commanded, but if any terminal is commanded to perform <strong>EOD</strong>, all linked terminals will carry out their <strong>EOD</strong> as well.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>POS-Linked EOS and EOD Report</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Using OPI Protocol</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>To perform an <strong>EOS</strong> and<strong> EOD</strong> using the OPI protocol, the operator will need to perform a shift sign-off and day end from the POS which will trigger the GemPAY3 terminal to perform its own <strong>EOS</strong> and<strong> EOD</strong>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Using F75</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>When using F75, <strong>EOS</strong> and <strong>EOD</strong> should be performed on the GemPAY3 terminal. Refer to the manual procedure above for instructions.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"star\"></a>Star Rewards</h3>\r\n<h4><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Running Star Rewards on Idle Mode on the Gempay 3&nbsp;Terminal</span></h4>\r\n<p>This will enable&nbsp;sites to&nbsp;award loyalty points for qualifying cash purchases.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Press the F2 key on the Gempay to start a manual sale.</li>\r\n<li>When asked for the supervisor code, please enter the site&rsquo;s supervisor code.</li>\r\n<li>When it displays the menu to enter an amount, enter the sale amount and press enter.</li>\r\n<li>Follow the prompt and enter Volume.</li>\r\n<li>When prompted for the card, swipe the loyalty card.</li>\r\n<li>Complete the loyalty transaction.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"time\"></a>Time Change</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Performing a time change due to daylight savings</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Press the silver button.</li>\r\n<li>Select control panel.</li>\r\n<li>Select terminal settings</li>\r\n<li>Select general settings</li>\r\n<li>Select Date/time</li>\r\n<li>Select Set time.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Site needs to&nbsp;manually enter the time then press the&nbsp;green button.</li>\r\n<li>Press the red button to exit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"brightness\"></a>Terminal/Pin Pad Brightness</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Terminal</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Silver button</li>\r\n<li>Terminal settings</li>\r\n<li>Eco mode</li>\r\n<li>Backlight low/ Backlight normal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Pin Pad</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>F * key</li>\r\n<li>Terminal settings</li>\r\n<li>Eco mode</li>\r\n<li>Blacklight low/Backlight normal</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a href=\"reboot\"></a><a id=\"reboot\"></a>Soft Reboot of Terminal or Pin Pad</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Terminal</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hold the yellow key down</li>\r\n<li>Hold the decimal/period/dot/[.] key down until \"Rebooting\" displays</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Pin Pad</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hold the yellow key down</li>\r\n<li>Hold the [.,#] key down until \"Rebooting\" displays</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a id=\"troubleshooting\"></a>Troubleshooting</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Card Recognition Error Messages</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Configuration Error</strong><br />Configuration error is displayed when the configuration file for a particular card is missing. For example, if the config file for <strong>UK Fuels application</strong> is missing, the terminal will display a \"<strong>UK FUELS CONFIGURATION ERROR</strong>\" message.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Terminal Error Messages</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Initialisation Missing File</strong><br />Initialisation Missing File is displayed when eSale application is missing.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Incorrect Password</strong><br />Incorrect password displays when the supervisor or engineer passwords are entered incorrectly.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>TMS Connection Error Message</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><strong>TMS No Connection<br /></strong>TMS No Connection is displayed when attempt to connect to TMS fails.<br />Note: When the terminal is connected, it sends the notification message to TMS and executes all commands received from TMS. When the communication is completed, the terminal returns to the idle state.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Tailed INIT error displayed</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If the Ethernet link to the POS is not connected or functional when the \"<strong>POS COMM LINK</strong>\" is initializing, the link initialization will time out, and the \"<strong>FAILED INIT ERROR</strong>\" will be displayed.</li>\r\n<li>Check that the Ethernet icon is present in the terminal display. If not, reconnect/check the cable and reboot the terminal.</li>\r\n<li>If the PIN pad (PP) icon is not present in the terminal display, disconnect the PIN pad and reboot the terminal. After initialization, reconnect the PIN pad.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Configuration error at the Card Validation Stage<br /></strong></span>If&nbsp;any of the following messages are displayed, the terminal&nbsp;will stop&nbsp;processing the card and will return to the idle state after a few seconds.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Entry Not Allowed</strong><br />If the application status is set not to allow key entry, the terminal will display the message \"<strong>KEY ENTERY NOT ALLOWED</strong>\" for 2 seconds when a&nbsp;user attempts to key in a card number.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Incorrect PAN</strong><br />An<strong> \"INCORRECT PAN\"</strong> message is displayed when the operator enters a card number incorrectly or when the luhn check has failed. This message is displayed for 2 seconds.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Expired Card</strong><br />The terminal will display \"<strong>EXPIRED CARD</strong>\" when the card is out of date.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-06-15 08:31:43', 'l7d23b', '2017-11-10 10:46:24', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Gempay 3 Guide', '', 80003, 'UK Support 1', 'N', '#functionkeys#menustructure#preauth#fuelcard#troubleshooting#eft#refunds#eoseod#download#star#time#brightness#reboot'),
(473, 'Valero Network Configuration Guide - Rapid Connect', '<p>We have sites that are now setting up VeriFone EMV/Rapid Connect.&nbsp; <a href=\"O:\\AMA-CC\\WTS-Wholesale Technical Support\\Reflex Articles\\Valero-NetCfg.06222017.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Here</a>&nbsp;you will find the configuration information.&nbsp; If you have any questions, please contact Kimberly Ford.</p>', '2017-06-23 17:13:08', 'lbfb2t', '2017-06-23 17:13:08', 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on the required changes for Rapid Connect', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(474, 'Voyager Transaction Corrections', '<p>To issue a correction or modification on a Voyager card, fill out the following document and send to Voyager. Email, fax, or mailing information is included on the linked document.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/MerchantInvoiceCorrectionForm.doc\" target=\"_blank\">Voyager correction form</a></p>', '2017-07-06 12:24:06', 'l7d23b', '2017-07-07 08:19:39', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on how to correct a Voyager transaction', '', 50006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ' V071213a'),
(475, 'UK On Call', '<p><strong>Pembroke Security: </strong><u>In the first instance please call 2297 (01646 649297) / </u><a href=\"mailto:VTOC@valero.com\">VTOC@valero.com</a><u> for the 24 hour Valero I/S helpdesk who will contact the on-call person if required.</u> If the issue is urgent and you are unable to get an answer on 2297, you can also try 2298. <u>Do not</u> call the on-call mobile directly unless you have called the VTOC first on the numbers mentioned.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>UK Regional I/S On Call&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</u></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>24<sup>th</sup> -31<sup>st</sup> August&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; David Steele&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mobile: +44 7469 379301&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><u></u><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><u>Before calling anyone direct or calling the UK on-call person, raise a call with the Valero Helpdesk</u></strong>. The person covering the late shift may not be on the Valero helpdesk, but they will all be monitoring the VHD chat and the helpdesk inbox (all tickets raised for Pembroke go to the helpdesk inbox). VTOC must also be called first for any Refinery Radio system issues.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong><u>Links for On-Call person</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>For SME information, please refer to SME On Call contact list document in the current year folder.</p>\r\n<p>Please check the procedures and the previous on-call summaries; they are <u>very</u> likely to have solutions for issues that have happened before</p>\r\n<p><strong>Procedures</strong> can be found in</p>\r\n<p>\\\\nasukpmrf01\\Group\\Information Technology\\Procedures</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Previous on call email summaries</strong> can be found in the PEM Helpdesk inbox, On Call folder (instructions on how to add this to Outlook is in the On Call folder)</p>\r\n<p>Contact numbers can be found in <a href=\"UK%20IS%20Contact%20Information.xls\">UK IS Contact Information.xls</a> in \\\\nasukpmrf01\\Group\\Information Technology\\On Call</p>\r\n<p>If you are unsure what the issue or solution is after checking the procedures and on call summaries, call the SME at the earliest possible opportunity, even if it&rsquo;s only for advice.</p>', '2017-07-14 06:05:53', 'l7d23b', '2017-08-24 05:03:00', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'UK On Call Information', '', 80006, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:VTOC@valero.com'),
(476, 'PCI Compliance', '<p>If a jobber calls in stating they have a site or group of sites currently being audited for<strong> PCI Compliance</strong>, and they are requesting written documentation, including but not limited to dates of compliance from <strong>Valero Energy Corporation</strong>, please gather the following information and email it to <a href=\"mailto:Kimberly.Ford@valero.com\">Kimberly.Ford@valero.com</a> with a request for her to call the auditor:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Auditor&rsquo;s Company Name:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Auditor&rsquo;s name:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Auditor&rsquo;s Phone #:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Jobber&rsquo;s Company Name:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Jobber Contact Name:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Jobber&rsquo;s Phone #:</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>', '2017-07-26 10:45:12', 'lqnwmy', '2017-07-26 10:45:12', 'lqnwmy', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'PCI Compliance', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:Kimberly.Ford@valero.com'),
(477, 'Resetting a Valero Consumer/Fleet Password', '<p>When a customer attempts to sign into their Valero account at <a href=\"http://www.valero.com\">www.valero.com</a> they only have a limited number of attempts to sign in using the correct information.&nbsp; If a customer enters their information incorrectly at the max amount of attempts, their account may be locked.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If a customer is needing to reset their password or unlock their account, we can do so in RAMS.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Fleet/Commercial Accounts</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>While on the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Customer Information</span>\" screen, type in \"<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">E</span></strong>\" on the Command line to navigate to the&nbsp;\"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Internet Profile Maintenance</span>\" screen. <br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/fleet-login.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"602\" height=\"371\" /></li>\r\n<li>In the Function field, type in \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>P</strong></span>\" and press Enter. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>On the blank line that appears in the Password field, type in \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">valero</span>\" (all in lower case)&nbsp;and press Enter.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Advise the customer to&nbsp;use the temporary password&nbsp;\"valero\" to sign into their Valero account.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once they enter that password, they will be prompted to change their current password.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Hint:</strong></span> If the first and last name fields are blank, RAMS will not reset the password.&nbsp; In order to put in a name into that field, type \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>P</strong></span>\" in the Function field and enter in the customer\'s first and last name (<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">this should be the account administrator who\'s name should be listed on the main screen under the address</span>).&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Consumer Accounts</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>While on the \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Customer Information</span>\" screen, type in \"<strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">E</span></strong>\" on the Command line to navigate to the&nbsp;\"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Internet Profile Maintenance</span>\" screen.<br /><br /><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/consumer-login.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"601\" height=\"372\" /></li>\r\n<li>In the Function field, type in \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>P</strong></span>\" and press Enter.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>On the next prompt, press Enter again. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Advise the customer to&nbsp;use the temporary password&nbsp;\"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">valero</span>\" to sign into their Valero account.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once they enter that password, they will be prompted to change their current password.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-07-28 11:27:36', 'ln524h', '2017-07-28 12:01:31', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'How to reset a customer\'s password in RAMS for their Valero Self Serve Sign In', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'http://www.valero.com'),
(478, 'Rapid Connect Upgrades', '<p>We are about to start going forward with Rapid Connect/EMV software upgrades for VeriFone systems.&nbsp; There has been an issue identified where our beta stores are seeing \"5A Password Invalid\" error when attempting to do an End of Day.&nbsp; This is going to be fixed but for now we will have to manually enter the password in the Merchant Setup screen in Buypass Tools.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">When you get a call from a tech doing the upgrade it is important that you follow these steps as part of the upgrade</span>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Log in to Clientline and go to Profile Maintenance -&gt; Merchant Setup -&gt; Settlement/Other Info. tab.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>You will see the field labeled \"Password\" in the right hand column.&nbsp; Replace the 123456 with 111111 in this field and press \"Update\" at the bottom right hand side of the page.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Next, set the site for a PDL and have the tech pull the download.&nbsp; Make sure to set&nbsp;the Terminal ID to&nbsp;2.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you have any questions, please let Israel know.&nbsp;</p>', '2017-08-09 10:52:21', 'lbfb2t', '2017-08-22 16:49:57', 'ln524h', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Workaround for 5A Password Invalid Errors on Rapid Connect', '', 30006, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '');
