(479, 'VeriFone Commander EMV Rapid Connect Software', '<p>This article contains all available information concerning the VeriFone Commander EMV Rapid Connect Software.&nbsp; Please check&nbsp;news postings on the front page of Reflex for any updates that become available to this article.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\">Please be sure to read this article thoroughly to verify all steps are taken when assisting a site/tech on this upgrade.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Guide:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/VASC Playbook for Valero EMV 08.2017.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">VASC Playbook for Valero EMV</a></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Additional Support Documents:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/auto-upgrade09152016.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Auto Upgrade</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/sales-bulletin-fd-emv-transition-team-valero-v2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Sales Bulletin</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/fd-network-conversion.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">FD Network Conversion </a></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"><strong>Update 10/02/17:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p>Please <a href=\"upload/vlr-rapidconnect-buildmaster-modified.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">click here</a> for a list of TNSLink routers that were not active at the time TNS remotely deployed the routing changes to support Rapid Connect.&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">If a site on the list calls in to report issues connecting to Rapid Connect</span>, please follow the instructions below (previously provided).</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">Send an email to:&nbsp;</span><a href=\"mailto:globalbroadband@tnsi.com\">globalbroadband@tnsi.com</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Subject line:</strong>&nbsp; Verifone EMV/Rapid Connect Conversion Connectivity Issue</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Body Contents:</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>TNS Router ID:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em>IE:&nbsp; VLRJOBBERDEALER</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em>**Note: No Change to remainder &ndash; please include as-is**</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The site referenced above has had the commander updated to redirect Transaction Authorizations to ONE of the following 2 FDC &ldquo;Rapid Connect&rdquo; Hosts:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>204.194.127.203 (fdc50a-host-79) &ndash; Verifone configured</p>\r\n<p>204.194.139.203 (fdc50a-host-80)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>TNS router should include a NAT to each of the above FDC Hosts and ACL Permits from 172.16.20.x.</p>\r\n<p>Commander IP&rsquo;s will be as follows:</p>\r\n<p>VLR Direct Clients: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 172.16.20.12 (host-1)</p>\r\n<p>VLR Branded Clients: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; wrs, vps, gpmi: 172.16.20.135 (host-135)</p>\r\n<p>fsm: 172.16.20.235 (host-235)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"><strong>Update 9/15/17:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p>If you get a site that is switching from any Point of Sale to a Commander/Rapid connect,&nbsp; you will need to request a new merchant id from Mitzi.&nbsp;&nbsp; The id\'s&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"><strong>CANNOT</strong></span> be flipped.&nbsp; Please contact Mitzi as soon as possible to get the request in.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffff00;\"><strong>Update 8/29/17:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>The wholesale communications team will be emailing the attached documents to our distributors this week and posting them on the Wholesale portal.&nbsp; Verifone has offered to assist sites during business hours with configuring the EMV settings.&nbsp; The attached Sales Bulletin provides the steps sites will need to follow.&nbsp; In addition to the Sales Bulleting, we will be emailing the Auto Upgrade document.</p>\r\n<p>Steps at a high level:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sites will need to request a software upgrade to 3.02.34 via <a href=\"http://support.verifone.com/\">http://support.verifone.com</a> , see the detailed steps in the Sales Bulletin\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Site has to have an active ASM contract</li>\r\n<li>Site has to have connectivity to Verifone&rsquo;s Remote Software Delivery (VRSD) server\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The commander communicates to VRSD through the EZR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Site will process credit on terminal 001 on ATL105 until EMV conversion is completed by Verifone</li>\r\n<li>If sites do not know their service ID, see article 463</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\">Once software upgrade is complete, site will need to visit support.verifone.com to request EMV configuration assistance from Verifone, see the detailed steps in the Sales Bulletin</span></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Verifone will work directly with the site on scheduling a date and time to complete the configuration (terminal 002)</li>\r\n<li>There are two document links presented on <a href=\"http://support.verifone.com/\">http://support.verifone.com</a>, one provides guidance on where to locate the information requested by Verifone (FD Network Conversion, attached), the other document is a generic sales bulletin (not attached)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I have also attached a document that has images of support.verifone.com, please let me know if additional information is needed.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline; background-color: #ffff00;\"><strong>Update 08/15/17:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>We have asked Verifone to release the Commander EMV software (3.02.34) to production. &nbsp;The announcement to our branded distributors will go out 08/15/17.&nbsp; Linked above is an update reference guide that will be provided to Verifone installers.&nbsp; This guide replaces all previous documents.&nbsp; This software will only support inside EMV.</p>\r\n<p>It is very likely that the VASCs will call the help desk for support.&nbsp; Please make sure to reference the attached document to answer questions. &nbsp;<br />Here are some important&nbsp;items concerning the upgrade:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All sites will use terminal 002 for Rapid Connect</li>\r\n<li>The VASC will only need to configure a host specific route for Rapid Connect</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>All service providers have made the necessary changes to support the new routes to Rapid Connect.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong><a id=\"stuff\"></a>***Additional Steps Required***:</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>Issues have been identified with the First Data merchant profile setup on <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">terminal 002</span>.&nbsp; Please make the following corrections, then set site for a PDL and validate it pulls successfully.&nbsp; First Data has been notified.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 1: Update Day Close Password</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Log in to Clientline and go to <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Profile Maintenance</span> &gt; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Merchant Setup</span> &gt; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Settlement/Other Info. tab</span>.&nbsp; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>You will see the field labeled \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Password</span>\" in the right hand column.&nbsp; Replace the 123456 with 111111 in this field and press \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Update</span>\" at the bottom right hand side of the page.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Step 2: Update Card Settings </strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Navigate to <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Terminal Setup</span> &gt; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Search Terminal</span>.&nbsp; Enter in the store\'s MID and use <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">2</span> for the Terminal No.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on the <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Cards Accepted</span> tab<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enable Velocity for Proprietary Card 1<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enable Buypass Fleet (leave the Velocity box unchecked)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Enable Diners and check option for velocity.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong><img src=\"upload/cards-accepted-tab - updated.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"856\" height=\"469\" /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Step 3: Update Velocity Settings</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Navigate to <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Velocity</span> &gt; <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Update Velocity<br /><br /></span></li>\r\n<li>Update Velocity parameters on <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">terminal 002</span> &ndash; should be 2/200 for<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"> line 1.&nbsp; <span style=\"color: #000000;\">Enter following amounts and the hit \"<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Add</span>\"</span></span><span style=\"color: #000000;\">:</span><br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Daily Count - 2</li>\r\n<li>Daily Amount - 200.0</li>\r\n<li>Period Count - 2</li>\r\n<li>Period Amount - 200.0</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"><img src=\"upload/velocity.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"876\" height=\"143\" /><br /></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-08-15 05:18:44', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-20 09:07:37', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Verifone Commander EMV Software', '', 10010, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', '\r\n Owner TNS Router ID Status VLR apo00015v apo00016v apo00017v apo00018v apo00021v apo00024v apo00025v apo00026v apo00027v apo00028v apo00029v apo00030v apo00031v apo00032v apo00033v bes00002v bke00004v bpl00010v bpl00011v bru00001v cay00003v cay00020v cay00043v cay00044v cay00045v cay00047v cay00048v csg00005v ctp00033v ctp00043v ctp00044v ctp00047v ctp00057v dco00005v dco00006v dco00007v dfp00009v dnv00001v dso00001v dso00007v dso00009v dso00011v dso00012v dso00013v dso00022v dso00023v dso00024v epr00055v eve00004v fcr00003v fto00011v fxo00001v fxo00002v geg0000