(481, 'Temporary Credit Limit Increase  Consumer Accounts', '<p>A TCL will only allow purchases up to $100.00 over the account credit limit. It is valid until midnight that same day and for one transaction only. A TCL can be initiated by a customer&rsquo;s request or by an agent&rsquo;s discretion. The ACCOUNT OWNER or individual with FULL AUTHOIRTY may request.&nbsp;TCL&rsquo;s cannot be given on accounts that are cancelled or expired.</p>\r\n<p>COMMAND: <strong>TCL</strong><em> (be mindful of the GTOT on the account. If a customer&rsquo;s credit limit is $500 and their GTOT is $550, the available credit after initiating the TCL will only be available for $50).</em></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Verify caller&rsquo;s name and address.</li>\r\n<li>Last four digits of caller&rsquo;s social security number.</li>\r\n<li>On the COMMAND line type: <strong>VERF</strong> and then press enter. This will make a note that account was verified.</li>\r\n<li>On the COMMAND line type: <strong>TCL</strong> (for increase).</li>\r\n<li>Enter <strong>ICAL</strong> to make a note.</li>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Enter Call Cause Code <strong>CARE </strong>on the first line.</li>\r\n<li>Document the account as to who you spoke with and explain why customer called to request the temporary limit increase.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</ol>', '2017-09-01 13:17:54', 'lbfb2t', '2017-09-01 13:19:49', 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Process for issuing a temporary credit increase to consumer accounts.', '', 60002, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(482, 'CST Commander Deployment', '<p>CST has plans to replace Sapphires at 300 locations with Commanders between October 2017 and April 2018.&nbsp; Each of these locations will have an Acumera AMG installed for credit card processing to First Data&rsquo;s Rapid Connect platform. CST plans to activate each AMG prior to the actual install. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In order for the AMGs to be activated in advance, CST will send an email to the WTS email address with the sites that they would like to activate.&nbsp; Once the email is received, please engage Acumera to activate the sites.&nbsp; Please contact&nbsp;Kimberly Ford&nbsp;with any questions or concerns.</p>\r\n<p>The flow will be as follows:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Acumera receives order, ships AMGs</li>\r\n<li>CST to connect AMG to Internet connection and directly connect Commander payment NIC</li>\r\n<li>CST to send email to WTS-AMA</li>\r\n<li>Valero to engage Acumera to activate sites listed in CST&rsquo;s email</li>\r\n<li>CST to ship activated AMG and Commander to Retail site for installation by tech\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Acumera will temporarily disable reporting in AcuVigil so the site will not appear down</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Tech to call Valero upon completion of install for Valero to close activation ticket in AcuVigil\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Acumera will enable reporting on day of install</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Help Desk Procedure:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>When you receive the pre-activation request, create a ticket for each of the sites.</li>\r\n<li>Forward email to Acumera at <a href=\"mailto:team@acumera.net\">team@acumera.net</a> copying yourself, Kimberly Ford, and WTS box advising that we need the request worked.&nbsp; Please include the ticket numbers in the body of the request.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Move the original email request to CST Pre-Activation Request email folder.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li><span style=\"background-color: #00ffff;\">Follow instructions in <a style=\"background-color: #00ffff;\" href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=479#stuff\" target=\"_blank\">article 479</a> for confirming the network profile is setup correctly.</span></li>\r\n<li>When you receive a response that the activation has been completed find the original email in the CST Pre-Activation Request folder and reply to all that the request has been completed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Please note and close tickets that were opened from the original request.</li>\r\n</ol>', '2017-09-15 15:23:09', 'ln524h', '2017-11-14 13:41:36', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'CST sites upgrading from Sapphire to Commander', '', 30007, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:team@acumera.netindex.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=479#stuff'),
(483, 'MID Update at Change of owner/Legal entity Process', '<h3>How a Change of owner/legal entity is initiated:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The request is for a change of owner is kicked off by a SIF (Site&nbsp;Information Form)&nbsp;generated by the VCS Administrator. SIF is sent off to all suppliers.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>At receipt of SIF, suppliers will schedule in the MID update to meet the &lsquo;required-by date&rsquo;. On the Required-by date, HTEC and other suppliers will implement the MID. HTEC Helpdesk must go back to the VCS Administrator after the MID update for confirmation. <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>HTEC will email VCS confirmation that the new MID has been implemented on the terminal.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Our Role</h3>\r\n<p>The VCS Helpdesk will log calls relating to MIDs. However, the Helpdesk <strong>will not be responsible for confirming MIDs to HTEC</strong>. MIDs will no longer be quoted from RAMS as they could possibly be inaccurate during a change of owner/legal.</p>\r\n<p>The duty of confirming MIDs should always be the VCS Administrator, and all escalations should be to the VCS Administrator. The VCS Administrator is also responsible for ensuring that the VCS Helpdesk is aware of the new MIDs whenever there has been a change of owner or other trading entity.</p>\r\n<p><strong>If HTEC is requesting an updated MID from our desk, send an email to <a href=\"mailto:vcssupport@valero.com\">vcssupport@valero.com</a> with the site information so they may relay the information to HTEC.</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><em><u>Please note</u></em></strong><u>:</u> This is to be distinguished from occasions where the site cannot take a Card and investigation by the Helpdesk points to an issue with the implementation. Having confirmed the correct MID with the VCS Administrator or via the most up to date correspondence sent by the VCS Administrator on the issue, the Helpdesk can pursue a fix or update to resolve the issue on site.</p>', '2017-09-18 13:52:05', 'l7d23b', '2017-09-19 05:15:25', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on the process of providing and validating MIDs after a change of owner has been performed ', '', 80002, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'mailto:vcssupport@valero.com'),
