(486, 'Rams 2 overview', '<p><img style=\"margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; display: block;\" src=\"upload/articles/R2/overview.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"850\" height=\"458\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Merchant Information tab\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This contains all information regarding the site.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Notes Screen\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Shows notes on the current distributor or dealer.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Quick Search Bar\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Allows you to search distributor, dealer, and alias records for a site.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Forward and Back buttons<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Moves to the next or previous dealer under a distributor.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Command List\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>When clicked, shows a list of available commands on the current site.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Site information<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/R2/1 site info.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"862\" height=\"153\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Site Details<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/R2/2 site detail.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"850\" height=\"152\" /></li>\r\n<li>Billing Section<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/R2/3%20site%20billing.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"824\" height=\"151\" /></li>\r\n<li>Alias<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/R2/4 site ids.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"638\" height=\"214\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Fileset G - This data is loaded from a file sent by FirstData. It is updated every Sunday night.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/R2/5 fileset g stuff.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"769\" height=\"88\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Edit Merchant - This will appear when the dealer or address block is clicked. <br />Use this to add/update phone numbers.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/R2/6 edit merchant.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"802\" height=\"584\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-09-26 12:19:27', 'l7d23b', '2017-09-29 08:54:40', 'l7d23b', 'no', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on using Rams 2', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(487, 'UKCS Support Mailbox Procedures', '<p>When working emails in the UKCS mailbox any emails to Jacqui, John, or Asif will need to be forwarded to their individual email addresses upon receipt.</p>\r\n<p>Forwarded emails will be sent to the individual and carbon copied to the UKCS mailbox. Once the carbon copy is received in the UKCS mailbox, <strong>both</strong> emails must be moved to the folder labaled <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Forwarded to UKRT</span>.</p>\r\n<p>When forwarding emails we will be using a standard message unless there is more information to be added to the email. If there is additional information required or requested, do not use the quicktext.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To setup quick text in outlook:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Copy and paste the following text snippet into a blank email<br />\r\n<table style=\"background-color: #edfaff; padding: 10px;\" cellpadding=\"10px\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Received in UKCS mailbox. Reviewed and forwarded for your handling.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Thank you</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once the text is pasted, highlight the text in outlook<br /><img src=\"upload/ukcsmb1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"492\" height=\"258\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on INSERT on the file menu at the top of the email window.<br /><img src=\"upload/ukcsmb21.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"295\" height=\"34\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click the Quick Parts dropdown.<br /><img src=\"upload/ukcsmb3.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"42\" height=\"69\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click Save Selection to Quick Part Gallery...<br /><img src=\"upload/ukcsmb4.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"407\" height=\"33\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Name it <strong>UKCS Forward</strong>.<br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>When returning to the Quick Parts menu, you will have the following entry on dropdown.<br /><img src=\"upload/ukcsmb5.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"407\" height=\"297\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>To add the quick text, click the entry on the quick parts menu.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-09-28 09:25:31', 'l7d23b', '2017-09-28 12:44:57', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Procedures for working the UKCS mailbox', '', 80001, 'UK Support 2', 'N', ''),
(488, ' Pre-Qualified/MLA changes', '<p>Due to recent Regulation (the Military Lending Act &ndash; MLA) effective 10/3/17 - All Pre-Qualified applications are set to \"order\" by the system.&nbsp; <span style=\"background-color: #ccffff;\"><strong>No disclosures are required under any circumstances on a Pre-Qualified offer that we are currently accepting.&nbsp; Pre-Qualified Procedures will be updated in the future.</strong></span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If the system <strong><em><u>approves</u></em></strong> the application <strong><em><u>and</u></em></strong> the MLA flag is set to Y<br /><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The system will present a new &ldquo;APPROVED&rdquo; script with MLA verbiage, script will be in turquoise.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/mla-rams.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"345\" height=\"311\" /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong><u>Approved MLA Flag set to Y Script (English and Spanish):<br /><br /></u></strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>&ldquo;Congratulations, your application has been approved and you should receive your card(s) within 7-10 days. Important information, including the terms and conditions of your account will accompany the credit card(s). Use of the card(s) constitutes acceptance of the terms and conditions. Upon receiving your new credit card(s), we invite you to register at valero.com/newcard to activate your card(s) and manage your account. To hear about important protections for service members and their dependents, please stay on the line and you will be transferred to a pre-recorded message. Thank you for calling and welcome to Valero. Is there anything else I can help you with today?&rdquo; <br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>&ldquo;Felicidades, su aplicaci&oacute;n para cr&eacute;dito ha sido aprobada y deber&aacute; recibir su tarjeta(s) por correo en 7-10 d&iacute;as. Informaci&oacute;n importante, incluyendo los t&eacute;rminos y condiciones de su cuenta ser&aacute;n enviadas con su(s) tarjeta(s) de cr&eacute;dito. El uso de la tarjeta, constituye aceptaci&oacute;n de los t&eacute;rminos y condiciones.&nbsp; Al recibir su(s) tarjeta(s), lo/la invitamos que se reg&iacute;strese en valero.com/newcard para activar su(s) tarjeta(s) y administrar su cuenta. Ahora le voy a dar informaci&oacute;n sobre las protecciones importantes para los miembros del servicio y sus dependientes. (<strong>READ THE MLA Spanish Disclosure</strong>).Gracias por llamar y bienvenido a Valero. Le puedo ayudar en algo m&aacute;s?&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>You will <strong><u>transfer</u></strong> (drop) the caller in extension 5441.&nbsp; (Do not stay on the line with the customer.)<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Read the following disclosure if extension 5441 is busy.<br /></strong><strong><br /></strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Valero and Gulf<br /></strong></li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>I would like to share with you some IMPORTANT PROTECTIONS FOR SERVICEMEMBERS AND THEIR DEPENDENTS. Federal law provides important protections to members of the Armed Forces and their dependents relating to extensions of consumer credit. In general, the cost of consumer credit to a member of the Armed Forces and his or her dependent may not exceed an Annual Percentage Rate or (APR) of 36 percent. This rate must include, as applicable to the credit transaction or account: The costs associated with credit insurance premiums; fees for ancillary products sold in connection with the credit transaction; any application fee charged (other than certain application fees for specified credit transactions or accounts); and any participation fee charged (other than certain participation fees for a credit card account). If, as a result of these protections, any Military Annual Percentage Rate or (MAPR) adjustments are made to an Account, the adjustments will be reflected on the Monthly Statement. If a balance is owed on your Account, a payment for the Minimum Payment Due or greater will be due each month. See your Credit Card Agreement for additional information about your payment obligation and how the Minimum Payment Due is calculated. If you are a &ldquo;covered borrower&rdquo; under this law and your Credit Card Agreement contains a section on Binding Arbitration, then the Binding Arbitration Provision does not apply to you. Thank you for your interest in our products and services.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Me gustar&iacute;a compartir con usted algunas protecciones importantes para los miembros del servicio y sus dependientes. La ley federal proporciona protecciones importantes para miembros de las fuerzas armadas y sus dependientes relacionadas con extensiones del cr&eacute;dito al consumidor. En general, el costo del cr&eacute;dito al consumidor para un miembro de las fuerzas armadas y sus dependientes no puede exceder una tasa de porcentaje anual de 36 porciento. Esta tarifa debe incluir, seg&uacute;n sea aplicable a la transacci&oacute;n o cuenta de cr&eacute;dito: Los costos asociados con prima de seguro de cr&eacute;dito; cargos de los productos auxiliares vendidos en relaci&oacute;n con la transacci&oacute;n de cr&eacute;dito; cualquier cargo por la aplicaci&oacute;n (con excepci&oacute;n de ciertos cargos de aplicaci&oacute;n de transacciones o cuentas de cr&eacute;dito determinadas); y cualquier costo de participaci&oacute;n cobrado (con excepci&oacute;n de ciertos cargos de la participaci&oacute;n para la cuenta de la tarjeta de cr&eacute;dito). Si, como resultado de estas protecciones, cualquier tasa anual de porcentaje militar o se realizan ajustes en la cuenta, los ajustes se reflejaran en el estado de cuenta mensual. Si ay un balance en su cuenta, un pago para el pago m&iacute;nimo requerido o m&aacute;s ser&aacute; debido cada mes.&nbsp; Consulte a los t&eacute;rminos de la tarjeta de cr&eacute;dito para obtener informaci&oacute;n adicional acerca de su obligaci&oacute;n de pago y c&oacute;mo se calcula el pago m&iacute;nimo. Si usted es un \"prestatario cubierto\" bajo esta ley y su contrato de tarjeta de cr&eacute;dito contiene una secci&oacute;n sobre arbitraje vinculante, entonces la provisi&oacute;n de arbitraje vinculante no le aplica a usted. Gracias por su inter&eacute;s en nuestros productos y servicios.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Note the application that you approved the application and transferred caller to 5441 due to MLA flag.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Watch the script screen -- NOT all applications will receive the new script.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><em><u>We will notified once the Pre-Qualified offers have expired and at that time we will&nbsp;treat them as regular phone applications with full disclosures.</u></em></p>', '2017-10-05 12:20:15', 'l7d23b', '2017-10-05 12:20:58', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', ' Pre-Qualified/MLA changes', '', 40001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(489, 'Outage Message Procedure - Telephone ', '<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\">From a <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">supervisor or the outage phone</span> do the following:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>To record a new announcement:</strong></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Dial # (pound) and then 4. You will hear a dial tone.</li>\r\n<li>Enter&nbsp;the announcement&nbsp;extension, 5339. You will hear a dial tone.</li>\r\n<li>Dial 1 to begin recording</li>\r\n<li>Speak the announcement into the phone. Your message is being recorded.</li>\r\n<li>Hang up the phone to end recording.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Note: </strong><span style=\"color: #000000;\">The announcement records the sound of the receiver returning to the phone. Hang up gently, press the drop button, or depress the switch hook with your finger.</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>To check the announcement:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Dial 5339</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>You have to wait 15 seconds before you can dial the extension 5339 to listen to your announcement.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Global Outage Script:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><em>Thank you for calling the Valero Wholesale Helpdesk. We are currently experiencing a nationwide outage. We apologize for the inconvenience and we are working urgently to resolve the issue. If you wish to speak to a technical support representative for any other issue, please remain on the line for assistance.</em></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\"><em>Holiday Closure Script:</em></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><em>Thank you for calling the Valero Wholesale Helpdesk.&nbsp; Our office will be closed at 10 pm CST on (date) and will reopen at 10 am on (date) in observance of the Christmas holiday. Thank you for calling and have a great day.&nbsp; </em></span></p>', '2017-10-23 07:55:38', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-24 16:09:06', 'ln524h', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on checking/recording the outage message', '', 60001, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', ''),
(490, 'US Outage Procedures', '<p>If you are receiving calls concerning a similar issue across multiple stations, follow the steps below.</p>\r\n<p>Before continuing, check the WTS box to make sure there are no <strong>rain fade</strong> notices from Sagenet. Rain fade can generate quite a few calls during severe hub weather but will usually clear up after a few minutes.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://forecast.weather.gov/MapClick.php?lat=33.95319000000006&amp;lon=-84.54587999999995\" target=\"_blank\">Check weather at the hub here.</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong></strong> <strong>Step 1</strong> - Send the initial notification that an <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>outage is occurring</strong></span>. <strong><a href=\"mailto:kimberly.ford@valero.com; debra.burnett@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com?Subject=Initial%20US%20Outage%20Notification&amp;Body=This%20is%20initial%20notification%20of%20a%20severe%20incident%20that%20is%20currently%20impacting%20station%20processing.%20We%20are%20in%20the%20process%20of%20identifying%20the%20specific%20point%20of%20failure%20and%20will%20update%20once%20we%20have%20more%20information.\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a></strong>.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>It is not necessary to identify the issue, this is an initial&nbsp;alert to notify management.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong> Step 2</strong> - Determine an agent to take point on the outage.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This agent will&nbsp;aux out of their phone to correlate information from agents and contact vendors to identify the issue.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong> Step&nbsp;3</strong> - Identify the issue.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If all incoming calls are for a specific vendor like SageNet, Acumera, or TNS, the issue probably lies with one vendor.</li>\r\n<li>If call are coming from all comm platform types, there may be an issue at FirstData.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong> Step&nbsp;4</strong> - Outage message.</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If current staffing is unable to handle the elevated call volume, activate the outage message&nbsp;by pressing the <strong>VALERO OUTAGE</strong> button.<br />&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li><strong> Step&nbsp;5</strong>&nbsp;- Send follow-up notification identifying the issue.<strong> Be sure to change the email as required</strong>. <strong><a href=\"mailto:kimberly.ford@valero.com; debra.burnett@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com?Subject=Update%20to%20US%20Outage%20Notification&amp;Body=We%20have%20identified%20an%20issue%20with%20VENDOR_OR_NETWORK_HERE.\" target=\"_blank\">Click here</a></strong>.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong> Step&nbsp;6 </strong>- Close out the outage once resolved:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Log out of the outage phone.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=202\" target=\"_blank\">Create a heatboard</a>&nbsp;(if not already done) to associate outage tickets to.</li>\r\n<li>Deliver beginning and ending dates and times, reason for outage, any further details gained to Debra. <br /><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=433\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"color: #ff00ff; text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Please follow the example linked here as a template for&nbsp;the wrap-up email.</strong></span></a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>', '2017-11-20 12:29:10', 'l7d23b', '2017-11-20 14:00:25', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Information on handling outages', '', 40009, 'Tech Support 1', 'N', 'http://forecast.weather.gov/MapClick.php?lat=33.95319000000006&amp;lon=-84.54587999999995mailto:kimberly.ford@valero.com; debra.burnett@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com?Subject=Initial US Outage Notification&amp;Body=This is initial notification of a severe incident that is currently impacting station processing. We are in the process of identifying the specific point of failure and will update once we have more information.mailto:kimberly.ford@valero.com; debra.burnett@valero.com; craig.sperry@valero.com; wts-ama@valero.com?Subject=Update to US Outage Notification&amp;Body=We have identified an issue with VENDOR_OR_NETWORK_HERE.index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=202index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=433'),
(491, 'Gempay 3 Call Handling', '<p><strong>When handling UK calls with sites that have an issue with their Gempay 3 device, extra steps are now required.</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>In the solution description use the following format:<br /><img src=\"upload/gp3sitesolution.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"389\" height=\"97\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>All tickets that are opened on Gempay 3 sites in heat must be documented in SharePoint as well.<br /><a href=\"http://intranet.valero.com/IS/UKI1TeamSite/RetailTechnology/Lists/Development Items/AllItems.aspx\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>UK SharePoint Link<br /></strong></span><br /><br /></a></li>\r\n<li>Click:<br /><img src=\"upload/gp3newitembutton - Copy 1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"235\" height=\"29\" /><br /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Fill out the following data:</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"upload/gp3newitem.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"612\" height=\"774\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 37px; float: left;\" width=\"249\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 239px;\">\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Title</strong> will contain site name and site number.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Set <strong>Delivery Organisation</strong> to Htec.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Set <strong>Status</strong> to In Development.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Leave <strong>Delivery ETA</strong> blank.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Set <strong>Platform</strong> to Gempay.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Detail</strong> will contain the Problem Description from Heat.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Working Notes</strong> will contact the Solution Description from Heat.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>Sites Impacted</strong> will have the site number.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Leave <strong>Bug Fix</strong> unchecked.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Leave <strong>Completed</strong> unchecked.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click <strong>Save.</strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-11-21 12:50:25', 'l7d23b', '2017-11-21 13:07:00', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'New procedures for handling Gempay 3 calls', '', 80001, 'UK Support 1', 'N', 'http://intranet.valero.com/IS/UKI1TeamSite/RetailTechnology/Lists/Development Items/AllItems.aspx');
