(493, 'TABS Denial Codes', '<p>Menu<a id=\"menu\"></a></p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 31px; width: 100%;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 26px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 32px; height: 26px;\" colspan=\"8\">TABS Denial Codes</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 98px; height: 26px;\" colspan=\"2\">TABS Error Codes</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 32px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d01\">01</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 36px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d02\">02</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d03\">03</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 42px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d04\">04</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 52px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d05\">05</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 47px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d06\">06</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d07\">07</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d08\">08</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 98px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#cons\">CONS</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 73px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#cred\">CRED</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 32px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d09\">09</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 36px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d10\">10</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 33px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d11\">11</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 42px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d12\">12</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 52px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d13\">13</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 47px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d14\">14</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 103px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d80\">80, 81, 98, 99</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 212px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#d307\">307 (or any seller/shipper #)</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 98px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#sell\">SELL</a></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 73px; height: 13px; text-align: center;\"><a href=\"#term\">TERM</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d01\"></a>Deny 01 &ndash; Invalid Seller ID</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>A Deny 01 is the result of the terminal using the wrong Seller ID on the authorization request.&nbsp; The Seller ID is a three digit number assigned by TABS that identifies what TABS account to send the BOL data to (ex: Valero=051, Valero Renewables=094, Exxon=045).&nbsp; This is configured wrong within the automation system and would require the terminal operator to correct this.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; To resolve this, we will need to contact DTN to have them assist working with the terminal owner/operator to configure their system to send the data properly.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Contact Setup representative for terminal.</li>\r\n<li>Setup will contact DTN to open a ticket. DTN will then work with the terminal to configure the TAS (Terminal Automation System) properly to send data to TABS.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d02\"></a>Deny 02 &ndash; Invalid Shipper ID</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>A Deny 02 is the result of the terminal using the wrong Shipper ID on the authorization request. PetroDex Support will need to work with the terminal to correct. You can see this data string in the transaction log pro report by clicking the details hyperlink on the right side of the line item. Shipper # example: Truman Arnold=172, SEI=307</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; To resolve this, we will need to contact DTN to have them assist working with the terminal owner/operator to configure their system to send the data properly.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Contact Setup representative for terminal.</li>\r\n<li>Setup will contact DTN to open a ticket. DTN will then work with the terminal to configure the TAS (Terminal Automation System) properly to send data to TABS.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d03\"></a>Deny 03 &ndash; Invalid Truck Number</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:</strong>&nbsp; The vehicle ID can be identified under the carrier setup page within TABS.&nbsp; Verify that they are using the correct truck number associated with the SCAC code.&nbsp; It will need to be changed within TABS or the automation system depending on what the correct number should be.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; To resolve this, we will need to contact DTN to have them assist working with the terminal owner/operator to configure their system to send the data properly.<em>&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><em>NOTE:&nbsp; Valero does not use Truck #&rsquo;s as part of our carrier authorizations, so it is extremely unlikely that we will ever receive this error.&nbsp; If you do&hellip;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Contact ACS representative for terminal.</li>\r\n<li>ACS will contact DTN to open a ticket. DTN will then work with the terminal to configure the TAS (Terminal Automation System) properly to send data to TABS.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d04\"></a>Deny 04 &ndash; Invalid Seller / Terminal</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Each TABS terminal is identified within TABS by a 9 digit unique code that is the 6 digit SPLC code + the 3 digit TABS owner code.&nbsp; (Ex:&nbsp; 123456051)&nbsp; A Deny 04 message indicates that the SPLC + Owner code being sent into TABS was not recognized by the TABS system.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; The terminal will need to be setup within TABS.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Escalate to the designated Setup team member for general setup issues. They will be able to determine which location this should be for and, if necessary, escalate internally to the proper analyst.</li>\r\n<li>Setup will then create the terminal in TABS and confirm that the consignee&rsquo;s have been assigned/populated.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d05\"></a>Deny 05 &ndash; Invalid Customer ID</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>The DENY 5 error is an indication that the consignee number being sent by the terminal is not recognized in the TABS system.<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>A DENY 5 error typically occurs under 2 conditions:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The specific consignee is not in TABS at all.</li>\r\n<li>The specific consignee is in TABS but is not setup for the terminal.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; The consignee # will either need to be added to TABS, added to the specific terminal, or, in some cases, not used at all (as it&rsquo;s an old/bad/incorrect loading #)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Record the consignee # being sent into the Pro-Log report<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-01.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"501\" height=\"56\" /><br /><br />NOTE:&nbsp; If the consignee name is BLANK, this is typically due to the consignee # is not in TABS at all (condition #1 above).&nbsp;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-02.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"520\" height=\"52\" /><br /><br />If the consignee name is NOT BLANK, this is typically indicative of the consignee # is in TABS but is not assigned to the specific terminal (condition #2 above).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>Open up &ldquo;Data Management&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Seller Consignee&rdquo; and then run the report for the consignee # by entering in the key word field. Be sure to select &ldquo;by Consignee ID&rdquo; in the drop down box and hit &ldquo;Search&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-03.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"393\" height=\"175\" /><br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-04.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"541\" height=\"55\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>If you see the response &ldquo;No Consignee&rsquo;s match your search criteria&rdquo;&nbsp;<strong><u>then STOP and go to step 4</u></strong>&nbsp;(this error indicates that the consignee # is not in TABS at all and needs setup to intervene). If you don&rsquo;t see this error, go to step 5.&nbsp;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-06.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"547\" height=\"57\" /><br /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong><em>Escalate to the designate setup analyst for the terminal.</em></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li>If the consignee # is in TABS, you&rsquo;ll see details populate for the consignee that you searched for in step #2<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-07.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"548\" height=\"61\" /><br /><br />Click on the hyperlink/details under &ldquo;consignee name&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n<li>In the &ldquo;Seller Consignee Details&rdquo; screen, review the &ldquo;Assigned Terminals&rdquo; details to confirm the locations that consignee is currently setup to load.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-08.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"549\" height=\"246\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ol start=\"7\">\r\n<li>Run SAP Transaction ZCI1 to confirm the locations in SAP customer is currently setup.<br /><br /><em>NOTE:&nbsp; In the &ldquo;Seller Consignee Details&rdquo; screen you have from step #6, the sold to and distributor&rsquo;s name should be included at the top of the screen.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-09.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"551\" height=\"89\" /><br /><br />Enter in the sold to and hit execute (green check) in ZCI1<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-10.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"345\" height=\"114\" /><br /><br /></em></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"8\">\r\n<li>Review the data returned in the report and confirm if the consignee is setup in SAP for the terminal where they are trying to load<br /><br />\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Select &ldquo;Petroex Loading #&rdquo; field and then filter for consignee # by right clicking on field header and selecting &ldquo;Set Filter&rdquo;.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-11.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"277\" height=\"243\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Search for terminal under the &ldquo;Plant Desc&rdquo; field.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>If terminal&nbsp;<strong><u>is NOT IN the list</u></strong>&nbsp;go to step 9</li>\r\n<li>If terminal is in the list go to step 10<br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>STOP</strong>: This consignee is not currently setup to load at this terminal.&nbsp; Inform the customer that this terminal is not currently authorized for loading and that they will need to contact setup to provide required details.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>If the terminal is setup in SAP, you can fix in TABS by doing the following:<br /><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Go back to &ldquo;Seller Consignee&rdquo; details.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the &ldquo;Terminals&rdquo; and &ldquo;Assigned Terminals&rdquo; setup fields, select the terminal they need to setup for on the left and move it to the right.<br /><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-roman;\">\r\n<li>Highlight terminal in &ldquo;Available Terminals&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-12.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"408\" height=\"177\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click green arrow<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/05-13.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"425\" height=\"138\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Save and request customer to attempt to load again.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d06\"></a>Deny 06 &ndash; Deny &ndash; No Check</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>A DENY 6 message indicates that an allocation is set to DENY for this customer.&nbsp; You can run a report to confirm what is set to DENY and then provide that detail to the ACS representative so that they can confirm if the denial is valid.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; The customer&rsquo;s consignee #, or consignee group, will need to be set to open and/or &ldquo;Credit and/or Product&rdquo; allocations.&nbsp; In some cases, the deny may be by design (i.e. we want this account/customer locked out from the location).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Run the allocation report by going to &ldquo;Reports&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Allocation Report&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/06-01.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"284\" height=\"96\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>Enter the terminal name in the &ldquo;Terminal or Terminal Group&rdquo; field.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>Enter the consignee # receiving the deny message (from the Pro-log report) into the &ldquo;Consignee or Consignee Group&rdquo; field.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n<li>Select the check box next to &ldquo;Credit Details&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li>Select the check box next to &ldquo;Product Details&rdquo;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n<li>Hit &ldquo;Export to Excel&rdquo; then send a copy of the report to the appropriate setup representative for review.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/06-02.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"572\" height=\"180\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d07\"></a>Deny 07 &ndash; No Credit Record</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>The DENY 7 error occurs when a customer is setup for credit allocations but there is no associated credit record attached to the allocation.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>NOTE:&nbsp; Valero creates all credit allocations at the &ldquo;Sold to&rdquo; group level for each customer.&nbsp; We do no attach credit allocations at the &ldquo;Channel of Trade&rdquo; consignee group level, like we do for product allocation records.<br /><br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-01.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"233\" height=\"75\" /></p>\r\n<p>The group at the top shows just the customer name and sold to (E.g. &ldquo;Sold to&rdquo; group).&nbsp; The group at the bottom shows the customer name, sold to, and channel of trade (E.g. Channel of Trade group).</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; Attach a credit record to the customer&rsquo;s account OR remove the customer from credit allocations all together.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the Pro-Log report, click on the consignee # hyperlink<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-02.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"259\" height=\"168\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>In the &ldquo;Seller Consignee Details&rdquo; section, scroll down to the bottom of the page where the &ldquo;assigned groups&rdquo; are listed and write down the &ldquo;Sold to&rdquo; name/sold to # for reference.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>Go to &ldquo;Allocations&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Credit&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Manage&rdquo; to confirm if a credit record has been already setup in the TABS system.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-02.PNG\" width=\"259\" height=\"168\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n<li>In the &ldquo;Search&rdquo; field, type in the customer&rsquo;s name or customers sold to # then hit &ldquo;Search&rdquo;.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-03.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"549\" height=\"59\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n<li>If a credit allocation record exists, then do the following steps. If no credit records exist, or the customer is not listed above in step #4,&nbsp;<strong><u>then STOP and go to step 6</u></strong>.<br /><br /><br />\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Go to &ldquo;Allocations&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Product Allocations&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Manage&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-04.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"238\" height=\"155\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the &ldquo;Consignee Group&rdquo; field, type in customers sold to # and select the &ldquo;sold to&rdquo; group<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-05.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"517\" height=\"97\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Under &ldquo;Terminals or Terminal Groups&rdquo;, select &ldquo;ALL Terminals&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-06.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"473\" height=\"85\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Hit &ldquo;Search&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-07.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"541\" height=\"102\" /><br />The &ldquo;Credit Allocation Details&rdquo; field will likely be blank.&nbsp; Click on &ldquo;Attach New Credit&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the drop down for &ldquo;Credit Name&rdquo; select the credit record for the Sold to/Sold to# and then click the paper-clip icon and then &ldquo;save&rdquo; at the top of the screen.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-08.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"534\" height=\"136\" /><br /><br />After hitting the paper-clip, the record should look like this:<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/07-09.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"526\" height=\"60\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Have customer attempt to load again. NOTE:&nbsp; If the &ldquo;Allocation Remaining&rdquo; amount is 0 or negative then the customer will NOT be able to load.&nbsp; Please inform the customer that they will need to contact the Valero Credit department to resolve.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d08\"></a>Deny 08 &ndash; No Product Record</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>The DENY 8 error is similar to the DENY 7 record above; however, in this case the customer is setup under the allocation header for &ldquo;Credit and/or Product&rdquo; and the &ldquo;Apply Product Allocations&rdquo; box is checked.&nbsp; Since there are no associated product allocation records setup, TABS will generate this error.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; Create the product allocation &ldquo;buckets&rdquo; for the customer&rsquo;s consignee group OR set the customer to &ldquo;Open&rdquo;.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution Steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the Pro Log report, click on the &ldquo;consignee #&rdquo; hyperlink to view the consignee group this customer is setup for.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/08-01.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"624\" height=\"52\" /><br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/08-02.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"335\" height=\"150\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>Go to &ldquo;Allocations&rdquo; and then &ldquo;Product&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Manage&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/08-03.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"242\" height=\"150\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>In the terminal field, key in the terminal name/# as shown in the Pro Log Report (in this example, it&rsquo;s &ldquo;Buckeye &ndash; Montgomery AL (B935).<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Consignee Group field, key in the consignee group name for the Channel of Trade (in this example, it&rsquo;s &ldquo;Musket Corporation &ndash; 120015 &ndash; W/S &ndash; UNB Contract&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Hit &ldquo;Search&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Click on &ldquo;Add New Product Allocation&rdquo; button<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/08-04.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"221\" height=\"41\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"7\">\r\n<li>Click on &ldquo;Restrict to Assigned Products&rdquo; and then select the Product Group you want to allocation from the &ldquo;Product Groups&rdquo; drop down list<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/08-05.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"553\" height=\"85\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"8\">\r\n<li>Type in the Product Allocation Name to match the product group and select the &ldquo;Flat&rdquo; radio button<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/08-06.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"601\" height=\"182\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"9\">\r\n<li>For the &ldquo;Monthly&rdquo;, &ldquo;Weekly&rdquo;, and &ldquo;Daily&rdquo; volumes repeat the following steps:\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n<li>Under &ldquo;Status&rdquo;, select &ldquo;Active&rdquo;</li>\r\n<li>Key in the start amount, in gallons.</li>\r\n<li>Key in the scale percentage (Monthly &ndash; 115, Weekly &ndash; 125, Daily &ndash; 150)</li>\r\n<li>Key in the refresh amount, in gallons (will equal start amount)</li>\r\n<li>Hit save</li>\r\n<li>NOTE: For the &ldquo;weekly&rdquo; refresh period, you will need to change the start date to the previous Thursday, unless you are adding this allocation on Thursday.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"10\">\r\n<li>Once all the allocations have been added, go back to step 8 and repeat steps 8 &ndash; 9 for all necessary product allocation buckets.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Once all product allocation buckets have been added, inform the customer and request that they attempt to load again.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d09\"></a>Deny 09 &ndash; Credit Limit Exceeded</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>The DENY 9 error occurs when the customer&rsquo;s credit allocation has been completely exhausted and they have no additional credit allocation available.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; Credit allocations are controlled by the Valero Credit department and this issue will need to be escalated to them.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution Steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Contact the appropriate credit department analyst for the customer&rsquo;s account, region/territory. Inform them of the credit denial in TABS and they will determine if additional credit will be given to the customer.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>NOTE:&nbsp; The Credit department has the ability to run a &ldquo;refresh&rdquo; of the available/calculated credit allocations within TABS.&nbsp; They should be able to execute the transaction in SAP to upload a new credit record for the customer if they are giving them additional credit.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d10\"></a>Deny 10 &ndash; Product Allocation Exhausted</h1>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Description:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>The DENY 10 error occurs when ALL available product allocations for a customer are completely exhausted.&nbsp; If any allocation for the customer has availability (E.g. they are out of allocation for DSL and UNL, but have PRE available) you will not see this error.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution summary:</strong>&nbsp; Add additional product allocation to one or more of the product allocation buckets assigned to the customer.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Resolution Steps:</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>From the Pro Log report, click on the &ldquo;consignee #&rdquo; hyperlink to view the consignee group this customer is setup for.<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/10-01.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"635\" height=\"54\" /><strong>&nbsp;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/10-02.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"315\" height=\"96\" /><br /></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n<li>Go to &ldquo;Allocations&rdquo; and then &ldquo;Product&rdquo; &gt; &ldquo;Manage&rdquo;<br /><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/10-03.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"244\" height=\"152\" /><br /><br /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n<li>In the terminal field, key in the terminal name/# as shown in the Pro Log Report (in this example, it&rsquo;s &ldquo;Magellan (Sofac) &ndash; Nashville TN (B060)&rdquo;.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>In the Consignee Group field, key in the consignee group name for the Channel of Trade (in this example, it&rsquo;s &ldquo;Pilot Travel Cente-122194-W/S &ndash; UNB Fwrd Cont&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Hit &ldquo;Search&rdquo;<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Review the Product allocation availability for all products that are assigned to the customer&rsquo;s account/consignee group.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Add additional allocation as required.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li>Inform customer and request that they attempt to load again.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d11\"></a>Deny 11 &ndash; Pre-Authorization Already Used</h1>\r\n<p>A Deny 11 means that you have issued a one-time authorization for this consignee to load at this terminal and they have already used that authorization.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/11-01.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"631\" height=\"119\" /></p>\r\n<p>In the allocation header, you will see the &ldquo;Auth Used&rdquo; box is ticked.&nbsp; If you want to prevent the Deny 11 and allow this consignee to load again, you can uncheck the &ldquo;Auth Used&rdquo; box or select a different option (Open, Credit and/or Product).&nbsp; Running an allocation report at the terminal/consignee level will show you which allocation is set to one time auth used.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/11-02.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"662\" height=\"75\" /></p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d12\"></a>Deny 12 &ndash; Invalid Transaction</h1>\r\n<p>A Deny 12 is caused by one of 2 main issues, both of which can be diagnosed by running an allocation report for the terminal/consignee receiving the error.&nbsp; You will then get 1 of 2 responses:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Sorry there are no allocations that meet your search criteria.</strong>&nbsp;If this is the case, the consignee in question does not have an allocation in place, even an OPEN record.&nbsp; If you add any type of allocation, even an OPEN record, then the deny 12 will be resolved.<br /><br /></li>\r\n<li><strong>There is (are) x allocation(s) that meet(s) your search criteria.&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>In this case you are looking for a record that is set to Credit and/or Product where the Apply Credit and Apply Product options are both set to No.&nbsp; This means you have told TABS to look for a credit or product allocation but have not told the system which one to look at. TABS will return a deny back to the terminal.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>In this case, we do have results:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/12-01.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"676\" height=\"301\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Scrolling down through the results finds this record set to Credit and/or Product but no flag set telling the system which one to look at:</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/12-02.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"664\" height=\"277\" /></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>You would need to verify if this record should be on product control or not.&nbsp; If so, check the Apply Product Allocation box.&nbsp; If this is not supposed to be active at this time you would want to change the record to OPEN.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"upload/articles/tabs/12-03.PNG\" alt=\"\" width=\"623\" height=\"237\" />&nbsp;</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d13\"></a>Deny 13 &ndash; Invalid Transaction Length</h1>\r\n<p>Indicates that the transaction was not the correct length to meet DTN TABS standards.&nbsp; This typically occurs when TAS programming encounters an error in building the TABS transaction.&nbsp; PetroDex Support will contact the terminal to resolve the programming issue.&nbsp; Contact PetroDex Support and we will work with the terminal to resolve the issue.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d14\"></a>Deny 14 &ndash; Invalid TCN</h1>\r\n<p>Indicates that the Terminal Control Number on the terminal record is invalid. You may need to re-enter the TCN on the terminal record.&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"> If a terminal has recently upgraded to Version 4.01 format a TCN is required.&nbsp; It is not required for Version 1.</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Check the terminal setup and verify the TCN entered is correct. You can verify the TCN in your TABS database by going into the Terminal Master under the terminal setup page or you can contact us and we can verify the correct TCN for you.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d80\"></a>Deny 80, 81, 98 &amp; 99 &ndash; TABS System Error</h1>\r\n<p>Contact PetroDex Support for assistance.ndicates that the Terminal Control Number on the terminal record is invalid. You may need to re-</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"d307\"></a>Deny 307(or any Seller/Shipper # - ex: Truman Arnold=172, SEI=307)</h1>\r\n<p>Customer uses Rack Marketer<strong>&nbsp;&ndash;&nbsp;</strong>Indicates that something in their database has changed. (i.e. the term is not in their system.)</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"cons\"></a>ERR: CONS Invalid Consignee</h1>\r\n<p>Indicates that the Consignee Number was incorrectly entered or that the Consignee Number as entered does not exist within your DTN TABS database. Can also indicate that the consignee is not assigned to load product from the terminal. Make sure the Consignee Number or ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system and that the consignee is assigned to the terminal.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"cred\"></a>ERR: CRED Invalid Credit Allocation</h1>\r\n<p>Indicates that the Credit Name or ID was incorrectly entered or that the Credit Name/ID as entered does not exist within your DTN TABS database. Make sure the Credit Name or ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"sell\"></a>ERR: SELL Invalid Seller ID</h1>\r\n<p>Indicates that Seller ID was incorrectly entered or that the Seller ID as entered does not exist within your DTN TABS database. Make sure the Seller ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><a id=\"term\"></a>ERR: TERM Invalid Terminal ID<strong>&nbsp;</strong></h1>\r\n<p>Indicates that Terminal ID was incorrectly entered or that the Terminal ID as entered does not exist within your DTN TABS database. Make sure the Terminal ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 5px;\" width=\"100%\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.2031px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 87.1031%; height: 13.2031px;\"><hr /></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 12.8969%; height: 13.2031px;\">&bull;&nbsp;<a href=\"#menu\">Return to Menu</a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', '2017-12-06 12:25:25', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-06 14:11:17', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'Description and Resolution steps', '', 120001, 'Allocations', 'N', '#d01#d02#d03#d04#d05#d06#d07#d08#cons#cred#d09#d10#d11#d12#d13#d14#d80#d307#sell#term#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu#menu'),
(494, 'TABS Decline Quick Reference', '<table>\r\n<thead>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p><strong>Deny/Error Code</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p><strong>Resolution Recommendation</strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</thead>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 01 &ndash; Invalid Seller ID</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the Seller ID does not exist within DTN TABS as received from the terminal. Either the terminal is sending the wrong Seller ID or the Seller has not been established in the DTN TABS database. PetroDex Support will work with the terminal to correct the Seller ID within the terminal automation system (TAS) or will set up the Seller ID in DTN TABS.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 02 &ndash; Invalid Shipper ID</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the Shipper ID for a third party transaction does not exist with your DTN TABS database as received from the terminal. PetroDex Support will work with the terminal to correct the Shipper ID within TAS or will set up the Shipper ID in DTN TABS.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 03 &ndash; Invalid Truck Number</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the Truck Number as received from the terminal does not exist within your DTN TABS database. PetroDex Support will work with the terminal to correct the Truck Number being sent by TAS or will set up the Truck Number for the corresponding carrier within DTN TABS.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 04 &ndash; Invalid Seller / Terminal</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the Terminal ID as received from TAS does not match a Terminal ID within your DTN TABS database. PetroDex Support will work with the terminal to correct the Terminal ID transmission from TAS or will add the Terminal ID to the Seller\'s DTN TABS database.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 05 &ndash; Invalid Customer ID</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the Consignee Number as received from TAS does not match a Consignee Number within your DTN TABS database. A Deny 05 code can also indicate that the consignee was not assigned to the terminal. PetroDex Support will work with the terminal to correct the Consignee Number transmitted by TAS or will add the Consignee Number to your DTN TABS database or will assign the consignee to the terminal.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 06 &ndash; Deny &ndash; No Check</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the allocation was set up as a Deny. The consignee will need to contact the seller in order to resolve the deny situation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 07 &ndash; No Credit Record</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the &ldquo;Apply Credit Allocations&rdquo; option in the Allocations Setup screen was selected but no credit allocation was created and attached to the allocation record. The seller needs to go the Allocations Setup screen and either de-select the &ldquo;Apply Credit Allocations&rdquo; option or create and attach a credit allocation to the allocation record.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 08 &ndash; No Product Record</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates that the &ldquo;Apply Product Allocations&rdquo; option in the Allocations Setup screen was selected but no product allocation was created and attached to the allocation record. The seller needs to go to the Allocations Setup screen and either de-select the &ldquo;Apply Product Allocations&rdquo; option or create and attach a product allocation to the allocation record.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 09 &ndash; Credit Limit Exceeded</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates the consignee has exceeded a limit established by a credit allocation for the consignee at this terminal. The consignee will have to contact the seller in order to update the credit allocation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 10 &ndash; Product Allocation Exhausted</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates the consignee has exceeded a limit established by a product allocation for the consignee at this terminal. The consignee will have to contact the seller in order to update the product allocation. A Deny 10 code can also indicate that the product allocation was not correctly setup with DTN TABS.&nbsp; PetroDex Support can review the Allocation Setup screen to be sure that a product allocation record was created, applied, and activated. PetroDex Support will also check to be sure that a Start Amount and Refresh Amount greater than zero were entered into the product allocation record. For a Deny 10 code, a Global Product Override may be issued with the seller\'s explicit, written approval only.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 11 &ndash; Pre-Authorization Already Used</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>For a CA transaction indicates the consignee has used up a one-time, pre-approved allocation. The consignee will need to contact the seller in order to update the allocation.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 12 &ndash; Invalid Transaction</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that the transaction was not an allowable DTN TABS transaction (CA, BB, CB, LA, BL, or BL unauth). This typically occurs when TAS programming encounters an error when building the TABS transaction. PetroDex Support will contact the terminal to resolve the programming issue. A Deny 12 code can also indicate that the customer was set up without an &ldquo;Open to Buy&rdquo; allocation record or any other allocation record. The seller will need to work with PetroDex Support to check the Allocation Setup screen and add an allocation if needed.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 13 &ndash; Invalid Transaction Length</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that the transaction was not the correct length to meet DTN TABS standards. This typically occurs when TAS programming encounters an error when building the TABS transaction. PetroDex Support will contact the terminal to resolve the programming issue.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 14 &ndash; Invalid TCN</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that the Terminal Control Number on the terminal record is invalid. You may need to re-enter the TCN on the terminal record.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 80 -- Retransmission Count Exceeded</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates a programming error in the transmission from TAS. PetroDex Support will contact the terminal to resolve the programming issue.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 81 -- Session Error Count Exceeded</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates a programming error in the transmission from TAS. PetroDex Support will contact the terminal to resolve the programming issue.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 98 -- System Temporarily Unavailable</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that DTN TABS is down. Contact PetroDex Support for assistance.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>Deny 99 -- TABS System Error</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Contact PetroDex Support for assistance.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>ERR: CONS &ndash; Invalid Consignee</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that the Consignee Number was incorrectly entered or that the Consignee Number as entered does not exist within your DTN TABS database. Can also indicate that the consignee is not assigned to load product from the terminal. Make sure the Consignee Number or ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system and that the consignee is assigned to the terminal.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>ERR: CRED &ndash; Invalid Credit Allocation</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that the Credit Name or ID was incorrectly entered or that the Credit Name/ID as entered does not exist within your DTN TABS database. Make sure the Credit Name or ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system.</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>ERR: SELL &ndash; Invalid Seller ID</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that the Seller ID was incorrectly entered or does not exist within DTN TABS as entered. Make sure the Seller ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>ERR: TERM &ndash; Invalid Terminal ID</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that the Terminal ID was incorrectly entered or that the Terminal ID as entered does not exist within your DTN TABS database. Make sure the Terminal ID used by the terminal matches that in your DTN TABS system.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"240\">\r\n<p>RNF: BOL &ndash; Record Not Found</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td width=\"403\">\r\n<p>Indicates that DTN TABS was unable to match a CA or LA transaction with a CB or BL transaction within the Seller&rsquo;s specified time frame. Thus the CA or LA record was dumped. When the BOL record finally came through, DTN TABS was unable to match it with the corresponding CA or LA transaction because it no longer existed. If you see a lot of RNF: BOL error codes on your Transaction Log Report, you may wish to contact Telvent DTN and increase the amount of time that Telvent DTN should hold CA or LA transactions.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', '2017-12-06 14:12:29', 'l7d23b', '2017-12-06 14:12:29', 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'no', '', '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 'TABS Decline Quick Reference', '', 120001, 'Allocations', 'N', '');
