(278, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Important Notice', '<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>Effective Immediately</strong></span><br /><strong>If you work on a consumer account after hours you will no longer email the mail team.</strong>&nbsp; Please email Debra for follow-up on all consumer accounts.&nbsp; Continue to email the Fleet group as necessary on any Fleet accounts.</p>\r\n<p>For station complaints, continue to email the mailteam.</p>\r\n<p>Be sure to&nbsp;include in&nbsp;your email:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>What the customer is requesting.&nbsp;Ex. A call back or refund.</li>\r\n<li>If the customer is a Valero account holder,<strong> include their account number </strong>in your email.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-10-27 10:49:11'),
(279, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Valero Card Services Moratorium', '<p>In order to ensure smooth VCS operations over the holiday period, there will be a moratorium of any site activity from <strong>Monday 19th December 2016</strong> until <strong>Friday 6<sup>th</sup> January 2017.</strong></p>', 'UK Support 1', '2016-11-02 05:09:01'),
(280, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Emergency Procedure', '<p><span style=\"color: #ff00ff; font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Very Important</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>WTS has new responsibilities via a change to the emergency preparedness guide.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=454\" target=\"_blank\">Please see article&nbsp;454 for more information. </a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-11-02 13:56:41'),
(281, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Spring Pre-Qualified', '<p>Spring Pre-Qualified offers with <strong><em>Promo codes</em> PS25</strong>, <strong>PS26</strong> and <strong>PS27</strong> have <em><u>expired</u></em>.&nbsp; The System will be ordering on these offers going forward.&nbsp; Continue to process the Fall Pre-Qualified as normal.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-11-04 23:56:41'),
(282, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'Visa Declines ', '<p>On October 25, 2016, all transactions for sites in California and Florida that are with Visa were run through the new Visa Transaction Advisor. &nbsp;Each transaction was scored by Visa for potential fraud and was given a score.&nbsp; Any transaction that scored above a certain threshold was soft declined at the pump and straight declined in the store.&nbsp;&nbsp;We don&rsquo;t think there were any calls about this decline but there is a possibility of a false positive.</p>\r\n<p>Effective today (11/07/2016),&nbsp;starting &nbsp;at 7:30AM, we put the Visa Transaction Advisor in place at all sites in our network for both inside and outside transactions.&nbsp;The decline code in ClientLine is &ldquo;KK&rdquo;. &nbsp; If, for some reason a customer calls us about this decline, simply refer &nbsp;the customer to their bank.&nbsp; The bank can let them know why they were declined.</p>\r\n<p>Please let David know if you have any questions.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-11-07 11:41:55'),
(283, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Letter to Our Stations', '<p>This letter was sent to our UK Retailers on Tuesday.</p>\r\n<p>Dear Customer</p>\r\n<p>We have recently received a number of calls to the VCS Help Desk reporting network or communications issues which were found to be caused by attempts by sites to change cabling or adding devices to the network.</p>\r\n<p>As a reminder, please do not remove the cable that connects the router to the BT socket, or connect any other equipment into the BT socket or the router.&nbsp; Your equipment has been set up in a specific way and any changes to it could result in you being unable to process card transactions online.</p>\r\n<p>If you are experiencing issues please call the VCS Help Desk on 020 7513 3800.</p>\r\n<p>Thank you for your support.</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2016-11-17 05:05:09'),
(284, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Changes on Fleet Online -vs- FAMS', '<p>If a PIN is changed on an <strong><em>existing driver</em></strong>, the change on <strong><em>Fleet Online </em></strong>and <strong><em>FAMS</em></strong> will take place in near real-time (99% in less than a minute). However, if a <strong><em>Driver is added </em></strong>via <strong><em>Fleet Online</em></strong>, the PIN number will not be available until the next day. If a <strong><em>Driver is added</em></strong> via <strong><em>FAMS</em></strong>, then the PIN is available immediately.</p>\r\n<p>If you come across any issues where a card is declined due to Invalid PIN and the change was made the same day via Fleet Online, ask the customer to try the old PIN and please let&nbsp;Nerybel know immediately.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-11-18 07:44:21'),
(285, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Fleet Skim Email Notifications', '<p>If a fleet account&nbsp;was&nbsp;involved with a skimming compromise and the cards were restricted from pump sales&nbsp;and/or reissued, an email is sent to the&nbsp;email address&nbsp;on file on the&nbsp;account.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The notes screen will show the following entry if a email has been sent:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">11/17/16 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; SYS&nbsp;&nbsp; T &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; NOTE &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; FC SKIM EMAIL VALLEY4MT</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This is done the same day as the restrictions/replacements are made to notify the account holder of the issue as soon as possible.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-11-18 08:54:41'),
(286, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'Thanksgiving Call Center Coverage', '<p>Today, 11/23/16, we will have Shanna Nail (ext.4707) and Katherine Johnston (ext.4705) here to help with calls in the call center from 3:00 pm to 5:00 pm.&nbsp; On Friday, 11/25/16, we will have Katherine Johnston (ext.4705) and Miriam Soumphonphakdy (ext.4696) from 8-5.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-11-23 08:31:43'),
(287, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Verifone Commander Known Issue', '<p>For sites installed with Verifone Commanders: the Valero consumer prop card will not prompt for AVS.&nbsp; This is a Verifone software issue and is actively being addressed.&nbsp; The fix will be provided in the upcoming EMV software release in late January.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-01 12:02:15'),
(288, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'SHA 256 Upgrade/Downgrade and Burst schedule', '<p>These changes at First Data will more than likely have no impact to our credit processing.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Upgrade/Downgrade Schedule&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Datawire Secure Transport will be conducting a temporary upgrade of the SSL Certificate for the URL vxn.datawire.net beginning on 12/05/2016 at 3:00 am CT and reverting back on 12/08/2016 at 3:00 am CT.</li>\r\n<li>Datawire Secure Transport will be conducting a temporary upgrade of the SSL Certificate for the URL vxn1.datawire.net beginning on 12/08/2016 at 3:00 am CT and reverting back on 12/12/2016 at 3:00 am CT.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>*** During the above timeframes, most clients should not experience any interruption in processing as they will failover to the secondary, non-compliant server.***</p>\r\n<p>Short Burst Upgrade Schedule&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Datawire Secure Transport will be conducting a temporary &ldquo;burst&rdquo; upgrade to EFSnet during the following timeframes:&nbsp;</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>12/06/2016 from 10:00 a.m. EST to 10:30 a.m. EST</li>\r\n<li>12/07/2016 from 2:00 p.m. EST to 2:30 p.m. EST&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>12/08/2016 from 4:00 p.m. EST to 4:30 p.m. EST</li>\r\n<li>12/09/2016 from 10:00 a.m. EST to 10:30 a.m. EST</li>\r\n<li>12/12/2016 from 3:00 p.m. EST to 3:30 p.m. EST</li>\r\n<li>12/13/2016 from 8:00 p.m. EST to 8:30 p.m. EST&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>12/15/2016 from 11:00 a.m. EST to 11:30 a.m. EST</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<li>Datawire Secure Transport will be conducting a temporary &ldquo;burst&rdquo; upgrade to VXN and VXN1 during the following timeframes:&nbsp;</li>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>12/06/2016 from 2:00 p.m. EST to 2:30 p.m. EST&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>12/08/2016 from 11:00 p.m. EST to 11:30 p.m. EST&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>12/09/2016 from 6:00&nbsp;p.m. EST to 6:30&nbsp;p.m. EST&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>12/14/2016 from 8:00 p.m. EST to 8:30 p.m. EST&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>12/16/2016 from 3:00&nbsp;p.m. EST to 3:30&nbsp;p.m. EST</li>\r\n<li>12/19/2016 from 11:00 a.m. EST to 11:30 a.m. EST</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</ul>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-05 07:41:10'),
(289, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Verizon Maintenance - Date: Dec 9 00:01 CST - Dec 9 06:00 CST', '<p>Verizon has scheduled maintenance for the primary network connection between Amarillo and San Antonio. All traffic should automatically switch to our backup circuit, so you should not experience any downtime. At most you might see some slow response for a minute or so. If you do have issues, please notify the San Antonio VTOC.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If there are questions or problems that are not being addressed, please call Chris Clemence.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-08 12:19:38'),
(290, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'New Commander Install Reminder', '<p>When you get a call from a technician that is getting ready to do a Commander install over a Prysm IDU, please make sure that you are creating a ticket and calling Sagenet to get Lan 1 and Lan 3 configured for the installation.&nbsp; Also, make sure they have ended the day and&nbsp;the store will not be doing any other credit or debit sales over the old POS. This needs to be done at the time of install and not beforehand. This is due to configuration changes that may potentially break existing serial/ip communications as they are applied.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-08 16:13:38'),
(291, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'CST Store Activations and Reloads', '<p>Cornerstore has implemented a new policy concerning the activation and reloads of gift cards.&nbsp; They will not do any activations or reloads between the hours of 8 pm and 6 am.&nbsp; This is the only change in the policy.&nbsp; All Cornerstores are still to accept credit, debit and cash for activations and reloads.&nbsp; If there is an issue please call customer relations.&nbsp; If you have a customer call in during this period please advise them and&nbsp;let them know that we can&nbsp;&nbsp;still process their request over the phone.&nbsp; Regular phone order policies will still apply.&nbsp; (ex...&nbsp; processing fees, per card cost.. etc.)</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-13 15:38:15'),
(292, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Gift Card Shipping Cutoff', '<p>After 12:00PM - 15th December, we can no longer promise pre-Christmas delivery on UPS Ground orders.</p>\r\n<p>Tuesday, 20th December will be the cutoff for two-day FedEx delivery.</p>\r\n<p>Wednesday, 21st December will be the cutoff for overnight FedEx deliveries.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-15 10:47:05'),
(293, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'EMV Liability Shift Extension', '<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=457\" target=\"_blank\">Please see article 457 for information.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-19 08:49:19'),
(294, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'Passport V.11 Software and TNS Fusion Point Express', '<p>An issue has been identified at sites using TNS FPX (VLink) and Passport v11.&nbsp; Please click <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=458\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>&nbsp;for information.&nbsp; (Article 458)</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-19 11:14:19'),
(295, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'VCS Christmas and New Year Support 2016/2017', '<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=459\" target=\"_blank\">Please see article 459 for schedule.</a></p>', 'UK Support 1', '2016-12-20 06:33:55'),
(296, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'CST Phone Coverage', '<p>We will be covering CST calls from 11:00AM - 12:00PM on Thursday 22nd December. This will be an all hands on deck situation.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=99\" target=\"_blank\">Please follow the procedures from the CST Overnight Article found here.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-20 13:39:05'),
(297, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Holiday Fleet Coverage', '<p>Today, 22nd Dec, Katherine and Karla will be here until 5:00PM and Celeste will be the Analyst here until 5:00PM.</p>\r\n<p>There will be no Fleet agents here on Friday or Monday.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-22 08:18:54'),
(298, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Vacation Scheduler', '<p>The Vacation Request scheduler is now live under the utilities menu.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2016-12-22 09:59:02'),
(299, 'lqnwmy', 'no', 'Bank Closure over Holidays Affecting UK Settlements', '<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=460\" target=\"_blank\">Please see Article 460 for information regarding settlement times for UK Holiday Bank Closures for 2016.</a></p>', 'UK Support 1', '2016-12-22 10:21:21'),
(300, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'WTS Inclement Weather Notice', '<table style=\"height: 326px; background-image: url(\'upload/blizzard.jpg\'); background-size: 100% 100%;\" width=\"529\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style=\"width: 519px;\">\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 14pt; font-family: \'arial black\', sans-serif; color: #993300;\">WTS Inclement Weather Notice</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>Please be aware that notices posted to the Valero Weather Line <strong>do not directly apply</strong> to our group.</p>\r\n<p>If there is a notice on the weather line that the Amarillo offices have been closed, contact <strong>your supervisor</strong> for further direction.</p>\r\n<p>The WTS group\'s business responsibilities extend far beyond the credit center\'s, therefore, there are different operations in place when we do experience inclement weather.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-05 09:32:04'),
(301, 'l7d23b', 'no', '2017 Vacation Scheduling', '<p>Please be aware that your first quarter vacation selections MUST be submitted <strong>before </strong>beginning of business on&nbsp;Monday, Jan 9th!</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-05 10:33:03'),
(302, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Voice Mail and Email Scheduling', '<p>As a reminder, there is a placeholder that <em>can</em> appear on your schedule for you to work the voice mails and emails. Be sure to check your schedules every day as you are responsible for working voice mails and emails during that time.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff00ff;\">*NEW*</span> This has also been added to schedules of individuals working the swing shift.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-05 14:03:48'),
(303, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Emergency Preparedness', '<p><span style=\"color: #ff00ff; font-size: 14pt;\"><strong>Very Important</strong></span></p>\r\n<p>WTS has new responsibilities via a change to the emergency preparedness guide. This can be found on page 25 of the guide that was just passed out.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=454\" target=\"_blank\">Please see article&nbsp;454 for more information. </a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-10 13:11:07'),
(304, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Final Vacation Deadline Approaching', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\"><span style=\"color: #800080;\"><strong>Reminder:</strong></span> The deadline to submit all vacation requests is <strong>January 20, 2017</strong>.</span></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-10 13:34:45'),
(305, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'TNS Cisco TNSLink', '<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Reminder</span>: Unlike FPXs, the TNSLink Cisco boxes are <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">site specific</span> and due to a recent policy change by our Vendor, will no longer be reprogrammed to another site.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-12 12:36:09'),
(306, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'New EMV Chargeback Info', '<p><span style=\"color: #800000;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">Important!</span></strong></span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=462\" target=\"_blank\">Please check article&nbsp;462 for new information regarding EMV chargebacks.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-19 09:30:54'),
(307, 'l7d23b', 'no', '2016 1099k Information', '<p>The 1099k Tax forms have not been mailed yet, but they will be mailed soon. (We are required to postmark them by Jan. 31.)</p>\r\n<p>The printed reports that detail the <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">data by store</span> were mailed on January 10.</p>\r\n<p>As a reminder, that this data is <strong>gross sales</strong> for 2016 (<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">no returns, reversals, or chargebacks</span>) and we are required to report based on the transaction date.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=201\" target=\"_blank\">For further details, click here.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-20 08:32:02'),
(308, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'Vacation Request', '<p>The time to request vacation through reflex has expired.&nbsp; If you need to make changes you will need to email Debra and Don directly with your requests.&nbsp;&nbsp; Vacation schedules are being worked on at this time and should be out shortly.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-23 09:29:38');
INSERT INTO `news` (`nid`, `usercreate`, `pubflag`, `newstitle`, `newsbody`, `role`, `createstamp`) VALUES
(310, 'lqnwmy', 'no', 'UK Contactless Pin Pad Ordering Update', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt;\">Due to&nbsp;<strong>equipment</strong> <strong>upgrades</strong> in the UK, there will be a<strong> 6 month wait</strong> on all new contactless pin pad install requests, <strong>effective immediately</strong>. If you receive a request for the installation of contactless pin pads at a UK site, you need to create a HEAT ticket with the amount of pin pads requested, advise the site of the cost per pin pad (150) and waiting period for install (6 months)<strong></strong>, and email Chris Major the Site ID, Site name, and amount of pin pads requested to be put on the master list. </span></p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-01-24 07:21:42'),
(311, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', '4R Errors/Commander Installs', '<p>We have noticed a that after some Commander/Ruby CI/Ruby 2 installations, some sites have been having an problem taking debit at the pump.&nbsp; They have been getting pin error 4R.&nbsp;&nbsp;Have them try to purge data from the pumps and reload them.&nbsp; This resolved the issue at a recent site.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-24 16:03:19'),
(312, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'New Manual Invoice Procedure', '<p>Imaging is having a problem lately with manuals scanning in where they are legible. We have realized that this is due to the way the carbon transfers on to the last layer of the manual.&nbsp; Going forward, please write directly on the last layer of the transmittal, summary, and invoice (paper copy), discarding the top two layers before writing on them.&nbsp; If you need to refer to the information, reference your HEAT ticket or check with imaging to pull the scanned copy.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-25 09:06:22'),
(313, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'EMV Chargeback Disputes', '<p>If you have a store call in concerning a chargeback that is coded 33 or 34, advise them that it is due to EMV liability shift to the stores as described in article 462.&nbsp; If they continue to dispute the chargeback, complete your heat ticket and email David Cantor advising that the customer is disputing the&nbsp;charge.&nbsp; Please include the heat ticket&nbsp;number in your email&nbsp;and&nbsp;advise the customer that we will research.&nbsp;&nbsp;When research is complete, David will provide the agent with his findings and that agent will call the store back.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-01-26 11:10:37'),
(314, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'Reminder on TNS Replacement Orders', '<p>If you take a call from a site and need to issue a replacement for equipment through TNS, please make sure to remind the site that the defective equipment will need to be returned to avoid a $400.00 equipment fee.&nbsp; Please make a note in your journal that&nbsp;you reminded the store.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-01 15:30:19'),
(315, 'l7d23b', 'yes', '1099k Information', '<p>There is a new line entry on the 1099k forms&nbsp;this year&nbsp;labeled&nbsp;\"Manual Totals.\" The IRS is now requiring separation of&nbsp;all sales where the card\'s presence at the store could not be proven. These&nbsp;are normally manually keyed transactions. This is a new requirement for our 1099k forms this year.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-02 09:20:34'),
(316, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Updated Reporting', '<p>The jobber/dealer monthly reports have been moved to the new VPS system. <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=464\" target=\"_blank\">Please see article 464 for information</a>.</p>\r\n<p>NOTE: If you get a username and login prompt when navigating to the reporting page, <a href=\"mailto:jason.york@valero.com?CC=karey.black@valero.com&amp;Subject=JReport%20Login%20Prompted&amp;Body=The%20VPS%20reporting%20screen%20has%20prompted%20me%20to%20login.%20%0APlease%20add%20my%20name%20to%20the%20list.\">please click here to send an email to Jason.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-03 11:25:38'),
(317, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'TNS Maintenance', '<p>TNS will be performing maintenance on February 15<sup>th</sup> between 03:00 &ndash; 06:00 ET.&nbsp; This maintenance should not impact traffic for our FPX users.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-13 07:02:10'),
(318, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Submitted Vacation Requests', '<p>All submitted vacation requests have been worked. Please review your submitted requests for approval status. Please follow any directions that may be included with your vacation selections and <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">be prompt&nbsp;</span>in taking any actions required.</p>\r\n<p>As a reminder, vacations are approved by supervisors only.&nbsp;Don does not have authority to approve or&nbsp;make changes to vacation requests.&nbsp;Please direct any questions, concerns, or feedback to Debra.</p>\r\n<p>-Debra</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-13 12:15:32'),
(319, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Urgent Gilbarco Software Update', '<p>Carolyn&rsquo;s team will be sending out email notifications to distributors today regarding an urgent software update for Gilbarco Passport. &nbsp;There are <strong>564</strong> Valero branded locations that need to apply the update.&nbsp; Please see the message below that will be sent out. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 8pt;\">Gilbarco has released an urgent update for Passport v11.01 to resolve a card-brand/non-compliance issue that may result in a VISA or MasterCard non-compliance fees.&nbsp; The Gilbarco help desk has proactively been shipping the v11.01D update to sites.&nbsp; If your site has received the update, but has not yet installed it, please contact the Gilbarco Help Desk at 800-800-7498 for installation assistance. If your site has not received the update, please contact the Gilbarco Help Desk at 800-800-7498.&nbsp; We appreciate your assistance.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 8pt;\">To identify the software version currently running on the Passport, please follow the following steps.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 8pt;\">From the Cashier screen:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 8pt;\">select More</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 8pt;\">select Stats</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 8pt;\">The Passport version line will show:&nbsp; Server version number / Maintenance pack / Brand or Network</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #333399; font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size: 8pt;\">Example software version format:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 11.01.23.01X VALERO</span></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-15 08:07:11'),
(320, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'POS Install/Update Reminder', '<p>When a technician calls in and is either doing an install or an update, please remind them to check AVS and Crind settings.&nbsp; We are starting to see sites with incorrect settings.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-16 11:53:35'),
(321, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'VX 570 Processing Issues', '<p>If a site calls having problems processing credit or debit over a VX 570 please send an email to Mitzi with the site details so that it can be replaced with a VX 520.&nbsp; First Data is no longer supporting the VX 570.&nbsp; Standard turn around in getting these terminals out will be 3-5 business days.&nbsp; If you have any additional questions, please contact Mitzi Land.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-21 12:45:30'),
(322, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'New Sagenet S1 Ticket Process', '<p>There is now a new process for handling S1 tickets.&nbsp; Please see article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=466\">466</a>&nbsp;for information.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-02-23 17:17:18'),
(323, 'lqnwmy', 'yes', 'Inventory Procedure for Replacement Routers', '<p>The UK Retail Technology Team keeps inventory on all TNS routers currently&nbsp;in UK sites. Due to the VCS Helpdesk\'s ability to request replacement routers for a number of issues, a new inventory procedure has been implemented to aid the UK Retail Technology Team&nbsp;in maintaining a reliable inventory of the current TNS routers in UK sites.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=215\">Refer to Article 215 for Procedure</a></p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-02-24 09:02:09'),
(324, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Vacation Tracking', '<p>Your scheduled vacation days&nbsp;are available under Utilities &gt; Vacation Tracker. These will be updated throughout the year if any changes are made.</p>\r\n<p>When it comes time to schedule the next year\'s vacation, the Vacation Tracker will revert back to it\'s scheduling mode.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-03-15 14:02:22'),
(325, 'lqnwmy', 'no', 'Pilot of GemPay Software Version 1.1.4.3', '<p>The newest version of the Gempay software, version 1.1.4.3, goes into pilot on March 28, 2017. It contains mostly bug fixes and the Euroshell fuel card PIN functionality update, triggering Pin on swipe of the Shell card.</p>\r\n<p>Pilot will run on two sites for a week commencing March 28, 2017:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Cotton street 490667</li>\r\n<li>Barking &nbsp;Service Station 251002</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>I have also enclosed documents for the pilot. The two sites will be getting a visit from Shell tomorrow after which they&rsquo;ll run a general pilot for the rest of the week. Sites have been advised.</p>\r\n<p><a title=\"Gempay Software Release Plan for package 1.1.4.3\" href=\"upload/docs/gempay-software-release-1.1.4.3-plan-002-.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Gempay Software Release Plan for package 1.1.4.3</a></p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-03-28 08:37:57'),
(326, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'Pre-Screened Overtime Sign-up', '<p>Over the next few days, Debra will provide prescreened sign ups exclusive to WTS. Please be thinking of times that you will be available to work this campaign.&nbsp; We are needing everyone&rsquo;s help with this campaign as it is a great opportunity to pick up some extra hours and help a vital part of our business. Times available are going to run from April 24 thru the end of May.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-03-28 11:49:59'),
(330, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'SEI CA Passport Install Update 03/30/17', '<p>The first round of SEI sites will be replacing their Sapphires with Passports in the next few weeks.&nbsp; New MID\'s have been ordered for these sites and a list of them can be found <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=217\">here</a>.&nbsp; Please make sure the EMV flag is set in Buypass and you will need to conference in Acumera so the AMG can be updated to support Gilbarco Passport.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-03-30 09:51:25'),
(331, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Prescreen Coverage - No Lunch Dates', '<p>As with last year, we have identified two days that will have an extremely high call volume during the lunch break hours.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>We will <strong>not</strong> be scheduling lunch breaks on April 27<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;and May 2<sup>nd</sup>.</p>\r\n<p>Lunch will be provided for the entire facility on those two dates.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-03-30 14:02:01'),
(332, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Early Release/ Good Friday Fleet coverage', '<p>There will be 2 agents, Katherine Johnston and Keith Rutherford, here until 5:00PM today, Apr 13th.</p>\r\n<p>The following agents will be here tomorrow Apr 14th.</p>\r\n<p>Karla Brim &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8-5pm &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(1pm lunch)</p>\r\n<p>Katherine Johnston &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 8-4:30pm (11-11:30 lunch)</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-04-13 12:01:29'),
(333, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Verizon Maintenance CST Network 4/27 @ 10:00 PM', '<p>Verizon will be performing maintenance on the power that supports their equipment that host&nbsp;CST store\'s circuits. The maintenance is estimated to take an hour. They do not anticipate any issues but if we receive any calls during the maintenance window, we were asked to call someone on the list below.</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 424.38px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 4.09px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 4.09px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p><strong><u>Person On-Call</u></strong></p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 4.09px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">&nbsp;<strong><u>Office Number</u></strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 4.09px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">&nbsp;<strong><u>Cell Phone Number</u></strong>&nbsp;</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 35px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>Roxanne Mojica</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>210-692-2620</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>210-857-8841</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 35px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>Omar Williams</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>210-692-2606</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>919-257-9335</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 35px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>Yan Landriault</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>514-499-6380</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>514-708-6119</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 35px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>Todd Sherinian</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>210-692-2622</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>830-822-1642</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 35px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>Mike Schrantz</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>210-692-2730</p>\r\n</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 120.38px; height: 35px; border-bottom-color: black; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: solid;\">\r\n<p>512-413-9063</p>\r\n</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-04-26 13:41:46'),
(334, 'ln524h', 'yes', 'Pre-Screen $.08 Discount', '<p>If a customer asks how the $.08 off per gallon offer works, here&rsquo;s the details:</p>\r\n<p>If the customer purchases in one billing cycle:</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">50-74 gallons &ndash; discount is $.04 per gallon</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">75-110 gallons &ndash; discount is $.08 per gallon</span></p>\r\n<p>This will appear as a credit on their bill.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-04-27 14:29:54'),
(335, 'ln524h', 'yes', 'Reminder: TNS Call Tags', '<p>Reminder,</p>\r\n<p>If a site or jobber is requesting a call tag to send back their Fusion Point device because they have upgraded to the TNS Link, please check if they have the original box that the TNS Link was delivered in.&nbsp; TNS actually includes a return shipping label in the same box that the TNS Link comes in.</p>\r\n<p>If they do not have it, please follow procedures in&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=449\">article # 449</a>.&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-04-28 10:55:13'),
(336, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'VCS / UKCS Mailboxes ', '<p>Please follow <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=298\" target=\"_blank\">article 298</a>&nbsp;to add the UKCS mailbox to your outlook. This mailbox will replace the VCS Support box at the end of the month.</p>\r\n<p>Please be aware that 3rd party/vendor notifications to us <strong>may still go to the VCS box. </strong>This includes notifications for outages or issues. <br />Because of this,&nbsp;do not remove&nbsp;the VCS box from outlook until notified.</p>\r\n<p>Also, Beginning immediately, we are to use the UKCS email address (&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:ukcs@valero.com\">ukcs@valero.com</a> )&nbsp;anywhere we <em>were </em>using the <a href=\"mailto:vcssupport@valero.com\">vcssupport@valero.com</a>.</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-05-05 06:53:20'),
(337, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Star Rewards Card Usage', '<p>There has been a recent update pushed to terminals that has disabled the ability to run a Star Rewards card <em><strong>after</strong> </em>a sale has been completed. This is an intended change that applies to all setups except stand alone terminals.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If you have a site with standalone terminals that is unable to perform a manual Star Rewards update, raise a ticket with HTEC.</p>\r\n<p>If the site needs to add points after the sale is completed, the customer will have to call the number on their Star Rewards card to have them added.</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-05-10 08:26:03'),
(338, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Star Rewards Cash Sales', '<p>Some sites are unable to issue Star Rewards point on cash sales. The sites are attempting to issue the points manually after the sale has completed.</p>\r\n<p>For sites to be able to issue point on cash sales, they will need to contact their till provider and have the <strong>loyalty prompt&nbsp;for cash sales</strong> enabled on the till.</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-05-23 08:31:23'),
(339, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Replacement Mini Keyboards', '<p>When a site raises a request for a replacement mini keyboard, please ask the site to return the old one back to us at our Westferry Circus address.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Should the site fail to return the damaged keyboard within a week of receipt of the new keyboard, we will bill them for the cost of the new keyboard (today, that is &pound;20, but it could change depending on where we source them from).</p>\r\n<p>Valero Energy Ltd <br />Floor 3, 1 Westferry Circus <br />London, E14 4HA<br />&nbsp;</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-05-31 06:34:46'),
(340, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'New MasterCard BIN Information', '<p>MasterCard will be releasing a new card in the near future.</p>\r\n<p>The information in the article below will be communicated to our distributors and posted to the portal&nbsp;soon.</p>\r\n<p>Please see <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=469\" target=\"_blank\">Article 469</a>&nbsp;for details.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-06-01 13:52:01'),
(341, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'SEI Passport Install Reminder', '<p>SEI Corporation is starting to have Passport point of sale systems installed to replace the Topaz/Sapphire systems they currently have.&nbsp; For now, we will need to have the MID flipped from TP to L3.&nbsp; Please remember to set partial auth and the EMV flag in the Clientline profile.&nbsp; These are older MID\'s and will not have them set by default.&nbsp; If you have any questions, please as Israel.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-06-07 10:32:43'),
(342, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'TNSLink Reminder', '<p><span style=\"color: #ff0000;\">Reminder</span>: Unlike FPXs, the TNSLink Cisco boxes are <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">site specific</span> and due to a recent policy change by our Vendor, will no longer be reprogrammed to another site.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-06-12 09:57:56'),
(343, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Verifone EMV', '<p>We will be starting our Verifone EMV software beta with the sites listed below starting next week.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00;\"><strong>If sites call in to report issues, please notify Kimberly Ford.&nbsp;</strong> </span></p>\r\n<p>The software beta was by invitation only.&nbsp;&nbsp;It will be tested&nbsp;for 4 weeks and, if no critical issues are identified, we will release it to production.&nbsp;<br />Kimberly&nbsp;will send an email when the production release is available.</p>\r\n<table style=\"border-color: #9c9c9c; width: 482.75px; height: 153px;\" border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"5\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 26px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 70px; height: 26px;\"><strong>Dealer</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 158px; height: 26px;\"><strong>Site ID</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 114px; height: 26px;\"><strong>Service Provider</strong></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 113.75px; height: 26px;\"><strong>Install Date</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 70px; height: 13px;\">29256</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 158px; height: 13px;\">BAZCO</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 114px; height: 13px;\">Acumera</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 113.75px; height: 13px;\">19-Jun</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 70px; height: 13px;\">30551</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 158px; height: 13px;\">Stripes Store 2169</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 114px; height: 13px;\">SageNet</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 113.75px; height: 13px;\">19-Jun</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 70px; height: 13px;\">10123</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 158px; height: 13px;\">Toot\'n Totum #56</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 114px; height: 13px;\">Acumera</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 113.75px; height: 13px;\">20-Jun</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 70px; height: 13px;\">94631</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 158p