(357, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Prescreen Article Information', '<p>The Prescreen&nbsp;can be found at&nbsp;<a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=440\" target=\"_blank\">article 440</a>&nbsp;and can also be accessed from the quicklinks at the right.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please be aware that there is no 6 month window that customers must wait for a limit increase.</strong> <br />If you have a customer requesting a higher credit limit than what was given, there is a link at the top of the prescreen article that will open an email form. Enter the account number (from the account approval screen) and the new limit requested and click send on the email. This will email a request to the supervisors to review the account.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-09 09:01:32'),
(358, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'Rapid Connect Upgrades', '<p>When you get a technician calling to do an upgrade to Rapid Connect on VeriFone Systems please click <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=478\">here</a>&nbsp;concerning important install information.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-09 10:41:23'),
(359, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Verizon Maintenance ', '<p>Verizon will be performing maintenance from Aug 18 2017 20:00 CDT - Aug 19 2017 07:00 CDT</p>\r\n<p>We do not believe that this outage should have any effect on our operations.<br />However, if you find that it does, please let Chris Clemence know and he&rsquo;ll help coordinate with Corporate to investigate.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-10 13:33:32'),
(360, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'UK Terminal Inventory', '<p>Please notify Jacqui on any and all&nbsp;station requests for additional terminals. She is now maintaining inventory data for our sites.</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-08-11 09:04:14'),
(361, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Verifone EMV', '<h4>Verifone will be releasing&nbsp;the Commander EMV software (3.02.34) to production today, 8/15.</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=479\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for article 479 for more details.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-15 05:14:52'),
(362, 'lqnwmy', 'yes', 'Loyalty Card Questions', '<p>Recently, we have received calls about customers that have won Gift Cards by swiping their Loyalty cards at select locations and while we have not received a large amount of these calls, below is the process for handling the call:</p>\r\n<p>These Gift Cards are filled here in&nbsp;Valero\'s Gift Card department; however,&nbsp;the Gift Card Dept. does&nbsp;not retain information regarding the winners here. The cards are supposed to be filled and mailed directly to the&nbsp;address the customer provides on their Rewards account&nbsp;within a 6-8 week time frame.</p>\r\n<p>If a site calls in with questions about a customer not receiving their Gift Card for their Loyalty account, you can check with Christina Castillo or David Neeley to see if the Gift Card has been processed and sent.</p>\r\n<p>You will need the customer\'s full name, address, the amount of the Gift Card expected,&nbsp;and&nbsp;the key tag # (which begins with a c).</p>\r\n<p>If Christina Castillo or David Neeley have not received the Gift Card for processing, you can contact:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Jenny Wilson by calling <span class=\"baec5a81-e4d6-4674-97f3-e9220f0136c1\" style=\"white-space: nowrap;\">210-345-1824<a style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 210-345-1824\" href=\"#\"><img style=\"margin: 0px; border: currentColor; left: 0px; top: 0px; width: 16px; height: 16px; right: 0px; bottom: 0px; overflow: hidden; vertical-align: middle; float: none; display: inline; white-space: nowrap; position: static !important;\" title=\"Call: 210-345-1824\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" /></a></span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>*Jenny Wilson prefers to speak directly with the customer, but will provide the information to the Valero Helpdesk group.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-15 09:20:07'),
(363, 'lqnwmy', 'no', 'Gift Card Inquirys through Aug. 18th', '<p>Christina Castillo will be out of the Office until Monday Aug. 21st. If you have any Gift card inquiries, please IM David Neeley.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-16 07:43:49'),
(364, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'Verifone EMV Chargebacks', '<p>Now that the EMV compliant software is out for VeriFone POS systems, dealers are going to be given until 12/31/2017 to have their systems updated.&nbsp; After that point they&nbsp;will start seeing chargebacks if they have not completed the update.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-17 08:57:15'),
(365, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'Verifone EMV/Rapid Connect Updates', '<p>Stores may download the new EMV compliant version of the Commander software from their Commander themselves.&nbsp; If they call us for assistance, we should refer them to Veriphone for assistance with that process.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-17 09:09:10'),
(366, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'WEX Adjustments', '<p>If you need to process a WEX transaction here (correction, return, etc.) be sure to key in the prefix &lsquo;690046&rsquo; on the terminal. <br />Key the full card number presented by Clientline so the transaction processes correctly through all systems.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>This was tested successfully today using a test WEX card provided by WEX.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-18 13:38:36'),
(367, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'EMV Network Profiles', '<p>There has been an issue discovered with new <strong>EMV/terminal 2</strong> profiles at&nbsp;First Data. The&nbsp;Buypass Fleet card is not being enabled and must be checked prior to the site pulling their PDL on the EMV software. You will also need to verify velocity on <strong>terminal 2</strong> is setup correctly as 2/200 for line 1.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-25 13:09:24'),
(368, 'ln524h', 'no', 'Verifone Commander EMV Rapid Connect Software', '', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-28 17:17:42'),
(369, 'ln524h', 'no', 'Verifone Commander EMV Rapid Connect Software', '<p>Please refer to <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=479\">Article # 479</a> for the latest updates. Latest update, 8/29/17. Please review.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-28 17:31:03'),
(370, 'ln524h', 'no', 'Verifone Commander EMV Rapid Connect Software ', '<p>Please refer to</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-08-29 16:49:42'),
(372, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Fuel Availability', '<p>Below is the approved script from corporate concerning Fuel Availability:</p>\r\n<p>While the devastating effects of hurricane Harvey have caused several Gulf Coast refineries to shut down, the industry is working hard to sustain fuel availability for customers and consumers.&nbsp; Fuel terminals serving the areas of Central and South Texas markets which are supplied out of the Corpus Christi area refineries have maintained supply to contract customers but at reduced volume. &nbsp;&nbsp;The Houston area is still experiencing extensive flooding, hampering logistical and transportation access to available fuel.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-01 10:52:03'),
(373, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Empire Acquisition of CST Sites - Important', '<p>Effective September 6th- Please review <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=480\" target=\"_blank\">Article #480</a> for further details.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-01 10:53:13'),
(374, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'Temporary Credit Limit Increase - Consumer Accounts', '<p>In order to provide support after hours, should you get a call from a customer requesting a credit limit increase on a consumer account that has been affected by Hurricane Harvey, follow article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=481\">#481</a> for more details.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-01 13:23:09'),
(375, 'ln524h', 'no', 'MID Issue with CST Sites Switching to Empire', '<p>There has been an issue identified with some techs unable to pull the PDL on sites switching from CST to Empire.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>If a tech is unable to pull a PDL verify that they have the full MID, including 001, in the Sapphire.&nbsp; If they do not have a place to put the terminal # in, they may be logged in under the wrong credentials.&nbsp; They will need to login via the backdoor (also referred to as helpdesk) on the Sapphire and that will allow them to enter the terminal # with the MID.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-06 17:20:58'),
(376, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Fleet After Hours', '<p>Beginning today, we will start receiving fleet calls at 5:30pm instead of 6:00pm.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-07 08:55:25'),
(377, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'CST / Empire Conversions Information', '<p>There has been an update concerning the conversion of sites from CST to Empire.&nbsp; Please read article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=480\">480</a> for information on known issues.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-07 16:12:05'),
(378, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Credit Card Center Emails', '<p>As a reminder, emails concerning a Valero account need to go to AMAMailteam or <a href=\"mailto:CS_Credit@valero.com\">CS_Credit@valero.com</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Only station complaints should be sent to WCS (<a href=\"mailto:customersupport@valero.com\">customersupport@valero.com</a>).</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-08 08:46:55'),
(379, 'lbfb2t', 'no', 'Outage Information 09/11/17', '<p>In reference to the outage please tell customers:&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\"We are currently experiencing an outage related to our sites on VSAT/Passport point of sale systems.&nbsp; Engineers are working on the issue but unfortunately we do not have an ETA at this time\".&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-11 10:05:28'),
(380, 'lqnwmy', 'yes', 'GemPay Mini Keyboard Replacement Guidelines ', '<p>If a UK Site requests a Replacement Mini Keyboard, refer to the guidelines in article <a title=\"245\" href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=245\">245</a>.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-13 10:10:35'),
(381, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'EMV/Rapid Connect Update', '<p>There has been an update to EMV/Rapid Connect article.&nbsp; Please read article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=479\">479</a>&nbsp;for information.&nbsp; (Update 9/15/17)</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-15 13:48:01'),
(382, 'ln524h', 'no', 'CST Commander Deployment', '<p>Please see <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=482\">article # 482 </a>with information concerning CST locations upgrading to the Commander POS.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-15 15:25:56'),
(383, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'MID Update at Change of owner/Legal entity Process', '<p>Please see <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=483\" target=\"_blank\">Article 483</a> for new information regarding releasing MIDs to HTEC.</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-09-18 14:05:14'),
(384, 'ln524h', 'no', 'Notification of 2017-2018 TNS Network Moratorium', '', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-20 16:12:53'),
(385, 'ln524h', 'yes', 'Notification of 2017-2018 TNS Network Moratorium', '<p>Please see <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=446\">article # 446</a> for information concerning the TNS Network Moratorium for 2017-2018.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-20 16:17:45'),
(386, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'Cash Redemption on Valero Gift Cards', '<p>There is an update to the list of states that allow a customer to redeem a Valero Gift Card for cash.&nbsp; Click <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=485\">here</a>&nbsp;to view the list.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-22 16:07:17'),
(387, 'ln524h', 'yes', 'Verifone EMV - Mobile Payment Acceptance Issue', '<p>An issue with acceptance of mobile payments (ApplePay, SamsungPay, &hellip;) has been identified with Verifone EMV software version 3.02.34. &nbsp;This issue will be resolved in an upcoming release in October.&nbsp; If calls are received, please let the caller know that we are aware of the issue and are closely working with Verifone to resolve.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-09-28 11:55:01'),
(389, 'ln524h', 'yes', 'TNSLink Router Changes - Rapid Connect', '<p>Please see <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=479\" target=\"_blank\">article # 479 </a>for latest update.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-10-02 10:18:29'),
(390, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Pre-Qualified/MLA changes', '<h4><span style=\"color: #ff00ff;\">IMPORTANT</span></h4>\r\n<p>Please see <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=488\" target=\"_blank\">Article 488</a>&nbsp;for new information regarding the pre-qualified application process.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-10-05 12:22:30'),
(391, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Early Release/Time off Prizes', '<p>If you received an early release or time off prize from customer service week, turn the slip in with your name and requested date to Debra.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-10-06 08:18:04'),
(392, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'IdM Portal Changes', '<p>There is a planned IdM upgrade scheduled for <strong>Friday </strong><strong>October 13<sup>th</sup> </strong><strong>from </strong><strong>7</strong><strong>pm</strong> <strong>to </strong><strong>Saturday October 14<sup>th</sup> </strong><strong>at </strong><strong>10pm (CDT)</strong>. During this time, the External Customer Portals (US, Canadian and UK/IE) <u>will still be available</u> but the following features will not be available.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Registration</li>\r\n<li>Forgot Password</li>\r\n<li>Reset Password (used by Amarillo and the help desk)</li>\r\n<li>Update user information, security questions and password (available under Account Settings within the portal)</li>\r\n<li>Requesting new access</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Once the upgrade is completed on Sunday, internal employees will notice a slightly different UI when approving role requests, requesting new access, etc. Please see article ZZZ for more information.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-10-10 09:14:45'),
(393, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Station Adjustment', '<p>Site 28200-70896 is having an amount debited for $4,528.60 on tomorrow\'s business. This was due to an incorrect MID loaded Sept 20th and 22nd.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-10-11 14:05:15'),
(394, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'TNS FPX Maintenance October 19th', '<p>On October 19th during our Maintenance window (between 3 and 6 am Eastern), we will be moving the routing associated with TNIP vlr01 in Kansas City to: asb-vlr0vtnip01 in Ashburn.</p>\r\n<p>FPX Traffic will still flow as normal through the other 2 TNIP&rsquo;s.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-10-13 08:50:04'),
(395, 'ln524h', 'yes', 'CST Commander Deployment - Update', '<p>CST is&nbsp;looking to install Commanders at 51 stores in November. &nbsp;The start date is November 6 and will hopefully complete on November 22.&nbsp; The installs will take place overnight, so upon completion of the install, the tech will call our help desk to request the Acumera activation ticket be closed.&nbsp; Please follow the instructions in article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=482\">482</a>.&nbsp; Please also validate the merchant profile setup is correct, article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=479\">479</a>.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-10-18 16:36:27'),
(397, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Time Change on Gempay 3', '<p>Due to the time change this weekend in the UK, some Gempay 3 terminals have not updated. To update the time manually, follow the instructions in article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=472#time\" target=\"_blank\">472</a>.</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-10-30 06:22:54'),
(398, 'l7d23b', 'no', 'Test news post', '<p>Test, please disregard.</p>', 'Allocations', '2017-10-31 10:23:36'),
(399, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'CST / Acumera Pre-Activation Update', '<p>There has been an update to the CST / Acumera Pre-Activation Process.&nbsp; Please review article <a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=482\" target=\"_blank\">482</a>&nbsp;for information.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-11-02 16:12:38');
INSERT INTO `news` (`nid`, `usercreate`, `pubflag`, `newstitle`, `newsbody`, `role`, `createstamp`) VALUES
(400, 'lqnwmy', 'yes', 'Valero Card Services Moratorium Christmas/New Year Period', '<p>In order to ensure smooth VCS operations over the holiday period, there will be a moratorium of any site activity from <strong>Friday 15<sup>th</sup> December 2017</strong> until <strong>Friday 5<sup>th</sup> January 2018</strong> inclusive.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong>Please bear this in mind when planning your site activities. If you foresee any problems, &nbsp;please can you let me know as soon as possible.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Many thanks for your support.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;Julie Lunnon</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"mailto:Julie.Lunnon@valero.com\">Julie.Lunnon@valero.com</a>&nbsp;</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-11-14 08:50:05'),
(401, 'l7d23b', 'yes', '2018 Vacation Scheduling', '<h4><span style=\"color: #339966;\"><strong>The vacation scheduler is now open.</strong></span></h4>\r\n<p>Be sure to update your holiday preferences under <strong>Utilities &gt;</strong> <strong>Holiday Preferences.</strong></p>\r\n<p>The deadline to submit all vacation requests is January 26th.</p>\r\n<p>If you are requesting vacation in January or February, please email the dates to Debra as soon as possible.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-11-14 12:43:58'),
(402, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'MasterCard Series 2 Card Update', '<h4><span style=\"color: #993300;\">Important</span></h4>\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=469\" target=\"_blank\">Please see&nbsp;article 469 for updates.</a> Corporate is notifying stations that are not able to accept these cards this week which could generate some calls.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-11-14 13:13:48'),
(403, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'US Outage Procedures', '<p>we have a quicklink to a new article: US Outage Procedures. This article outlines the procedures for handling a US outage. Please read up on the article.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-11-20 13:58:49'),
(404, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'UK Gempay 3 Call Handling', '<p>We have a new process for handling Gempay 3 calls that must be raised with HTEC. Please check out the article as the process is changing quite a bit.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"index.php?pagereq=article&amp;view=article&amp;artid=491\" target=\"_blank\">Please see article 491 for more info.</a></p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-11-21 13:06:27'),
(405, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Gilbarco Passport Beta 11.01G', '<p>We have three sites participating in beta testing patch G for Gilbarco Passport.&nbsp; Please notify Kimberly of any issues reported by the sites.</p>\r\n<table style=\"height: 45px;\" border=\"1\" width=\"100%\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13.68px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13.68px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">MID</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 13.68px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Name</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39%; height: 13.68px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">Address</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19%; height: 13.68px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13.68px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13.68px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">622641</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">JJ\'S FASTRAC</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">781 W BEDFORD EULESS RD</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">HURST&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">TX</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">76053</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">864591</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">LYONS MAIN STOP</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">105 W MORENCI ST&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">LYONS&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">OH</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">43533</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">697128</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 25%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">COFFINS CORNER 1</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 39%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">519 N EDDY ST&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 19%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">GRAND ISLAND&nbsp;</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">NE</span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 10%; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 8pt;\">68801</span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-11-22 07:48:17'),
(406, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Empire Commander Installs', '<p>Empire has provided their Commander deployment schedule.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"color: #ff00ff;\"><strong>Important Note:</strong></span> <strong>The tech will call into our help desk during the install. Acumera will need to be engaged since the sites are migrating from Sapphire to Commander.</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/EMPIRE COMMANDER INSTALL MASTER LIST REV 1 to Dennie.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">Click here for the master list.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-11-28 12:08:48'),
(407, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'CST December Conversions', '<p>Linked below is the CST Commander install schedule for the month of December.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"upload/docs/December Conversions.xlsx\" target=\"_blank\">Schedule can be found here.</a></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-11-28 12:35:17'),
(408, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Barclays T+1 Settlement Due 1st December 2017', '<p>Due to an application platform change T+1 customers who would normally receive payments first thing this morning will experience a delay.&nbsp; Barclays have guarantee that they will still receive their payment today but it will be later in the day.</p>\r\n<p>Current T+1 Sites:</p>\r\n<table style=\"width: 305px; height: 90px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Site ID</strong></span></td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\"><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong>Name</strong></span></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">886415</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Sutton Corner S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">886874</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Culverstone S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">257399</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Lime S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">886917</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">New Invention S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">258643</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Molineux S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">886069</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Corner Park S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">259867</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Horwich S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">886986</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Ram Jam S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">887020</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">Houndsmill S/Stn</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 13px;\">\r\n<td style=\"width: 62.82px; height: 13px;\">887051</td>\r\n<td style=\"width: 226.18px; height: 13px;\">West Drayton</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', 'UK Support 1', '2017-12-01 09:01:25'),
(409, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Allocation Project Announcement', '<p>The allocations project is scheduled to kickoff first quarter! Stay tuned for more updates and information.</p>', 'Allocations', '2017-12-06 14:14:24'),
(410, 'l7d23b', 'yes', '2017 Gift Card Shipping Cutoff', '<p>Gift card orders made through Sunday&nbsp;the 17th&nbsp;<span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">SHOULD</span> be delivered before Christmas. Let the customer know that we<strong> cannot guarantee</strong> delivery due to shipping delays or extraneous&nbsp;issues but we will try our hardest to get orders out in a timely manner.</p>\r\n<p>Orders made Monday and Tuesday will be shipped priority <strong>at our expense </strong>to attempt to get cards delivered before Christmas as well.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Please reiterate to the customer that we\'re making all attempts to get them their orders before Christmas but there could be factors that delay delivery past the holiday.</strong></p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-12-14 10:22:26'),
(411, 'ln524h', 'yes', 'Mastercard Extension Received', '<p>We&rsquo;ve been granted an additional extension on the new 2-series MasterCard. Previously we communicated sites had until December 31, 2017 to be compliant.</p>\r\n<p>However, now our Valero sites have until <span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><strong>June 30, 2018</strong> </span>to upgrade hardware and/or software to support the new 2-series MasterCard. Failure to accept the new card will result in fines from MasterCard.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-12-19 14:50:13'),
(412, 'l7d23b', 'yes', 'Fleet Assistance 12/20', '<p>We will be assisting with Fleet coverage from 10:15a to 1:00p to&nbsp;allow fleet agents to attend Kathy\'s funeral.</p>\r\n<p>Jessica, Noemi, Keith and Angie will be here while the rest of the Fleet team are out. &nbsp;If we&nbsp;get a call that is outside the scope of our after hour training, we can try to call Jessica, Noemi, Keith or Angie.&nbsp; Most likely they will be on another call.&nbsp; That being the case,&nbsp;apologize to the customer and advise to call back after 1:00pm.</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2017-12-20 09:09:43'),
(413, 'lbfb2t', 'yes', 'EMV Update', '<p>If a technician calls in due to an EMV Upgrade or Install, please check to make sure that the time zone is correct on the profile under terminal id 002.&nbsp;&nbsp; There have been some that are not set correctly.&nbsp;</p>', 'Tech Support 1', '2018-01-14 14:00:00');
